window.PEDIA_CONTENT = {"budaya_alat_musik_angklung_1":{"id":"budaya_alat_musik_angklung_1","title_id":"Angklung","title_en":"Angklung","subtitle_id":"Alat musik bambu Sunda yang dimainkan dengan digoyang","subtitle_en":"The Sundanese bamboo instrument you play by shaking","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jawa Barat (Sunda)","value_en":"West Java (Sundanese)"},{"icon":"park","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Bambu","value_en":"Bamboo"},{"icon":"music_note","label_id":"Cara main","label_en":"How to play","value_id":"Digoyang-goyang","value_en":"Shaken"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Dimainkan","label_en":"Played","value_id":"Bersama-sama","value_en":"Together as a team"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"music_note","h_id":"Apa Itu Angklung?","h_en":"What Is Angklung?","body_id":"Angklung adalah alat musik tradisional dari masyarakat Sunda di Jawa Barat. Alat musik ini dibuat dari tabung-tabung bambu yang diikat pada sebuah bingkai. Kamu memainkannya dengan cara menggoyangkannya, lalu tabung bambu akan berbenturan dan menghasilkan bunyi yang merdu. Setiap angklung punya nada sendiri, jadi semua orang harus bermain bersama agar lagunya lengkap dan indah.","body_en":"Angklung is a traditional instrument from the Sundanese people of West Java. It is made from bamboo tubes tied onto a frame. You play it by shaking it, and the bamboo tubes knock together to make a sweet, ringing sound. Each angklung has only its own note, so everyone has to play together to make the whole song complete and beautiful."},{"icon":"build","h_id":"Terbuat dari Bambu","h_en":"Made from Bamboo","body_id":"Angklung dibuat dari bambu pilihan, seperti bambu hitam dan bambu ater. Bambu dipotong dan diraut dengan hati-hati supaya menghasilkan nada yang tepat. Tabung yang besar berbunyi rendah, dan tabung yang kecil berbunyi tinggi. Setiap angklung biasanya punya 2 sampai 4 tabung yang berbunyi serempak dalam satu nada.","body_en":"Angklung is made from special bamboo, such as black bamboo and ater bamboo. The bamboo is cut and shaped very carefully so it makes exactly the right note. A big tube makes a low sound, and a small tube makes a high sound. Each angklung usually has 2 to 4 tubes that ring together as one note."},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Bermain Bersama","h_en":"Playing Together","body_id":"Karena satu angklung hanya bisa membunyikan satu nada, alat musik ini paling seru dimainkan beramai-ramai. Setiap pemain memegang satu atau dua angklung dan menggoyangkannya saat gilirannya tiba. Seorang pemimpin di depan memberi aba-aba dengan tangannya. Kalau semua kompak, banyak angklung kecil bisa berubah menjadi satu lagu yang utuh dan indah.","body_en":"Because one angklung can only make one note, this instrument is most fun when played in a big group. Each player holds one or two angklung and shakes it when it is their turn. A leader at the front gives signals with their hands. When everyone works together, many little angklung turn into one complete, beautiful song."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Cerita Lama Angklung","h_en":"The Old Story of Angklung","body_id":"Sudah ratusan tahun lalu, orang Sunda memainkan angklung. Dahulu angklung dibunyikan dalam upacara padi untuk menghormati Dewi Sri, dewi padi, agar tanaman tumbuh subur. Angklung juga pernah dipakai untuk membangkitkan semangat para pejuang. Lama-kelamaan, angklung berkembang menjadi musik yang menghibur dan dimainkan di mana-mana.","body_en":"For hundreds of years, the Sundanese people have played angklung. Long ago, angklung was played in rice ceremonies to honor Dewi Sri, the rice goddess, so the crops would grow well. Angklung was also once used to lift the spirits of warriors. Over time, angklung grew into joyful music played in many places."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pada tahun 2010, UNESCO mengakui angklung sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia. Artinya, angklung dianggap istimewa dan harus dijaga oleh semua orang. Sekarang angklung diajarkan di sekolah-sekolah dan dimainkan sampai ke luar negeri. Ayo kita ikut bangga dan terus melestarikan musik bambu yang ceria ini!","body_en":"In 2010, UNESCO recognized angklung as a World Cultural Heritage. That means angklung is seen as very special and should be protected by everyone. Today angklung is taught in schools and played all the way to other countries. Let's be proud and keep this cheerful bamboo music alive!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Satu angklung hanya bisa membunyikan satu nada, jadi harus dimainkan beramai-ramai!","en":"One angklung can only make one note, so it must be played in a big group!"},{"id":"Kamu memainkan angklung cukup dengan menggoyang-goyangkannya.","en":"You play angklung simply by shaking it."},{"id":"Angklung dibuat dari bambu, bukan dari logam atau kayu.","en":"Angklung is made from bamboo, not metal or wood."},{"id":"UNESCO mengakui angklung sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2010.","en":"UNESCO recognized angklung as a World Heritage in 2010."},{"id":"Nama 'angklung' berasal dari bunyi 'klung' yang terdengar saat dimainkan.","en":"The name 'angklung' comes from the 'klung' sound it makes when played."},{"id":"Dahulu angklung dibunyikan dalam upacara padi untuk Dewi Sri.","en":"Long ago angklung was played in rice ceremonies for Dewi Sri."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Bambu","def_id":"Tanaman tinggi berongga yang batangnya kuat dan dipakai membuat angklung.","def_en":"A tall, hollow plant with a strong stem used to make angklung."},{"term":"Nada","def_id":"Bunyi tinggi atau rendah dalam musik.","def_en":"A high or low sound in music."},{"term":"Tabung","def_id":"Potongan bambu berbentuk pipa yang menghasilkan bunyi pada angklung.","def_en":"A pipe-shaped piece of bamboo that makes the sound in an angklung."},{"term":"Sunda","def_id":"Suku dan budaya yang berasal dari Jawa Barat.","def_en":"An ethnic group and culture from West Java."},{"term":"Warisan budaya","def_id":"Sesuatu yang berharga dari nenek moyang yang harus kita jaga.","def_en":"Something precious from our ancestors that we must protect."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3678684be69ee7c3.jpg","caption_id":"Deretan angklung bambu siap dimainkan di sebuah sanggar musik.","caption_en":"Rows of bamboo angklung ready to be played at a music studio.","credit":"dicky satarman from bandung, indonesia","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4473eefddbfe418b.jpg","caption_id":"Angklung digantung berjajar, memperlihatkan tabung-tabung bambunya.","caption_en":"Angklung hung in a row, showing off their bamboo tubes.","credit":"Terry Ballard from Merrick, New York, USA","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/18c7b883c75fd11f.jpg","caption_id":"Satu buah angklung dengan tabung besar dan kecil pada bingkainya.","caption_en":"A single angklung with big and small tubes on its frame.","credit":"Putri siska","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3d7fcc87f64c8054.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama anak-anak Jawa Barat memegang angklung lebih dari seratus tahun lalu.","caption_en":"An old photo of West Javanese children holding angklung over a hundred years ago.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/23ccd8e4cc6ddccd.jpg","caption_id":"Satu set angklung lengkap yang dipajang di museum musik.","caption_en":"A complete set of angklung on display in a music museum.","credit":"Malibugalz","license":"CC BY 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angklung"},"budaya_batik_indonesia":{"id":"budaya_batik_indonesia","title_id":"Batik","title_en":"Batik","subtitle_id":"Kain bergambar indah yang dilukis dengan lilin malam","subtitle_en":"Beautiful patterned cloth drawn with wax","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jawa, Indonesia","value_en":"Java, Indonesia"},{"icon":"brush","label_id":"Teknik","label_en":"Technique","value_id":"Canting & malam (lilin)","value_en":"Canting & wax"},{"icon":"checkroom","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Kain (katun/sutra)","value_en":"Cloth (cotton/silk)"},{"icon":"palette","label_id":"Ciri khas","label_en":"Special for","value_id":"Motif beraneka ragam","value_en":"Many kinds of patterns"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"brush","h_id":"Apa Itu Batik?","h_en":"What Is Batik?","body_id":"Batik adalah kain bergambar indah yang berasal dari Indonesia, terutama dari Pulau Jawa. Gambar atau pola pada batik dibuat dengan cara yang sangat khusus, yaitu menggunakan lilin malam yang panas. Batik bukan hanya kain biasa, melainkan sebuah karya seni. Orang Indonesia memakai batik untuk ke sekolah, ke kantor, ke pesta, sampai acara penting lainnya.","body_en":"Batik is beautiful patterned cloth that comes from Indonesia, especially from the island of Java. The pictures or patterns on batik are made in a very special way, using hot wax. Batik is not just ordinary cloth; it is a work of art. Indonesian people wear batik to school, to the office, to parties, and to other important events."},{"icon":"edit","h_id":"Canting dan Malam","h_en":"The Canting and the Wax","body_id":"Untuk membuat batik tulis, pengrajin memakai alat kecil bernama canting. Canting punya wadah kecil dan ujung pipa untuk mengeluarkan lilin malam yang panas. Lilin dilukiskan di atas kain mengikuti pola gambar. Setelah kering, kain dicelup ke pewarna. Bagian yang tertutup lilin tidak akan terkena warna, sehingga muncullah gambar yang cantik.","body_en":"To make hand-drawn batik, the crafter uses a small tool called a canting. The canting has a tiny cup and a thin spout to pour out hot wax. The wax is drawn onto the cloth following the pattern. After it dries, the cloth is dipped into dye. The parts covered by wax do not catch the color, so a beautiful picture appears."},{"icon":"format_paint","h_id":"Batik Tulis dan Batik Cap","h_en":"Hand-Drawn and Stamped Batik","body_id":"Ada dua cara utama membuat batik. Yang pertama adalah batik tulis, yaitu pola dilukis satu per satu dengan canting. Batik tulis butuh waktu lama dan sangat teliti, kadang sampai berminggu-minggu. Yang kedua adalah batik cap, yaitu pola dibuat dengan stempel tembaga, sehingga lebih cepat. Keduanya sama-sama indah dan disukai orang.","body_en":"There are two main ways to make batik. The first is hand-drawn batik, where the pattern is drawn one piece at a time with a canting. Hand-drawn batik takes a long time and great care, sometimes many weeks. The second is stamped batik, where the pattern is made with a copper stamp, so it is faster. Both are equally beautiful and loved by people."},{"icon":"auto_awesome","h_id":"Motif Penuh Makna","h_en":"Patterns Full of Meaning","body_id":"Setiap motif batik punya nama dan cerita sendiri. Ada motif Parang yang bergaris miring seperti ombak, ada motif Kawung, Mega Mendung, dan banyak motif bunga serta hewan. Dahulu, beberapa motif hanya boleh dipakai oleh keluarga raja. Sekarang siapa saja boleh memakai batik dan menikmati keindahannya.","body_en":"Every batik pattern has its own name and story. There is the Parang pattern with slanted lines like waves, there is the Kawung pattern, Mega Mendung, and many flower and animal patterns. Long ago, some patterns could only be worn by the royal family. Today anyone may wear batik and enjoy its beauty."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pada tanggal 2 Oktober 2009, UNESCO menetapkan batik sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia dari Indonesia. Karena itu, setiap tanggal 2 Oktober kita rayakan sebagai Hari Batik Nasional. Pada hari itu, banyak orang memakai baju batik dengan bangga. Ayo kita cintai dan lestarikan batik agar tidak hilang ditelan zaman!","body_en":"On October 2, 2009, UNESCO declared batik a World Cultural Heritage from Indonesia. Because of this, every October 2 is celebrated as National Batik Day. On that day, many people proudly wear batik clothes. Let's love and protect batik so it is never lost to time!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Batik dibuat dengan melukis lilin malam panas di atas kain.","en":"Batik is made by drawing hot wax onto cloth."},{"id":"Alat kecil untuk melukis lilin disebut canting.","en":"The small tool for drawing the wax is called a canting."},{"id":"Setiap tanggal 2 Oktober dirayakan sebagai Hari Batik Nasional.","en":"Every October 2 is celebrated as National Batik Day."},{"id":"UNESCO mengakui batik sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2009.","en":"UNESCO recognized batik as a World Heritage in 2009."},{"id":"Batik tulis bisa memakan waktu berminggu-minggu untuk satu kain.","en":"One hand-drawn batik cloth can take many weeks to finish."},{"id":"Setiap motif batik, seperti Parang, punya nama dan ceritanya sendiri.","en":"Each batik pattern, like Parang, has its own name and story."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Canting","def_id":"Alat kecil dengan ujung pipa untuk melukis lilin malam di atas kain.","def_en":"A small tool with a thin spout for drawing wax onto cloth."},{"term":"Malam","def_id":"Lilin khusus yang dipanaskan untuk membuat pola batik.","def_en":"A special wax that is heated to make batik patterns."},{"term":"Motif","def_id":"Pola atau gambar berulang yang menghiasi kain batik.","def_en":"A repeating pattern or picture that decorates batik cloth."},{"term":"Batik tulis","def_id":"Batik yang polanya dilukis satu per satu dengan tangan memakai canting.","def_en":"Batik whose pattern is drawn by hand, piece by piece, with a canting."},{"term":"Batik cap","def_id":"Batik yang polanya dibuat dengan stempel tembaga sehingga lebih cepat.","def_en":"Batik whose pattern is made with a copper stamp, so it is faster."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/09d194fb586a5d23.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang nenek pengrajin melukis pola batik tulis dengan canting.","caption_en":"An elderly crafter draws a batik pattern by hand with a canting.","credit":"Stephen Kennedy","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/24231244229c8455.jpg","caption_id":"Beberapa pembatik bekerja bersama membuat kain batik.","caption_en":"Several batik makers work together on a piece of cloth.","credit":"Mw.Prof.Dr. C.H.M. (Hetty) Nooy-Palm","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b2dcc550e068e505.jpg","caption_id":"Canting dipakai dari dekat untuk menorehkan lilin malam ke kain.","caption_en":"A close look at a canting laying down hot wax onto the cloth.","credit":"essenziale","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7dc2f7001835484f.jpg","caption_id":"Kain batik kuno dengan motif Parang yang bergaris miring.","caption_en":"An antique batik cloth with the slanted Parang pattern.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f6103348bd747575.jpg","caption_id":"Gedung Museum Batik tempat kain-kain batik dijaga dan dipamerkan.","caption_en":"A Batik Museum building, where batik cloths are kept and shown.","credit":"JV03 Novia Rochmawati","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batik"},"budaya_candi_prambanan":{"id":"budaya_candi_prambanan","title_id":"Candi Prambanan","title_en":"Prambanan Temple","subtitle_id":"Candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"The biggest Hindu temple in Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Location","value_id":"Perbatasan Yogyakarta & Jawa Tengah","value_en":"Border of Yogyakarta & Central Java"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Dibangun","label_en":"Built","value_id":"Sekitar tahun 850 M (abad ke-9)","value_en":"Around 850 CE (9th century)"},{"icon":"temple_hindu","label_id":"Agama","label_en":"Religion","value_id":"Hindu (untuk Trimurti)","value_en":"Hindu (for the Trimurti)"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Height","value_id":"Candi Siwa setinggi 47 meter","value_en":"Shiva temple is 47 meters tall"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Nama Asli","label_en":"Original Name","value_id":"Siwagrha ('Rumah Siwa')","value_en":"Shivagrha ('House of Shiva')"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan Dunia UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO World Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"temple_hindu","h_id":"Apa Itu Prambanan?","h_en":"What Is Prambanan?","body_id":"Candi Prambanan adalah candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia. Bentuknya tinggi, ramping, dan runcing seperti gunung-gunung batu yang menjulang ke langit. Candi ini juga disebut Candi Rara Jonggrang. Banyak orang menyebutnya salah satu candi terindah di Asia Tenggara!","body_en":"Prambanan is the biggest Hindu temple in Indonesia. It is tall, slim, and pointy, like stone mountains reaching up to the sky. The temple is also called Rara Jonggrang Temple. Many people call it one of the most beautiful temples in all of Southeast Asia!"},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Rumah Tiga Dewa","h_en":"Home of Three Gods","body_id":"Prambanan dibangun untuk memuliakan Trimurti, yaitu tiga dewa utama Hindu. Mereka adalah Brahma sang pencipta, Wisnu sang pemelihara, dan Siwa sang pemusnah. Candi yang paling besar dan tinggi adalah Candi Siwa di tengah. Di dalamnya ada patung Siwa setinggi tiga meter.","body_en":"Prambanan was built to honor the Trimurti, the three main Hindu gods. They are Brahma the creator, Vishnu the keeper, and Shiva the destroyer. The biggest and tallest building is the Shiva temple in the middle. Inside it stands a three-meter-tall statue of Shiva."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Kapan & Siapa Pembangunnya?","h_en":"When and Who Built It?","body_id":"Prambanan mulai dibangun sekitar tahun 850 Masehi, lebih dari 1.000 tahun yang lalu. Raja Rakai Pikatan memulainya pada masa Kerajaan Medang Mataram. Raja-raja sesudahnya terus memperbesar dan memperindah candi ini. Nama aslinya adalah Siwagrha, yang berarti 'Rumah Siwa'.","body_en":"Prambanan began to be built around 850 CE, more than 1,000 years ago. King Rakai Pikatan started it during the Medang Mataram Kingdom. The kings who came after kept making the temple bigger and more beautiful. Its original name was Shivagrha, which means 'House of Shiva'."},{"icon":"festival","h_id":"Tarian di Bawah Cahaya","h_en":"Dancing Under the Lights","body_id":"Sampai hari ini Prambanan menjadi tempat pertunjukan dan wisata. Pada malam hari, candi disinari lampu dan penari menampilkan kisah Ramayana di depannya. Wisatawan dari seluruh dunia datang untuk melihat keindahannya. Candi ini membuat banyak orang kagum pada budaya Indonesia.","body_en":"To this day Prambanan is a place for shows and visits. At night, the temple is lit up and dancers perform the Ramayana story in front of it. Tourists from all over the world come to see its beauty. The temple makes many people admire Indonesian culture."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Runtuh, Lalu Dibangun Lagi","h_en":"Fallen, Then Rebuilt","body_id":"Dahulu Prambanan pernah runtuh dan berubah menjadi tumpukan batu selama ratusan tahun. Gempa bumi dan waktu membuat banyak candinya roboh. Lalu orang-orang menyusun kembali batu-batunya dengan hati-hati. Sekarang Prambanan dilindungi sebagai Warisan Dunia UNESCO.","body_en":"Long ago Prambanan fell down and turned into piles of stone for hundreds of years. Earthquakes and time made many of its temples collapse. Then people carefully put the stones back together. Today Prambanan is protected as a UNESCO World Heritage site."}],"facts":[{"id":"Prambanan adalah candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia!","en":"Prambanan is the biggest Hindu temple in Indonesia!"},{"id":"Candi Siwa di tengah tingginya mencapai 47 meter, setinggi gedung belasan lantai.","en":"The Shiva temple in the middle is 47 meters tall, like a building over ten floors high."},{"id":"Candi ini dipersembahkan untuk tiga dewa Hindu: Brahma, Wisnu, dan Siwa.","en":"The temple is dedicated to three Hindu gods: Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva."},{"id":"Nama aslinya, Siwagrha, berarti 'Rumah Siwa'.","en":"Its original name, Shivagrha, means 'House of Shiva'."},{"id":"Prambanan dibangun lebih dari 1.000 tahun yang lalu dari batu yang disusun tanpa semen.","en":"Prambanan was built more than 1,000 years ago from stones stacked without cement."},{"id":"Pada malam hari, kisah Ramayana ditarikan di depan candi yang bercahaya.","en":"At night, the Ramayana story is danced in front of the glowing temple."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Candi","def_id":"Bangunan suci dari batu peninggalan zaman Hindu-Buddha di Nusantara.","def_en":"A stone holy building left from the Hindu-Buddhist era in the Indonesian islands."},{"term":"Trimurti","def_id":"Tiga dewa utama Hindu: Brahma, Wisnu, dan Siwa.","def_en":"The three main Hindu gods: Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva."},{"term":"Hindu","def_id":"Salah satu agama tertua di dunia yang memuja banyak dewa.","def_en":"One of the world's oldest religions, which worships many gods."},{"term":"Ramayana","def_id":"Cerita kuno tentang Pangeran Rama yang sering ditarikan dan dimainkan.","def_en":"An ancient story about Prince Rama, often danced and performed."},{"term":"Relief","def_id":"Gambar atau cerita yang dipahat timbul pada permukaan batu candi.","def_en":"A picture or story carved so it stands out on a temple's stone surface."},{"term":"Warisan Dunia","def_id":"Tempat istimewa yang dilindungi UNESCO untuk seluruh umat manusia.","def_en":"A special place protected by UNESCO for all of humanity."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/42287c7242816945.jpg","caption_id":"Menara-menara Candi Prambanan yang tinggi dan runcing, berdiri megah di antara rumput hijau.","caption_en":"The tall, pointy towers of Prambanan Temple, standing grandly among green grass.","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/92c42f475f93bd84.jpg","caption_id":"Puncak Prambanan menyembul di antara kabut pagi dan pohon-pohon kelapa.","caption_en":"Prambanan's peaks rise through the morning mist and coconut trees.","credit":"Dwi Oblo of Reuters Indonesia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/69edac8c406826da.jpg","caption_id":"Penari membawakan kisah Ramayana pada malam hari, dengan candi yang bercahaya di belakang.","caption_en":"Dancers perform the Ramayana story at night, with the glowing temple behind them.","credit":"Maria Ismawi","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/82f3e41268621818.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama tahun 1895 saat Prambanan masih berupa reruntuhan batu sebelum diperbaiki.","caption_en":"An old 1895 photo when Prambanan was still a pile of ruins before it was repaired.","credit":"William Henry Jackson","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Candi_Prambanan"},"budaya_tari_kecak_bali":{"id":"budaya_tari_kecak_bali","title_id":"Tari Kecak","title_en":"Kecak Dance","subtitle_id":"Tarian Bali dengan paduan suara 'cak' dari puluhan penari","subtitle_en":"A Balinese dance with the 'cak' chant of dozens of dancers","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Bali, Indonesia","value_en":"Bali, Indonesia"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Penari","label_en":"Performers","value_id":"Puluhan pria","value_en":"Dozens of men"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Iringan","label_en":"Music","value_id":"Suara 'cak', tanpa alat musik","value_en":"The 'cak' chant, no instruments"},{"icon":"theater_comedy","label_id":"Cerita","label_en":"Story","value_id":"Kisah Ramayana","value_en":"The Ramayana story"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Suasana","label_en":"Setting","value_id":"Sering di sore atau malam","value_en":"Often at sunset or night"}],"sections":[{"icon":"theater_comedy","h_id":"Apa Itu Tari Kecak?","h_en":"What Is the Kecak Dance?","body_id":"Tari Kecak adalah tarian sekaligus drama khas dari Pulau Bali. Tarian ini sangat terkenal karena dimainkan oleh puluhan penari laki-laki yang duduk melingkar. Mereka tidak memakai alat musik sama sekali. Sebagai gantinya, para penari berseru 'cak-cak-cak' bersama-sama dengan irama yang cepat. Dari seruan itulah tarian ini mendapat nama 'Kecak'.","body_en":"The Kecak dance is a dance and drama from the island of Bali. It is very famous because it is performed by dozens of male dancers sitting in a circle. They do not use any musical instruments at all. Instead, the dancers chant 'cak-cak-cak' together in a fast rhythm. That chant is how the dance got the name 'Kecak'."},{"icon":"campaign","h_id":"Suara Manusia Jadi Musik","h_en":"Voices Become the Music","body_id":"Yang membuat Kecak istimewa adalah musiknya yang berasal dari suara manusia. Para penari yang duduk melingkar menyerukan 'cak' berulang-ulang dengan irama berbeda-beda. Ada yang berseru cepat, ada yang lambat, sehingga terdengar seperti orkestra. Sambil bersuara, mereka mengangkat dan menggerakkan kedua tangan ke atas. Suara puluhan orang ini terdengar sangat menggetarkan hati.","body_en":"What makes Kecak special is that its music comes from human voices. The dancers sitting in a circle chant 'cak' over and over in different rhythms. Some chant fast and some slow, so it sounds like an orchestra. While chanting, they raise and wave their arms up high. The sound of dozens of people together feels very powerful and exciting."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Kisah Ramayana","h_en":"The Ramayana Story","body_id":"Tari Kecak menceritakan kisah lama yang bernama Ramayana. Dalam cerita ini, Putri Shinta diculik oleh raksasa jahat bernama Rahwana. Pangeran Rama lalu berjuang untuk menyelamatkannya. Ia dibantu oleh pasukan kera dan kera putih yang gagah berani bernama Hanoman. Para penari yang duduk melingkar berperan sebagai pasukan kera dalam cerita seru ini.","body_en":"The Kecak dance tells an old story called the Ramayana. In this story, Princess Sinta is taken away by an evil giant named Ravana. Prince Rama then fights to rescue her. He is helped by an army of monkeys and a brave white monkey named Hanoman. The dancers sitting in the circle play the monkey army in this exciting story."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Did It Come From?","body_id":"Tari Kecak tumbuh dari sebuah ritual lama di Bali yang disebut Sanghyang. Pada tahun 1930-an, seorang seniman Bali bernama Wayan Limbak bekerja sama dengan pelukis dari Jerman, Walter Spies. Mereka mengubah ritual itu menjadi pertunjukan tari yang menceritakan Ramayana. Wayan Limbak lalu memperkenalkan Tari Kecak ke berbagai negara di dunia.","body_en":"The Kecak dance grew out of an old Balinese ritual called Sanghyang. In the 1930s, a Balinese artist named Wayan Limbak worked together with a German painter, Walter Spies. They turned the ritual into a dance show that tells the Ramayana. Wayan Limbak then introduced the Kecak dance to many countries around the world."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Pertunjukan yang Memukau","h_en":"An Amazing Show","body_id":"Sekarang, Tari Kecak menjadi pertunjukan yang sangat digemari, terutama oleh wisatawan di Bali. Pertunjukan sering diadakan saat matahari terbenam di tepi pantai, seperti di Pura Uluwatu yang indah. Beberapa pertunjukan bahkan menampilkan tarian api yang menegangkan. Tari Kecak membuat banyak orang kagum pada keindahan budaya Bali.","body_en":"Today, the Kecak dance is a very popular show, especially for visitors in Bali. Performances are often held at sunset by the sea, such as at the beautiful Uluwatu Temple. Some shows even feature a thrilling fire dance. The Kecak dance makes many people amazed by the beauty of Balinese culture."}],"facts":[{"id":"Tari Kecak tidak memakai alat musik sama sekali, hanya suara penari!","en":"The Kecak dance uses no instruments at all, only the dancers' voices!"},{"id":"Nama 'Kecak' berasal dari seruan 'cak-cak-cak' yang dinyanyikan penari.","en":"The name 'Kecak' comes from the 'cak-cak-cak' chant the dancers sing."},{"id":"Tarian ini dimainkan oleh puluhan penari laki-laki yang duduk melingkar.","en":"The dance is performed by dozens of male dancers sitting in a circle."},{"id":"Tari Kecak menceritakan kisah Ramayana tentang Rama dan Shinta.","en":"The Kecak dance tells the Ramayana story about Rama and Sinta."},{"id":"Kera putih pemberani dalam cerita ini bernama Hanoman.","en":"The brave white monkey in the story is named Hanoman."},{"id":"Tari Kecak diciptakan sekitar tahun 1930-an di Bali.","en":"The Kecak dance was created around the 1930s in Bali."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Ramayana","def_id":"Cerita lama tentang Pangeran Rama yang menyelamatkan Putri Shinta.","def_en":"An old story about Prince Rama rescuing Princess Sinta."},{"term":"Hanoman","def_id":"Kera putih gagah berani yang membantu Rama dalam cerita Ramayana.","def_en":"The brave white monkey who helps Rama in the Ramayana story."},{"term":"Paduan suara","def_id":"Banyak orang yang bersuara atau bernyanyi bersama-sama.","def_en":"Many people making sounds or singing together at the same time."},{"term":"Ritual","def_id":"Upacara khusus yang dilakukan dengan cara tertentu sejak dahulu.","def_en":"A special ceremony done in a certain way since long ago."},{"term":"Pura","def_id":"Tempat ibadah umat Hindu di Bali.","def_en":"A Hindu place of worship in Bali."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/434a268d42c0bbcb.jpg","caption_id":"Puluhan penari Kecak duduk melingkar mengelilingi nyala api saat malam.","caption_en":"Dozens of Kecak dancers sit in a circle around a flame at night.","credit":"Jeong seolah","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/70caa26bf68f5173.jpg","caption_id":"Para penari mengangkat tangan tinggi-tinggi sambil menyerukan 'cak'.","caption_en":"The dancers raise their arms high while chanting 'cak'.","credit":"Mr Aaron","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/fa7dc6c738c04f2e.jpg","caption_id":"Tokoh Hanoman si kera putih tampil di tengah penonton.","caption_en":"The character Hanoman, the white monkey, performs among the audience.","credit":"NarayaIsIyoSoup","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9abe45cd2fb19fe7.jpg","caption_id":"Tarian api yang menegangkan menjadi bagian seru dari pertunjukan Kecak.","caption_en":"A thrilling fire dance is an exciting part of the Kecak show.","credit":"Yuma patarihan79","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/18ef104a014c5287.jpg","caption_id":"Dilihat dari atas, ratusan penari membentuk lingkaran besar yang rapi.","caption_en":"Seen from above, hundreds of dancers form one big, neat circle.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kecak"},"budaya_tari_saman":{"id":"budaya_tari_saman","title_id":"Tari Saman","title_en":"Saman Dance","subtitle_id":"Tarian Aceh dengan tepuk tangan cepat dan gerak kompak","subtitle_en":"An Aceh dance with fast claps and perfect teamwork","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Aceh (Suku Gayo)","value_en":"Aceh (Gayo people)"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Penari","label_en":"Performers","value_id":"Belasan penari, berjajar","value_en":"Many dancers, in a row"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Iringan","label_en":"Music","value_id":"Tepuk tangan & nyanyian","value_en":"Claps & singing"},{"icon":"diversity_3","label_id":"Ciri khas","label_en":"Famous for","value_id":"Gerak kompak & cepat","value_en":"Fast, united moves"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Apa Itu Tari Saman?","h_en":"What Is the Saman Dance?","body_id":"Tari Saman adalah tarian tradisional dari Suku Gayo di Provinsi Aceh. Tarian ini terkenal di seluruh dunia karena gerakannya yang sangat cepat dan kompak. Para penari duduk berjajar rapat bahu-membahu, lalu bergerak bersama-sama seolah-olah satu tubuh. Tari Saman sering disebut 'Tari Seribu Tangan' karena banyaknya tangan yang bergerak serempak.","body_en":"The Saman dance is a traditional dance from the Gayo people in Aceh Province. It is famous all over the world because of its very fast and united movements. The dancers sit in a tight row, shoulder to shoulder, and move together as if they were one body. The Saman dance is often called the 'Dance of a Thousand Hands' because so many hands move at the same time."},{"icon":"back_hand","h_id":"Tepuk Tangan dan Tepuk Dada","h_en":"Clapping Hands and Chest","body_id":"Yang paling seru dari Tari Saman adalah gerakan tangannya. Para penari bertepuk tangan, menepuk dada, dan menepuk paha dengan sangat cepat. Mereka juga menggoyangkan badan dan kepala ke kiri dan ke kanan. Semua gerakan ini harus dilakukan dengan tepat dan serempak. Kalau satu penari saja salah, gerakannya bisa terlihat tidak kompak.","body_en":"The most exciting part of the Saman dance is its hand movements. The dancers clap their hands, slap their chests, and pat their thighs very fast. They also sway their bodies and heads to the left and right. All of these moves must be done exactly and at the same time. If even one dancer makes a mistake, the dance can look out of step."},{"icon":"campaign","h_id":"Nyanyian dan Pemimpin","h_en":"Singing and the Leader","body_id":"Tari Saman tidak memakai alat musik. Musiknya berasal dari tepuk tangan para penari dan nyanyian mereka. Ada seorang pemimpin yang disebut syekh. Syekh bertugas menyanyikan syair dan mengatur kapan gerakan harus cepat atau lambat. Para penari lalu menjawab nyanyian itu bersama-sama, sehingga terdengar sangat merdu dan bersemangat.","body_en":"The Saman dance uses no musical instruments. Its music comes from the dancers' claps and their singing. There is a leader called the syekh. The syekh sings the verses and decides when the moves should be fast or slow. The dancers then answer the song together, so it sounds very sweet and full of spirit."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Pesan dalam Tarian","h_en":"A Message in the Dance","body_id":"Dahulu, Tari Saman dipakai untuk menyampaikan pesan-pesan yang baik kepada masyarakat. Syair lagunya berisi nasihat tentang kebaikan, sopan santun, dan kebersamaan. Tarian ini juga mengajarkan kita untuk kompak dan saling bekerja sama. Sampai sekarang, Tari Saman sering ditampilkan dalam acara-acara penting dan perayaan di Aceh.","body_en":"Long ago, the Saman dance was used to share good messages with the people. Its song verses contain advice about kindness, good manners, and togetherness. The dance also teaches us to work as a team and help one another. Even today, the Saman dance is often performed at important events and celebrations in Aceh."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pada tahun 2011, UNESCO mengakui Tari Saman sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia. Pengakuan ini membuat masyarakat Indonesia sangat bangga. Sekarang Tari Saman dipelajari oleh banyak anak dan ditampilkan sampai ke luar negeri. Ayo kita ikut menjaga dan melestarikan tarian yang penuh semangat ini agar tidak pernah hilang!","body_en":"In 2011, UNESCO recognized the Saman dance as a World Cultural Heritage. This recognition made Indonesian people very proud. Today the Saman dance is learned by many children and performed all the way to other countries. Let's help protect and keep this spirited dance alive so it is never lost!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Tari Saman sering disebut 'Tari Seribu Tangan' karena gerakan tangannya yang banyak dan serempak.","en":"The Saman dance is often called the 'Dance of a Thousand Hands' for its many hands moving at once."},{"id":"Tarian ini tidak memakai alat musik, hanya tepuk tangan dan nyanyian.","en":"The dance uses no instruments, only claps and singing."},{"id":"Para penari duduk berjajar rapat dan bergerak seperti satu tubuh.","en":"The dancers sit in a tight row and move like one body."},{"id":"UNESCO mengakui Tari Saman sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2011.","en":"UNESCO recognized the Saman dance as a World Heritage in 2011."},{"id":"Pemimpin Tari Saman yang menyanyi dan memberi aba-aba disebut syekh.","en":"The leader of the Saman dance who sings and gives signals is called the syekh."},{"id":"Tari Saman berasal dari Suku Gayo di Provinsi Aceh.","en":"The Saman dance comes from the Gayo people in Aceh Province."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Suku Gayo","def_id":"Kelompok masyarakat yang tinggal di dataran tinggi Provinsi Aceh.","def_en":"A group of people who live in the highlands of Aceh Province."},{"term":"Syekh","def_id":"Pemimpin Tari Saman yang menyanyi dan mengatur gerakan penari.","def_en":"The leader of the Saman dance who sings and guides the dancers' moves."},{"term":"Syair","def_id":"Kata-kata indah yang dinyanyikan dalam sebuah lagu atau tarian.","def_en":"Beautiful words that are sung in a song or dance."},{"term":"Kompak","def_id":"Bergerak atau bekerja bersama-sama dengan rapi dan serempak.","def_en":"Moving or working together neatly and at the same time."},{"term":"Warisan budaya","def_id":"Sesuatu yang berharga dari nenek moyang yang harus kita jaga.","def_en":"Something precious from our ancestors that we must protect."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cf3e3f9a0adcac15.jpg","caption_id":"Para penari mengangkat tangan serempak dengan pakaian warna-warni yang cerah.","caption_en":"Dancers raise their hands together in bright, colorful costumes.","credit":"Herusutimbul","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7add58c305f10a61.jpg","caption_id":"Penari laki-laki berjajar bertepuk tangan dengan busana adat Gayo merah-hitam.","caption_en":"Male dancers in a row clap their hands in red-and-black Gayo costume.","credit":"Winara al gayo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c716b9089d1b40c5.jpg","caption_id":"Ribuan penari menampilkan Tari Saman bersama dalam satu pertunjukan besar.","caption_en":"Thousands of dancers perform the Saman dance together in one huge show.","credit":"Adearmanda","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/83001be976af9ce4.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok penari berpose dengan busana adat Gayo yang indah.","caption_en":"A group of dancers pose in their beautiful Gayo costumes.","credit":"Fajriboy","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6bf9be7327a5f3ed.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama masyarakat Gayo berkumpul lebih dari seratus tahun yang lalu.","caption_en":"An old photo of the Gayo people gathering more than a hundred years ago.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tari_Saman"},"budaya_wayang_kulit":{"id":"budaya_wayang_kulit","title_id":"Wayang Kulit","title_en":"Shadow Puppets","subtitle_id":"Boneka kulit yang bercerita lewat bayangan!","subtitle_en":"Leather puppets that tell stories with shadows!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Budaya Jawa, Indonesia","value_en":"Javanese culture, Indonesia"},{"icon":"texture","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Kulit kerbau atau sapi","value_en":"Buffalo or cow leather"},{"icon":"auto_stories","label_id":"Cerita","label_en":"Stories","value_id":"Ramayana & Mahabharata","value_en":"Ramayana & Mahabharata"},{"icon":"person","label_id":"Pemain","label_en":"Performer","value_id":"Dalang (memainkan semua tokoh)","value_en":"Dalang (plays all characters)"},{"icon":"music_note","label_id":"Musik","label_en":"Music","value_id":"Gamelan & nyanyian pesinden","value_en":"Gamelan & singer's songs"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan Budaya UNESCO (2003)","value_en":"UNESCO Cultural Heritage (2003)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"theater_comedy","h_id":"Apa Itu Wayang Kulit?","h_en":"What Is Wayang Kulit?","body_id":"Wayang kulit adalah boneka pipih yang dibuat dari kulit hewan. Boneka ini dipakai untuk memainkan cerita di balik layar putih. Wayang kulit berasal dari budaya Jawa di Indonesia. Kata 'wayang' berarti 'bayangan', karena penonton melihat bayangan boneka di layar.","body_en":"Wayang kulit is a flat puppet made from animal leather. These puppets are used to act out stories behind a white screen. Wayang kulit comes from Javanese culture in Indonesia. The word 'wayang' means 'shadow', because the audience watches the puppets' shadows on the screen."},{"icon":"person","h_id":"Dalang Sang Pencerita","h_en":"The Dalang, the Storyteller","body_id":"Wayang kulit dimainkan oleh satu orang hebat bernama dalang. Dalang menggerakkan semua boneka sambil mengisi suara setiap tokoh. Ia duduk di balik kelir, yaitu layar kain putih, dengan lampu menyala di belakangnya. Sebuah dalang bisa bercerita semalam suntuk tanpa lelah!","body_en":"Wayang kulit is performed by one amazing person called the dalang. The dalang moves all the puppets while giving each character a voice. The dalang sits behind the kelir, a white cloth screen, with a lamp shining behind it. A dalang can tell a story all night long without getting tired!"},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Cerita yang Dimainkan","h_en":"The Stories Performed","body_id":"Cerita wayang disebut lakon. Cerita yang paling terkenal berasal dari kisah Ramayana dan Mahabharata. Kisah-kisah ini bercerita tentang ksatria, raja, raksasa, dan kebaikan melawan kejahatan. Ada juga tokoh lucu bernama punakawan: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, dan Bagong.","body_en":"A wayang story is called a lakon. The most famous stories come from the Ramayana and Mahabharata. These tales are about knights, kings, giants, and good against evil. There are also funny characters called the punakawan: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, and Bagong."},{"icon":"brush","h_id":"Bagaimana Wayang Dibuat?","h_en":"How a Puppet Is Made","body_id":"Wayang kulit dibuat dari kulit kerbau, sapi, atau kambing yang sudah dikeringkan. Pengrajin memahat lubang-lubang kecil dengan alat besi tajam supaya wayang terlihat berhias indah. Tangan wayang disambung agar bisa digerakkan. Lalu wayang diberi warna emas dan cat yang cantik.","body_en":"Wayang kulit is made from dried buffalo, cow, or goat leather. Craftspeople carve tiny holes with sharp iron tools so the puppet looks beautifully decorated. The puppet's arms are joined so they can move. Then the puppet is colored with gold and pretty paint."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Harta Budaya Kita","h_en":"Our Cultural Treasure","body_id":"Wayang kulit sudah ada sejak lebih dari seribu tahun yang lalu. Dahulu, Sunan Kalijaga memakai wayang untuk mengajarkan kebaikan kepada masyarakat. Pada tahun 2003, UNESCO mengakui wayang kulit sebagai warisan budaya dunia yang indah dan berharga. Ayo kita ikut menjaga seni asli Indonesia ini!","body_en":"Wayang kulit has existed for more than a thousand years. Long ago, Sunan Kalijaga used wayang to teach good values to the people. In 2003, UNESCO recognized wayang kulit as a beautiful and precious world cultural heritage. Let's all help protect this original Indonesian art!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Kata 'wayang' berarti 'bayangan' dalam bahasa Jawa.","en":"The word 'wayang' means 'shadow' in Javanese."},{"id":"Satu dalang bisa memainkan dan menyuarakan puluhan tokoh sendirian!","en":"A single dalang can play and voice dozens of characters all alone!"},{"id":"Wayang dibuat dari kulit kerbau atau sapi, bukan dari kertas.","en":"Puppets are made from buffalo or cow leather, not from paper."},{"id":"Pertunjukan wayang diiringi musik gamelan dan nyanyian pesinden.","en":"A wayang show is accompanied by gamelan music and a singer's songs."},{"id":"Punakawan seperti Semar dan Petruk adalah tokoh lucu kesukaan penonton.","en":"The punakawan, like Semar and Petruk, are funny characters the audience loves."},{"id":"UNESCO menetapkan wayang kulit sebagai warisan budaya dunia pada tahun 2003.","en":"UNESCO named wayang kulit a world cultural heritage in 2003."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Dalang","def_id":"Orang yang memainkan wayang, mengisi suara, dan menceritakan kisahnya.","def_en":"The person who moves the puppets, voices them, and tells the story."},{"term":"Kelir","def_id":"Layar kain putih tempat bayangan wayang ditampilkan.","def_en":"The white cloth screen where the puppets' shadows appear."},{"term":"Lakon","def_id":"Cerita atau kisah yang dimainkan dalam pertunjukan wayang.","def_en":"The story or tale acted out in a wayang show."},{"term":"Gamelan","def_id":"Kelompok alat musik Jawa yang mengiringi pertunjukan wayang.","def_en":"A set of Javanese musical instruments that accompanies a wayang show."},{"term":"Punakawan","def_id":"Tokoh-tokoh pelayan yang lucu dan bijak: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, Bagong.","def_en":"The funny, wise servant characters: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, and Bagong."},{"term":"Pesinden","def_id":"Penyanyi wanita yang menyanyikan tembang saat pertunjukan wayang.","def_en":"A female singer who sings songs during a wayang show."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/30caf2d89435c2c5.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang dalang cilik mengangkat wayang kulit yang berhias rumit di balik lampu pertunjukan.","caption_en":"A young dalang lifts an intricately decorated wayang puppet behind the show's lamp.","credit":"Badroe Zaman, Semarang, Central Java","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/88fcf4bc4917deb0.jpg","caption_id":"Inilah bayangan wayang di layar; karena inilah wayang disebut seni 'bayangan'.","caption_en":"These are the puppets' shadows on the screen; this is why wayang is called the art of 'shadows'.","credit":"Jpatokal (English Wikipedia)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/018084a5b2063f22.jpg","caption_id":"Dalang menggerakkan beberapa wayang sekaligus di depan layar yang bercahaya.","caption_en":"A dalang moves several puppets at once in front of the glowing screen.","credit":"Gunawan Kartapranata","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/934d4dd073fedc8b.jpg","caption_id":"Dalang mengangkat dua gunungan berbentuk daun, biasanya untuk membuka cerita wayang.","caption_en":"A dalang raises two leaf-shaped gunungan puppets, usually to open the wayang story.","credit":"FaizAttariqi","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/198af794fca34940.jpg","caption_id":"Gambar wayang berwarna-warni memperlihatkan hiasan rumit dan bentuk khas sebuah tokoh.","caption_en":"A colorful drawing of a puppet shows the detailed decoration and special shape of one character.","credit":"Mangkunagara VII","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayang_kulit"},"ekonomi_uang_rupiah":{"id":"ekonomi_uang_rupiah","title_id":"Uang Rupiah","title_en":"The Rupiah","subtitle_id":"Uang resmi Indonesia yang kita pakai untuk membeli barang dan menabung.","subtitle_en":"Indonesia's official money that we use to buy things and to save.","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Negara","label_en":"Country","value_id":"Indonesia","value_en":"Indonesia"},{"icon":"payments","label_id":"Simbol","label_en":"Symbol","value_id":"Rp (kode IDR)","value_en":"Rp (code IDR)"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Penerbit","label_en":"Issued by","value_id":"Bank Indonesia","value_en":"Bank Indonesia"},{"icon":"toll","label_id":"Bentuk","label_en":"Forms","value_id":"Uang kertas dan uang logam","value_en":"Paper notes and metal coins"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Gambar","label_en":"Pictures","value_id":"Wajah pahlawan nasional","value_en":"Faces of national heroes"}],"sections":[{"icon":"payments","h_id":"Apa Itu Uang Rupiah?","h_en":"What Is the Rupiah?","body_id":"Rupiah adalah uang resmi yang dipakai di seluruh Indonesia. Kita memakainya untuk membeli makanan, baju, buku, dan banyak hal lain. Tanda atau lambang rupiah adalah \"Rp\". Nama rupiah berasal dari kata Sanskerta \"rupya\" yang artinya perak, karena dahulu uang dibuat dari logam perak. Dengan uang, kita bisa menukarnya dengan barang yang kita butuhkan.","body_en":"The rupiah is the official money used all over Indonesia. We use it to buy food, clothes, books, and many other things. The sign or symbol for the rupiah is \"Rp\". The name rupiah comes from the Sanskrit word \"rupya\", which means silver, because long ago money was made from silver metal. With money, we can trade it for the things we need."},{"icon":"account_balance","h_id":"Siapa yang Membuat Uang?","h_en":"Who Makes the Money?","body_id":"Tidak sembarang orang boleh membuat uang. Di Indonesia, hanya Bank Indonesia yang berhak mencetak dan mengeluarkan uang rupiah. Bank Indonesia menjaga agar jumlah uang pas dan nilainya tetap terjaga. Setiap lembar uang dibuat dengan tanda pengaman khusus agar tidak mudah dipalsukan. Karena itu, uang asli harus selalu berasal dari Bank Indonesia.","body_en":"Not just anyone is allowed to make money. In Indonesia, only Bank Indonesia has the right to print and issue the rupiah. Bank Indonesia makes sure the amount of money is just right and its value stays steady. Each piece of money is made with special safety marks so it cannot easily be copied. That is why real money must always come from Bank Indonesia."},{"icon":"toll","h_id":"Uang Kertas dan Uang Logam","h_en":"Notes and Coins","body_id":"Uang rupiah ada dalam dua bentuk. Yang pertama adalah uang kertas, yang lembut dan berwarna-warni, seperti seribu, lima ribu, sepuluh ribu, sampai seratus ribu rupiah. Yang kedua adalah uang logam, yang keras dan bulat, biasanya bernilai kecil seperti lima ratus atau seribu rupiah. Keduanya sama-sama uang yang sah dan bisa dipakai berbelanja.","body_en":"The rupiah comes in two forms. The first is paper money, which is soft and colorful, such as one thousand, five thousand, ten thousand, up to one hundred thousand rupiah. The second is coins, which are hard and round, usually worth small amounts like five hundred or one thousand rupiah. Both are legal money and can be used for shopping."},{"icon":"military_tech","h_id":"Pahlawan di Uang Kita","h_en":"The Heroes on Our Money","body_id":"Coba perhatikan gambar di uang kertas rupiah. Wajah-wajah yang ada di sana adalah pahlawan nasional Indonesia, orang-orang yang berjasa besar bagi negara kita. Ada juga gambar pemandangan indah, tarian daerah, dan bunga khas Indonesia. Lewat gambar-gambar ini, uang rupiah membantu kita mengenal dan mengenang sejarah serta kekayaan budaya bangsa.","body_en":"Take a look at the pictures on the rupiah notes. The faces there are Indonesia's national heroes, people who did great things for our country. There are also pictures of beautiful scenery, traditional dances, and Indonesian flowers. Through these pictures, the rupiah helps us learn about and remember our nation's history and rich culture."},{"icon":"savings","h_id":"Menabung Uang","h_en":"Saving Money","body_id":"Uang sebaiknya tidak dihabiskan sekaligus. Kita bisa menyimpan sebagian uang dengan menabung, misalnya di celengan atau di bank. Sedikit demi sedikit, tabungan kita akan tumbuh menjadi banyak. Dengan menabung, kita bisa membeli barang yang kita inginkan kelak atau memakainya saat membutuhkan. Menabung mengajarkan kita untuk hidup hemat dan bijak.","body_en":"Money should not be spent all at once. We can keep some of our money by saving, for example in a piggy bank or at a bank. Little by little, our savings will grow into a lot. By saving, we can buy something we want later or use it when we need it. Saving teaches us to live thriftily and wisely."}],"facts":[{"id":"Lambang uang rupiah adalah \"Rp\" dan kode resminya adalah IDR.","en":"The symbol for the rupiah is \"Rp\" and its official code is IDR."},{"id":"Hanya Bank Indonesia yang boleh mencetak dan mengeluarkan uang rupiah.","en":"Only Bank Indonesia is allowed to print and issue the rupiah."},{"id":"Kata \"rupiah\" berasal dari bahasa Sanskerta yang berarti perak.","en":"The word \"rupiah\" comes from Sanskrit and means silver."},{"id":"Wajah di uang kertas rupiah adalah para pahlawan nasional Indonesia.","en":"The faces on rupiah notes are Indonesia's national heroes."},{"id":"Uang rupiah ada dua bentuk: uang kertas dan uang logam.","en":"The rupiah comes in two forms: paper notes and coins."},{"id":"Setiap uang asli memiliki tanda pengaman agar tidak mudah dipalsukan.","en":"Every real banknote has safety marks so it cannot easily be faked."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Rupiah","def_id":"Uang resmi yang dipakai di seluruh Indonesia, berlambang Rp.","def_en":"The official money used all over Indonesia, with the symbol Rp."},{"term":"Bank Indonesia","def_id":"Lembaga yang berhak mencetak dan mengatur uang rupiah.","def_en":"The body that has the right to print and manage the rupiah."},{"term":"Uang kertas","def_id":"Uang yang terbuat dari bahan lembut dan berwarna-warni.","def_en":"Money made from a soft material and printed in colors."},{"term":"Uang logam","def_id":"Uang keras berbentuk bulat dari logam, biasanya bernilai kecil.","def_en":"Hard, round money made of metal, usually of small value."},{"term":"Pahlawan nasional","def_id":"Orang yang sangat berjasa bagi Indonesia dan dikenang bangsa.","def_en":"A person who did great things for Indonesia and is remembered."},{"term":"Menabung","def_id":"Menyimpan sebagian uang agar terkumpul dan bisa dipakai nanti.","def_en":"Keeping some money so it adds up and can be used later."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b06a638c2740c2bf.jpg","caption_id":"Satu set lengkap uang kertas rupiah terbaru, dari seribu sampai seratus ribu rupiah.","caption_en":"A full set of the newest rupiah notes, from one thousand to one hundred thousand rupiah.","credit":"Rizardianz2","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/045410260c06f650.jpg","caption_id":"Uang seribu rupiah dengan gambar pahlawan nasional Cut Meutia.","caption_en":"A one-thousand-rupiah note showing the national hero Cut Meutia.","credit":"Bank Indonesia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6aa01f6df908c8ed.jpg","caption_id":"Beberapa uang kertas rupiah lama yang menampilkan wajah para pahlawan.","caption_en":"Several older rupiah notes showing the faces of national heroes.","credit":"EvanC0912 / Davidelit","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2ae58535b3707c6c.jpg","caption_id":"Bagian belakang uang sepuluh ribu rupiah lama bergambar Candi Borobudur.","caption_en":"The back of an older ten-thousand-rupiah note picturing Borobudur Temple.","credit":"Bank Indonesia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rupiah"},"ensiklopedia_anggrek_macan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_anggrek_macan","title_id":"Anggrek Tebu","title_en":"Giant Orchid","subtitle_id":"Anggrek terbesar di dunia, berat dan tinggi!","subtitle_en":"The biggest orchid in the whole world!","data_card":[{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Tanaman anggrek","value_en":"Orchid plant"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan tropis Asia Tenggara","value_en":"Southeast Asian rainforest"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sampai 7,6 meter","value_en":"Up to 7.6 meters tall"},{"icon":"savings","label_id":"Berat","label_en":"Weight","value_id":"Bisa lebih dari 1 ton","value_en":"Can be over 1 ton"},{"icon":"local_florist","label_id":"Mekar","label_en":"Blooms","value_id":"Sekali tiap 2-4 tahun","value_en":"Once every 2-4 years"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Indonesia & Asia Tenggara","value_en":"Indonesia & SE Asia"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Anggrek Tebu?","h_en":"What Is the Giant Orchid?","body_id":"Anggrek tebu adalah anggrek terbesar di dunia. Orang juga memanggilnya Anggrek Raksasa, Anggrek Harimau, atau Ratu Anggrek. Tanaman ini bisa tumbuh sangat besar dan berat sekali. Bayangkan, ada yang beratnya lebih dari satu ton!","body_en":"The giant orchid is the biggest orchid in the world. People also call it the Giant Orchid, Tiger Orchid, or Queen of Orchids. This plant can grow huge and very heavy. Imagine, some weigh more than one ton!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Anggrek tebu tumbuh di hutan-hutan Asia Tenggara. Kamu bisa menemukannya di Indonesia, seperti di Sumatra, Jawa, Sulawesi, dan Kalimantan. Tanaman ini juga ada di Thailand, Myanmar, Vietnam, dan Malaysia. Ia suka tempat yang hangat dan terkena cahaya matahari.","body_en":"The giant orchid grows in the forests of Southeast Asia. You can find it in Indonesia, like in Sumatra, Java, Sulawesi, and Borneo. It also lives in Thailand, Myanmar, Vietnam, and Malaysia. It loves warm spots with plenty of sunshine."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Special Features","body_id":"Anggrek ini bisa tumbuh setinggi rumah! Pernah ada yang mencapai lebih dari 7 meter. Batangnya yang tebal disebut pseudobulb dan bisa sepanjang 2,5 meter. Anggrek tebu adalah tanaman epifit, artinya ia tumbuh menempel di pohon lain. Akarnya tumbuh seperti ikatan tebal yang menempel di pohon atau batu.","body_en":"This orchid can grow as tall as a house! One was even taller than 7 meters. Its thick stems are called pseudobulbs and can be 2.5 meters long. The giant orchid is an epiphyte, which means it grows clinging onto other trees. Its roots grow in thick bundles that hold onto trees or rocks."},{"icon":"local_florist","h_id":"Bunga yang Istimewa","h_en":"Its Amazing Flowers","body_id":"Bunganya berwarna kuning cerah dengan bintik-bintik merah tua. Satu tangkai bisa punya hingga 80 bunga, dan satu tanaman bisa berbunga ribuan! Anggrek ini hanya mekar sekali setiap dua sampai empat tahun. Tapi saat mekar, bunganya tetap segar dan indah sampai berminggu-minggu.","body_en":"Its flowers are bright yellow with dark red spots. One stalk can have up to 80 flowers, and one plant can bloom thousands! This orchid blooms only once every two to four years. But when it blooms, the flowers stay fresh and pretty for weeks."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Kita Jaga!","h_en":"Let's Take Care of It!","body_id":"Anggrek tebu adalah harta alam Indonesia yang langka dan istimewa. Tanaman ini tumbuh lambat dan butuh hutan yang sehat untuk hidup. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap hijau. Dengan begitu, anak-anak masa depan juga bisa melihat raksasa cantik ini!","body_en":"The giant orchid is a rare and special treasure of Indonesia's nature. This plant grows slowly and needs healthy forests to live. We can help by keeping forests green. That way, future children can also see this beautiful giant!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Anggrek tebu adalah anggrek terbesar di dunia!","en":"The giant orchid is the biggest orchid in the world!"},{"id":"Pernah ada yang tingginya lebih dari 7 meter, setinggi rumah.","en":"One was over 7 meters tall, as tall as a house."},{"id":"Beratnya bisa lebih dari satu ton, seperti seekor sapi besar.","en":"It can weigh over one ton, like a big cow."},{"id":"Satu tanaman pernah berbunga sampai ribuan kuntum sekaligus!","en":"One plant once bloomed with thousands of flowers at once!"},{"id":"Anggrek ini hanya mekar sekali setiap 2 sampai 4 tahun.","en":"This orchid blooms only once every 2 to 4 years."},{"id":"Ada satu yang ditanam tahun 1861 dan masih hidup hingga kini!","en":"One planted in 1861 is still alive today!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Anggrek","def_id":"Jenis tanaman berbunga indah yang sering tumbuh menempel di pohon.","def_en":"A kind of plant with beautiful flowers that often grows on trees."},{"term":"Pseudobulb","def_id":"Batang anggrek yang tebal dan menggembung untuk menyimpan air dan makanan.","def_en":"The thick, swollen orchid stem that stores water and food."},{"term":"Epifit","def_id":"Tanaman yang tumbuh menempel di pohon lain, tapi tidak mencuri makanannya.","def_en":"A plant that grows clinging onto another tree without stealing its food."},{"term":"Mekar","def_id":"Saat kuncup bunga terbuka dan menjadi bunga yang cantik.","def_en":"When a flower bud opens up into a pretty flower."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/63ce9b63483762b3.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok bunga anggrek tebu kuning kecokelatan bermandi cahaya matahari.","caption_en":"A cluster of golden-brown giant orchid flowers basking in sunlight.","credit":"Meneerke bloem","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0660c966a101239b.jpg","caption_id":"Satu bunga anggrek tebu kuning dengan bintik-bintik merah tua, di antara daun hijau.","caption_en":"A single yellow giant orchid flower with dark red spots among green leaves.","credit":"Brutusaurus","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/12eb3e4b61ec0623.jpg","caption_id":"Bunga anggrek tebu menghadap depan, memperlihatkan kelopak berbintik yang indah.","caption_en":"A giant orchid flower facing front, showing off its beautiful spotted petals.","credit":"Brutusaurus","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anggrek_tebu"},"ensiklopedia_anoa_sulawesi_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_anoa_sulawesi_1","title_id":"Anoa","title_en":"Anoa","subtitle_id":"Kerbau kerdil istimewa khas Pulau Sulawesi.","subtitle_en":"The special dwarf buffalo of Sulawesi.","data_card":[{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Class","value_id":"Mamalia (keluarga kerbau)","value_en":"Mammal (buffalo family)"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan lebat","value_en":"Thick rainforest"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Sulawesi & Pulau Buton","value_en":"Sulawesi & Buton Island"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Size","value_id":"60-100 cm di pundak","value_en":"60-100 cm at the shoulder"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Daun & tumbuhan hutan","value_en":"Leaves & forest plants"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam punah","value_en":"Endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Anoa?","h_en":"What Is an Anoa?","body_id":"Anoa adalah kerbau mungil yang sering disebut kerbau kerdil. Bentuk tubuhnya mirip kerbau, tapi ukurannya jauh lebih kecil. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi dan Pulau Buton di Indonesia. Karena hanya ada di sana, anoa disebut hewan endemik.","body_en":"The anoa is a tiny buffalo often called the dwarf buffalo. Its body looks like a buffalo, but it is much smaller. This animal lives only on Sulawesi Island and Buton Island in Indonesia. Because it lives only there, the anoa is called an endemic animal."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Anoa tinggal di dalam hutan hujan yang masih lebat dan jarang dilewati manusia. Pulau Sulawesi adalah rumah istimewa bagi banyak hewan yang hanya ada di sana. Salah satu kebiasaan favorit anoa adalah berkubang di lumpur. Berkubang membantu tubuhnya tetap sejuk dan bersih.","body_en":"The anoa lives deep in thick rainforests that people rarely visit. Sulawesi Island is a special home for many animals found nowhere else. One of the anoa's favorite habits is wallowing in mud. Wallowing helps keep its body cool and clean."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Special Features","body_id":"Anoa punya tanduk yang mengarah ke belakang dan dasarnya berbentuk seperti segitiga. Kepalanya mirip sapi, dan kakinya mirip banteng. Ada dua jenis anoa: anoa dataran rendah yang lebih besar, dan anoa pegunungan yang lebih kecil. Anoa pegunungan punya tanduk melingkar dan ekor pendek yang lembut.","body_en":"The anoa has horns that point backward with a triangle-shaped base. Its head looks like a cow's, and its legs look like a wild ox's. There are two kinds: the bigger lowland anoa and the smaller mountain anoa. The mountain anoa has curved horns and a short, soft tail."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Anoa adalah kebanggaan dan ciri khas Pulau Sulawesi. Ia tinggal di Wallacea, daerah unik yang penuh hewan dan tumbuhan yang hanya ada di sana. Anoa termasuk hewan yang pemalu dan suka menyendiri. Para ilmuwan menyayangi anoa karena ia sangat penting bagi alam Indonesia.","body_en":"The anoa is the pride and symbol of Sulawesi Island. It lives in Wallacea, a unique area full of animals and plants found only there. The anoa is a shy creature that likes to be alone. Scientists love the anoa because it is so important to Indonesia's nature."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Sekarang jumlah anoa semakin sedikit, jadi ia perlu kita lindungi. Hewan ini sudah dijaga oleh hukum Indonesia sejak tahun 1931. Anoa butuh hutan yang aman dan sehat untuk hidup. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu anoa terus berkembang biak dengan bahagia.","body_en":"Today there are fewer anoa, so we need to protect it. This animal has been guarded by Indonesian law since 1931. The anoa needs safe and healthy forests to live. By protecting forests, we help the anoa keep growing happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Anoa adalah kerbau terkecil di dunia, disebut kerbau kerdil!","en":"The anoa is the smallest wild buffalo in the world, the dwarf buffalo!"},{"id":"Anoa hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi dan Pulau Buton.","en":"The anoa lives only on Sulawesi and Buton Islands."},{"id":"Ada dua jenis: anoa pegunungan dan anoa dataran rendah.","en":"There are two kinds: the mountain anoa and the lowland anoa."},{"id":"Anoa suka berkubang di lumpur agar tubuhnya tetap sejuk.","en":"The anoa loves to wallow in mud to keep its body cool."},{"id":"Tanduk anoa berbentuk segitiga di bagian dasarnya.","en":"The anoa's horns have a triangle shape at their base."},{"id":"Anoa sudah dilindungi hukum Indonesia sejak tahun 1931.","en":"The anoa has been protected by Indonesian law since 1931."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hidup hanya di satu tempat di dunia.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives in only one place in the world."},{"term":"Berkubang","def_id":"Berguling-guling di lumpur agar tubuh tetap sejuk dan bersih dari serangga.","def_en":"Rolling around in mud to stay cool and clean of bugs."},{"term":"Wallacea","def_id":"Daerah istimewa di Indonesia, termasuk Sulawesi, yang penuh hewan unik.","def_en":"A special region of Indonesia, including Sulawesi, full of unique animals."},{"term":"Mamalia","def_id":"Hewan yang menyusui anaknya dan biasanya berbulu, seperti anoa dan sapi.","def_en":"An animal that feeds milk to its babies and usually has fur, like the anoa and cows."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9aadc51ed284047d.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa muda berdiri dan menatap kita, tubuhnya kecil seperti kerbau mini.","caption_en":"A young anoa stands and looks at us, its body small like a mini buffalo.","credit":"RianHS","license":"CC BY 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/db38c2979418f98f.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa menundukkan kepala, memperlihatkan tanduk runcing yang mengarah ke belakang.","caption_en":"An anoa lowers its head, showing its sharp horns that point backward.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cc575629ae3b55cf.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa berwarna cokelat sedang beristirahat dengan tenang.","caption_en":"A brown anoa resting calmly.","credit":"JERRYE AND ROY KLOTZ MD","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b769606dc03bc3bc.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa dataran rendah berwarna hitam berdiri di antara rerumputan hijau.","caption_en":"A black lowland anoa stands among green plants.","credit":"Bluemoose at English Wikipedia","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anoa"},"ensiklopedia_badak_jawa":{"id":"ensiklopedia_badak_jawa","title_id":"Badak Jawa","title_en":"Javan Rhinoceros","subtitle_id":"Badak bercula satu paling langka di dunia.","subtitle_en":"The rarest one-horned rhino in the world.","data_card":[{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Class","value_id":"Mamalia besar","value_en":"Large mammal"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan dataran rendah","value_en":"Lowland rainforest"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon","value_en":"Ujung Kulon National Park"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Daun & pucuk tumbuhan","value_en":"Leaves & plant shoots"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Usia","label_en":"Lifespan","value_id":"30-45 tahun","value_en":"30-45 years"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Sangat langka (kritis)","value_en":"Critically endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Badak Jawa?","h_en":"What Is the Javan Rhino?","body_id":"Badak jawa adalah badak bercula satu yang tubuhnya cukup kecil di antara badak lainnya. Kulitnya tebal dan berlipat-lipat, seperti memakai baju pelindung dari baja. Hewan ini adalah salah satu badak paling langka di seluruh dunia. Culanya pendek, biasanya tidak lebih panjang dari sejengkal tangan.","body_en":"The Javan rhino is a one-horned rhino with a smaller body than most other rhinos. Its skin is thick and folded, like it is wearing armor made of steel. This animal is one of the rarest rhinos in the whole world. Its horn is short, usually no longer than a hand's span."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Hari ini, semua badak jawa liar hanya tinggal di satu tempat: Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon. Tempat ini berada di ujung paling barat Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Dulu badak jawa hidup di banyak negara Asia, tapi sekarang tinggal sedikit. Ujung Kulon bahkan diakui dunia sebagai Situs Warisan Dunia UNESCO.","body_en":"Today, all wild Javan rhinos live in just one place: Ujung Kulon National Park. This park is on the far western tip of Java Island, Indonesia. Long ago Javan rhinos lived in many Asian countries, but now only a few remain. Ujung Kulon is even recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site."},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Badak jawa suka tinggal di hutan dataran rendah yang lebat dan padang rumput yang basah. Hewan ini senang menyendiri dan biasanya berjalan-jalan sendirian. Mereka suka berkubang di lumpur untuk mendinginkan tubuh. Badak dewasa hampir tidak punya musuh, dan bisa hidup sampai 30 hingga 45 tahun!","body_en":"The Javan rhino loves thick lowland forests and wet grasslands. This animal enjoys being alone and usually wanders by itself. It likes to wallow in mud to cool down its body. Adult rhinos have almost no enemies, and can live up to 30 to 45 years!"},{"icon":"photo_camera","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Badak jawa sangat langka, jadi para ilmuwan jarang melihatnya langsung. Mereka memakai kamera jebakan yang memotret saat badak lewat. Pada tahun 2011, kamera berhasil merekam ibu-ibu badak bersama anaknya. Itu berita yang membahagiakan, karena membuktikan badak jawa masih punya bayi di alam liar!","body_en":"The Javan rhino is so rare that scientists rarely see it in person. They use camera traps that take photos when a rhino walks by. In 2011, cameras filmed mother rhinos with their babies. That was happy news, because it proved Javan rhinos still have babies in the wild!"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Karena jumlahnya tinggal sedikit, badak jawa sangat butuh perlindungan kita. Para penjaga taman bekerja keras menjaga mereka tetap aman. Menjaga hutan Ujung Kulon tetap sehat sangat penting bagi badak. Kalau kita semua peduli, badak jawa bisa terus hidup untuk waktu yang lama.","body_en":"Because so few are left, the Javan rhino really needs our protection. Park rangers work hard to keep them safe. Keeping the Ujung Kulon forest healthy is very important for the rhinos. If we all care, the Javan rhino can keep living for a long time."}],"facts":[{"id":"Badak jawa adalah salah satu badak paling langka di dunia!","en":"The Javan rhino is one of the rarest rhinos in the world!"},{"id":"Semua badak jawa liar hanya hidup di Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon.","en":"All wild Javan rhinos live only in Ujung Kulon National Park."},{"id":"Kulitnya berlipat-lipat seperti memakai baju zirah dari baja.","en":"Its folded skin looks like armor made of steel."},{"id":"Badak jawa bisa hidup sampai 30 hingga 45 tahun di alam liar.","en":"The Javan rhino can live 30 to 45 years in the wild."},{"id":"Para ilmuwan memakai kamera jebakan untuk mengintip badak.","en":"Scientists use camera traps to peek at the rhinos."},{"id":"Tahun 2011, kamera merekam bayi badak bersama ibunya!","en":"In 2011, cameras filmed baby rhinos with their moms!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Cula","def_id":"Tanduk keras di hidung badak; badak jawa hanya punya satu cula.","def_en":"The hard horn on a rhino's nose; the Javan rhino has just one."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan yang hidup hanya di satu tempat di dunia.","def_en":"An animal that lives in only one place in the world."},{"term":"Kamera jebakan","def_id":"Kamera di hutan yang memotret sendiri saat ada hewan lewat.","def_en":"A camera in the forest that snaps a photo by itself when an animal passes."},{"term":"Berkubang","def_id":"Berguling-guling di lumpur agar tubuh tetap sejuk.","def_en":"Rolling in mud to keep the body cool."},{"term":"Situs Warisan Dunia","def_id":"Tempat istimewa yang dilindungi dunia karena sangat penting bagi alam.","def_en":"A special place protected by the world because it is so important to nature."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/01c213da6cb774ae.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama seekor badak jawa, memperlihatkan kulit tebal berlipat seperti baju zirah.","caption_en":"An old photo of a Javan rhino, showing its thick folded skin like armor.","credit":"T.Dixon. The Zoological Society of London","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/360d5dadfb2dfc50.jpg","caption_id":"Seekor induk badak bercula satu menjaga anaknya, mirip cara badak jawa merawat bayinya.","caption_en":"A one-horned rhino mother guards her calf, much like how Javan rhinos care for their babies.","credit":"Jo Oh","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/17b1a5b62b81d39f.jpg","caption_id":"Hutan hijau Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon, rumah terakhir badak jawa di alam liar.","caption_en":"The green forest of Ujung Kulon National Park, the last wild home of the Javan rhino.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Badak_jawa"},"ensiklopedia_bekantan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_bekantan","title_id":"Bekantan","title_en":"Proboscis Monkey","subtitle_id":"Monyet berhidung panjang khas Pulau Kalimantan.","subtitle_en":"The long-nosed monkey of Borneo.","data_card":[{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Class","value_id":"Mamalia (monyet)","value_en":"Mammal (monkey)"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan, rawa & hutan pantai","value_en":"Forests, swamps & coast"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Pulau Kalimantan","value_en":"Borneo"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Buah, biji & daun","value_en":"Fruit, seeds & leaves"},{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Kemampuan","label_en":"Talent","value_id":"Perenang & penyelam hebat","value_en":"Great swimmer & diver"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam punah","value_en":"Endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Bekantan?","h_en":"What Is the Proboscis Monkey?","body_id":"Bekantan adalah monyet berhidung panjang dengan rambut hitam kemerahan. Hidung yang besar dan panjang hanya dimiliki bekantan jantan. Orang juga memanggilnya kera belanda atau monyet belanda. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Pulau Kalimantan, jadi disebut hewan endemik.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey is a long-nosed monkey with reddish-black fur. Only the male proboscis monkeys have the big, long nose. People also call it the Dutch monkey or long-nosed monkey. This animal lives only on Borneo, so it is called an endemic animal."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Bekantan tinggal di hutan, rawa, dan hutan dekat pantai di Kalimantan. Kamu bisa menemukannya di Kalimantan Selatan, Timur, dan Utara. Bekantan adalah hewan kebanggaan Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan. Ia berbagi rumah dengan teman-temannya seperti orangutan dan lutung kelabu.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey lives in forests, swamps, and coastal forests in Borneo. You can find it in South, East, and North Kalimantan. The proboscis monkey is the pride animal of South Kalimantan Province. It shares its home with friends like orangutans and gray langurs."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Perut Buncit","h_en":"Food & Its Big Belly","body_id":"Bekantan suka makan buah, biji-bijian, dan aneka daun. Daun yang dimakannya menghasilkan banyak gas saat dicerna. Itulah kenapa perut bekantan terlihat buncit dan besar. Jadi, perut buncit itu adalah ciri khas yang lucu dari bekantan!","body_en":"The proboscis monkey loves to eat fruits, seeds, and many kinds of leaves. The leaves it eats make lots of gas when digested. That is why the proboscis monkey has a round, big belly. So its big belly is a funny special feature of the proboscis monkey!"},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Perenang yang Hebat","h_en":"A Great Swimmer","body_id":"Bekantan hidup berkelompok, biasanya 10 sampai 32 monyet bersama. Mereka juga jago berenang, bahkan menyeberang dari satu pulau ke pulau lain! Di sela jari kakinya ada selaput tipis yang membantunya berenang. Hidungnya punya semacam katup, jadi ia bisa menyelam beberapa detik.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey lives in groups, usually 10 to 32 monkeys together. They are also great swimmers, even crossing from one island to another! Between their toes is a thin web that helps them swim. Their nose has a kind of valve, so they can dive for a few seconds."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Bekantan perlu kita lindungi karena hutannya semakin berkurang. Kabar baiknya, di Kalimantan Selatan jumlah bekantan naik dari sekitar 3.000 menjadi 4.000 ekor. Ini terjadi karena banyak orang ikut menjaga mereka. Kalau kita menjaga hutan, bekantan bisa terus berenang dan bermain dengan bahagia.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey needs our protection because its forests are shrinking. The good news is that in South Kalimantan their number rose from about 3,000 to 4,000. This happened because many people helped protect them. If we protect the forests, proboscis monkeys can keep swimming and playing happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Hanya bekantan jantan yang punya hidung panjang dan besar!","en":"Only male proboscis monkeys have the long, big nose!"},{"id":"Bekantan hanya hidup di Pulau Kalimantan.","en":"The proboscis monkey lives only on Borneo."},{"id":"Perutnya buncit karena banyak makan daun yang menghasilkan gas.","en":"Its belly is big from eating many gassy leaves."},{"id":"Bekantan jago berenang dan punya selaput di sela jari kaki.","en":"The proboscis monkey is a great swimmer with webbed toes."},{"id":"Bekantan adalah hewan kebanggaan Kalimantan Selatan.","en":"The proboscis monkey is the pride animal of South Kalimantan."},{"id":"Jumlahnya di Kalimantan Selatan naik menjadi sekitar 4.000 ekor!","en":"Their number in South Kalimantan rose to about 4,000!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan yang hidup hanya di satu tempat di dunia, seperti bekantan di Kalimantan.","def_en":"An animal that lives in only one place in the world, like the proboscis monkey in Borneo."},{"term":"Selaput","def_id":"Kulit tipis di sela jari kaki yang membantu bekantan berenang.","def_en":"Thin skin between the toes that helps the monkey swim."},{"term":"Katup","def_id":"Penutup kecil yang bisa membuka dan menutup, di sini menutup hidung saat menyelam.","def_en":"A little flap that can open and close, here to shut the nose when diving."},{"term":"Kelompok","def_id":"Sekumpulan bekantan yang hidup dan mencari makan bersama-sama.","def_en":"A group of proboscis monkeys that live and find food together."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e136b48c3214f29a.jpg","caption_id":"Wajah bekantan jantan dari dekat, dengan hidung besar dan panjang yang khas.","caption_en":"A close-up of a male proboscis monkey's face, with its big, long signature nose.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/91931c7b866f4c18.jpg","caption_id":"Keluarga bekantan: jantan, betina, dan anak duduk bersama di tepi hutan.","caption_en":"A proboscis monkey family: a male, a female, and a young one sitting together at the forest edge.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9361a077e9d3bc15.jpg","caption_id":"Bekantan jantan sedang makan, hidung panjangnya terlihat jelas dari samping.","caption_en":"A male proboscis monkey eating, its long nose clearly seen from the side.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/585d5d0fc86c23e0.jpg","caption_id":"Bekantan muda dengan hidung yang masih kecil, memegang makanan dengan tangannya.","caption_en":"A young proboscis monkey with a still-small nose, holding food in its hand.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/574c0804ed7e522c.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok bekantan bertengger di hutan bakau, rumah basah kesukaan mereka.","caption_en":"A group of proboscis monkeys perched in a mangrove forest, their favorite watery home.","credit":"Ade Putri Amelia Az-Zahra","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bekantan"},"ensiklopedia_bunga_bangkai":{"id":"ensiklopedia_bunga_bangkai","title_id":"Bunga Bangkai Raksasa","title_en":"Giant Corpse Flower","subtitle_id":"Bunga raksasa berbau busuk dari hutan Sumatra!","subtitle_en":"A giant smelly flower from Sumatra's forests!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan tropis Sumatra","value_en":"Sumatran tropical rainforest"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Height","value_id":"Bisa lebih dari 3 meter","value_en":"Can be over 3 meters"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Mekar","label_en":"Bloom","value_id":"Hanya sekitar 7 hari","value_en":"Only about 7 days"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Kerinci & Lampung, Sumatra","value_en":"Kerinci & Lampung, Sumatra"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam (IUCN Red List)","value_en":"Threatened (IUCN Red List)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Bunga Bangkai?","h_en":"What Is the Corpse Flower?","body_id":"Bunga bangkai raksasa (Amorphophallus titanum) adalah tumbuhan dengan bunga majemuk terbesar di dunia. Bunga ini berasal dari Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia. Namanya 'bunga bangkai' karena baunya seperti bangkai yang busuk! Banyak orang mengira ia sama dengan Rafflesia, padahal keduanya tumbuhan yang berbeda.","body_en":"The giant corpse flower (Amorphophallus titanum) is the plant with the largest cluster of flowers in the world. It comes from the island of Sumatra in Indonesia. It is called the 'corpse flower' because it smells like rotting meat! Many people mix it up with the Rafflesia, but they are two different plants."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Bunga ini tumbuh di hutan hujan tropis Sumatra, seperti di Kerinci dan Lampung. Ia suka tanah berkapur dan tempat yang lembap di bawah pepohonan besar. Kamu juga bisa melihatnya mekar di Kebun Raya Bogor, Cibodas, dan Purwodadi.","body_en":"This flower grows in the tropical rainforests of Sumatra, like in Kerinci and Lampung. It likes limestone soil and damp, shady spots under tall trees. You can also see it bloom at the Bogor, Cibodas, and Purwodadi Botanical Gardens."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bunga bangkai bisa tumbuh sangat tinggi, bahkan lebih tinggi dari orang dewasa! Bagian tengahnya yang menjulang disebut spadix, dikelilingi seludang besar berwarna merah hati dan hijau. Di bawah tanah ada umbi raksasa yang menyimpan makanannya, dan bijinya berwarna merah.","body_en":"The corpse flower can grow very tall, even taller than a grown-up! Its tall middle part is called the spadix, surrounded by a big leafy spathe that is dark red and green. Underground there is a giant tuber that stores its food, and its seeds are red."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Kapan Mekar & Baunya","h_en":"When It Blooms & Its Smell","body_id":"Bunga ini sangat sabar! Ia menyimpan makanan di umbinya selama bertahun-tahun, lalu mekar hanya sekitar 7 hari saja. Saat mekar, bunga betinanya siap lebih dulu, baru bunga jantannya, agar tidak menyerbuki diri sendiri. Bau busuknya mengundang kumbang dan lalat untuk membantu menyerbukinya.","body_en":"This flower is very patient! It stores food in its tuber for years, then blooms for only about 7 days. When it blooms, its female flowers are ready first and the male flowers later, so it does not pollinate itself. Its stinky smell invites beetles and flies to help pollinate it."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Bunga bangkai liar makin sedikit karena hutannya berubah menjadi kebun dan rumah. Burung rangkong membantu menyebar bijinya. Dengan menjaga hutan dan burung rangkong, kita bisa membantu bunga ajaib ini tetap mekar untuk anak-anak masa depan.","body_en":"Wild corpse flowers are getting rarer because their forests are turning into farms and houses. Hornbill birds help spread their seeds. By protecting the forest and the hornbills, we can help this amazing flower keep blooming for children of the future."}],"facts":[{"id":"Ini adalah bunga majemuk terbesar di dunia!","en":"It is the largest cluster of flowers in the world!"},{"id":"Baunya seperti daging busuk untuk menarik lalat dan kumbang.","en":"It smells like rotten meat to attract flies and beetles."},{"id":"Bunganya hanya mekar sekitar 7 hari saja.","en":"Its flower blooms for only about 7 days."},{"id":"Umbinya bisa seberat 100 kilogram di bawah tanah!","en":"Its underground tuber can weigh up to 100 kilograms!"},{"id":"Bunga ini bisa tunggu bertahun-tahun sebelum mekar.","en":"This flower can wait for years before it blooms."},{"id":"Tumbuhan ini hanya ada di Indonesia.","en":"This plant is found only in Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Spadix","def_id":"Bagian tengah bunga yang menjulang tinggi seperti tongkol.","def_en":"The tall central part of the flower that rises up like a spike."},{"term":"Seludang","def_id":"Kelopak besar yang membungkus dan melindungi bunga saat mekar.","def_en":"The big leafy hood that wraps around and protects the flower as it opens."},{"term":"Umbi","def_id":"Bagian gemuk di bawah tanah tempat tumbuhan menyimpan makanan.","def_en":"The thick underground part where the plant stores its food."},{"term":"Penyerbukan","def_id":"Cara bunga membuat biji dengan bantuan serangga yang memindahkan serbuk sari.","def_en":"How a flower makes seeds with the help of insects that move pollen."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f726ea8c7f07ce2d.jpg","caption_id":"Bunga bangkai mekar penuh, seludang merah hatinya terbuka lebar mengelilingi spadix yang menjulang.","caption_en":"A corpse flower in full bloom, its dark-red spathe wide open around the towering spadix.","credit":"Credits: US Botanic Garden.","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e00355769094147e.jpg","caption_id":"Bunga raksasa ini berdiri lebih tinggi dari seorang penjaga di sebelahnya, menunjukkan betapa besarnya.","caption_en":"This giant flower stands taller than a guard beside it, showing just how huge it is.","credit":"Shubert Ciencia from Nueva Ecija, Philippines","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a62a3929167cadac.jpg","caption_id":"Pada fase daun, tumbuhan ini tumbuh seperti pohon kecil berbatang tunggal sebelum kelak berbunga.","caption_en":"In its leaf phase, the plant grows like a small single-stemmed tree before it later flowers.","credit":"Steve Fitzgerald","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c4896d72d51fd585.jpg","caption_id":"Dekat dari pangkalnya, terlihat kuncup-kuncup bunga kecil menempel di dasar spadix yang kuning.","caption_en":"Up close at the base, tiny flower buds cluster around the bottom of the yellow spadix.","credit":"Björn S...","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3048cd57126f2150.jpg","caption_id":"Tiga orang dengan susah payah mengangkat umbi raksasa bunga ini yang beratnya lebih dari 100 kg.","caption_en":"Three people carefully lift the flower's giant tuber, which weighs more than 100 kg.","credit":"Foto © W. Barthlott","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bunga_bangkai_raksasa"},"ensiklopedia_burung_maleo_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_burung_maleo_1","title_id":"Burung Maleo","title_en":"Maleo Bird","subtitle_id":"Burung unik yang menetaskan telur dari panas bumi!","subtitle_en":"A unique bird that hatches eggs with earth's heat!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan tropis & pantai Sulawesi","value_en":"Sulawesi forests & beaches"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sebesar ayam, sekitar 55 cm","value_en":"Chicken-sized, about 55 cm"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Buah, biji & serangga kecil","value_en":"Fruits, seeds & small insects"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Hanya Pulau Sulawesi","value_en":"Only Sulawesi Island"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Burung megapoda","value_en":"Megapode birds"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam & dilindungi","value_en":"Threatened & protected"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Burung Maleo?","h_en":"What Is the Maleo Bird?","body_id":"Maleo (Macrocephalon maleo) adalah burung istimewa yang juga disebut kalkun sikat. Ia termasuk kelompok burung megapoda. Maleo senkawor hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia, dan tidak ada di tempat lain di dunia.","body_en":"The maleo (Macrocephalon maleo) is a special bird also called the brush-turkey. It belongs to a group of birds called megapodes. The maleo lives only on the island of Sulawesi, Indonesia, and nowhere else in the world."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Maleo tinggal di hutan tropis Sulawesi. Mereka suka pergi ke pantai berpasir atau tanah hangat dekat sumber panas bumi. Tempat hangat ini sangat penting untuk telur-telur mereka.","body_en":"The maleo lives in the tropical forests of Sulawesi. They like to go to sandy beaches or warm ground near volcanic hot spots. These warm places are very important for their eggs."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Maleo punya bulu hitam, dada putih kemerahan, dan ciri khas berupa benjolan keras di kepalanya. Benjolan ini membuatnya terlihat seperti memakai topi! Kakinya kuat untuk menggali tanah dan pasir.","body_en":"The maleo has black feathers, a pinkish-white chest, and a special hard bump on its head. This bump makes it look like it is wearing a hat! Its legs are strong for digging in soil and sand."},{"icon":"egg","h_id":"Telur Ajaib","h_en":"Magic Eggs","body_id":"Maleo tidak mengerami telurnya sendiri. Ia mengubur telur di pasir hangat atau tanah dekat panas bumi, lalu panas alam itu yang menetaskannya! Telur maleo sangat besar, jauh lebih besar dari telur ayam.","body_en":"The maleo does not sit on its eggs. It buries them in warm sand or soil near volcanic heat, and nature's warmth hatches them! Maleo eggs are very big, much larger than chicken eggs."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Burung maleo terancam karena telurnya sering diambil dan hutannya berkurang. Anak maleo harus mandiri sejak menetas. Dengan menjaga sarang dan hutan Sulawesi, kita bisa membantu burung unik ini tetap ada.","body_en":"The maleo bird is threatened because its eggs are often taken and its forests are shrinking. Baby maleos must take care of themselves from the moment they hatch. By protecting their nests and Sulawesi's forests, we can help this unique bird survive."}],"facts":[{"id":"Maleo hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia!","en":"The maleo lives only on Sulawesi Island, Indonesia!"},{"id":"Mereka menetaskan telur memakai panas bumi dan matahari.","en":"They hatch eggs using the heat of the earth and sun."},{"id":"Telur maleo jauh lebih besar daripada telur ayam.","en":"Maleo eggs are much bigger than chicken eggs."},{"id":"Anak maleo bisa langsung terbang dan mencari makan sendiri.","en":"Baby maleos can fly and find food on their own right away."},{"id":"Maleo punya benjolan keras seperti topi di kepalanya.","en":"The maleo has a hard, hat-like bump on its head."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Megapoda","def_id":"Kelompok burung berkaki besar yang mengubur telurnya agar menetas oleh panas alam.","def_en":"A group of big-footed birds that bury their eggs so nature's heat can hatch them."},{"term":"Mengerami","def_id":"Mendekap telur dengan tubuh agar tetap hangat sampai menetas; maleo justru tidak melakukannya.","def_en":"Sitting on eggs with the body to keep them warm until they hatch; the maleo does not do this."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan yang hanya hidup di satu daerah saja, seperti maleo di Sulawesi.","def_en":"An animal that lives in only one area, like the maleo in Sulawesi."},{"term":"Panas bumi","def_id":"Panas alami yang keluar dari dalam tanah, misalnya dekat gunung berapi.","def_en":"Natural heat that comes out of the ground, such as near a volcano."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/fddc7ccf6df38c39.jpg","caption_id":"Maleo berjalan di tanah berpasir, memperlihatkan tubuh hitam, perut merah jambu, dan benjolan keras di kepalanya.","caption_en":"A maleo walks on sandy ground, showing its black body, pinkish belly, and the hard bump on its head.","credit":"Jean-Paul Boerekamps","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9896525663b797d0.jpg","caption_id":"Berdiri tegak di rerumputan, maleo menunjukkan kaki kuat dan wajah kuning oranye khasnya.","caption_en":"Standing tall in the grass, the maleo shows its strong legs and trademark orange-yellow face.","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/abe550888eb52d60.jpg","caption_id":"Dari samping terlihat jelas benjolan hitam di kepala dan dada merah jambu burung maleo.","caption_en":"From the side you can clearly see the maleo's black head bump and pinkish chest.","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1c5a3301bc8d33af.jpg","caption_id":"Maleo mencari makan di antara rumput hijau yang basah oleh embun pagi.","caption_en":"A maleo forages among green grass still wet with morning dew.","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maleo"},"ensiklopedia_candi_borobudur_2":{"id":"ensiklopedia_candi_borobudur_2","title_id":"Candi Borobudur","title_en":"Borobudur Temple","subtitle_id":"Candi Buddha terbesar di dunia!","subtitle_en":"The biggest Buddhist temple in the world!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Location","value_id":"Magelang, Jawa Tengah","value_en":"Magelang, Central Java"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Dibangun","label_en":"Built","value_id":"Sekitar tahun 800-an M","value_en":"Around the 800s CE"},{"icon":"self_improvement","label_id":"Agama","label_en":"Religion","value_id":"Buddha Mahayana","value_en":"Mahayana Buddhism"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Bentuk","label_en":"Design","value_id":"6 teras persegi & 3 pelataran bundar","value_en":"6 square terraces & 3 round platforms"},{"icon":"filter_drama","label_id":"Stupa","label_en":"Stupas","value_id":"72 stupa berlubang + 1 stupa utama","value_en":"72 holed stupas + 1 main stupa"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan Dunia UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO World Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"account_balance","h_id":"Apa Itu Borobudur?","h_en":"What Is Borobudur?","body_id":"Borobudur adalah candi Buddha raksasa di Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Candi ini adalah candi Buddha terbesar di seluruh dunia! Bentuknya seperti gunung batu bertingkat dengan banyak stupa berbentuk lonceng di puncaknya. Kita patut bangga karena bangunan menakjubkan ini ada di negeri kita.","body_en":"Borobudur is a giant Buddhist temple on the island of Java, Indonesia. It is the biggest Buddhist temple in the whole world! It looks like a stepped stone mountain with many bell-shaped stupas at the top. We can be proud that this amazing building stands in our country."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Siapa yang Membangunnya?","h_en":"Who Built It?","body_id":"Borobudur dibangun lebih dari 1.200 tahun yang lalu, sekitar tahun 800-an Masehi. Yang membangunnya adalah para penganut agama Buddha pada masa wangsa Syailendra. Candi ini terletak di Magelang, Jawa Tengah, tak jauh dari Kota Yogyakarta. Membangunnya butuh waktu bertahun-tahun dan ribuan batu yang disusun rapi.","body_en":"Borobudur was built more than 1,200 years ago, around the 800s CE. It was built by Buddhists during the time of the Sailendra dynasty. The temple sits in Magelang, Central Java, not far from the city of Yogyakarta. Building it took many years and thousands of carefully stacked stones."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Cerita di Dindingnya","h_en":"Stories on Its Walls","body_id":"Dinding Borobudur dihiasi 2.672 panel relief, yaitu gambar yang dipahat pada batu. Relief ini bercerita tentang ajaran Buddha, seperti buku batu raksasa! Dahulu ada 504 patung Buddha di candi ini. Di puncaknya, 72 patung Buddha duduk bersila di dalam stupa berlubang seperti lonceng.","body_en":"Borobudur's walls are decorated with 2,672 relief panels, which are pictures carved into stone. These carvings tell stories from the Buddha's teachings, like a giant stone book! Long ago there were 504 Buddha statues here. At the top, 72 Buddha statues sit cross-legged inside holed, bell-shaped stupas."},{"icon":"hiking","h_id":"Tempat untuk Berziarah","h_en":"A Place for Pilgrimage","body_id":"Borobudur dibuat sebagai tempat suci untuk berziarah. Peziarah masuk dari sisi timur, lalu berjalan mengelilingi candi searah jarum jam sambil naik ke tingkat berikutnya. Naik dari bawah ke atas melambangkan perjalanan menuju kebijaksanaan. Setiap tahun umat Buddha berkumpul di sini untuk merayakan Hari Waisak.","body_en":"Borobudur was made as a holy place for pilgrimage. Pilgrims enter from the east, then walk around the temple clockwise while climbing to the next level. Going from the bottom to the top stands for a journey toward wisdom. Every year Buddhists gather here to celebrate Vesak Day."},{"icon":"construction","h_id":"Ditemukan & Dirawat Kembali","h_en":"Found and Cared For Again","body_id":"Borobudur pernah ditinggalkan dan tertutup tanah serta tanaman selama ratusan tahun. Pada tahun 1814, candi ini ditemukan kembali dan mulai dibersihkan. Pemerintah Indonesia dan UNESCO memperbaikinya besar-besaran pada tahun 1975 sampai 1982. Sekarang Borobudur dijaga sebagai Warisan Dunia agar bisa dinikmati anak cucu kita.","body_en":"Borobudur was once abandoned and covered by soil and plants for hundreds of years. In 1814, the temple was found again and people began cleaning it. The Indonesian government and UNESCO repaired it in a big project from 1975 to 1982. Today Borobudur is protected as a World Heritage site so our grandchildren can enjoy it too."}],"facts":[{"id":"Borobudur adalah candi Buddha terbesar di dunia!","en":"Borobudur is the biggest Buddhist temple in the world!"},{"id":"Dindingnya punya 2.672 panel relief, koleksi relief Buddha terlengkap di dunia.","en":"Its walls have 2,672 relief panels, the most complete collection of Buddhist reliefs in the world."},{"id":"Di puncaknya ada 72 stupa berlubang, masing-masing berisi satu patung Buddha.","en":"At the top are 72 holed stupas, each holding one Buddha statue."},{"id":"Candi ini dibangun lebih dari 1.200 tahun yang lalu tanpa semen.","en":"The temple was built more than 1,200 years ago without any cement."},{"id":"Borobudur sempat hilang dan tertutup tanah, lalu ditemukan lagi tahun 1814.","en":"Borobudur was once lost under soil, then found again in 1814."},{"id":"Borobudur adalah tempat wisata yang paling banyak dikunjungi di Indonesia.","en":"Borobudur is the most visited tourist spot in Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Candi","def_id":"Bangunan suci dari batu peninggalan zaman Hindu-Buddha di Nusantara.","def_en":"A stone holy building left from the Hindu-Buddhist era in the Indonesian islands."},{"term":"Stupa","def_id":"Bangunan berbentuk lonceng atau kubah yang suci dalam agama Buddha.","def_en":"A bell- or dome-shaped structure that is holy in Buddhism."},{"term":"Relief","def_id":"Gambar atau cerita yang dipahat timbul pada permukaan batu.","def_en":"A picture or story carved so it stands out on a stone surface."},{"term":"Ziarah","def_id":"Kunjungan ke tempat suci untuk berdoa dan beribadah.","def_en":"A visit to a holy place to pray and worship."},{"term":"Waisak","def_id":"Hari raya umat Buddha yang dirayakan setiap tahun di Borobudur.","def_en":"A Buddhist holy day celebrated every year at Borobudur."},{"term":"Warisan Dunia","def_id":"Tempat istimewa yang dilindungi UNESCO untuk seluruh umat manusia.","def_en":"A special place protected by UNESCO for all of humanity."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/be4bf279d82901a3.jpg","caption_id":"Para biksu dan peziarah berbaju putih berjalan mengelilingi Borobudur, persis seperti ritual ziarah.","caption_en":"Monks and white-robed pilgrims walk around Borobudur, just like the pilgrimage ritual.","credit":"Heri nugroho","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8d64b52a927e9f09.jpg","caption_id":"Stupa-stupa Borobudur saat fajar, dengan Gunung Merapi mengepulkan asap di kejauhan.","caption_en":"Borobudur's stupas at dawn, with Mount Merapi puffing smoke in the distance.","credit":"ctsnow","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4c76caf7d05112a1.jpg","caption_id":"Stupa berlubang seperti lonceng di teras atas, menghadap bukit hijau dan pohon kelapa.","caption_en":"Holed, bell-shaped stupas on the upper terrace, facing green hills and coconut trees.","credit":"Heaven's Army (uploader at EN.Wikipedia)","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6beb87baaa96d37c.jpg","caption_id":"Borobudur terlihat dari kejauhan, dikelilingi hutan rimbun dan perbukitan.","caption_en":"Borobudur seen from afar, surrounded by lush forest and rolling hills.","credit":"Gunkarta (en.wikipedia)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/401e6f0d2546f4f2.jpg","caption_id":"Lukisan lama menggambarkan orang berziarah ke Borobudur dengan gajah dan payung warna-warni.","caption_en":"An old painting shows people making a pilgrimage to Borobudur with elephants and colorful parasols.","credit":"Gijsbert Brandt Hooijer (1848-1934)","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/32d1ddcf8e637aa0.jpg","caption_id":"Foto hitam-putih tertua Borobudur, diambil tak lama setelah candi ditemukan kembali.","caption_en":"A very old black-and-white photo of Borobudur, taken not long after the temple was rediscovered.","credit":"Isidore van Kinsbergen","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borobudur"},"ensiklopedia_cendrawasih":{"id":"ensiklopedia_cendrawasih","title_id":"Cendrawasih","title_en":"Bird-of-Paradise","subtitle_id":"Burung surga cantik dari tanah Papua!","subtitle_en":"The beautiful bird of paradise from Papua!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan tropis Papua","value_en":"Papuan tropical rainforest"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Burung pengicau kecil-sedang","value_en":"Small-to-medium songbird"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Buah-buahan & serangga kecil","value_en":"Fruits & small insects"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Papua & pulau sekitarnya","value_en":"Papua & nearby islands"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Famili Paradisaeidae","value_en":"Family Paradisaeidae"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Dilindungi","value_en":"Protected"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Cendrawasih?","h_en":"What Is the Bird-of-Paradise?","body_id":"Cendrawasih adalah burung pengicau cantik dari keluarga Paradisaeidae. Banyak orang menyebutnya 'burung surga' karena bulunya yang indah dan berwarna-warni. Ada banyak jenisnya, seperti cendrawasih merah, kuning, raja, kaisar, dan raggiana.","body_en":"The bird-of-paradise is a beautiful songbird from the Paradisaeidae family. Many people call it the 'bird of heaven' because of its lovely, colorful feathers. There are many kinds, like the red, yellow, king, emperor, and raggiana birds-of-paradise."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Cendrawasih hidup di hutan-hutan lebat di Papua, Indonesia, dan pulau-pulau di sekitarnya. Mereka suka tinggal tinggi di atas pepohonan hutan hujan tropis. Karena keindahannya, burung ini menjadi kebanggaan tanah Papua dan namanya dipakai untuk teluk serta universitas di sana.","body_en":"Birds-of-paradise live in the thick forests of Papua, Indonesia, and nearby islands. They like to stay high up in the trees of the tropical rainforest. Because of their beauty, these birds are the pride of Papua, and their name is even used for a bay and a university there."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Cendrawasih jantan memiliki bulu yang sangat indah dengan warna-warna cerah seperti merah, kuning, dan hijau. Beberapa punya bulu panjang yang menjuntai seperti pita atau kawat. Bulu cantik ini hanya dimiliki oleh burung jantan; betinanya berwarna lebih kalem.","body_en":"Male birds-of-paradise have very beautiful feathers in bright colors like red, yellow, and green. Some have long feathers that flow like ribbons or wires. These lovely feathers belong only to the male birds; the females have plainer colors."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kebiasaan Menari","h_en":"Their Dancing Habit","body_id":"Cendrawasih jantan suka menari untuk menarik perhatian betina! Mereka memamerkan bulu indahnya sambil bergoyang di atas dahan. Mereka memakan buah-buahan dan serangga kecil di hutan.","body_en":"Male birds-of-paradise love to dance to attract the females! They show off their beautiful feathers while swaying on the branches. They eat fruits and small insects in the forest."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Cendrawasih harus kita jaga agar tidak punah. Mereka terancam karena hutan tempat tinggalnya berkurang dan perburuan bulunya. Dengan menjaga hutan Papua, kita membantu burung surga ini terus terbang bebas dan menari.","body_en":"We must protect birds-of-paradise so they do not disappear. They are threatened because their forest homes are shrinking and people hunt them for their feathers. By protecting Papua's forests, we help these heavenly birds keep flying free and dancing."}],"facts":[{"id":"Cendrawasih dijuluki 'burung surga' karena keindahannya.","en":"The bird-of-paradise is nicknamed the 'bird of heaven' for its beauty."},{"id":"Burung jantan menari untuk memikat pasangannya.","en":"Male birds dance to win a partner."},{"id":"Hanya burung jantan yang punya bulu hias super cantik.","en":"Only the male birds have super pretty show feathers."},{"id":"Cendrawasih adalah lambang kebanggaan tanah Papua.","en":"The bird-of-paradise is a symbol of pride for Papua."},{"id":"Ada belasan jenis cendrawasih di Indonesia.","en":"There are over a dozen kinds of birds-of-paradise in Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Paradisaeidae","def_id":"Nama keluarga ilmiah untuk semua jenis burung cendrawasih.","def_en":"The scientific family name for all kinds of birds-of-paradise."},{"term":"Pengicau","def_id":"Kelompok burung yang pandai bersuara dan berkicau, seperti cendrawasih.","def_en":"A group of birds that are good at singing and chirping, like the bird-of-paradise."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hanya hidup di satu daerah tertentu saja.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives only in one particular area."},{"term":"Punah","def_id":"Keadaan ketika suatu jenis hewan habis dan tidak ada lagi di dunia.","def_en":"When a kind of animal runs out and no longer exists in the world."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/47ba731e94dfca1a.jpg","caption_id":"Cendrawasih jantan bertengger gagah, memamerkan bulu cokelat keemasan dan ekor putih panjang yang menjuntai.","caption_en":"A male bird-of-paradise perches proudly, showing off its golden-brown plumage and long flowing white tail.","credit":"Philip Nalangan","license":"CC BY 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cenderawasih_%28disambiguasi%29"},"ensiklopedia_gajah_sumatra":{"id":"ensiklopedia_gajah_sumatra","title_id":"Gajah Sumatra","title_en":"Sumatran Elephant","subtitle_id":"Mamalia terbesar dan tercerdas di Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"Indonesia's biggest and smartest mammal!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan rawa & dataran rendah","value_en":"Swamp & lowland forests"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Setinggi 3,5 m, sampai 6 ton","value_en":"Up to 3.5 m tall, 6 tons"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Herbivora: rumput, daun, kulit kayu","value_en":"Herbivore: grass, leaves, bark"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Hanya Pulau Sumatra","value_en":"Only Sumatra Island"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Subspesies gajah Asia","value_en":"Asian elephant subspecies"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Sangat terancam punah","value_en":"Critically endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Gajah Sumatra?","h_en":"What Is the Sumatran Elephant?","body_id":"Gajah sumatra (Elephas maximus sumatranus) adalah jenis gajah Asia yang hanya hidup di Pulau Sumatra. Ia adalah mamalia terbesar di Indonesia! Tubuhnya sedikit lebih kecil daripada gajah dari India, dan biasanya hanya gajah jantan yang punya gading.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant (Elephas maximus sumatranus) is a kind of Asian elephant that lives only on the island of Sumatra. It is the biggest mammal in Indonesia! Its body is a little smaller than the elephant from India, and usually only the males have tusks."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Gajah sumatra hidup di hutan-hutan luas, seperti hutan rawa, hutan gambut, dan hutan hujan dataran rendah. Mereka butuh wilayah jelajah yang sangat luas untuk berkeliling, dan satu gajah saja bisa butuh ratusan hektar. Mereka juga suka tempat yang dekat dengan sumber air.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant lives in wide forests, like swamp forests, peat forests, and lowland rainforests. They need a very large area to roam around, and a single elephant can need hundreds of hectares. They also like places close to water."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Gajah sumatra bisa setinggi 3,5 meter di bahu dan beratnya mencapai beberapa ton! Telinganya yang besar membantunya mendengar dan menjaga tubuh tetap sejuk. Belalainya yang panjang dipakai untuk meraih makanan dan air seperti tangan.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant can be 3.5 meters tall at the shoulder and weigh several tons! Its big ears help it hear well and keep its body cool. Its long trunk is used to grab food and water like a hand."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Gajah sumatra adalah herbivora, jadi ia hanya makan tumbuhan! Ia suka rumput, semak muda, daun, dan kulit kayu yang lembut, dan bisa makan sampai 200 kg sehari. Gajah sangat cerdas dan punya otak besar. Bayi gajah dikandung selama 22 bulan sebelum lahir.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant is a herbivore, so it eats only plants! It likes grass, young shrubs, leaves, and soft bark, and can eat up to 200 kg a day. Elephants are very smart and have a big brain. A baby elephant grows for 22 months before it is born."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Gajah sumatra sangat terancam punah karena hutannya banyak berubah menjadi perkebunan. Gajah penting sekali karena membantu menyebarkan biji tanaman di hutan. Dengan menjaga hutan dan hidup damai bersama gajah, kita bisa menyelamatkan sahabat raksasa ini.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant is highly endangered because much of its forest has been turned into plantations. Elephants are very important because they help spread plant seeds in the forest. By protecting the forest and living peacefully with elephants, we can save this giant friend."}],"facts":[{"id":"Gajah sumatra adalah mamalia terbesar di Indonesia!","en":"The Sumatran elephant is the biggest mammal in Indonesia!"},{"id":"Otaknya lebih besar dari mamalia darat lainnya.","en":"Its brain is bigger than other land mammals'."},{"id":"Bayi gajah dikandung selama 22 bulan, hampir 2 tahun!","en":"A baby elephant grows for 22 months, almost 2 years!"},{"id":"Gajah bisa hidup sampai sekitar 70 tahun.","en":"Elephants can live up to about 70 years."},{"id":"Gajah membantu menanam hutan dengan menyebar biji.","en":"Elephants help grow forests by spreading seeds."},{"id":"Belalai gajah dipakai seperti tangan untuk meraup makanan.","en":"An elephant's trunk works like a hand to scoop up food."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Subspesies","def_id":"Kelompok khusus di dalam satu jenis hewan; gajah sumatra adalah subspesies gajah Asia.","def_en":"A special group within one kind of animal; the Sumatran elephant is a subspecies of the Asian elephant."},{"term":"Herbivora","def_id":"Hewan yang hanya makan tumbuhan dan tidak makan daging.","def_en":"An animal that eats only plants and no meat."},{"term":"Belalai","def_id":"Hidung panjang gajah yang dipakai seperti tangan untuk meraih makanan dan air.","def_en":"An elephant's long nose, used like a hand to reach food and water."},{"term":"Wilayah jelajah","def_id":"Daerah luas tempat hewan berkeliling untuk mencari makan dan air.","def_en":"The wide area an animal roams around to find food and water."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/990889d90c287246.jpg","caption_id":"Gajah sumatra jantan bergading berdiri di sungai, dengan hutan hijau di belakangnya.","caption_en":"A tusked male Sumatran elephant stands in a river, with green forest behind it.","credit":"Léodras","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/22f9acabeae4d8b6.jpg","caption_id":"Induk gajah menjaga anaknya yang masih kecil di tepi hutan Taman Nasional Tesso Nilo.","caption_en":"A mother elephant watches over her little calf at the edge of Tesso Nilo National Park.","credit":"Afrianto silalahi","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/88199b85ba995c0c.jpg","caption_id":"Gajah berenang di sungai hijau jernih, telinganya yang besar terkembang lebar.","caption_en":"An elephant bathes in a clear green river, its big ears spread wide.","credit":"kusuma wijaya","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/46667cb5f2bff657.jpg","caption_id":"Manusia dan gajah bermain air bersama di sungai, contoh hidup damai berdampingan.","caption_en":"People and elephants splash together in a river, a picture of peaceful coexistence.","credit":"Panyahatan Siregar","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gajah_sumatra"},"ensiklopedia_harimau_sumatra_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_harimau_sumatra_1","title_id":"Harimau Sumatra","title_en":"Sumatran Tiger","subtitle_id":"Kucing besar penjaga hutan Pulau Sumatra","subtitle_en":"The big cat guarding Sumatra's forests","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan dataran rendah sampai pegunungan","value_en":"Lowland to mountain forests"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Jantan sampai 250 cm, berat ~140 kg","value_en":"Males up to 250 cm, about 140 kg"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Babi hutan, rusa, unggas, kadang ikan","value_en":"Wild boar, deer, birds, sometimes fish"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Hanya di Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia","value_en":"Only on Sumatra island, Indonesia"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Kritis, tinggal sekitar 400-500 ekor","value_en":"Critically endangered, about 400-500 left"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Kucing besar (Panthera tigris)","value_en":"Big cat (Panthera tigris)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Harimau Sumatra?","h_en":"What Is the Sumatran Tiger?","body_id":"Harimau sumatra adalah kucing besar yang hanya hidup di Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia. Ia adalah harimau paling kecil di antara semua jenis harimau di dunia. Tubuhnya yang mungil membuatnya gesit menjelajahi hutan. Ia satu-satunya harimau sunda yang masih hidup sampai sekarang, jadi sangat istimewa.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is a big cat that lives only on the island of Sumatra, Indonesia. It is the smallest of all tiger types in the world. Its small body makes it quick and nimble in the forest. It is the only Sunda tiger still alive today, which makes it very special."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Harimau sumatra tinggal di hutan-hutan Pulau Sumatra. Ia bisa hidup di hutan dataran rendah, lahan gambut, sampai hutan hujan di pegunungan. Banyak yang tinggal di taman nasional dan cagar alam yang dilindungi. Di jari-jarinya ada selaput, jadi ia juga pandai berenang!","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger lives in the forests of Sumatra island. It can live in lowland forests, peat swamps, and rainforests high in the mountains. Many live in protected national parks and nature reserves. It has webbing between its toes, so it is also a great swimmer!"},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bulu harimau sumatra berwarna oranye tua dengan garis hitam yang lebar dan rapat. Warnanya paling gelap di antara semua harimau di dunia. Harimau jantan punya lebih banyak janggut dan surai di wajahnya. Loreng ini membantunya bersembunyi di balik bayang-bayang hutan, seperti pakaian penyamaran.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger's fur is deep orange with wide, close-set black stripes. Its color is the darkest of all tigers in the world. Males have more beard and mane around the face. These stripes help it hide among the forest shadows, like a camouflage suit."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Harimau sumatra adalah pemburu yang sabar dan pandai. Ia memakan babi hutan, rusa, kijang, unggas, dan kadang ikan. Sebagai pemangsa utama, ia menjaga jumlah hewan lain di hutan tetap seimbang. Induk harimau biasanya melahirkan 2 atau 3 anak yang sangat lucu dan dijaga dengan penuh kasih.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is a patient and clever hunter. It eats wild boar, deer, muntjac, birds, and sometimes fish. As a top predator, it keeps the number of other animals in the forest balanced. A mother tiger usually has 2 or 3 adorable cubs that she cares for lovingly."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Harimau sumatra sangat langka, hanya tersisa sekitar 400-500 ekor di alam liar. Hutannya makin sempit karena ditebang untuk ladang dan kebun, sehingga ia sulit mencari rumah. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap lestari dan hijau. Dengan kerja sama, harimau gagah ini bisa terus hidup bahagia!","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is very rare, with only about 400-500 left in the wild. Its forest is shrinking because it is cleared for fields and plantations, making it hard to find a home. We can help by keeping forests healthy and green. Working together, this brave tiger can keep living happily!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Harimau sumatra adalah harimau terkecil di dunia!","en":"The Sumatran tiger is the smallest tiger in the world!"},{"id":"Warna bulunya paling gelap di antara semua harimau.","en":"Its fur is the darkest of all tigers."},{"id":"Ada selaput di jari kakinya supaya bisa berenang cepat.","en":"It has webbed toes so it can swim fast."},{"id":"Loreng setiap harimau berbeda, seperti sidik jari manusia.","en":"Every tiger's stripes are unique, like a human fingerprint."},{"id":"Di alam liar, harimau sumatra bisa hidup sampai 15 tahun.","en":"In the wild, a Sumatran tiger can live up to 15 years."},{"id":"Anak harimau baru membuka matanya pada hari kesepuluh.","en":"Tiger cubs open their eyes on the tenth day."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hanya hidup di satu tempat khusus di dunia.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives in only one special place in the world."},{"term":"Pemangsa utama","def_id":"Hewan pemburu di puncak rantai makanan yang tidak diburu hewan lain.","def_en":"A top hunter at the head of the food chain that no other animal hunts."},{"term":"Kritis (terancam punah)","def_id":"Keadaan saat hewan sangat langka dan bisa hilang selamanya jika tidak dijaga.","def_en":"When an animal is very rare and could disappear forever unless it is protected."},{"term":"Habitat","def_id":"Tempat alami sebuah hewan tinggal, mencari makan, dan berkembang biak.","def_en":"The natural place where an animal lives, finds food, and raises its young."},{"term":"Kamuflase","def_id":"Warna atau pola tubuh yang membantu hewan menyatu dengan sekitarnya.","def_en":"Body colors or patterns that help an animal blend into its surroundings."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2ea82aae5a4338e2.jpg","caption_id":"Harimau sumatra menatap dengan tenang sambil berbaring, memperlihatkan wajah dan loreng yang khas.","caption_en":"A Sumatran tiger gazes calmly while resting, showing its distinctive face and stripes.","credit":"Nichollas Harrison","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5e0df62e7237ee3e.jpg","caption_id":"Tubuh harimau yang gagah terlihat penuh saat ia berjalan di atas batu, lorengnya lebar dan rapat.","caption_en":"The tiger's powerful body is shown in full as it walks across the rocks, its stripes wide and close-set.","credit":"Captain Herbert","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3deabfd4d2601a73.jpg","caption_id":"Wajah harimau dari dekat memperlihatkan kumis panjang dan janggut tebal khas harimau sumatra.","caption_en":"A close-up of the tiger's face shows the long whiskers and thick beard typical of the Sumatran tiger.","credit":"Moonlight0551 from Australia","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5c5afa2d73eaab29.jpg","caption_id":"Seekor harimau sumatra melangkah di tanah terbuka dekat tepi hutan, gesit dan waspada.","caption_en":"A Sumatran tiger steps across open ground near the forest edge, nimble and alert.","credit":"Official Website of Ministry of Environment and Forestry Indonesia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harimau_sumatra"},"ensiklopedia_hiu_paus":{"id":"ensiklopedia_hiu_paus","title_id":"Hiu Paus","title_en":"Whale Shark","subtitle_id":"Ikan terbesar di dunia yang ramah","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest, friendliest fish","data_card":[{"icon":"waves","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Lautan tropis yang hangat","value_en":"Warm tropical oceans"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Rata-rata ~9,7 meter, berat sampai 9 ton","value_en":"About 9.7 meters long, up to 9 tons"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Plankton dan makhluk laut kecil","value_en":"Plankton and tiny sea creatures"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Samudra tropis dunia, termasuk Indonesia","value_en":"Tropical seas worldwide, including Indonesia"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam, sering terjerat jaring nelayan","value_en":"Threatened, often caught in fishing nets"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Ikan hiu (Rhincodon typus)","value_en":"Shark fish (Rhincodon typus)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"waves","h_id":"Apa Itu Hiu Paus?","h_en":"What Is the Whale Shark?","body_id":"Hiu paus adalah ikan terbesar di seluruh dunia! Walaupun namanya hiu, ia lembut dan tidak berbahaya bagi manusia. Ia disebut hiu paus karena tubuhnya besar dan cara makannya menyaring air laut seperti paus. Di Indonesia ia juga dipanggil hiu tutul atau geger lintang karena punggungnya bertotol seperti bintang.","body_en":"The whale shark is the biggest fish in the whole world! Even though it is a shark, it is gentle and harmless to people. It is called a whale shark because of its huge body and the way it eats by filtering seawater, just like a whale. In Indonesia it is also called 'hiu tutul' or 'geger lintang' because of the star-like spots on its back."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Hiu paus berenang di lautan tropis yang hangat di seluruh dunia. Ia suka mengembara jauh dan termasuk ikan yang suka bermigrasi. Di Indonesia, hiu paus bisa ditemui di banyak tempat penyelaman yang indah. Ia bahkan bisa menyelam sangat dalam, lebih dari 1.000 meter ke dasar laut!","body_en":"The whale shark swims in warm, tropical oceans all around the world. It loves to wander far and is a fish that migrates. In Indonesia, whale sharks can be spotted at many beautiful diving spots. It can even dive very deep, more than 1,000 meters down into the sea!"},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Tubuh hiu paus berwarna abu-abu dengan perut putih. Punggungnya penuh bintik dan garis putih kekuningan yang tampak seperti taburan bintang di langit malam. Pola bintik ini berbeda pada setiap hiu, seperti sidik jari. Mulutnya sangat lebar dan datar di ujung kepalanya, dengan dua mata kecil di sisinya.","body_en":"The whale shark's body is gray with a white belly. Its back is covered in yellowish-white spots and stripes that look like stars sprinkled across the night sky. This spot pattern is different on every shark, like a fingerprint. Its mouth is very wide and flat at the front of its head, with two small eyes on the sides."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Hiu paus makan dengan cara menyaring air laut lewat mulutnya yang besar. Makanan kesukaannya adalah plankton, yaitu makhluk laut yang sangat kecil. Ia berenang pelan dengan mulut terbuka lebar, lalu air keluar lewat insang dan makanan tertinggal di dalam. Walau giginya banyak dan kecil-kecil, ia tidak memakainya untuk mengunyah.","body_en":"The whale shark eats by filtering seawater through its big mouth. Its favorite food is plankton, which are tiny sea creatures. It swims slowly with its mouth wide open, then water flows out through its gills while the food stays inside. Even though it has many tiny teeth, it does not use them to chew."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Hiu paus sangat ramah, kadang membiarkan penyelam berenang pelan di dekatnya. Ia bisa hidup sampai 70 tahun dan dipercaya sudah ada sejak 60 juta tahun lalu. Sayangnya, ia bisa terancam karena tertangkap jaring nelayan tanpa sengaja. Yuk, kita jaga laut tetap bersih agar raksasa lembut ini terus berenang bahagia!","body_en":"The whale shark is very friendly and sometimes lets divers swim slowly near it. It can live up to 70 years and is believed to have existed since 60 million years ago. Sadly, it can be in danger from getting caught in fishing nets by accident. Let's keep our oceans clean so this gentle giant can keep swimming happily!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Hiu paus adalah ikan terbesar di dunia!","en":"The whale shark is the biggest fish in the world!"},{"id":"Ia bisa hidup sampai 70 tahun.","en":"It can live up to 70 years."},{"id":"Pola bintik di punggungnya unik, seperti sidik jari.","en":"The spots on its back are unique, like a fingerprint."},{"id":"Hiu paus bisa menyelam lebih dari 1.000 meter ke dasar laut.","en":"Whale sharks can dive more than 1,000 meters deep."},{"id":"Walau besar, hiu paus jinak dan tidak berbahaya.","en":"Despite its size, the whale shark is tame and harmless."},{"id":"Hiu paus suka makan plankton yang sangat kecil.","en":"Whale sharks love eating tiny plankton."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Plankton","def_id":"Makhluk laut yang sangat kecil dan mengapung, menjadi makanan banyak hewan laut.","def_en":"Very tiny sea creatures that float in the water and feed many ocean animals."},{"term":"Menyaring (filter)","def_id":"Cara makan dengan mengambil makanan kecil dari air dan membuang airnya.","def_en":"A way of eating by taking tiny food from the water and letting the water out."},{"term":"Insang","def_id":"Bagian tubuh ikan untuk bernapas dan tempat air keluar saat menyaring makanan.","def_en":"The body part a fish uses to breathe, and where water exits when it filters food."},{"term":"Bermigrasi","def_id":"Berpindah jauh dari satu tempat ke tempat lain untuk mencari makan atau berbiak.","def_en":"Travelling a long way from one place to another to find food or to breed."},{"term":"Tropis","def_id":"Daerah hangat di dekat garis khatulistiwa, seperti laut di sekitar Indonesia.","def_en":"Warm regions near the equator, such as the seas around Indonesia."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0db4e5bbcb6017eb.jpg","caption_id":"Hiu paus berenang dengan anggun, memperlihatkan bintik-bintik putih di punggung abu-abunya yang lebar.","caption_en":"A whale shark glides gracefully, showing the white spots across its wide gray back.","credit":"User:Zac Wolf (original), en:User:Stefan (cropping)","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ea8a69023305e034.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang penyelam berenang di dekat mulut hiu paus yang sangat lebar dan datar untuk menyaring makanan.","caption_en":"A snorkeler swims near the whale shark's very wide, flat mouth used to filter its food.","credit":"Jaontiveros","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e82213409de96120.jpg","caption_id":"Dua hiu paus raksasa berenang tenang di akuarium besar, menunjukkan betapa besar tubuhnya.","caption_en":"Two giant whale sharks swim calmly in a huge aquarium, showing just how big they are.","credit":"Jordy Meow","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ef8e657a0d08a540.jpg","caption_id":"Pengunjung memandang takjub saat hiu paus melintas di balik kaca akuarium yang besar.","caption_en":"Visitors watch in wonder as a whale shark passes behind the large aquarium glass.","credit":"Zac Wolf","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiu_paus"},"ensiklopedia_hutan_mangrove":{"id":"ensiklopedia_hutan_mangrove","title_id":"Hutan Mangrove","title_en":"Mangrove Forest","subtitle_id":"Hutan ajaib penjaga pantai dan rumah satwa","subtitle_en":"Magical coastal forest, home to wildlife","data_card":[{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Location","value_id":"Tepi laut berlumpur, teluk, dan muara sungai","value_en":"Muddy seashores, bays, and river mouths"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Tumbuhan utama","label_en":"Main plants","value_id":"Pohon bakau, api-api, dan nipah","value_en":"Mangrove, api-api, and nipa trees"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Hewan penghuni","label_en":"Animals","value_id":"Ikan, kepiting, udang, dan burung","value_en":"Fish, crabs, shrimp, and birds"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Manfaat","label_en":"Benefit","value_id":"Menahan ombak dan melindungi pantai","value_en":"Holds back waves and protects the coast"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Sumatra, Kalimantan, dan Papua","value_en":"Sumatra, Kalimantan, and Papua"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terluas di dunia, sebagian perlu dijaga","value_en":"Largest in the world, some needs caring for"}],"sections":[{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Apa Itu Hutan Mangrove?","h_en":"What Is a Mangrove Forest?","body_id":"Hutan mangrove, atau hutan bakau, adalah hutan istimewa yang tumbuh di tepi laut. Pohon-pohonnya berdiri di tanah berlumpur yang sering tergenang air pasang. Hanya tumbuhan khusus yang bisa hidup di sini karena airnya asin. Hutan ini sering tumbuh di teluk yang tenang dan di muara sungai tempat lumpur mengendap.","body_en":"A mangrove forest is a special forest that grows along the seashore. Its trees stand in muddy soil that is often flooded by the tide. Only special plants can live here because the water is salty. These forests often grow in calm bays and at river mouths where mud settles."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Tumbuhnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Grow?","body_id":"Hutan mangrove tumbuh di tempat-tempat yang hangat di dekat garis khatulistiwa. Indonesia punya hutan mangrove terluas di seluruh dunia! Hutan ini banyak ditemukan di pantai timur Sumatra, Kalimantan, dan sekitar Teluk Bintuni di Papua. Sekitar seperempat hutan mangrove dunia ada di negara kita.","body_en":"Mangrove forests grow in warm places near the equator. Indonesia has the largest mangrove forests in the whole world! They are found along the east coast of Sumatra, in Kalimantan, and around Bintuni Bay in Papua. About a quarter of the world's mangroves are in our country."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Pohon yang Hebat","h_en":"Amazing Trees","body_id":"Pohon bakau punya akar khusus yang menjulur seperti kaki-kaki yang kokoh. Sebagian akarnya bahkan menyembul ke atas lumpur untuk bernapas. Ada banyak jenis pohon mangrove, dan sekitar 39 jenis tumbuh di Indonesia. Pohon-pohon ini tumbuh berlapis-lapis, dari tepi laut sampai ke daratan.","body_en":"Mangrove trees have special roots that stretch out like sturdy legs. Some roots even poke up above the mud to breathe. There are many kinds of mangrove trees, and about 39 kinds grow in Indonesia. They grow in layers, from the seashore all the way inland."},{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Rumah Banyak Hewan","h_en":"Home to Many Animals","body_id":"Hutan mangrove adalah rumah yang nyaman bagi banyak hewan. Ikan kecil, kepiting, dan udang bersembunyi di antara akar-akarnya. Burung-burung indah, seperti jalak bali, juga suka tinggal di sini. Tempat ini seperti taman bermain yang penuh kehidupan!","body_en":"The mangrove forest is a cozy home for many animals. Small fish, crabs, and shrimp hide among its roots. Beautiful birds, like the Bali myna, also love to live here. This place is like a playground full of life!"},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Pelindung Pantai","h_en":"Guardian of the Coast","body_id":"Hutan mangrove adalah perisai alami yang melindungi pantai. Akar-akarnya yang rapat menahan ombak besar agar tidak merusak daratan. Hutan ini juga mencegah tanah pantai terkikis air laut. Yuk, kita jaga hutan mangrove agar pantai dan hewan-hewannya tetap aman dan sehat!","body_en":"The mangrove forest is a natural shield that protects the coast. Its thick roots hold back big waves so they cannot harm the land. The forest also stops the shore from being washed away by the sea. Let's protect mangrove forests so our coasts and animals stay safe and healthy!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Indonesia punya hutan mangrove terluas di dunia!","en":"Indonesia has the largest mangrove forest in the world!"},{"id":"Seperempat mangrove dunia ada di Indonesia.","en":"A quarter of the world's mangroves are in Indonesia."},{"id":"Akar bakau menahan ombak besar agar pantai aman.","en":"Mangrove roots hold back big waves to keep the coast safe."},{"id":"Sekitar 39 jenis pohon bakau tumbuh di Indonesia.","en":"About 39 kinds of mangrove trees grow in Indonesia."},{"id":"Ikan, kepiting, dan burung tinggal di antara akarnya.","en":"Fish, crabs, and birds live among its roots."},{"id":"Pohon bakau bisa hidup di air laut yang asin.","en":"Mangrove trees can live in salty seawater."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Air pasang","def_id":"Saat permukaan air laut naik dan menggenangi tepi pantai.","def_en":"When the sea level rises and floods the edge of the shore."},{"term":"Muara sungai","def_id":"Tempat sungai bertemu laut, sering berlumpur dan tenang.","def_en":"The place where a river meets the sea, often muddy and calm."},{"term":"Akar napas","def_id":"Akar bakau yang menyembul ke atas lumpur agar pohon bisa bernapas.","def_en":"Mangrove roots that poke up above the mud so the tree can breathe."},{"term":"Salinitas","def_id":"Banyaknya kadar garam di dalam air, membuat air terasa asin.","def_en":"The amount of salt in the water, which makes it taste salty."},{"term":"Ekosistem","def_id":"Tempat tumbuhan, hewan, dan alam hidup bersama dan saling membutuhkan.","def_en":"A place where plants, animals, and nature live together and need each other."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6ff699218b04654d.jpg","caption_id":"Semak bakau hijau berdiri di atas akar tunjang yang kokoh di tepi pantai berpasir.","caption_en":"Green mangrove shrubs stand on sturdy prop roots along a sandy shore.","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9e46ea2e529bcdeb.jpg","caption_id":"Saat air surut, terlihat akar bakau yang melengkung dan akar napas kecil menyembul dari lumpur.","caption_en":"At low tide, arching mangrove roots and small breathing roots poke up from the mud.","credit":"Ron from Nieuwegein / South Moreton Oxfordshire, Netherlands / UK","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b4e2647dc204423d.jpg","caption_id":"Pemandangan setengah di atas dan setengah di bawah air memperlihatkan akar bakau yang menjadi tempat berlindung ikan.","caption_en":"A half-above and half-below water view shows the mangrove roots that shelter fish.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c211ef295f34d967.jpg","caption_id":"Hutan mangrove yang lebat membentang di tepi pantai di bawah langit biru cerah.","caption_en":"A thick mangrove forest stretches along the coast under a bright blue sky.","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hutan_mangrove"},"ensiklopedia_jalak_bali_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_jalak_bali_1","title_id":"Jalak Bali","title_en":"Bali Myna","subtitle_id":"Burung putih cantik kebanggaan Pulau Bali","subtitle_en":"Bali's beautiful white pride bird","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan & savana","value_en":"Forest & savanna"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sekitar 25 cm","value_en":"About 25 cm"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Serangga & buah","value_en":"Insects & fruit"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Bali Barat","value_en":"West Bali"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Burung pengicau","value_en":"Songbird"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Sangat langka","value_en":"Critically rare"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Jalak Bali?","h_en":"What Is the Bali Myna?","body_id":"Jalak bali adalah burung pengicau cantik berukuran sedang, panjangnya sekitar 25 cm. Burung ini hanya ditemukan di hutan bagian barat Pulau Bali. Ia satu-satunya hewan asli khas Bali, jadi sangat istimewa. Pada tahun 1991, jalak bali dipilih menjadi lambang fauna Provinsi Bali.","body_en":"The Bali myna is a beautiful medium-sized songbird, about 25 cm long. This bird is found only in the forests of western Bali. It is the only animal native to Bali, so it is very special. In 1991, the Bali myna was chosen as the official animal symbol of Bali Province."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bulu jalak bali hampir seluruhnya berwarna putih bersih. Hanya ujung sayap dan ekornya yang berwarna hitam. Di sekeliling matanya ada pelupuk berwarna biru tua yang sangat cantik. Burung jantan punya jambul indah di kepalanya.","body_en":"The Bali myna's feathers are almost entirely pure white. Only the tips of its wings and tail are black. Around its eyes is a lovely deep-blue patch. The male has a beautiful crest on its head."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Jalak bali suka tinggal di hutan mangrove, hutan rawa, dan daerah savana. Rumah aslinya ada di Taman Nasional Bali Barat. Ia membuat sarang di dalam lubang pohon, cukup tinggi dari tanah. Burung ini suka terbang berombongan bersama teman-temannya.","body_en":"The Bali myna loves to live in mangrove forests, swamp forests, and savanna areas. Its natural home is in West Bali National Park. It builds its nest inside tree holes, fairly high off the ground. This bird loves to fly in flocks with its friends."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kebiasaan Lucu","h_en":"Fun Habits","body_id":"Jalak bali punya kicauan khas berupa siulan dan lengkingan yang nyaring. Ia bahkan pandai menirukan suara burung lain! Burung ini sangat suka kebersihan dan senang bermain air untuk mandi. Setelah mandi, ia berjemur di bawah sinar matahari agar bulunya kering dan berkilau.","body_en":"The Bali myna has a special song of whistles and bright, ringing calls. It is even good at copying the sounds of other birds! This bird loves cleanliness and enjoys splashing in water to bathe. After bathing, it suns itself so its feathers dry and shine."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Jalak bali termasuk burung yang sangat langka di alam liar. Jumlahnya pernah menurun sampai tinggal sedikit sekali. Untungnya, banyak orang baik bekerja keras menjaga dan menangkarkannya. Yuk, kita sayangi jalak bali agar burung cantik ini terus berkicau di Bali!","body_en":"The Bali myna is a very rare bird in the wild. Its numbers once dropped down to very few. Luckily, many kind people work hard to protect and breed them. Let's care for the Bali myna so this beautiful bird keeps singing in Bali!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Jalak bali adalah satu-satunya hewan khas asli Bali!","en":"The Bali myna is the only animal native to Bali!"},{"id":"Bulunya hampir 90 persen berwarna putih bersih.","en":"About 90 percent of its feathers are pure white."},{"id":"Ia menjadi lambang fauna Provinsi Bali sejak 1991.","en":"It has been Bali Province's animal symbol since 1991."},{"id":"Jalak bali pandai menirukan suara burung lain.","en":"The Bali myna is good at copying other birds' sounds."},{"id":"Ia membuat sarang di dalam lubang pohon.","en":"It builds its nest inside tree holes."},{"id":"Burung ini sangat suka mandi dan menjaga kebersihan.","en":"This bird loves bathing and staying clean."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hanya hidup di satu tempat di dunia.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives in only one place in the world."},{"term":"Pengicau","def_id":"Burung yang pandai bernyanyi dan berkicau.","def_en":"A bird that is good at singing and chirping."},{"term":"Jambul","def_id":"Bulu yang berdiri di atas kepala burung.","def_en":"Feathers that stand up on top of a bird's head."},{"term":"Penangkaran","def_id":"Tempat hewan dijaga dan dikembangbiakkan agar tidak punah.","def_en":"A place where animals are kept and bred so they don't go extinct."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a6fa2ef43c702575.jpg","caption_id":"Jalak bali bertengger, memamerkan bulu putih dan pelupuk biru khasnya.","caption_en":"A Bali myna perched, showing its white feathers and signature blue eye-patch.","credit":"JJ Harrison","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8e23caa6af095eb7.jpg","caption_id":"Jalak bali di antara dahan dan buah-buahan hutan.","caption_en":"A Bali myna among branches and forest fruits.","credit":"Ady Kristanto","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/000c823cf42ebd18.jpg","caption_id":"Tampak depan jalak bali dengan dada putih bersih.","caption_en":"Front view of a Bali myna with a clean white chest.","credit":"Stavenn","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1e55d1be9f083cac.jpg","caption_id":"Jalak bali bertengger tenang di sebuah ranting.","caption_en":"A Bali myna perched calmly on a twig.","credit":"User:Cburnett","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalak_bali"},"ensiklopedia_kantong_semar":{"id":"ensiklopedia_kantong_semar","title_id":"Kantong Semar","title_en":"Pitcher Plant","subtitle_id":"Tumbuhan ajaib pemakan serangga!","subtitle_en":"A magical insect-eating plant!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Rawa & hutan lembap","value_en":"Swamps & damp forests"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Height","value_id":"Memanjat hingga 15-20 m","value_en":"Climbs up to 15-20 m"},{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Cara makan","label_en":"How it eats","value_id":"Menjebak serangga di kantong","value_en":"Traps insects in its pouch"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Kalimantan & Sumatra","value_en":"Borneo & Sumatra"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Nepenthes (130+ jenis)","value_en":"Nepenthes (130+ kinds)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Kantong Semar?","h_en":"What Is the Pitcher Plant?","body_id":"Kantong semar adalah tumbuhan yang memakan serangga! Para ilmuwan menyebut kelompoknya Nepenthes. Tumbuhan ini punya kantong berisi cairan khusus yang bisa melarutkan serangga kecil. Dari serangga itulah ia mendapat makanan tambahan.","body_en":"The pitcher plant is a plant that eats insects! Scientists call its group Nepenthes. It has a pouch filled with a special liquid that can dissolve tiny insects. That is how it gets extra food."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Kantong semar suka tempat lembap seperti rawa-rawa. Ia tumbuh di Indonesia, terutama di pulau Kalimantan dan Sumatra. Di Kalimantan Barat, orang menyebutnya entuyut. Ada yang hidup di tepi pantai, ada pula yang tinggi di pegunungan.","body_en":"Pitcher plants love damp places like swamps. They grow in Indonesia, especially on the islands of Borneo and Sumatra. In West Kalimantan, people call it entuyut. Some live near the beach, and others live high in the mountains."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Kantong semar memanjat tanaman lain dan bisa tumbuh sangat tinggi. Di ujung daunnya ada sulur yang berubah menjadi kantong perangkap. Ada kantong atas yang menggantung untuk menangkap nyamuk dan lalat. Ada juga kantong bawah dekat tanah untuk menjebak semut.","body_en":"Pitcher plants climb other plants and can grow very tall. At the tip of each leaf is a tendril that turns into a trap-pouch. The upper pouch hangs high to catch mosquitoes and flies. The lower pouch sits near the ground to trap ants."},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Cara Lembut Menangkap Serangga","h_en":"How It Gently Traps Insects","body_id":"Bibir kantong licin dan harum, jadi serangga datang untuk mencicipi. Saat menginjak tepi yang licin, serangga tergelincir masuk ke dalam kantong. Di dalam ada cairan berenzim yang perlahan mengubah serangga menjadi makanan. Begitulah tumbuhan ini mendapat nutrisi tanpa harus berburu.","body_en":"The rim of the pouch is slippery and sweet-smelling, so insects come for a taste. When they step on the slick edge, they slide down into the pouch. Inside is a special liquid with enzymes that slowly turns the insect into food. That is how the plant gets nutrients without hunting."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Kantong semar tumbuh di tanah miskin makanan, jadi ia pintar mencari nutrisi sendiri. Bahkan kelelawar kecil suka tidur di dalam kantongnya yang aman! Karena unik, kita harus menjaga rawa dan hutan tempatnya hidup. Dengan melindungi rumahnya, tumbuhan ajaib ini bisa terus tumbuh.","body_en":"Pitcher plants grow in soil that is poor in food, so they cleverly find their own nutrients. Tiny bats even like to sleep safely inside their pouches! Because they are so unique, we must protect the swamps and forests where they live. By saving their home, this magical plant can keep growing."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kantong semar memakan serangga, bukan dimakan serangga!","en":"The pitcher plant eats insects instead of being eaten by them!"},{"id":"Ada lebih dari 130 jenis kantong semar di dunia.","en":"There are more than 130 kinds of pitcher plants in the world."},{"id":"Kelelawar berbulu wol suka tidur aman di dalam kantongnya.","en":"Woolly bats like to sleep safely inside the pouch."},{"id":"Cairan di dalam kantong bisa melarutkan serangga kecil.","en":"The liquid inside the pouch can dissolve tiny insects."},{"id":"Di Kalimantan, kantongnya dipakai sebagai wadah membuat kue!","en":"In Borneo, the pouch is used as a container for making cakes!"},{"id":"Ada kantong semar yang tumbuh tinggi di gunung, lebih dari 3.000 meter!","en":"Some pitcher plants grow high on mountains, over 3,000 meters up!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Insektivora","def_id":"Tumbuhan atau hewan yang memakan serangga sebagai makanan.","def_en":"A plant or animal that eats insects for food."},{"term":"Nepenthes","def_id":"Nama ilmiah untuk kelompok tumbuhan kantong semar.","def_en":"The scientific name for the group of pitcher plants."},{"term":"Sulur","def_id":"Bagian tipis dan panjang di ujung daun yang berubah menjadi kantong.","def_en":"A thin, long part at the tip of a leaf that turns into the pouch."},{"term":"Enzim","def_id":"Cairan khusus yang membantu melarutkan serangga menjadi makanan.","def_en":"A special liquid that helps dissolve insects into food."},{"term":"Nutrisi","def_id":"Zat makanan yang dibutuhkan agar tumbuhan bisa hidup dan tumbuh.","def_en":"The food substances a plant needs to live and grow."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3c337722596ebff7.jpg","caption_id":"Kantong bawah dengan bibir merah cerah, siap menjebak semut yang lewat.","caption_en":"A lower pouch with a bright red rim, ready to trap passing ants.","credit":"Kleo Marlo Sialongo","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e2749697e68a1792.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok kantong hijau tumbuh rapat di tepi air yang lembap.","caption_en":"A cluster of green pouches grows close together by the damp water's edge.","credit":"en:User:Rbrtjong","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4ebbe0488c825f13.jpg","caption_id":"Kantong atas menggantung di antara dahan untuk menangkap serangga terbang.","caption_en":"An upper pouch hangs among the branches to catch flying insects.","credit":"Pavel Kirillov from St.Petersburg, Russia","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0beaf77174ac2dc2.jpg","caption_id":"Sebuah tangan menunjukkan betapa besar kantong semar ini bisa tumbuh.","caption_en":"A hand shows just how big this pitcher plant pouch can grow.","credit":"NoverKelana","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kantong_semar"},"ensiklopedia_komodo_2":{"id":"ensiklopedia_komodo_2","title_id":"Komodo","title_en":"Komodo Dragon","subtitle_id":"Kadal terbesar di dunia dari Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest lizard, from Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"grass","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Padang rumput & hutan belukar","value_en":"Grasslands & scrub forest"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"2-3 m, hingga 100 kg","value_en":"2-3 m, up to 100 kg"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Pemakan daging","value_en":"Meat-eater"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Nusa Tenggara Timur","value_en":"East Nusa Tenggara"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Rentan, dilindungi","value_en":"Vulnerable, protected"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Biawak (Varanidae)","value_en":"Monitor lizards (Varanidae)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Komodo?","h_en":"What Is the Komodo Dragon?","body_id":"Komodo adalah biawak raksasa dan kadal terbesar di dunia! Panjangnya bisa 2 sampai 3 meter, sepanjang sebuah mobil kecil. Orang asli pulau Komodo menyebutnya ora. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Indonesia, jadi kita patut bangga!","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a giant monitor lizard and the biggest lizard in the world! It can be 2 to 3 meters long, about as long as a small car. The local people of Komodo Island call it ora. This animal lives only in Indonesia, so we can be proud!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Komodo hanya hidup di beberapa pulau di Nusa Tenggara Timur, Indonesia. Pulau-pulaunya bernama Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, dan Gili Dasami. Mereka suka padang rumput terbuka dan hutan belukar. Tempat tinggalnya kini dilindungi sebagai Taman Nasional Komodo.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon lives only on a few islands in East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia. The islands are called Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, and Gili Dasami. They like open grasslands and bushy forests. Their home is now protected as Komodo National Park."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Komodo punya kulit tebal berwarna abu-abu sampai cokelat dan ekor sepanjang tubuhnya. Lidahnya panjang dan bercabang, dipakai untuk mencium bau dari jauh. Komodo bahkan bisa mencium makanan dari jarak beberapa kilometer! Cakarnya kuat untuk menggali lubang tempat berlindung.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon has thick gray-to-brown skin and a tail as long as its body. Its long, forked tongue is used to smell from far away. A Komodo can even smell food from several kilometers away! Its strong claws help dig burrows for shelter."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Komodo adalah pemakan daging dan memburu hewan dengan cara mengendap-endap diam-diam. Ia suka menyendiri dan hanya berkumpul saat makan atau berkembang biak. Walau besar, komodo bisa berlari cepat, berenang, bahkan menyelam. Saat masih muda, ia juga pandai memanjat pohon dengan cakarnya.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a meat-eater and hunts by quietly sneaking up on animals. It likes to be alone and only gathers to eat or to breed. Even though it is big, it can run fast, swim, and even dive. When young, it is also good at climbing trees with its claws."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Komodo adalah hewan langka yang hanya ada di Indonesia, jadi sangat istimewa. Sayangnya rumahnya makin sempit karena ulah manusia. Pemerintah melindunginya dan membuat Taman Nasional Komodo. Dengan menjaga hutan dan pulaunya, komodo bisa hidup bahagia untuk waktu yang lama.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a rare animal found only in Indonesia, so it is very special. Sadly, its home is getting smaller because of people. The government protects it and created Komodo National Park. By caring for its forests and islands, the Komodo dragon can live happily for a long time."}],"facts":[{"id":"Komodo adalah kadal terbesar di dunia!","en":"The Komodo dragon is the biggest lizard in the world!"},{"id":"Lidahnya yang bercabang bisa mencium bau dari berkilo-kilometer jauhnya.","en":"Its forked tongue can smell from kilometers away."},{"id":"Komodo bisa berlari hingga 20 km per jam dalam jarak pendek.","en":"A Komodo can run up to 20 km per hour over short distances."},{"id":"Ia pandai berenang dan bisa menyelam sedalam 4,5 meter.","en":"It is a good swimmer and can dive 4.5 meters deep."},{"id":"Komodo punya sekitar 60 gigi tajam di mulutnya.","en":"A Komodo has about 60 sharp teeth in its mouth."},{"id":"Komodo hanya hidup liar di Indonesia, tidak di tempat lain di dunia!","en":"Komodo dragons live in the wild only in Indonesia, nowhere else!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Biawak","def_id":"Kadal besar berkaki empat dengan lidah bercabang; komodo termasuk biawak.","def_en":"A large four-legged lizard with a forked tongue; the Komodo is a monitor lizard."},{"term":"Lidah bercabang","def_id":"Lidah yang terbelah dua di ujungnya, dipakai untuk mencium bau.","def_en":"A tongue that splits in two at the tip, used to smell."},{"term":"Sabana","def_id":"Padang rumput luas yang terbuka, tempat komodo suka berjalan.","def_en":"A wide, open grassland where the Komodo likes to roam."},{"term":"Rentan","def_id":"Hewan yang jumlahnya makin sedikit dan perlu kita lindungi.","def_en":"An animal whose numbers are getting small and needs our protection."},{"term":"Taman nasional","def_id":"Daerah khusus yang dijaga agar hewan dan tumbuhannya tetap aman.","def_en":"A special protected area where animals and plants are kept safe."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7d2a3b45ec0eb402.jpg","caption_id":"Komodo besar berjalan di jalan setapak, lidahnya menjulur untuk mencium bau.","caption_en":"A big Komodo walks along a trail, its tongue flicking out to smell the air.","credit":"Charles J. Sharp","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d5599131a75bee94.jpg","caption_id":"Berjemur di atas batu di antara dedaunan hijau yang segar.","caption_en":"Basking on a rock among fresh green leaves.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d9c808ccbd1c5e2b.jpg","caption_id":"Dua komodo berjalan bersama di pulau Rinca yang berumput.","caption_en":"Two Komodo dragons walk together on grassy Rinca Island.","credit":"Markofjohnson","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/14ec90a093111f14.jpg","caption_id":"Lihat dekat kaki dan cakarnya yang kuat untuk menggali dan berjalan.","caption_en":"A close look at its foot and strong claws, used for digging and walking.","credit":"Markofjohnson at English Wikipedia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Komodo"},"ensiklopedia_orangutan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_orangutan","title_id":"Orang Utan","title_en":"Orangutan","subtitle_id":"Kera cerdas penghuni pohon hutan hujan!","subtitle_en":"The clever ape of the rainforest trees!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan tropis","value_en":"Tropical rainforest"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Jantan ~75 kg, betina ~37 kg","value_en":"Male ~75 kg, female ~37 kg"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Buah, daun, madu, serangga","value_en":"Fruit, leaves, honey, insects"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Kalimantan & Sumatra","value_en":"Borneo & Sumatra"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam kritis","value_en":"Critically endangered"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Kera besar (Pongo)","value_en":"Great apes (Pongo)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Orang Utan?","h_en":"What Is the Orangutan?","body_id":"Orang utan adalah kera besar berbulu cokelat kemerahan. Namanya berasal dari bahasa Melayu yang berarti orang hutan. Ada tiga jenis orang utan: Kalimantan, Sumatra, dan Tapanuli. Mereka adalah saudara jauh kita yang sangat pintar.","body_en":"The orangutan is a great ape with reddish-brown hair. Its name comes from the Malay words meaning person of the forest. There are three kinds of orangutan: Bornean, Sumatran, and Tapanuli. They are our clever distant cousins."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Orang utan hidup di hutan hujan Indonesia dan Malaysia. Sekarang mereka hanya ditemukan di pulau Kalimantan dan Sumatra. Mereka adalah kera besar yang paling suka tinggal di atas pohon. Hampir sepanjang hari dihabiskan di antara dahan-dahan yang tinggi.","body_en":"Orangutans live in the rainforests of Indonesia and Malaysia. Today they are found only on the islands of Borneo and Sumatra. They are the great apes that love living in trees the most. Almost all day is spent high among the branches."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Orang utan punya lengan yang sangat panjang dan kaki yang pendek, sempurna untuk berayun di pohon. Tubuhnya tertutup rambut cokelat kemerahan. Orang utan jantan dewasa lebih besar dan punya bantalan lebar di kedua pipinya. Jantan juga sering berteriak panjang yang terdengar dari jauh.","body_en":"Orangutans have very long arms and short legs, perfect for swinging through trees. Their bodies are covered in reddish-brown hair. Adult males are bigger and have wide pads on their cheeks. Males also make long calls that can be heard from far away."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Makanan kesukaan orang utan adalah buah-buahan. Mereka juga makan daun, kulit kayu, madu, serangga, dan telur burung. Orang utan sangat pintar dan bisa memakai alat untuk membantu mencari makan. Setiap malam mereka membuat sarang baru dari ranting dan daun untuk tidur.","body_en":"The orangutan's favorite food is fruit. They also eat leaves, tree bark, honey, insects, and bird eggs. Orangutans are very smart and can use tools to help find food. Every night they build a new nest from twigs and leaves to sleep in."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Orang utan adalah salah satu primata paling cerdas di dunia. Sayangnya ketiga jenisnya kini sangat terancam punah. Hutan tempat tinggalnya banyak ditebang, dan itu membuat mereka kehilangan rumah. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu orang utan tetap hidup bebas dan bahagia.","body_en":"Orangutans are among the smartest primates in the world. Sadly, all three kinds are now in great danger of disappearing. Many of their forests have been cut down, leaving them without a home. By protecting the forests, we help orangutans stay free and happy."}],"facts":[{"id":"Orang utan berarti orang hutan dalam bahasa Melayu.","en":"Orangutan means person of the forest in Malay."},{"id":"Mereka kera besar yang paling suka tinggal di atas pohon.","en":"They are the great apes that love living in trees the most."},{"id":"Orang utan membuat sarang baru dari ranting setiap malam.","en":"Orangutans build a new nest from twigs every night."},{"id":"Mereka sangat pintar dan bisa memakai alat untuk mencari makan.","en":"They are very clever and can use tools to find food."},{"id":"Orang utan bisa hidup lebih dari 30 tahun.","en":"Orangutans can live more than 30 years."},{"id":"Lengan orang utan lebih panjang daripada kakinya untuk berayun.","en":"An orangutan's arms are longer than its legs for swinging."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Kera besar","def_id":"Kelompok primata bertubuh besar tanpa ekor, seperti orang utan dan gorila.","def_en":"A group of large, tailless primates, like orangutans and gorillas."},{"term":"Arboreal","def_id":"Hewan yang menghabiskan sebagian besar hidupnya di atas pohon.","def_en":"An animal that spends most of its life up in the trees."},{"term":"Bantalan pipi","def_id":"Lipatan lebar di pipi orang utan jantan dewasa.","def_en":"The wide cheek pads on an adult male orangutan."},{"term":"Primata","def_id":"Kelompok hewan pintar seperti kera, monyet, dan manusia.","def_en":"A group of clever animals like apes, monkeys, and humans."},{"term":"Terancam punah","def_id":"Hewan yang jumlahnya sangat sedikit dan bisa hilang dari bumi.","def_en":"An animal so few in number that it could vanish from the Earth."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b30a1e77d5d9e4fc.jpg","caption_id":"Orang utan duduk di dahan sambil memegang kelapa dengan jari-jarinya yang lihai.","caption_en":"An orangutan sits on a branch, holding a coconut with its clever fingers.","credit":"Eleifert","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c430a7d4906c53b7.jpg","caption_id":"Tiga jenis orang utan jantan: Kalimantan, Sumatra, dan Tapanuli.","caption_en":"The three kinds of male orangutan: Bornean, Sumatran, and Tapanuli.","credit":"Eric Kilby, Aiwok, Tim Laman","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/63fb91ec52199d0b.jpg","caption_id":"Orang utan Tapanuli jantan (kiri) dan betina (kanan) di hutan Sumatra.","caption_en":"A male (left) and female (right) Tapanuli orangutan in the Sumatran forest.","credit":"Tim Laman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orang_utan"},"ensiklopedia_penyu_hijau_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_penyu_hijau_1","title_id":"Penyu Hijau","title_en":"Green Sea Turtle","subtitle_id":"Penyu laut besar yang menjelajahi samudra hangat","subtitle_en":"A big sea turtle that roams warm oceans","data_card":[{"icon":"waves","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Laut tropis & subtropis yang hangat","value_en":"Warm tropical & subtropical seas"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Cangkang sampai sekitar 1 meter","value_en":"Shell up to about 1 meter"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Lamun & rumput laut (dewasa)","value_en":"Seagrass & seaweed (as adults)"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Samudra Atlantik & Pasifik; tangkar di Ujung Genteng","value_en":"Atlantic & Pacific Oceans; bred at Ujung Genteng"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam, jumlahnya makin sedikit","value_en":"Threatened, numbers are falling"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Reptil laut, satu-satunya jenis Chelonia","value_en":"Sea reptile, the only Chelonia species"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Penyu Hijau?","h_en":"What Is a Green Sea Turtle?","body_id":"Penyu hijau (Chelonia mydas) adalah penyu laut yang besar dan termasuk reptil. Ia hidup di laut dan membawa rumahnya sendiri, yaitu cangkang yang kuat. Namanya 'hijau' bukan karena cangkangnya hijau, tetapi karena ada lemak berwarna hijau di bawah cangkangnya. Penyu hijau adalah satu-satunya jenis dalam golongan Chelonia.","body_en":"The green sea turtle (Chelonia mydas) is a large sea turtle and a reptile. It lives in the ocean and carries its own home, a strong shell. It is called 'green' not because the shell is green, but because of the green fat under its shell. The green sea turtle is the only species in the Chelonia group."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di semua laut tropis dan subtropis yang hangat, terutama di Samudra Atlantik dan Samudra Pasifik. Ia suka air hangat yang jernih. Di Indonesia, penyu ini dirawat dan ditangkarkan di Ujung Genteng, Sukabumi, agar jumlahnya tetap terjaga.","body_en":"Green sea turtles swim in all warm tropical and subtropical seas, especially the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans. They love clear, warm water. In Indonesia, they are cared for and bred at Ujung Genteng in Sukabumi to help keep their numbers safe."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Penyu hijau punya cangkang keras di atas tubuhnya untuk melindungi diri. Cangkang ini terdiri dari bagian atas (karapaks) dan bagian bawah (plastron). Kaki-kakinya berbentuk seperti dayung supaya bisa berenang cepat di air. Ia bernapas dengan paru-paru, jadi harus naik ke permukaan untuk menghirup udara.","body_en":"The green sea turtle has a hard shell on top of its body for protection. The shell has an upper part (carapace) and a lower part (plastron). Its legs are shaped like paddles so it can swim quickly through the water. It breathes with lungs, so it must come up to the surface for air."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Penyu hijau dewasa suka makan tumbuhan laut, seperti lamun dan rumput laut. Itulah sebabnya ia sering disebut penyu pemakan tumbuhan. Induk penyu kembali ke pantai untuk bertelur di pasir, lalu bayi-bayi kecilnya menetas dan bergegas menuju laut.","body_en":"Adult green sea turtles love eating sea plants, such as seagrass and seaweed. That is why they are known as plant-eating turtles. Mother turtles return to the beach to lay eggs in the sand, then the tiny babies hatch and hurry to the sea."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Jumlah penyu hijau makin sedikit karena diburu untuk diambil cangkang, telur, dan dagingnya. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga laut dan pantai tetap bersih dari sampah. Jika kita semua peduli, penyu hijau bisa terus berenang bahagia di laut.","body_en":"Green sea turtles are becoming fewer because they are hunted for their shells, eggs, and meat. We can help by keeping the sea and beaches clean and free of trash. If we all care, green sea turtles can keep swimming happily in the ocean."}],"facts":[{"id":"Namanya 'hijau' karena lemak hijau di bawah cangkangnya!","en":"It is called 'green' because of the green fat under its shell!"},{"id":"Penyu hijau adalah satu-satunya spesies dalam golongan Chelonia.","en":"The green sea turtle is the only species in the Chelonia group."},{"id":"Kakinya seperti dayung untuk berenang di laut.","en":"Its legs are like paddles for swimming in the sea."},{"id":"Ia bernapas dengan paru-paru dan harus naik untuk mengambil udara.","en":"It breathes with lungs and must surface for air."},{"id":"Induk penyu kembali ke pantai untuk bertelur di pasir.","en":"Mother turtles return to the beach to lay eggs in the sand."},{"id":"Penyu hijau dewasa suka makan rumput laut dan lamun.","en":"Adult green sea turtles love to eat seaweed and seagrass."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Karapaks","def_id":"Bagian atas cangkang penyu yang keras dan melindungi punggungnya.","def_en":"The hard upper part of a turtle's shell that protects its back."},{"term":"Plastron","def_id":"Bagian bawah cangkang penyu yang menutupi perutnya.","def_en":"The lower part of a turtle's shell that covers its belly."},{"term":"Lamun","def_id":"Rumput laut yang tumbuh di dasar laut dan menjadi makanan penyu hijau.","def_en":"A grass that grows on the sea floor and is food for green sea turtles."},{"term":"Subtropis","def_id":"Daerah laut yang hangat, dekat dengan daerah tropis.","def_en":"Warm sea areas that lie next to the tropical zone."},{"term":"Menetas","def_id":"Saat bayi penyu keluar dari telurnya.","def_en":"When a baby turtle comes out of its egg."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a0443bdd8b758053.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di atas terumbu karang dengan kaki seperti dayung.","caption_en":"A green sea turtle glides over a coral reef with its paddle-like legs.","credit":"Brocken Inaglory","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3f165b798896b430.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau dewasa merumput di hamparan lamun di dasar laut.","caption_en":"An adult green sea turtle grazes on a bed of seagrass on the sea floor.","credit":"P.Lindgren","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/55b6d280e713b6d1.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau berenang naik ke permukaan untuk menghirup udara.","caption_en":"A green sea turtle swims up toward the surface to take a breath of air.","credit":"Brocken Inaglory","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8665f0e91260185d.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok penyu hijau beristirahat di pantai berpasir.","caption_en":"A group of green sea turtles resting on a sandy beach.","credit":"E bailey","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e3dc74e7f0e3cb54.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di air dangkal yang jernih dekat pantai.","caption_en":"A green sea turtle swims in clear, shallow water near the shore.","credit":"Tokugawapants at English Wikipedia + PiccoloNamek (Modifie version)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penyu_hijau"},"ensiklopedia_rafflesia_arnoldii":{"id":"ensiklopedia_rafflesia_arnoldii","title_id":"Rafflesia Arnoldii (Padma Raksasa)","title_en":"Rafflesia Arnoldii","subtitle_id":"Bunga terbesar di dunia dari hutan Indonesia","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest flower from Indonesia's forests","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan lembap di Sumatra & Kalimantan","value_en":"Damp rainforests of Sumatra & Borneo"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Lebar 70-110 cm, berat sekitar 11 kg","value_en":"70-110 cm wide, about 11 kg heavy"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Lama Mekar","label_en":"Bloom Time","value_id":"Hanya sekitar 5-7 hari lalu layu","value_en":"Only about 5-7 days, then it wilts"},{"icon":"place","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Bengkulu, 'Bumi Rafflesia'; Taman Nasional Kerinci Seblat","value_en":"Bengkulu, 'Land of Rafflesia'; Kerinci Seblat National Park"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Langka & terancam, dilindungi sejak 1993","value_en":"Rare & threatened, protected since 1993"},{"icon":"spa","label_id":"Cara Hidup","label_en":"Way of Life","value_id":"Parasit, menempel pada akar merambat Tetrastigma","value_en":"Parasite, attached to the Tetrastigma vine"}],"sections":[{"icon":"local_florist","h_id":"Apa Itu Rafflesia?","h_en":"What Is Rafflesia?","body_id":"Rafflesia arnoldii adalah bunga terbesar di dunia! Saat mekar, lebarnya bisa mencapai sekitar 70 sampai 110 sentimeter, kira-kira selebar ban mobil, dan beratnya bisa sampai 11 kilogram. Bunga raksasa ini juga salah satu bunga nasional kebanggaan Indonesia.","body_en":"Rafflesia arnoldii is the biggest flower in the world! When it blooms, it can grow about 70 to 110 centimeters wide, roughly as wide as a car tire, and it can weigh up to 11 kilograms. This giant flower is also one of Indonesia's proud national flowers."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Rafflesia tumbuh di hutan hujan yang lembap di Pulau Sumatra dan Kalimantan. Daerah Bengkulu dikenal sebagai 'Bumi Rafflesia' karena bunga ini pertama ditemukan di sana pada tahun 1818. Taman Nasional Kerinci Seblat adalah tempat penting untuk menjaganya.","body_en":"Rafflesia grows in the damp rainforests of Sumatra and Borneo. The Bengkulu area is known as the 'Land of Rafflesia' because the flower was first found there in 1818. Kerinci Seblat National Park is an important place that protects it."},{"icon":"spa","h_id":"Bunga Tanpa Daun & Akar","h_en":"A Flower With No Leaves or Roots","body_id":"Rafflesia sangat unik karena tidak punya daun, akar, atau batang, hanya bunganya saja! Karena tak punya daun, ia tidak bisa membuat makanan sendiri. Jadi ia hidup sebagai parasit, menempel pada tumbuhan merambat bernama Tetrastigma dan mengambil makanan dari sana, seperti tamu yang menumpang makan.","body_en":"Rafflesia is very unusual because it has no leaves, roots, or stem, just the flower! Because it has no leaves, it cannot make its own food. So it lives as a parasite, attached to a climbing vine called Tetrastigma and takes food from it, like a guest borrowing a meal."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Mekar & Baunya","h_en":"Blooming & Its Smell","body_id":"Rafflesia punya lima kelopak besar berwarna merah dengan bintik-bintik putih. Bunga ini hanya mekar sekitar lima sampai tujuh hari, lalu layu dan mati. Baunya kuat seperti bau bangkai, jadi orang menyebutnya 'bunga bangkai'. Bau itu memanggil lalat untuk membantu bunga membuat benih.","body_en":"Rafflesia has five big red petals with white spots. The flower blooms for only about five to seven days, then it wilts and dies. It smells strong like something rotten, so people call it the 'corpse flower'. That smell calls flies to help the flower make seeds."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Rafflesia sangat langka dan terancam punah karena hutan tempatnya hidup banyak ditebang. Sejak tahun 1993, bunga ini dilindungi sebagai puspa langka Indonesia. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap utuh agar bunga raksasa ini terus mekar.","body_en":"Rafflesia is very rare and endangered because the forests where it lives are being cut down. Since 1993, this flower has been protected as a rare flower of Indonesia. We can help by keeping forests safe so this giant flower can keep blooming."}],"facts":[{"id":"Rafflesia arnoldii adalah bunga terbesar di dunia!","en":"Rafflesia arnoldii is the biggest flower in the world!"},{"id":"Saat mekar, lebarnya bisa sampai 70-110 cm dan beratnya sekitar 11 kilogram.","en":"When open it can be 70-110 cm wide and weigh about 11 kilograms."},{"id":"Bunganya hanya mekar sekitar 5-7 hari lalu layu.","en":"The flower blooms for only about 5-7 days, then wilts."},{"id":"Baunya seperti bangkai, itu sebabnya disebut 'bunga bangkai'.","en":"It smells rotten, which is why it's called the 'corpse flower'."},{"id":"Rafflesia tidak punya daun, akar, atau batang, hanya bunga!","en":"Rafflesia has no leaves, roots, or stem, just the flower!"},{"id":"Namanya dari Thomas Stamford Raffles dan Dr. Joseph Arnold.","en":"It is named after Thomas Stamford Raffles and Dr. Joseph Arnold."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Parasit","def_id":"Makhluk hidup yang menempel pada makhluk lain dan mengambil makanannya.","def_en":"A living thing that attaches to another and takes its food."},{"term":"Tetrastigma","def_id":"Tumbuhan merambat (liana) yang menjadi tempat hidup dan sumber makanan Rafflesia.","def_en":"A climbing vine that Rafflesia lives on and takes its food from."},{"term":"Kelopak","def_id":"Bagian bunga yang lebar dan berwarna; Rafflesia punya lima kelopak merah.","def_en":"The wide, colorful part of a flower; Rafflesia has five red petals."},{"term":"Mekar","def_id":"Saat bunga membuka penuh dan terlihat indah.","def_en":"When a flower opens up fully and looks beautiful."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hanya hidup di satu daerah tertentu dan tidak di tempat lain.","def_en":"Found living only in one certain place and nowhere else."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/385c30fce59c6dae.jpg","caption_id":"Rafflesia mekar penuh di lantai hutan, dengan kuncup lain di belakangnya.","caption_en":"A Rafflesia in full bloom on the forest floor, with another bud behind it.","credit":"Maizal Chaniago","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/df932888e453e9ab.jpg","caption_id":"Lima kelopak merah berbintik putih mengelilingi lubang di tengah bunga.","caption_en":"Five red petals with white spots circle the opening at the center of the flower.","credit":"ma_suska","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5bdda5cecc92b796.jpg","caption_id":"Rafflesia tumbuh di tengah hutan hujan yang lembap dan hijau.","caption_en":"A Rafflesia growing in the middle of a damp, green rainforest.","credit":"SofianRafflesia","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Padma_raksasa"},"ensiklopedia_rumah_gadang":{"id":"ensiklopedia_rumah_gadang","title_id":"Rumah Gadang","title_en":"Rumah Gadang","subtitle_id":"Rumah adat Minangkabau dengan atap melengkung seperti tanduk kerbau!","subtitle_en":"The Minangkabau traditional house with a roof curved like buffalo horns!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Minangkabau, Sumatra Barat","value_en":"Minangkabau, West Sumatra"},{"icon":"home","label_id":"Ciri khas","label_en":"Feature","value_id":"Atap gonjong (tanduk kerbau)","value_en":"Gonjong roof (buffalo horns)"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Kayu, ijuk, dan bambu","value_en":"Wood, palm fiber, and bamboo"},{"icon":"festival","label_id":"Fungsi","label_en":"Use","value_id":"Rumah adat keluarga besar","value_en":"Home for the extended family"},{"icon":"diversity_3","label_id":"Pemilik","label_en":"Owner","value_id":"Diwariskan kepada perempuan","value_en":"Passed down to women"}],"sections":[{"icon":"home","h_id":"Apa Itu Rumah Gadang?","h_en":"What Is the Rumah Gadang?","body_id":"Rumah Gadang adalah rumah adat suku Minangkabau di Sumatra Barat, Indonesia. Namanya berarti 'rumah besar'. Yang paling istimewa adalah atapnya yang melengkung runcing ke atas, mirip tanduk kerbau. Karena bentuk atap ini, rumah ini juga disebut Rumah Bagonjong. Sebuah rumah gadang bisa menjadi tempat tinggal satu keluarga besar bersama-sama.","body_en":"The Rumah Gadang is the traditional house of the Minangkabau people in West Sumatra, Indonesia. Its name means 'big house'. The most special part is its roof, which curves up into sharp points like a buffalo's horns. Because of this roof, the house is also called Rumah Bagonjong. One rumah gadang can be home to a whole big family living together."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Rumah Gadang berasal dari Alam Minangkabau di Sumatra Barat. Rumah ini hanya boleh dibangun di sebuah desa adat yang disebut nagari. Di halaman depannya biasanya ada bangunan kecil bernama rangkiang, yaitu lumbung untuk menyimpan padi. Tidak jauh dari rumah, sering dibangun pula sebuah surau sebagai tempat ibadah dan belajar.","body_en":"The Rumah Gadang comes from the Minangkabau homeland in West Sumatra. It may only be built in a traditional village called a nagari. In front of the house there are usually small buildings called rangkiang, which are barns for storing rice. Not far from the house, a small prayer house called a surau is often built for worship and study."},{"icon":"build","h_id":"Bagaimana Dibangun?","h_en":"How Is It Built?","body_id":"Rumah Gadang dibuat dari tiang-tiang kayu yang panjang dan kuat. Dindingnya dari papan kayu, lalu dinding bagian belakang dari bambu. Atapnya dahulu dibuat dari ijuk, yaitu serat hitam dari pohon enau, yang bisa tahan puluhan tahun. Yang hebat, untuk menyambung kayu tidak dipakai paku, melainkan pasak kayu, jadi rumah ini dibangun seperti menyusun balok raksasa.","body_en":"The Rumah Gadang is built from long, strong wooden posts. Its walls are made of wooden planks, while the back wall is made of bamboo. Long ago its roof was made of ijuk, the black fiber from the sugar palm tree, which could last for tens of years. Amazingly, the wood is joined with wooden pegs instead of nails, so the house is built like stacking giant building blocks."},{"icon":"auto_awesome","h_id":"Tahan Gempa & Penuh Ukiran","h_en":"Earthquake-Safe & Full of Carvings","body_id":"Sumatra Barat sering terkena gempa, jadi Rumah Gadang dibuat tahan gempa. Tiangnya tidak ditanam ke tanah, tetapi hanya berdiri di atas batu datar yang lebar. Saat gempa, rumah bergoyang pelan seperti sedang menari, lalu kembali tegak lagi. Dinding depannya juga penuh ukiran indah bermotif bunga, daun, dan akar yang melingkar-lingkar.","body_en":"West Sumatra often has earthquakes, so the Rumah Gadang is built to be earthquake-safe. Its posts are not planted in the ground but simply stand on wide, flat stones. During an earthquake, the house sways gently as if it is dancing, then stands tall again. The front wall is also covered with beautiful carvings of flowers, leaves, and curling vines."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Rumah Milik Perempuan","h_en":"A House That Belongs to Women","body_id":"Di adat Minangkabau, Rumah Gadang diwariskan dari ibu kepada anak perempuan. Jumlah kamar tidur mengikuti jumlah perempuan dewasa yang tinggal di sana. Bagian sayap kanan dan kiri rumah disebut anjung, dipakai untuk tempat pengantin duduk atau saat menobatkan kepala adat. Karena itu rumah ini juga dijuluki Rumah Baanjuang.","body_en":"In Minangkabau custom, the Rumah Gadang is passed down from mother to daughter. The number of bedrooms matches the number of grown-up women living there. The right and left wings of the house are called anjung, used as a seat for a bride or for crowning the customary leader. That is why the house is also nicknamed Rumah Baanjuang."}],"facts":[{"id":"Atap Rumah Gadang melengkung runcing seperti tanduk kerbau.","en":"The Rumah Gadang roof curves into sharp points like buffalo horns."},{"id":"Rumah ini dibangun tanpa paku, hanya memakai pasak dari kayu.","en":"The house is built without nails, using only wooden pegs."},{"id":"Tiangnya berdiri di atas batu, jadi rumah ini tahan gempa.","en":"Its posts stand on stones, making the house earthquake-safe."},{"id":"Dinding depannya penuh ukiran bunga, daun, dan akar.","en":"Its front wall is covered with carvings of flowers, leaves, and vines."},{"id":"Rumah Gadang diwariskan kepada anak perempuan dalam keluarga.","en":"The Rumah Gadang is passed down to the daughters in the family."},{"id":"Di halaman ada rangkiang, lumbung kecil untuk menyimpan padi.","en":"In the yard there is a rangkiang, a small barn for storing rice."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Rumah adat","def_id":"Rumah tradisional khas suatu daerah yang dibangun menurut adat setempat.","def_en":"A traditional house of a region, built according to local custom."},{"term":"Gonjong","def_id":"Puncak atap yang runcing dan melengkung ke atas seperti tanduk kerbau.","def_en":"The roof peak that is pointed and curves upward like a buffalo's horn."},{"term":"Minangkabau","def_id":"Suku asli dari Sumatra Barat yang membangun Rumah Gadang.","def_en":"The native people of West Sumatra who build the Rumah Gadang."},{"term":"Rangkiang","def_id":"Bangunan lumbung kecil di depan rumah untuk menyimpan padi.","def_en":"A small barn building in front of the house for storing rice."},{"term":"Ijuk","def_id":"Serat hitam dari pohon enau yang dahulu dipakai untuk atap.","def_en":"Black fiber from the sugar palm tree once used for roofing."},{"term":"Pasak","def_id":"Paku dari kayu untuk menyambung bagian-bagian rumah.","def_en":"A wooden peg used to join the parts of the house together."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e814415018eb952f.jpg","caption_id":"Rumah Gadang berwarna-warni dengan atap gonjong runcing dan dinding penuh ukiran, terpantul di kolam.","caption_en":"A colorful Rumah Gadang with pointed gonjong roofs and carved walls, reflected in a pond.","credit":"MichaelJLowe","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/98c629ac8c0d3521.jpg","caption_id":"Deretan Rumah Gadang tua di sebuah desa, atapnya menjulang di bawah langit mendung.","caption_en":"A row of old Rumah Gadang in a village, their roofs rising under a cloudy sky.","credit":"RaiyaniM","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/104ecd45492b3bb0.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama keluarga Minangkabau berpakaian adat di depan Rumah Gadang mereka.","caption_en":"An old photo of a Minangkabau family in traditional dress in front of their Rumah Gadang.","credit":"Christiaan Benjamin Nieuwenhuis","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c904235336bebf18.jpg","caption_id":"Model mini Rumah Gadang memperlihatkan tiang-tiang kayu dan atap ijuk dari dekat.","caption_en":"A small model of a Rumah Gadang shows the wooden posts and palm-fiber roof up close.","credit":"Tropenmuseum","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/622c0db0fbcccceb.jpg","caption_id":"Rumah Gadang dengan atap seng dan dinding tembok, perpaduan gaya lama dan baru.","caption_en":"A Rumah Gadang with a tin roof and plastered wall, mixing old and new styles.","credit":"Alfatajri","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rumah_Gadang"},"ensiklopedia_tarsius":{"id":"ensiklopedia_tarsius","title_id":"Tarsius","title_en":"Tarsier","subtitle_id":"Primata mungil bermata besar dari Sulawesi","subtitle_en":"A tiny big-eyed primate from Sulawesi","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Pohon-pohon di hutan yang rimbun","value_en":"Trees in leafy forests"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sangat kecil, muat di telapak tangan","value_en":"Very small, fits in your palm"},{"icon":"bug_report","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Serangga seperti jangkrik & belalang","value_en":"Insects like crickets & grasshoppers"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia","value_en":"The island of Sulawesi, Indonesia"},{"icon":"dark_mode","label_id":"Aktif","label_en":"Active","value_id":"Malam hari (nokturnal)","value_en":"At night (nocturnal)"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Primata kecil, famili Tarsiidae","value_en":"Small primate, family Tarsiidae"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Tarsius?","h_en":"What Is a Tarsier?","body_id":"Tarsius adalah primata yang sangat kecil, kerabat jauh dari monyet dan manusia. Tubuhnya mungil dan bisa muat di telapak tangan orang dewasa. Tarsius termasuk famili Tarsiidae. Walau kecil, tarsius punya mata yang sangat besar dan menggemaskan!","body_en":"The tarsier is a very small primate, a distant relative of monkeys and humans. Its tiny body can fit in an adult's palm. The tarsier belongs to the family Tarsiidae. Even though it is small, the tarsier has huge, adorable eyes!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Tarsius berasal dari pulau-pulau di Asia Tenggara. Semua spesies dalam genus Tarsius ditemukan di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia. Mereka tinggal di pohon-pohon dalam hutan yang rimbun dan berpegangan erat pada dahan.","body_en":"Tarsiers come from islands in Southeast Asia. Every species in the genus Tarsius is found on the island of Sulawesi, Indonesia. They live up in the trees of leafy forests and cling tightly to the branches."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Mata Raksasa & Tubuh","h_en":"Giant Eyes & Body","body_id":"Mata tarsius sangat besar dibanding tubuhnya, membantunya melihat dalam gelap. Ia punya jari-jari panjang untuk berpegangan erat di dahan pohon. Tarsius juga bisa memutar kepalanya jauh ke belakang untuk melihat sekeliling tanpa menggerakkan tubuhnya.","body_en":"A tarsier's eyes are huge compared to its body, helping it see in the dark. It has long fingers for gripping tree branches tightly. A tarsier can also turn its head far around to look behind itself without moving its body."},{"icon":"dark_mode","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan Malam","h_en":"Food & Night Habits","body_id":"Tarsius aktif di malam hari dan tidur saat siang. Dengan mata besarnya, ia berburu serangga seperti jangkrik dan belalang. Ia melompat dengan lincah dari satu dahan ke dahan lain untuk menangkap makanan.","body_en":"Tarsiers are active at night and sleep during the day. With their big eyes, they hunt insects like crickets and grasshoppers. They leap nimbly from branch to branch to catch their food."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Tarsius adalah hewan istimewa yang hanya hidup di tempat tertentu, jadi kita harus menjaganya. Hutan tempat tinggalnya perlu dilindungi agar tarsius punya rumah yang aman. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu tarsius tetap melompat bahagia.","body_en":"The tarsier is a special animal that lives only in certain places, so we must take care of it. The forests it lives in need protection so the tarsier has a safe home. By protecting forests, we help tarsiers keep leaping happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Tarsius adalah primata yang sangat kecil, bisa muat di telapak tangan.","en":"The tarsier is a tiny primate that can fit in your palm."},{"id":"Matanya sangat besar untuk melihat dalam gelap.","en":"Its eyes are very big for seeing in the dark."},{"id":"Tarsius aktif di malam hari dan tidur saat siang.","en":"Tarsiers are active at night and sleep during the day."},{"id":"Ia bisa memutar kepalanya jauh ke belakang.","en":"It can turn its head far around to look behind."},{"id":"Jari-jarinya panjang untuk berpegangan erat di dahan.","en":"Its fingers are long for gripping branches tightly."},{"id":"Semua tarsius dari genus ini ditemukan di Pulau Sulawesi.","en":"All tarsiers of this genus are found on the island of Sulawesi."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Primata","def_id":"Kelompok hewan yang mencakup monyet, kera, dan manusia.","def_en":"A group of animals that includes monkeys, apes, and humans."},{"term":"Nokturnal","def_id":"Hewan yang aktif di malam hari dan tidur di siang hari.","def_en":"An animal that is active at night and sleeps during the day."},{"term":"Genus","def_id":"Kelompok hewan atau tumbuhan yang berkerabat dekat.","def_en":"A group of animals or plants that are close relatives."},{"term":"Serangga","def_id":"Hewan kecil berkaki enam seperti jangkrik dan belalang.","def_en":"Small six-legged animals like crickets and grasshoppers."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5cc5af4876e10978.jpg","caption_id":"Tarsius berpegangan erat pada batang pohon dengan jari-jarinya yang panjang.","caption_en":"A tarsier clings tightly to a tree trunk with its long fingers.","credit":"Lip Kee Yap","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/bf0952f593d2b213.jpg","caption_id":"Mata besar dan telinga lebar tarsius membantunya berburu serangga di malam hari.","caption_en":"A tarsier's big eyes and wide ears help it hunt insects at night.","credit":"Meldy Tamenge","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tarsius_%28genus%29"},"kewarganegaraan_hak_anak":{"id":"kewarganegaraan_hak_anak","title_id":"Hak Anak","title_en":"Children's Rights","subtitle_id":"Hal yang berhak dimiliki setiap anak","subtitle_en":"Things every child deserves to have","data_card":[{"icon":"child_care","label_id":"Apa itu","label_en":"What it is","value_id":"Hak yang dimiliki setiap anak","value_en":"Rights that belong to every child"},{"icon":"school","label_id":"Contoh","label_en":"Examples","value_id":"Belajar, bermain, sehat, dilindungi","value_en":"To learn, play, be healthy, be protected"},{"icon":"family_restroom","label_id":"Pelindung","label_en":"Protected by","value_id":"Keluarga, negara, dan PBB","value_en":"Family, the state, and the UN"},{"icon":"gavel","label_id":"Aturan dunia","label_en":"World agreement","value_id":"Konvensi Hak Anak","value_en":"Convention on the Rights of the Child"},{"icon":"celebration","label_id":"Hari Anak","label_en":"Children's Day","value_id":"23 Juli (Indonesia)","value_en":"23 July (Indonesia)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Apa Itu Hak Anak?","h_en":"What Are Children's Rights?","body_id":"Hak anak adalah hal-hal baik yang berhak dimiliki dan didapat oleh setiap anak, di mana pun mereka tinggal. Setiap anak — laki-laki atau perempuan, kaya atau sederhana — punya hak yang sama. Orang dewasa bertugas menjaga dan memenuhi hak ini.","body_en":"Children's rights are the good things that every child deserves to have and receive, wherever they live. Every child — boy or girl, rich or simple — has the same rights. Grown-ups have the job of protecting and fulfilling these rights."},{"icon":"school","h_id":"Hak untuk Belajar dan Bermain","h_en":"The Right to Learn and Play","body_id":"Setiap anak berhak bersekolah dan belajar agar menjadi pintar dan siap menggapai cita-cita. Anak juga berhak bermain dan beristirahat, karena bermain membuat anak tumbuh sehat, gembira, dan kreatif.","body_en":"Every child has the right to go to school and learn, to grow smart and ready to reach their dreams. Children also have the right to play and rest, because playing helps them grow healthy, happy, and creative."},{"icon":"health_and_safety","h_id":"Hak untuk Sehat dan Dilindungi","h_en":"The Right to Be Healthy and Safe","body_id":"Anak berhak mendapat makanan bergizi, air bersih, dan perawatan saat sakit. Anak juga berhak merasa aman dan dilindungi dari kekerasan atau perlakuan kasar. Setiap anak berhak punya nama dan keluarga yang menyayanginya.","body_en":"Children have the right to healthy food, clean water, and care when they are sick. They also have the right to feel safe and be protected from violence or harsh treatment. Every child has the right to a name and a loving family."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Siapa yang Menjaga Hak Anak?","h_en":"Who Protects Children's Rights?","body_id":"Keluarga, sekolah, dan pemerintah bersama-sama menjaga hak anak. Hampir semua negara di dunia juga menyepakati aturan bersama bernama Konvensi Hak Anak dari PBB. Di Indonesia, Hari Anak Nasional dirayakan setiap 23 Juli.","body_en":"Families, schools, and the government work together to protect children's rights. Almost every country in the world also agreed on shared rules called the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child. In Indonesia, National Children's Day is celebrated every 23 July."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Kamu Juga Punya Kewajiban","h_en":"You Have Duties Too","body_id":"Selain hak, anak juga punya kewajiban: belajar dengan rajin, menghormati orang tua dan guru, serta menyayangi teman. Dengan begitu, semua anak bisa tumbuh bahagia dan saling menghargai.","body_en":"Besides rights, children also have duties: to study hard, to respect parents and teachers, and to be kind to friends. That way, all children can grow up happy and respect one another."}],"facts":[{"id":"Setiap anak berhak punya nama dan keluarga.","en":"Every child has the right to a name and a family."},{"id":"Belajar dan bermain sama-sama merupakan hak anak.","en":"Both learning and playing are children's rights."},{"id":"Hampir semua negara menyepakati Konvensi Hak Anak.","en":"Almost every country agreed to the Convention on the Rights of the Child."},{"id":"Di Indonesia, Hari Anak Nasional jatuh pada 23 Juli.","en":"In Indonesia, National Children's Day is on 23 July."},{"id":"Selain hak, anak juga punya kewajiban untuk dijalankan.","en":"Besides rights, children also have duties to carry out."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Hak","def_id":"Sesuatu yang berhak kita miliki atau dapatkan.","def_en":"Something we deserve to have or receive."},{"term":"Kewajiban","def_id":"Sesuatu yang harus kita lakukan.","def_en":"Something we must do."},{"term":"Konvensi","def_id":"Kesepakatan atau perjanjian bersama antarnegara.","def_en":"A shared agreement among countries."},{"term":"Perlindungan","def_id":"Penjagaan agar anak aman dari bahaya.","def_en":"Keeping a child safe from harm."},{"term":"PBB","def_id":"Perserikatan Bangsa-Bangsa, perkumpulan negara-negara di dunia.","def_en":"The United Nations, an organization of the world's countries."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7ce65f94fddbc1cb.jpg","caption_id":"Anak-anak bermain riang — bermain adalah salah satu hak anak.","caption_en":"Children playing joyfully — playing is one of every child's rights.","credit":"Jubair Ahmed Arnob","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a889df1738e77843.jpg","caption_id":"Anak-anak yang mendapat hak untuk belajar dan bersekolah.","caption_en":"Children enjoying their right to learn and go to school.","credit":"Tropical Research and Development Centre","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hak-hak_anak"},"kewarganegaraan_pancasila":{"id":"kewarganegaraan_pancasila","title_id":"Pancasila","title_en":"Pancasila","subtitle_id":"Lima dasar negara Indonesia","subtitle_en":"The five foundations of Indonesia","data_card":[{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Apa itu","label_en":"What it is","value_id":"Dasar negara Indonesia","value_en":"The foundation of the Indonesian state"},{"icon":"looks_5","label_id":"Jumlah sila","label_en":"Number of principles","value_id":"5 sila","value_en":"5 principles"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Lambang","label_en":"Symbol","value_id":"Garuda Pancasila","value_en":"Garuda Pancasila"},{"icon":"person","label_id":"Pencetus","label_en":"Proposed by","value_id":"Soekarno, 1 Juni 1945","value_en":"Soekarno, 1 June 1945"},{"icon":"translate","label_id":"Arti nama","label_en":"Name meaning","value_id":"Panca = lima, Sila = asas","value_en":"Panca = five, Sila = principle"}],"sections":[{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Apa Itu Pancasila?","h_en":"What Is Pancasila?","body_id":"Pancasila adalah dasar negara Republik Indonesia. Kata 'Pancasila' berasal dari bahasa Sanskerta: 'panca' artinya lima dan 'sila' artinya asas atau dasar. Jadi Pancasila berarti lima dasar yang menjadi pedoman hidup berbangsa dan bernegara.","body_en":"Pancasila is the foundation of the Republic of Indonesia. The word 'Pancasila' comes from Sanskrit: 'panca' means five and 'sila' means principle. So Pancasila means the five principles that guide our life as a nation."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Lahirnya Pancasila","h_en":"The Birth of Pancasila","body_id":"Saat menyiapkan kemerdekaan tahun 1945, para tokoh bangsa memikirkan apa dasar negara Indonesia. Pada 1 Juni 1945, Soekarno menyampaikan gagasan lima dasar dan menamainya 'Pancasila'. Karena itu, 1 Juni diperingati sebagai Hari Lahir Pancasila.","body_en":"While preparing for independence in 1945, the nation's leaders thought about what Indonesia's foundation should be. On 1 June 1945, Soekarno presented the idea of five principles and named it 'Pancasila'. That is why 1 June is celebrated as Pancasila Day."},{"icon":"format_list_numbered","h_id":"Lima Sila Pancasila","h_en":"The Five Principles","body_id":"Sila 1: Ketuhanan Yang Maha Esa. Sila 2: Kemanusiaan yang adil dan beradab. Sila 3: Persatuan Indonesia. Sila 4: Kerakyatan yang dipimpin oleh hikmat kebijaksanaan dalam permusyawaratan/perwakilan. Sila 5: Keadilan sosial bagi seluruh rakyat Indonesia.","body_en":"1st: Belief in the one almighty God. 2nd: A just and civilized humanity. 3rd: The unity of Indonesia. 4th: Democracy led by wisdom through deliberation. 5th: Social justice for all Indonesians."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Lambang Garuda","h_en":"The Garuda Symbol","body_id":"Lambang Pancasila adalah burung Garuda yang gagah. Di dadanya ada perisai berisi lima gambar yang mewakili kelima sila: bintang, rantai, pohon beringin, kepala banteng, serta padi dan kapas. Garuda juga membawa pita bertuliskan 'Bhinneka Tunggal Ika' — berbeda-beda tetapi tetap satu.","body_en":"The symbol of Pancasila is the mighty Garuda bird. On its chest is a shield with five pictures for the five principles: a star, a chain, a banyan tree, a buffalo head, and rice with cotton. The Garuda also carries a ribbon reading 'Bhinneka Tunggal Ika' — different yet still one."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Pancasila dalam Hidup Kita","h_en":"Pancasila in Our Lives","body_id":"Kita bisa mengamalkan Pancasila setiap hari: berdoa, menyayangi sesama, menjaga persatuan, suka bermusyawarah, dan berlaku adil. Pancasila membuat Indonesia yang beragam tetap rukun dan bersatu.","body_en":"We can live out Pancasila every day: praying, caring for others, keeping unity, discussing together, and being fair. Pancasila keeps our diverse Indonesia peaceful and united."}],"facts":[{"id":"'Pancasila' berasal dari bahasa Sanskerta: panca (lima) + sila (asas).","en":"'Pancasila' comes from Sanskrit: panca (five) + sila (principle)."},{"id":"1 Juni diperingati sebagai Hari Lahir Pancasila.","en":"1 June is celebrated as the Birthday of Pancasila."},{"id":"Soekarno yang pertama memperkenalkan nama 'Pancasila'.","en":"Soekarno was the first to introduce the name 'Pancasila'."},{"id":"Lambangnya adalah burung Garuda Pancasila.","en":"Its symbol is the Garuda Pancasila bird."},{"id":"Garuda membawa semboyan 'Bhinneka Tunggal Ika'.","en":"The Garuda carries the motto 'Bhinneka Tunggal Ika' (unity in diversity)."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Dasar negara","def_id":"Pedoman utama yang menjadi pegangan sebuah negara.","def_en":"The main guide a country is built upon."},{"term":"Sila","def_id":"Asas atau dasar; Pancasila punya lima sila.","def_en":"A principle; Pancasila has five of them."},{"term":"Garuda","def_id":"Burung gagah yang menjadi lambang negara Indonesia.","def_en":"The mighty bird that is Indonesia's national emblem."},{"term":"Bhinneka Tunggal Ika","def_id":"Semboyan yang berarti 'berbeda-beda tetapi tetap satu'.","def_en":"A motto meaning 'different yet still one'."},{"term":"Musyawarah","def_id":"Berunding bersama untuk mencapai keputusan.","def_en":"Discussing together to reach a decision."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cde6430545ee68c5.jpg","caption_id":"Garuda Pancasila dengan lima lambang sila di perisainya.","caption_en":"The Garuda Pancasila with the five principle symbols on its shield.","credit":"Government of Indonesia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/82d54b3a965df50a.png","caption_id":"Lambang Garuda Pancasila, lambang negara Indonesia.","caption_en":"The Garuda Pancasila emblem, Indonesia's national symbol.","credit":"M. Rizky Fathoni","license":"CC0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pancasila"},"kuliner_gado_gado":{"id":"kuliner_gado_gado","title_id":"Gado-gado","title_en":"Gado-gado","subtitle_id":"Salad sayur Indonesia yang disiram bumbu kacang!","subtitle_en":"An Indonesian vegetable salad drizzled with peanut sauce!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jakarta & Pulau Jawa","value_en":"Jakarta & the island of Java"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Salad sayur + bumbu kacang","value_en":"Vegetable salad + peanut sauce"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Sayur, tahu, tempe, telur, kentang","value_en":"Vegetables, tofu, tempeh, egg, potato"},{"icon":"local_dining","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, sedikit manis, segar","value_en":"Savory, a little sweet, fresh"},{"icon":"rice_bowl","label_id":"Disajikan","label_en":"Served with","value_id":"Lontong & kerupuk","value_en":"Lontong & crackers"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Gado-gado?","h_en":"What Is Gado-gado?","body_id":"Gado-gado adalah salad sayur khas Indonesia yang disiram bumbu kacang yang gurih. Isinya bermacam sayuran seperti kangkung, kacang panjang, kol, dan tauge, ditambah tahu, tempe, telur rebus, dan kentang. Karena penuh sayuran, gado-gado sering disebut salad-nya Indonesia. Makanan ini sehat sekaligus mengenyangkan.","body_en":"Gado-gado is an Indonesian vegetable salad covered with a savory peanut sauce. It is filled with many vegetables such as water spinach, long beans, cabbage, and bean sprouts, plus tofu, tempeh, boiled egg, and potato. Because it is full of vegetables, gado-gado is often called Indonesia's salad. This dish is healthy and filling at the same time."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Nama 'gado-gado' berasal dari kata 'gado' atau 'digado', yang dalam bahasa Jawa berarti makan lauk tanpa nasi. Makanan ini berkembang di Pulau Jawa dan menjadi sangat terkenal di Jakarta. Karena bahannya sederhana dan mudah didapat, gado-gado dengan cepat disukai banyak orang di seluruh Indonesia.","body_en":"The name 'gado-gado' comes from the word 'gado' or 'digado', which in Javanese means eating the side dishes without rice. This food grew up on the island of Java and became very famous in Jakarta. Because its ingredients are simple and easy to find, gado-gado quickly became loved by many people across Indonesia."},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Bahan & Cara Membuatnya","h_en":"Ingredients & How It's Made","body_id":"Sayuran seperti tauge, kacang panjang, dan kol direbus sebentar, sementara mentimun dipakai mentah. Sayuran lalu ditata bersama tahu, tempe, telur rebus, dan kentang. Bumbu kacang dibuat dengan menghaluskan kacang tanah goreng, bawang putih, cabai, gula merah, dan air jeruk. Bumbu itu disiramkan di atas sayuran, lalu ditaburi kerupuk atau emping.","body_en":"Vegetables like bean sprouts, long beans, and cabbage are boiled briefly, while cucumber is used raw. The vegetables are then arranged together with tofu, tempeh, boiled egg, and potato. The peanut sauce is made by grinding fried peanuts, garlic, chili, palm sugar, and lime juice. The sauce is poured over the vegetables, then topped with crackers or emping chips."},{"icon":"local_dining","h_id":"Rasa & Cara Menyantapnya","h_en":"Taste & How It's Eaten","body_id":"Gado-gado terasa gurih dan sedikit manis dari bumbu kacang, segar dari sayuran, dan renyah dari kerupuk. Semua isi diaduk rata supaya setiap suapan penuh rasa. Gado-gado bisa dimakan begitu saja, atau bersama lontong dan nasi agar lebih kenyang. Makanan ini enak disantap kapan saja, baik siang maupun malam.","body_en":"Gado-gado tastes savory and a little sweet from the peanut sauce, fresh from the vegetables, and crunchy from the crackers. Everything is mixed together so each bite is full of flavor. Gado-gado can be eaten on its own, or with lontong and rice to be more filling. This dish is tasty any time, whether at lunch or in the evening."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Makanan Saudara Gado-gado","h_en":"Gado-gado's Cousins","body_id":"Gado-gado punya banyak 'saudara' di Indonesia yang juga memakai bumbu kacang. Ada pecel dari Jawa Timur, lotek dan karedok dari Jawa Barat, serta rujak yang lebih manis dan pedas. Setiap daerah punya cara sendiri membuat bumbu kacangnya, sehingga rasanya berbeda-beda walau sama-sama lezat.","body_en":"Gado-gado has many 'cousins' in Indonesia that also use peanut sauce. There is pecel from East Java, lotek and karedok from West Java, and rujak which is sweeter and spicier. Each region has its own way of making the peanut sauce, so the taste is different even though they are all delicious."}],"facts":[{"id":"Nama 'gado-gado' artinya makan lauk saja tanpa nasi.","en":"The name 'gado-gado' means eating just the side dishes without rice."},{"id":"Gado-gado sering disebut sebagai salad khas Indonesia.","en":"Gado-gado is often called Indonesia's very own salad."},{"id":"Bumbu kacangnya dibuat dari kacang tanah yang dihaluskan dengan gula merah dan jeruk.","en":"Its peanut sauce is made from ground peanuts with palm sugar and lime."},{"id":"Di sebagian daerah, bumbu kacang diulek dadakan tepat sebelum disajikan.","en":"In some areas, the peanut sauce is ground fresh right before serving."},{"id":"Gado-gado penuh sayuran, jadi termasuk makanan yang sehat.","en":"Gado-gado is full of vegetables, so it is a healthy dish."},{"id":"Pecel, lotek, dan karedok adalah saudara gado-gado yang juga pakai bumbu kacang.","en":"Pecel, lotek, and karedok are gado-gado's cousins that also use peanut sauce."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Gado-gado","def_id":"Salad sayur Indonesia yang disiram bumbu kacang.","def_en":"An Indonesian vegetable salad drizzled with peanut sauce."},{"term":"Bumbu kacang","def_id":"Saus kental dan gurih dari kacang tanah yang dihaluskan.","def_en":"A thick, savory sauce made from ground peanuts."},{"term":"Tempe","def_id":"Makanan dari kedelai yang difermentasi dan dipadatkan, khas Indonesia.","def_en":"A food made from fermented, pressed soybeans, special to Indonesia."},{"term":"Tahu","def_id":"Makanan lembut berwarna putih yang dibuat dari sari kacang kedelai.","def_en":"A soft white food made from soybean milk."},{"term":"Tauge","def_id":"Tunas muda kacang hijau yang renyah, sering dipakai di gado-gado.","def_en":"Crunchy young sprouts of mung beans, often used in gado-gado."},{"term":"Kerupuk","def_id":"Camilan tipis dan renyah yang digoreng, sebagai pelengkap makanan.","def_en":"A thin, crispy fried snack served alongside food."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5822ba951dec9719.jpg","caption_id":"Sepiring gado-gado dengan bumbu kacang kental, telur rebus, tahu, kacang panjang, dan kerupuk.","caption_en":"A plate of gado-gado with thick peanut sauce, boiled egg, tofu, long beans, and crackers.","credit":"Takeaway","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b808de8db32fec33.jpg","caption_id":"Gado-gado lengkap dengan sayuran segar, mentimun, telur, dan emping yang renyah.","caption_en":"A full gado-gado with fresh vegetables, cucumber, egg, and crispy emping chips.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/825176f2be8f19e1.jpg","caption_id":"Gado-gado dalam wadah besar, dihias telur rebus dan irisan mentimun untuk disantap bersama.","caption_en":"Gado-gado in a big tray, topped with boiled eggs and cucumber slices to share.","credit":"Supardisahabu","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/73d86bcd259f22c6.jpg","caption_id":"Gado-gado diaduk di atas cobek batu agar sayuran tercampur rata dengan bumbu kacang.","caption_en":"Gado-gado being mixed on a stone mortar so the vegetables blend well with the peanut sauce.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gado-gado"},"kuliner_nasi_goreng":{"id":"kuliner_nasi_goreng","title_id":"Nasi Goreng","title_en":"Nasi Goreng (Fried Rice)","subtitle_id":"Nasi yang digoreng dengan kecap manis, makanan favorit sejuta orang Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"Rice fried with sweet soy sauce, a favorite food of millions in Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Indonesia (populer se-Asia)","value_en":"Indonesia (popular across Asia)"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Nasi, kecap manis, dan bumbu","value_en":"Rice, sweet soy sauce, and spices"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih dan sedikit manis","value_en":"Savory with a touch of sweet"},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Makanan utama sehari-hari","value_en":"An everyday main dish"},{"icon":"storefront","label_id":"Dijual","label_en":"Sold by","value_id":"Gerobak & warung pinggir jalan","value_en":"Carts and roadside stalls"}],"sections":[{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Apa Itu Nasi Goreng?","h_en":"What Is Nasi Goreng?","body_id":"Nasi goreng adalah nasi yang digoreng di dalam wajan bersama bumbu-bumbu. Di Indonesia, yang membuatnya istimewa adalah kecap manis, yang memberi warna cokelat dan rasa gurih-manis. Biasanya ditambah telur, sayuran, ayam, atau makanan laut. Nasi goreng adalah salah satu makanan yang paling disukai di Indonesia dan bisa dimakan pagi, siang, atau malam.","body_en":"Nasi goreng is rice fried in a pan together with seasonings. In Indonesia, what makes it special is sweet soy sauce, which gives it a brown color and a sweet-savory taste. It is usually mixed with egg, vegetables, chicken, or seafood. Nasi goreng is one of the most loved foods in Indonesia and can be eaten morning, noon, or night."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Nasi goreng populer di banyak negara Asia, tetapi versi Indonesia punya ciri khas sendiri karena memakai kecap manis. Dahulu nasi goreng sering dibuat dari nasi sisa kemarin agar tidak terbuang. Nasi yang sudah dingin justru lebih enak digoreng karena tidak lembek. Dari kebiasaan hemat inilah lahir banyak sekali ragam nasi goreng.","body_en":"Nasi goreng is popular in many Asian countries, but the Indonesian version has its own character because it uses sweet soy sauce. Long ago, nasi goreng was often made from yesterday's leftover rice so it would not be wasted. Cold rice is actually better for frying because it does not get mushy. From this thrifty habit, many kinds of nasi goreng were born."},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Bagaimana Dimasak?","h_en":"How Is It Cooked?","body_id":"Membuat nasi goreng cukup cepat. Pertama, bawang putih dan bawang merah ditumis sampai harum. Lalu telur diorak-arik, ditambah ayam atau sayuran. Setelah itu nasi dimasukkan dan diaduk cepat dengan kecap manis dan sedikit garam. Semua diaduk di atas api besar sampai panas merata dan wangi. Nasi goreng pun siap dihidangkan selagi hangat.","body_en":"Making nasi goreng is quite fast. First, garlic and shallots are stir-fried until fragrant. Then an egg is scrambled in, with chicken or vegetables added. After that the rice goes in and is stirred quickly with sweet soy sauce and a little salt. Everything is tossed over high heat until it is evenly hot and smells wonderful. The nasi goreng is then ready to serve while warm."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Banyak Sekali Ragamnya","h_en":"So Many Kinds","body_id":"Hampir setiap daerah di Indonesia punya nasi goreng sendiri. Ada nasi goreng kampung, nasi goreng seafood, dan nasi goreng ikan asin. Ada juga nasi goreng Jawa yang gurih, dan di Jawa Timur ada nasi goreng merah yang memakai saus tomat, bukan kecap. Jadi nasi goreng bisa berbeda rasa dan warna di setiap tempat.","body_en":"Almost every region in Indonesia has its own nasi goreng. There is village nasi goreng, seafood nasi goreng, and salted-fish nasi goreng. There is also savory Javanese nasi goreng, and in East Java there is red nasi goreng that uses tomato sauce instead of soy sauce. So nasi goreng can taste and look different in each place."},{"icon":"storefront","h_id":"Jajanan Kaki Lima","h_en":"Street-Food Favorite","body_id":"Di kota-kota Indonesia, penjual nasi goreng sering berkeliling membawa gerobak. Pada malam hari mereka berhenti di jalan dan memasak langsung di tempat. Suara sendok yang dipukulkan ke wajan menjadi tanda bahwa tukang nasi goreng sudah datang. Nasi goreng biasa disajikan dengan telur ceplok, kerupuk, acar, dan irisan timun.","body_en":"In Indonesian cities, nasi goreng sellers often roam around pushing a cart. At night they stop along the street and cook right on the spot. The sound of a spoon tapping the pan is a sign that the nasi goreng seller has arrived. Nasi goreng is usually served with a fried egg, crackers, pickles, and slices of cucumber."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kecap manis adalah bahan yang membuat nasi goreng Indonesia berbeda.","en":"Sweet soy sauce is what makes Indonesian nasi goreng different."},{"id":"Nasi goreng paling enak dibuat dari nasi dingin sisa kemarin.","en":"Nasi goreng tastes best when made from cold, leftover rice."},{"id":"Penjual nasi goreng keliling memukul wajan agar orang tahu mereka datang.","en":"Roaming nasi goreng sellers tap the pan so people know they have arrived."},{"id":"Setiap daerah di Indonesia punya nasi goreng dengan rasa khasnya sendiri.","en":"Each region in Indonesia has nasi goreng with its own special taste."},{"id":"Nasi goreng sering ditemani telur ceplok, kerupuk, dan acar.","en":"Nasi goreng is often paired with a fried egg, crackers, and pickles."},{"id":"Nasi goreng terkenal sampai ke Belanda dan negara-negara tetangga.","en":"Nasi goreng is famous all the way to the Netherlands and neighboring countries."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Nasi goreng","def_id":"Nasi yang digoreng di wajan bersama bumbu, telur, dan lauk.","def_en":"Rice fried in a pan together with seasonings, egg, and toppings."},{"term":"Kecap manis","def_id":"Saus kedelai kental dan manis khas Indonesia, pemberi warna cokelat.","def_en":"A thick, sweet Indonesian soy sauce that gives a brown color."},{"term":"Menumis","def_id":"Menggoreng cepat dengan sedikit minyak sambil diaduk-aduk.","def_en":"To stir-fry quickly with a little oil while tossing the food."},{"term":"Telur ceplok","def_id":"Telur yang digoreng utuh dengan kuning di tengahnya.","def_en":"An egg fried whole with the yolk in the middle."},{"term":"Kerupuk","def_id":"Camilan tipis yang renyah, sering jadi teman makan nasi goreng.","def_en":"A thin, crunchy cracker often eaten alongside nasi goreng."},{"term":"Kaki lima","def_id":"Pedagang makanan di pinggir jalan, sering memakai gerobak.","def_en":"A street food vendor by the roadside, often using a cart."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5801720d4ba9466e.jpg","caption_id":"Nasi goreng merah dengan telur ceplok, kerupuk, ayam suwir, dan kol di atas daun pisang.","caption_en":"Reddish nasi goreng with a fried egg, cracker, shredded chicken, and cabbage on a banana leaf.","credit":"Crisco 1492","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/18f7e40acb18e954.jpg","caption_id":"Nasi goreng kecap berwarna cokelat dengan acar timun dan wortel di piring putih.","caption_en":"Brown soy-sauce nasi goreng with cucumber and carrot pickles on a white plate.","credit":"Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2437def0744ad284.jpg","caption_id":"Nasi goreng dalam mangkuk cokelat, ditaburi gulungan telur dadar yang diiris tipis.","caption_en":"Nasi goreng in a brown bowl, topped with thin slices of rolled omelette.","credit":"Luca Nebuloni","license":"CC BY 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nasi_goreng"},"kuliner_rendang":{"id":"kuliner_rendang","title_id":"Rendang","title_en":"Rendang","subtitle_id":"Daging berbumbu Minangkabau yang dimasak berjam-jam sampai empuk dan hitam!","subtitle_en":"Minangkabau spiced meat slow-cooked for hours until tender and dark!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Minangkabau, Sumatra Barat","value_en":"Minangkabau, West Sumatra"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Daging sapi, santan, dan rempah","value_en":"Beef, coconut milk, and spices"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, pedas, dan kaya rempah","value_en":"Savory, spicy, and rich with spices"},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Lauk untuk teman nasi","value_en":"A side dish to go with rice"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Lama masak","label_en":"Cooking time","value_id":"Sekitar 4-5 jam","value_en":"About 4-5 hours"}],"sections":[{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Apa Itu Rendang?","h_en":"What Is Rendang?","body_id":"Rendang adalah lauk daging berbumbu yang berasal dari Minangkabau, Sumatra Barat. Daging dimasak pelan-pelan dengan santan dan banyak rempah sampai bumbunya meresap dan berwarna cokelat kehitaman. Rasanya gurih, sedikit pedas, dan sangat kaya. Rendang biasa dimakan bersama nasi hangat dan menjadi salah satu makanan kebanggaan Indonesia.","body_en":"Rendang is a spiced meat dish from Minangkabau in West Sumatra. The meat is cooked slowly with coconut milk and many spices until the flavor soaks in and it turns dark brown. It tastes savory, a little spicy, and very rich. Rendang is usually eaten with warm rice and is one of Indonesia's most beloved foods."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Rendang lahir di tanah Minangkabau. Dahulu orang Minang gemar merantau, yaitu pergi jauh ke daerah lain. Mereka butuh bekal makanan yang awet dan tahan lama. Karena rendang dimasak sampai kering, ia bisa bertahan berminggu-minggu tanpa basi. Maka rendang menjadi bekal sempurna untuk perjalanan jauh, dan kini terkenal sampai ke luar negeri.","body_en":"Rendang was born in the Minangkabau land. Long ago the Minang people loved to merantau, which means to travel far to other regions. They needed food supplies that would last a long time. Because rendang is cooked until dry, it can keep for weeks without spoiling. So rendang became the perfect food to carry on long journeys, and now it is famous even in other countries."},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Bagaimana Dimasak?","h_en":"How Is It Cooked?","body_id":"Memasak rendang butuh kesabaran. Mula-mula santan dan bumbu dimasak bersama daging sampai mendidih, warnanya masih kuning. Lalu api dikecilkan dan terus diaduk pelan-pelan. Lama-kelamaan santan mengental menjadi cokelat keemasan, disebut kalio. Kalau diteruskan sampai kering dan hitam, barulah jadi rendang. Semua proses ini bisa memakan waktu empat sampai lima jam!","body_en":"Cooking rendang takes patience. First the coconut milk and spices are cooked with the meat until it boils, and it is still yellow. Then the heat is lowered and it is stirred slowly. Little by little the coconut milk thickens into golden brown, called kalio. If you keep going until it is dry and dark, only then does it become rendang. All of this can take four to five hours!"},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Bumbu Ajaib Rendang","h_en":"Rendang's Magic Spices","body_id":"Rendang memakai banyak rempah seperti cabai, serai, lengkuas, kunyit, jahe, bawang putih, dan bawang merah. Bumbu-bumbu ini bukan hanya membuat rasanya enak, tetapi juga bekerja seperti pengawet alami yang melawan kuman. Itulah rahasianya kenapa rendang bisa tahan lama. Karena gizinya terjaga, rendang sering dikirim sebagai bantuan makanan untuk korban bencana.","body_en":"Rendang uses many spices such as chili, lemongrass, galangal, turmeric, ginger, garlic, and shallots. These spices not only make it delicious but also work like a natural preserver that fights germs. That is the secret of why rendang lasts so long. Because it stays nutritious, rendang is often sent as food aid for disaster victims."},{"icon":"emoji_events","h_id":"Rendang Juara Dunia","h_en":"World-Champion Rendang","body_id":"Pada tahun 2011, rendang dipilih sebagai makanan terlezat nomor satu di dunia oleh CNN International. Pada tahun 2018, rendang resmi menjadi salah satu dari lima makanan nasional Indonesia. Bagi masyarakat Minangkabau, rendang juga punya makna khusus dan selalu hadir di acara adat, pesta, dan saat menyambut tamu istimewa.","body_en":"In 2011, rendang was chosen as the number one most delicious food in the world by CNN International. In 2018, rendang officially became one of Indonesia's five national dishes. For the Minangkabau people, rendang also has a special meaning and is always served at traditional ceremonies, feasts, and when welcoming honored guests."}],"facts":[{"id":"Pada 2011, rendang dinobatkan sebagai makanan terlezat di dunia oleh CNN.","en":"In 2011, rendang was named the most delicious food in the world by CNN."},{"id":"Rendang dimasak sangat lama, sekitar empat sampai lima jam.","en":"Rendang is cooked for a very long time, about four to five hours."},{"id":"Karena dimasak sampai kering, rendang bisa tahan berminggu-minggu.","en":"Because it is cooked until dry, rendang can last for weeks."},{"id":"Rempah dalam rendang bekerja seperti pengawet alami melawan kuman.","en":"The spices in rendang work like a natural preserver against germs."},{"id":"Dahulu rendang dibuat dari daging rusa sebelum memakai daging sapi.","en":"Long ago rendang was made from deer meat before using beef."},{"id":"Rendang adalah salah satu dari lima makanan nasional Indonesia.","en":"Rendang is one of Indonesia's five national dishes."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Rendang","def_id":"Lauk daging Minangkabau yang dimasak lama dengan santan dan rempah.","def_en":"A Minangkabau meat dish cooked slowly with coconut milk and spices."},{"term":"Santan","def_id":"Cairan putih dari kelapa parut yang membuat masakan gurih.","def_en":"The white liquid from grated coconut that makes food creamy and savory."},{"term":"Rempah","def_id":"Bumbu dari tumbuhan seperti cabai, jahe, dan kunyit yang menambah rasa.","def_en":"Seasonings from plants such as chili, ginger, and turmeric that add flavor."},{"term":"Kalio","def_id":"Rendang setengah jadi yang masih basah dan berwarna cokelat keemasan.","def_en":"Half-cooked rendang that is still moist and golden brown."},{"term":"Merantau","def_id":"Pergi jauh meninggalkan kampung halaman, kebiasaan orang Minang.","def_en":"To travel far away from one's home village, a Minangkabau custom."},{"term":"Lauk","def_id":"Makanan pendamping yang dimakan bersama nasi.","def_en":"A side dish eaten together with rice."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2d2d80ccc29f7c5b.jpg","caption_id":"Rendang sapi yang sudah matang, berwarna cokelat hitam, disajikan dengan ketupat.","caption_en":"Finished beef rendang, dark brown in color, served with woven rice cakes.","credit":"Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9994fb623f08aa04.jpg","caption_id":"Ibu-ibu berpakaian adat Minang memasak rendang dalam kuali besar di depan Rumah Gadang.","caption_en":"Women in Minangkabau dress cook rendang in big pots in front of a Rumah Gadang.","credit":"Government of West Sumatra Province","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e877670c14e66af2.jpg","caption_id":"Tahap awal: santan kuning mendidih bersama daging dan bumbu di dalam kuali.","caption_en":"Early stage: yellow coconut milk boils together with the meat and spices in the pan.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b3dfb3a7a76ee4a9.jpg","caption_id":"Tahap tengah: santan mulai mengental dan berwarna oranye kecokelatan, disebut kalio.","caption_en":"Middle stage: the coconut milk thickens and turns orange-brown, called kalio.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/04d8bc802340047b.jpg","caption_id":"Tahap akhir: bumbu mengering dan menghitam, daging pun siap menjadi rendang.","caption_en":"Final stage: the spices dry and darken, and the meat is ready to become rendang.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rendang"},"kuliner_sate":{"id":"kuliner_sate","title_id":"Sate","title_en":"Satay","subtitle_id":"Daging ditusuk dan dibakar di atas bara, disiram bumbu kacang!","subtitle_en":"Skewered meat grilled over coals, drizzled with peanut sauce!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jawa, Indonesia (Ponorogo)","value_en":"Java, Indonesia (Ponorogo)"},{"icon":"kebab_dining","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Daging tusuk yang dibakar","value_en":"Grilled meat on skewers"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Ayam, kambing, atau sapi","value_en":"Chicken, goat, or beef"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, manis, sedikit berasap","value_en":"Savory, sweet, a little smoky"},{"icon":"rice_bowl","label_id":"Disajikan","label_en":"Served with","value_id":"Bumbu kacang, nasi atau lontong","value_en":"Peanut sauce, rice or lontong"}],"sections":[{"icon":"kebab_dining","h_id":"Apa Itu Sate?","h_en":"What Is Satay?","body_id":"Sate adalah makanan dari potongan daging kecil yang ditusuk dengan lidi atau tusuk bambu, lalu dibakar di atas bara arang sampai matang dan harum. Setelah matang, sate biasanya disiram bumbu kacang atau kecap manis. Sate sangat terkenal di seluruh Indonesia dan dianggap salah satu masakan nasional kita.","body_en":"Satay is a food made from small pieces of meat threaded onto thin sticks or bamboo skewers, then grilled over hot charcoal until cooked and fragrant. Once done, satay is usually drizzled with peanut sauce or sweet soy sauce. Satay is famous all over Indonesia and is seen as one of our national dishes."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Sate berasal dari Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Banyak orang percaya kota asalnya adalah Ponorogo di Jawa Timur. Dari Jawa, sate menyebar ke seluruh Nusantara, lalu ke negara tetangga seperti Malaysia, Singapura, dan Thailand. Sate bahkan terkenal sampai ke Belanda. Setiap daerah membuat sate dengan resep khasnya sendiri.","body_en":"Satay comes from the island of Java, Indonesia. Many people believe its home town is Ponorogo in East Java. From Java, satay spread across the whole archipelago, then to neighboring countries like Malaysia, Singapore, and Thailand. Satay even became famous as far away as the Netherlands. Each region makes satay with its own special recipe."},{"icon":"local_fire_department","h_id":"Bahan & Cara Membuatnya","h_en":"Ingredients & How It's Made","body_id":"Daging untuk sate bisa berupa ayam, kambing, sapi, atau yang lain. Daging dipotong kecil, diberi bumbu seperti kunyit atau kecap manis, lalu ditusuk satu per satu. Tusukan daging itu dibakar di atas arang sambil dikipas, supaya matang merata dan keluar bau harum yang menggoda. Asap dari bara inilah yang membuat sate terasa istimewa.","body_en":"The meat for satay can be chicken, goat, beef, or others. The meat is cut into small pieces, seasoned with spices like turmeric or sweet soy sauce, then threaded onto skewers one by one. The skewers are grilled over charcoal while being fanned, so they cook evenly and give off a tempting aroma. The smoke from the coals is what makes satay taste so special."},{"icon":"rice_bowl","h_id":"Rasa & Cara Menyantapnya","h_en":"Taste & How It's Eaten","body_id":"Sate terasa gurih, sedikit manis, dan harum oleh asap arang. Paling enak disantap saat masih hangat, dengan siraman bumbu kacang yang kental atau kecap manis. Biasanya sate dimakan bersama nasi hangat atau lontong, ditambah irisan bawang merah, mentimun, dan kadang sambal. Kita bisa menemukan sate dari gerobak keliling sampai restoran besar.","body_en":"Satay tastes savory, a little sweet, and smells wonderful from the charcoal smoke. It is best enjoyed while still warm, with thick peanut sauce or sweet soy sauce poured over it. Satay is usually eaten with warm rice or lontong (rice cake), plus slices of shallot, cucumber, and sometimes chili sauce. You can find satay everywhere, from pushcart sellers to big restaurants."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Aneka Sate Nusantara","h_en":"Many Kinds of Satay","body_id":"Indonesia punya koleksi jenis sate paling banyak di dunia! Ada Sate Ponorogo dengan daging ayam yang dipotong memanjang, Sate Madura dengan bumbu kacang manis, Sate Padang dengan kuah kuning kental, dan Sate Lilit dari Bali yang dililitkan pada batang serai. Setiap sate punya rasa dan cerita yang berbeda.","body_en":"Indonesia has the biggest collection of satay types in the world! There is Satay Ponorogo with long-sliced chicken, Satay Madura with sweet peanut sauce, Satay Padang with a thick yellow gravy, and Satay Lilit from Bali that is wrapped around lemongrass sticks. Each satay has its own flavor and story."}],"facts":[{"id":"Sate dipilih sebagai peringkat ke-14 dalam daftar '50 Makanan Terlezat di Dunia' versi CNN.","en":"Satay was ranked 14th on CNN's list of the 'World's 50 Most Delicious Foods'."},{"id":"Hampir semua jenis daging bisa dibuat sate, bahkan udang dan telur puyuh!","en":"Almost any kind of meat can be made into satay, even shrimp and quail eggs!"},{"id":"Indonesia punya jenis sate paling banyak di dunia, lebih dari 50 macam.","en":"Indonesia has the most types of satay in the world, more than 50 kinds."},{"id":"Pada Sate Ponorogo, setiap tusuk berisi satu potong daging ayam yang diiris panjang.","en":"In Satay Ponorogo, each skewer holds one piece of chicken sliced long."},{"id":"Kantor gubernur di Bandung dijuluki 'Gedung Sate' karena hiasan atapnya mirip tusuk sate.","en":"A government building in Bandung is nicknamed 'Gedung Sate' because its roof ornament looks like a satay skewer."},{"id":"Banyak makanan di dunia mirip sate, seperti yakitori dari Jepang dan kebab dari Turki.","en":"Many foods around the world are like satay, such as yakitori from Japan and kebab from Turkey."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Sate","def_id":"Potongan daging yang ditusuk dan dibakar di atas bara arang.","def_en":"Pieces of meat threaded on a skewer and grilled over charcoal."},{"term":"Tusuk sate","def_id":"Lidi atau batang bambu tipis tempat daging ditusuk.","def_en":"A thin stick or bamboo skewer that the meat is threaded onto."},{"term":"Bumbu kacang","def_id":"Saus kental dan gurih yang dibuat dari kacang tanah yang dihaluskan.","def_en":"A thick, savory sauce made from ground peanuts."},{"term":"Bara arang","def_id":"Potongan arang yang membara dan panas, dipakai untuk membakar sate.","def_en":"Glowing, hot pieces of charcoal used to grill the satay."},{"term":"Lontong","def_id":"Nasi yang dipadatkan dan dibungkus daun, dipotong untuk teman makan sate.","def_en":"Rice pressed and wrapped in leaves, sliced to eat alongside satay."},{"term":"Kecap manis","def_id":"Saus kedelai berwarna cokelat tua yang manis dan kental, khas Indonesia.","def_en":"A dark, sweet, thick soybean sauce that is special to Indonesia."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ab984e0f411917f6.jpg","caption_id":"Sate ayam Ponorogo di atas bumbu kacang, dengan irisan bawang merah dan jeruk nipis.","caption_en":"Ponorogo chicken satay over peanut sauce, with sliced shallots and lime.","credit":"Gunawan Kartapranata","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sate"},"kuliner_soto_nusantara":{"id":"kuliner_soto_nusantara","title_id":"Soto Nusantara","title_en":"Soto of the Archipelago","subtitle_id":"Sup berkuah hangat dengan ratusan resep dari seluruh Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"A warm soupy dish with hundreds of recipes from all over Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Pesisir utara Jawa Tengah","value_en":"North coast of Central Java"},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Sup berkuah dari kaldu","value_en":"A soup made from broth"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Kaldu daging ayam atau sapi & sayur","value_en":"Chicken or beef broth & vegetables"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, hangat, harum rempah","value_en":"Savory, warm, fragrant with spices"},{"icon":"rice_bowl","label_id":"Disajikan","label_en":"Served with","value_id":"Nasi, lontong, atau bihun","value_en":"Rice, lontong, or rice vermicelli"}],"sections":[{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Apa Itu Soto?","h_en":"What Is Soto?","body_id":"Soto adalah makanan berkuah khas Indonesia yang mirip sup. Kuahnya dibuat dari kaldu daging yang dimasak bersama rempah-rempah sampai harum, lalu diisi potongan daging dan sayuran. Daging yang paling sering dipakai adalah ayam dan sapi. Soto disajikan hangat dan cocok dimakan kapan saja, terutama saat cuaca dingin.","body_en":"Soto is an Indonesian soupy dish that is like a soup. Its broth is made from meat stock cooked with spices until fragrant, then filled with pieces of meat and vegetables. The meats most often used are chicken and beef. Soto is served warm and is great to eat any time, especially when the weather is cool."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Soto banyak ditemukan pertama kali di kota-kota pelabuhan di pesisir utara Jawa Tengah, seperti Tegal, Pekalongan, Semarang, dan Kudus. Karena ramai oleh pedagang dari berbagai bangsa, resep soto pun ikut menyebar dan berubah-ubah. Dari sana, soto berkembang ke seluruh Nusantara dan setiap daerah membuat versinya sendiri.","body_en":"Soto was first found in port cities on the north coast of Central Java, such as Tegal, Pekalongan, Semarang, and Kudus. Because these cities were busy with traders from many nations, soto recipes spread and changed along the way. From there, soto grew across the whole archipelago and each region made its own version."},{"icon":"local_fire_department","h_id":"Bahan & Cara Membuatnya","h_en":"Ingredients & How It's Made","body_id":"Untuk membuat soto, daging direbus lama hingga menghasilkan kaldu yang gurih. Bumbu seperti kunyit, jahe, serai, bawang putih, dan bawang merah dihaluskan, ditumis, lalu dimasukkan ke dalam kuah. Daging yang sudah empuk disuwir atau dipotong kecil. Saat disajikan, soto dituang di atas nasi atau bihun dan ditaburi bawang goreng serta seledri.","body_en":"To make soto, the meat is boiled for a long time to create a savory broth. Spices like turmeric, ginger, lemongrass, garlic, and shallots are ground, fried, then added to the broth. The tender meat is shredded or cut small. When served, soto is poured over rice or vermicelli and topped with fried shallots and celery."},{"icon":"rice_bowl","h_id":"Rasa & Cara Menyantapnya","h_en":"Taste & How It's Eaten","body_id":"Soto terasa gurih dan hangat, dengan aroma rempah yang harum. Banyak orang menambahkan perasan jeruk nipis, sambal, dan kecap supaya rasanya makin segar dan sesuai selera. Soto biasa dimakan bersama nasi, lontong, atau bihun, ditambah pelengkap seperti kerupuk, perkedel, telur, dan emping yang renyah.","body_en":"Soto tastes savory and warm, with a fragrant smell of spices. Many people add a squeeze of lime, chili sauce, and sweet soy sauce to make it fresher and just right for their taste. Soto is usually eaten with rice, lontong, or vermicelli, plus sides like crackers, potato patties, egg, and crispy emping chips."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Soto dari Berbagai Daerah","h_en":"Soto from Many Regions","body_id":"Hampir setiap daerah di Indonesia punya soto sendiri! Soto Ayam Lamongan berkuah kuning dan ditaburi koya, Soto Betawi dari Jakarta memakai santan atau susu sehingga gurih, Soto Banjar dari Kalimantan harum oleh kayu manis dan cengkih, sedangkan Coto Makassar dari Sulawesi berkuah kental dan kaya rempah. Karena begitu banyak ragamnya, soto disebut Soto Nusantara.","body_en":"Almost every region in Indonesia has its own soto! Soto Ayam Lamongan has a yellow broth sprinkled with koya, Soto Betawi from Jakarta uses coconut milk or dairy to make it creamy, Soto Banjar from Kalimantan is fragrant with cinnamon and cloves, while Coto Makassar from Sulawesi has a thick, spice-rich broth. Because there are so many kinds, soto is called Soto Nusantara, the soto of the archipelago."}],"facts":[{"id":"Hampir setiap kota di Indonesia punya jenis soto khasnya sendiri.","en":"Almost every city in Indonesia has its own special kind of soto."},{"id":"Soto punya banyak nama daerah, seperti sroto, sauto, tauto, dan coto.","en":"Soto has many local names, such as sroto, sauto, tauto, and coto."},{"id":"Soto Betawi dibuat gurih dengan santan atau susu.","en":"Soto Betawi is made creamy with coconut milk or dairy."},{"id":"Warna kuning pada banyak soto berasal dari kunyit.","en":"The yellow color in many sotos comes from turmeric."},{"id":"Koya, taburan dari kerupuk dan bawang putih, membuat Soto Lamongan makin gurih.","en":"Koya, a topping of crushed crackers and garlic, makes Soto Lamongan even tastier."},{"id":"Soto paling enak disantap selagi hangat, apalagi saat hujan.","en":"Soto is best enjoyed while warm, especially when it rains."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Soto","def_id":"Makanan berkuah khas Indonesia yang dibuat dari kaldu daging dan rempah.","def_en":"An Indonesian soupy dish made from meat broth and spices."},{"term":"Kaldu","def_id":"Air rebusan daging atau tulang yang gurih, menjadi dasar kuah soto.","def_en":"The savory liquid from boiling meat or bones, used as the base of soto broth."},{"term":"Kunyit","def_id":"Rempah berwarna kuning yang membuat kuah soto berwarna dan harum.","def_en":"A yellow spice that gives soto broth its color and aroma."},{"term":"Bawang goreng","def_id":"Irisan bawang merah yang digoreng renyah dan ditaburkan di atas soto.","def_en":"Slices of shallot fried until crispy and sprinkled on top of soto."},{"term":"Koya","def_id":"Taburan gurih dari kerupuk dan bawang putih yang dihaluskan.","def_en":"A savory topping of crackers and garlic ground together."},{"term":"Lontong","def_id":"Nasi yang dipadatkan dan dibungkus daun, sering dimakan dengan soto.","def_en":"Rice pressed and wrapped in leaves, often eaten with soto."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/068a2245a5a30674.jpg","caption_id":"Soto ayam berkuah kuning dengan suwiran ayam, bawang goreng, emping, dan irisan tomat.","caption_en":"Chicken soto with a yellow broth, shredded chicken, fried shallots, emping chips, and sliced tomato.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a2dbe61a12196d14.jpg","caption_id":"Soto Banjar dari Kalimantan dengan perasan jeruk nipis, suwiran ayam, dan perkedel.","caption_en":"Soto Banjar from Kalimantan with a squeeze of lime, shredded chicken, and a potato patty.","credit":"Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soto"},"lingkungan_hutan_tropis":{"id":"lingkungan_hutan_tropis","title_id":"Hutan Hujan Tropis","title_en":"Tropical Rainforest","subtitle_id":"Hutan hijau yang selalu basah, paru-paru dunia","subtitle_en":"Always-wet green forest, the lungs of the world","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Di daerah hangat dekat garis khatulistiwa","value_en":"Warm places near the equator"},{"icon":"rainy","label_id":"Iklim","label_en":"Climate","value_id":"Panas dan lembap, dengan hujan yang banyak","value_en":"Hot and humid, with lots of rain"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Penghuni","label_en":"Life","value_id":"Rumah bagi separuh jenis hewan dan tumbuhan dunia","value_en":"Home to half the world's animals and plants"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Manfaat","label_en":"Benefit","value_id":"\"Paru-paru dunia\", membuat udara bersih dan oksigen","value_en":"\"Lungs of the world\", makes clean air and oxygen"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Di Indonesia","label_en":"In Indonesia","value_id":"Sumatra, Kalimantan, Sulawesi, Maluku, dan Papua","value_en":"Sumatra, Kalimantan, Sulawesi, Maluku, and Papua"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Cara Menjaga","label_en":"How to Help","value_id":"Menanam pohon dan tidak menebang sembarangan","value_en":"Plant trees and don't cut them carelessly"}],"sections":[{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Apa Itu Hutan Hujan Tropis?","h_en":"What Is a Tropical Rainforest?","body_id":"Hutan hujan tropis adalah hutan yang selalu basah dan lembap sepanjang tahun. Hutan ini tumbuh di daerah hangat dekat garis khatulistiwa, tempat matahari bersinar terang dan hujan turun hampir setiap hari. Pohon-pohonnya hijau terus tanpa musim gugur. Karena hujannya sangat banyak, hutan ini disebut hutan hujan!","body_en":"A tropical rainforest is a forest that stays wet and damp all year round. It grows in warm places near the equator, where the sun shines bright and rain falls almost every day. Its trees stay green without a falling-leaf season. Because it rains so much, this forest is called a rainforest!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Letaknya?","h_en":"Where Is It Found?","body_id":"Hutan hujan tropis ada di Asia, Afrika, Amerika Selatan, dan Kepulauan Pasifik. Indonesia sangat beruntung karena punya banyak hutan hujan! Kita bisa menemukannya di Sumatra, Kalimantan, sebagian Sulawesi, Maluku, dan Papua. Hutan-hutan ini tumbuh di dataran rendah sampai ke perbukitan yang sering tertutup awan dan kabut.","body_en":"Tropical rainforests are found in Asia, Africa, South America, and the Pacific Islands. Indonesia is very lucky to have many rainforests! We can find them in Sumatra, Kalimantan, part of Sulawesi, Maluku, and Papua. These forests grow from the lowlands up to the hills, which are often covered in clouds and mist."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Pohon Berlapis-lapis","h_en":"Trees in Many Layers","body_id":"Di hutan hujan tropis, pohon-pohon tumbuh berlapis-lapis seperti gedung bertingkat. Pohon yang paling tinggi bisa mencapai 45 meter, lebih tinggi dari rumah berlantai sepuluh! Di bagian atas ada kanopi, yaitu atap hijau dari dedaunan yang rapat. Di lapisan paling bawah, lantai hutan agak gelap karena cahaya matahari sulit menembusnya.","body_en":"In a tropical rainforest, the trees grow in layers like a tall building. The tallest trees can reach 45 meters, higher than a ten-story house! At the top is the canopy, a green roof of thick leaves. On the lowest level, the forest floor is a bit dark because sunlight has trouble getting through."},{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Rumah Banyak Makhluk Hidup","h_en":"Home to Many Living Things","body_id":"Hutan hujan tropis adalah rumah bagi separuh dari semua jenis hewan dan tumbuhan di seluruh dunia! Orangutan berayun di antara pohon, burung-burung berkicau, dan ribuan jenis serangga sibuk bekerja. Banyak bunga, anggrek, dan lumut menempel di dahan. Hutan ini seperti taman raksasa yang penuh kejutan.","body_en":"The tropical rainforest is home to half of all the kinds of animals and plants in the whole world! Orangutans swing between the trees, birds sing, and thousands of kinds of insects are busy at work. Many flowers, orchids, and mosses cling to the branches. This forest is like a giant garden full of surprises."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Paru-paru Dunia, Yuk Kita Jaga!","h_en":"Lungs of the World, Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Hutan hujan tropis dijuluki \"paru-paru dunia\" karena pohon-pohonnya membuat udara bersih dan oksigen yang kita hirup. Hutan ini juga jadi \"apotek\" alam, karena banyak obat berasal dari tumbuhannya. Kita bisa membantu dengan menanam pohon, hemat kertas, dan menyayangi hewan. Setiap tindakan kecilmu sangat berarti untuk bumi!","body_en":"The tropical rainforest is nicknamed the \"lungs of the world\" because its trees make the clean air and oxygen we breathe. It is also nature's \"pharmacy\", because many medicines come from its plants. We can help by planting trees, saving paper, and loving animals. Every small thing you do means a lot to the Earth!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Hutan hujan tropis adalah rumah bagi separuh jenis makhluk hidup di dunia!","en":"Tropical rainforests are home to half the world's living things!"},{"id":"Pohon tertingginya bisa mencapai 45 meter, setinggi gedung sepuluh lantai.","en":"Its tallest trees can reach 45 meters, as tall as a ten-story building."},{"id":"Hampir seperempat obat modern berasal dari tumbuhan hutan hujan.","en":"Almost a quarter of modern medicines come from rainforest plants."},{"id":"Di hutan ini hujan turun hampir setiap hari sepanjang tahun.","en":"In this forest, rain falls almost every day all year long."},{"id":"Indonesia punya hutan hujan di Sumatra, Kalimantan, dan Papua.","en":"Indonesia has rainforests in Sumatra, Kalimantan, and Papua."},{"id":"Pohon-pohonnya menghasilkan oksigen yang kita hirup setiap hari.","en":"Its trees make the oxygen we breathe every day."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Khatulistiwa","def_id":"Garis khayal di tengah bumi tempat daerah paling panas berada.","def_en":"An imaginary line around the middle of the Earth where the hottest places are."},{"term":"Kanopi","def_id":"Atap hijau hutan yang dibentuk oleh dedaunan pohon-pohon tinggi.","def_en":"The green roof of the forest made by the leaves of tall trees."},{"term":"Oksigen","def_id":"Gas dari tumbuhan yang kita hirup agar bisa bernapas dan hidup.","def_en":"A gas from plants that we breathe in so we can live."},{"term":"Lembap","def_id":"Keadaan udara yang basah dan terasa banyak airnya.","def_en":"Air that is damp and feels full of moisture."},{"term":"Keanekaragaman hayati","def_id":"Banyaknya jenis tumbuhan dan hewan yang hidup di satu tempat.","def_en":"The many different kinds of plants and animals living in one place."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c31a8589fe0d2d82.jpg","caption_id":"Hutan hujan tropis yang lebat di Pegunungan Mugajah, Aceh, tertutup sentuhan awan dan kabut.","caption_en":"A lush tropical rainforest in the Mugajah Mountains, Aceh, touched by clouds and mist.","credit":"Hugo Rio Aditya","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1626c77020c45013.jpg","caption_id":"Induk orangutan Sumatra sedang memberi makan anaknya sambil bergantung di pohon hutan.","caption_en":"A Sumatran orangutan mother feeds her baby while hanging from a forest tree.","credit":"Pratechno","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/91f6ce7261833523.jpg","caption_id":"Dilihat dari atas, kanopi hijau hutan hujan Amazon terbentang sejauh mata memandang.","caption_en":"Seen from above, the green canopy of the Amazon rainforest stretches as far as the eye can see.","credit":"The original uploader was בן הטבע at Hebrew Wikipedia.","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cf38805f3b0c5bb7.jpg","caption_id":"Pohon-pohon tinggi hutan hujan asli di Khao Sok, Thailand, berdiri di depan perbukitan berkabut.","caption_en":"Tall trees of the primary rainforest in Khao Sok, Thailand, stand before misty hills.","credit":"Vyacheslav Argenberg","license":"CC BY 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8c4cbed287ef6c23.jpg","caption_id":"Sungai cokelat mengalir tenang melewati tepi hutan hujan yang hijau di Peru.","caption_en":"A brown river flows calmly past the green edge of the rainforest in Peru.","credit":"Roosevelt Garcia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hutan_hujan_tropika"},"lingkungan_perubahan_iklim":{"id":"lingkungan_perubahan_iklim","title_id":"Perubahan Iklim","title_en":"Climate Change","subtitle_id":"Bumi makin hangat, dan kita bisa membantunya","subtitle_en":"The Earth is getting warmer, and we can help it","data_card":[{"icon":"factory","label_id":"Penyebab","label_en":"Cause","value_id":"Terlalu banyak gas rumah kaca di udara","value_en":"Too many greenhouse gases in the air"},{"icon":"thermostat","label_id":"Dampak","label_en":"Effects","value_id":"Bumi makin panas dan cuaca jadi tidak menentu","value_en":"The Earth gets hotter and weather gets unpredictable"},{"icon":"ac_unit","label_id":"Tanda","label_en":"Signs","value_id":"Es di kutub mencair dan air laut naik","value_en":"Polar ice melts and the sea rises"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Penolong","label_en":"Helpers","value_id":"Pohon dan energi bersih dari matahari serta angin","value_en":"Trees and clean energy from sun and wind"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Yang Bisa Kita Lakukan","label_en":"What We Can Do","value_id":"Hemat energi, tanam pohon, dan kurangi sampah","value_en":"Save energy, plant trees, and make less waste"}],"sections":[{"icon":"thermostat","h_id":"Apa Itu Perubahan Iklim?","h_en":"What Is Climate Change?","body_id":"Iklim adalah pola cuaca di suatu tempat selama waktu yang sangat lama. Perubahan iklim berarti pola cuaca itu perlahan berubah, dan saat ini bumi kita menjadi semakin hangat. Perubahan ini terjadi pelan-pelan selama bertahun-tahun. Kabar baiknya, banyak orang di seluruh dunia bekerja sama untuk membantu bumi tetap sehat.","body_en":"Climate is the pattern of weather in a place over a very long time. Climate change means that pattern is slowly changing, and right now our Earth is getting warmer. This change happens slowly over many years. The good news is that many people around the world are working together to help keep the Earth healthy."},{"icon":"factory","h_id":"Kenapa Bumi Makin Hangat?","h_en":"Why Is the Earth Getting Warmer?","body_id":"Di sekeliling bumi ada selimut udara yang menjaga kita tetap hangat. Selimut ini terbuat dari gas rumah kaca. Saat manusia membakar bahan bakar seperti bensin dan batu bara, selimut ini menjadi semakin tebal. Akibatnya, panas dari matahari lebih banyak tertahan, dan bumi pun menjadi lebih hangat dari biasanya.","body_en":"Around the Earth is a blanket of air that keeps us warm. This blanket is made of greenhouse gases. When people burn fuels like gasoline and coal, the blanket gets thicker. Because of this, more of the sun's heat is trapped, and the Earth becomes warmer than usual."},{"icon":"ac_unit","h_id":"Tanda-tanda di Sekitar Kita","h_en":"Signs Around Us","body_id":"Karena bumi makin hangat, es tebal di kutub utara dan selatan perlahan mencair, sehingga air laut naik sedikit demi sedikit. Cuaca juga jadi lebih sulit ditebak: kadang hujan sangat lebat, kadang panas yang panjang. Para ilmuwan mengamati tanda-tanda ini agar kita semua bisa bersiap dan saling menjaga.","body_en":"Because the Earth is getting warmer, the thick ice at the north and south poles is slowly melting, so the sea rises little by little. The weather also becomes harder to predict: sometimes very heavy rain, sometimes long heat. Scientists watch for these signs so we can all get ready and look after each other."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Penolong Bumi","h_en":"The Earth's Helpers","body_id":"Pohon adalah penolong hebat! Pohon menyerap gas rumah kaca dan memberi kita udara segar, jadi makin banyak pohon, makin baik. Manusia juga membuat energi bersih dari matahari, angin, dan air, yang tidak membuat udara kotor. Energi bersih ini bisa menyalakan lampu dan menggerakkan mobil tanpa mengganggu selimut udara bumi.","body_en":"Trees are great helpers! Trees soak up greenhouse gases and give us fresh air, so the more trees the better. People also make clean energy from the sun, wind, and water, which does not make the air dirty. This clean energy can light up our lamps and move our cars without disturbing the Earth's blanket of air."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Aksi Kecil dari Kita","h_en":"Small Actions from Us","body_id":"Kamu bisa ikut membantu bumi setiap hari! Matikan lampu dan keran air saat tidak dipakai, jalan kaki atau bersepeda untuk jarak dekat, dan kurangi sampah. Ajak temanmu menanam pohon dan menyayangi alam. Kalau kita semua melakukan hal-hal baik bersama-sama, bumi akan menjadi tempat yang sejuk dan nyaman untuk semua.","body_en":"You can help the Earth every day! Turn off lights and taps when they are not in use, walk or bike for short trips, and make less waste. Invite your friends to plant trees and love nature. If we all do good things together, the Earth will become a cool and comfortable home for everyone."}],"facts":[{"id":"Bumi punya \"selimut\" gas yang menjaganya tetap hangat.","en":"The Earth has a 'blanket' of gas that keeps it warm."},{"id":"Pohon menyerap gas rumah kaca dan memberi kita udara segar.","en":"Trees soak up greenhouse gases and give us fresh air."},{"id":"Matahari, angin, dan air bisa menjadi sumber energi bersih.","en":"The sun, wind, and water can be sources of clean energy."},{"id":"Es di kutub mencair perlahan saat bumi makin hangat.","en":"Polar ice melts slowly as the Earth gets warmer."},{"id":"Mematikan lampu yang tidak dipakai membantu menghemat energi.","en":"Turning off unused lights helps save energy."},{"id":"Negara-negara di dunia bekerja sama menjaga bumi tetap sejuk.","en":"Countries around the world work together to keep the Earth cool."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Iklim","def_id":"Pola cuaca di suatu tempat selama waktu yang sangat lama.","def_en":"The pattern of weather in a place over a very long time."},{"term":"Gas rumah kaca","def_id":"Gas di udara yang menahan panas matahari agar bumi tetap hangat.","def_en":"Gas in the air that traps the sun's heat to keep the Earth warm."},{"term":"Pemanasan global","def_id":"Naiknya suhu rata-rata bumi sehingga menjadi lebih hangat.","def_en":"The rise in the Earth's average temperature so it becomes warmer."},{"term":"Energi bersih","def_id":"Tenaga dari matahari, angin, atau air yang tidak mengotori udara.","def_en":"Power from the sun, wind, or water that does not make the air dirty."},{"term":"Kutub","def_id":"Daerah paling utara dan paling selatan bumi yang dingin dan penuh es.","def_en":"The far north and far south of the Earth, which are cold and icy."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/76111cf0823863f6.jpg","caption_id":"Dasar danau yang mengering dan tanahnya retak-retak saat cuaca panas yang panjang.","caption_en":"A dried lakebed with cracked soil during a long spell of hot weather.","credit":"National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f00c08a36b1b10ae.jpg","caption_id":"Ladang jagung yang mengering karena kekurangan hujan di bawah langit berawan.","caption_en":"A corn field dried out from a lack of rain under a cloudy sky.","credit":"USDA photo by Bob Nichols","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e28d72973f7a7113.jpg","caption_id":"Karang yang memutih di laut yang menghangat; karang sehat biasanya berwarna-warni.","caption_en":"A coral turned white in warming seas; healthy coral is usually colorful.","credit":"Vardhanjp","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perubahan_iklim"},"lingkungan_polusi_udara":{"id":"lingkungan_polusi_udara","title_id":"Pencemaran Udara","title_en":"Air Pollution","subtitle_id":"Menjaga udara tetap bersih dan segar untuk dihirup","subtitle_en":"Keeping the air clean and fresh to breathe","data_card":[{"icon":"directions_car","label_id":"Penyebab","label_en":"Cause","value_id":"Asap dari kendaraan, pabrik, dan pembakaran sampah","value_en":"Smoke from vehicles, factories, and burning trash"},{"icon":"masks","label_id":"Dampak","label_en":"Effects","value_id":"Udara jadi kotor dan bisa membuat napas sesak","value_en":"Air gets dirty and can make breathing hard"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Pelindung","label_en":"Helpers","value_id":"Pohon menyaring udara, masker menjaga hidung","value_en":"Trees filter the air, masks protect the nose"},{"icon":"air","label_id":"Solusi","label_en":"Solution","value_id":"Transportasi bersih dan menanam banyak pohon","value_en":"Clean transport and planting many trees"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Yang Bisa Kita Lakukan","label_en":"What We Can Do","value_id":"Jalan kaki, bersepeda, dan tidak membakar sampah","value_en":"Walk, bike, and don't burn trash"}],"sections":[{"icon":"air","h_id":"Apa Itu Pencemaran Udara?","h_en":"What Is Air Pollution?","body_id":"Udara yang sehat itu bersih dan segar untuk dihirup. Pencemaran udara terjadi ketika ada zat kotor, seperti asap dan debu, yang bercampur di udara. Zat ini bisa berupa gas atau partikel kecil yang melayang. Udara yang kotor bisa kita temui di luar maupun di dalam ruangan. Untungnya, kita bisa membantu menjaga udara tetap bersih!","body_en":"Healthy air is clean and fresh to breathe. Air pollution happens when dirty things, like smoke and dust, mix into the air. These can be gases or tiny floating bits. Dirty air can be found both outdoors and indoors. Luckily, we can help keep the air clean!"},{"icon":"directions_car","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Sebagian besar pencemaran udara berasal dari pembakaran bahan bakar. Asap keluar dari knalpot mobil dan motor saat mesinnya menyala. Cerobong pabrik juga mengeluarkan asap saat membuat barang. Membakar sampah dan kayu di rumah ikut mengotori udara. Debu dari jalan dan tanah yang kering juga bisa beterbangan ke udara.","body_en":"Most air pollution comes from burning fuel. Smoke comes out of car and motorbike exhausts when their engines run. Factory chimneys also release smoke while making things. Burning trash and wood at home dirties the air too. Dust from roads and dry soil can also blow into the air."},{"icon":"masks","h_id":"Mengapa Udara Bersih Penting?","h_en":"Why Is Clean Air Important?","body_id":"Setiap hari kita bernapas ribuan kali, jadi kita butuh udara yang bersih agar tubuh kita sehat. Udara yang kotor bisa membuat hidung gatal, mata perih, atau napas terasa sesak. Saat udara sedang berdebu, kita bisa memakai masker untuk melindungi hidung dan mulut. Udara yang segar membuat kita merasa nyaman dan penuh tenaga.","body_en":"Every day we breathe thousands of times, so we need clean air to keep our bodies healthy. Dirty air can make the nose itchy, the eyes sting, or breathing feel hard. When the air is dusty, we can wear a mask to protect our nose and mouth. Fresh air makes us feel comfortable and full of energy."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Pohon, Sang Penyaring Udara","h_en":"Trees, the Air Filters","body_id":"Pohon adalah pahlawan udara bersih! Daun-daunnya menangkap debu dan mengubah udara kotor menjadi segar kembali. Semakin banyak pohon dan taman di sekitar kita, semakin bersih udara yang kita hirup. Itulah sebabnya kota-kota menanam pohon di tepi jalan dan membuat taman hijau yang rindang untuk semua orang.","body_en":"Trees are the heroes of clean air! Their leaves catch dust and turn dirty air fresh again. The more trees and parks around us, the cleaner the air we breathe. That is why cities plant trees along the roads and build shady green parks for everyone."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Yuk, Jaga Udara Kita!","h_en":"Let's Protect Our Air!","body_id":"Ada banyak cara seru untuk menjaga udara tetap bersih. Untuk jarak dekat, kita bisa jalan kaki atau bersepeda agar tidak menambah asap kendaraan. Kita juga sebaiknya tidak membakar sampah, tetapi membuangnya pada tempatnya. Yang paling menyenangkan, kita bisa menanam dan merawat pohon. Udara bersih membuat semua orang lebih sehat dan bahagia!","body_en":"There are many fun ways to keep the air clean. For short trips, we can walk or bike so we don't add vehicle smoke. We should also not burn trash, but throw it away properly instead. Best of all, we can plant and care for trees. Clean air makes everyone healthier and happier!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Setiap hari kita bernapas ribuan kali, jadi udara bersih itu penting!","en":"Every day we breathe thousands of times, so clean air is important!"},{"id":"Daun pohon bisa menangkap debu dan menyegarkan udara.","en":"Tree leaves can catch dust and freshen the air."},{"id":"Mobil listrik tidak mengeluarkan asap dari knalpot.","en":"Electric cars don't release smoke from an exhaust pipe."},{"id":"Memakai masker melindungi hidung saat udara berdebu.","en":"Wearing a mask protects the nose when the air is dusty."},{"id":"Jalan kaki dan bersepeda membuat udara tetap bersih.","en":"Walking and biking help keep the air clean."},{"id":"Menanam pohon di kota membuat udara lebih segar untuk dihirup.","en":"Planting trees in the city makes the air fresher to breathe."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Polutan","def_id":"Zat kotor seperti asap atau debu yang mencemari udara.","def_en":"A dirty substance like smoke or dust that pollutes the air."},{"term":"Partikel","def_id":"Butiran sangat kecil yang melayang di udara dan sulit terlihat.","def_en":"Very tiny bits that float in the air and are hard to see."},{"term":"Knalpot","def_id":"Saluran di kendaraan tempat keluarnya asap dari mesin.","def_en":"The pipe on a vehicle where smoke comes out of the engine."},{"term":"Cerobong","def_id":"Pipa tinggi di pabrik tempat asap dilepaskan ke udara.","def_en":"A tall pipe on a factory where smoke is released into the air."},{"term":"Transportasi bersih","def_id":"Cara bepergian yang tidak mengotori udara, seperti sepeda atau mobil listrik.","def_en":"Ways of traveling that don't dirty the air, like bikes or electric cars."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4611669cf371e9a2.jpg","caption_id":"Sebuah cerobong mengeluarkan asap gelap ke langit saat matahari terbenam di balik bukit.","caption_en":"A chimney puffs dark smoke into the sky as the sun sets behind the hills.","credit":"Janak Bhatta","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/565ec3c2b168e6d0.jpg","caption_id":"Cerobong-cerobong pabrik mengeluarkan asap tebal yang naik ke langit biru.","caption_en":"Factory chimneys release thick smoke that rises into the blue sky.","credit":"NPS","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polusi_udara"},"lingkungan_sampah_plastik":{"id":"lingkungan_sampah_plastik","title_id":"Sampah Plastik","title_en":"Plastic Waste","subtitle_id":"Masalah besar yang bisa kita atasi bersama","subtitle_en":"A big problem we can solve together","data_card":[{"icon":"delete","label_id":"Sumber","label_en":"Source","value_id":"Botol, kantong, sedotan, dan kemasan makanan","value_en":"Bottles, bags, straws, and food packaging"},{"icon":"water","label_id":"Masalah","label_en":"Problem","value_id":"Mencemari laut, sungai, dan tanah","value_en":"Pollutes the sea, rivers, and soil"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Lama terurai","label_en":"Decompose time","value_id":"Sangat lama, sulit hancur secara alami","value_en":"Very long, hard to break down naturally"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Korban","label_en":"Affected","value_id":"Hewan laut seperti penyu dan burung laut","value_en":"Sea animals like turtles and seabirds"},{"icon":"recycling","label_id":"Solusi","label_en":"Solution","value_id":"Kurangi, pakai ulang, dan daur ulang (3R)","value_en":"Reduce, reuse, and recycle (3R)"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Harapan","label_en":"Hope","value_id":"Setiap orang bisa membantu, termasuk kamu!","value_en":"Everyone can help, including you!"}],"sections":[{"icon":"delete","h_id":"Apa Itu Sampah Plastik?","h_en":"What Is Plastic Waste?","body_id":"Plastik ada di mana-mana di sekitar kita. Botol minuman, kantong belanja, sedotan, dan bungkus makanan banyak yang terbuat dari plastik. Plastik dibuat manusia karena murah, ringan, dan kuat. Tetapi ketika kita membuangnya sembarangan, plastik berubah menjadi sampah yang menumpuk dan mengotori lingkungan kita.","body_en":"Plastic is everywhere around us. Drink bottles, shopping bags, straws, and food wrappers are often made of plastic. People make plastic because it is cheap, light, and strong. But when we throw it away carelessly, plastic turns into waste that piles up and dirties our environment."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Mengapa Plastik Sulit Hilang?","h_en":"Why Is Plastic Hard to Get Rid Of?","body_id":"Daun dan sisa makanan bisa membusuk dan menyatu kembali dengan tanah dalam waktu singkat. Tetapi plastik berbeda. Bahan plastik sangat kuat sehingga alam butuh waktu yang amat lama untuk menguraikannya. Karena itu, satu botol plastik yang kita buang hari ini bisa tetap ada jauh lebih lama daripada usia kita.","body_en":"Leaves and food scraps can rot and return to the soil quickly. But plastic is different. Plastic is so tough that nature needs a very long time to break it down. That is why one plastic bottle we throw away today can stay around far longer than we live."},{"icon":"water","h_id":"Plastik dan Lautan","h_en":"Plastic and the Ocean","body_id":"Sampah plastik sering terbawa angin dan air hujan ke selokan, lalu mengalir ke sungai dan akhirnya sampai ke laut. Di sana plastik mengapung dan berkumpul menjadi sangat banyak. Para peneliti khawatir, jika kita tidak bertindak, suatu hari nanti bisa ada lebih banyak plastik daripada ikan di laut. Itulah mengapa kita harus menjaga laut sejak sekarang.","body_en":"Plastic waste is often carried by wind and rain into drains, then flows into rivers and finally reaches the sea. There it floats and gathers into huge amounts. Researchers worry that if we do nothing, one day there could be more plastic than fish in the ocean. That is why we must protect the sea starting now."},{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Hewan yang Terancam","h_en":"Animals in Danger","body_id":"Banyak hewan laut tidak bisa membedakan plastik dengan makanan. Penyu kadang mengira kantong plastik adalah ubur-ubur, lalu memakannya. Burung laut juga bisa menelan potongan plastik kecil. Plastik juga bisa menjerat tubuh hewan sehingga mereka sulit bergerak. Dengan menjaga sampah kita, kita ikut melindungi sahabat-sahabat di lautan.","body_en":"Many sea animals cannot tell plastic from food. Turtles sometimes mistake a plastic bag for a jellyfish and eat it. Seabirds can also swallow tiny pieces of plastic. Plastic can even tangle around an animal's body so it cannot move well. By caring for our trash, we help protect our friends in the ocean."},{"icon":"recycling","h_id":"Yuk, Lakukan 3R!","h_en":"Let's Do the 3R!","body_id":"Kabar baiknya, kita semua bisa membantu dengan 3R: Reduce, Reuse, Recycle! Reduce artinya kurangi plastik, misalnya membawa tas kain dan botol minum sendiri. Reuse artinya pakai ulang barang plastik yang masih bagus. Recycle artinya daur ulang, yaitu memilah sampah agar bisa diolah menjadi barang baru. Mulailah dari hal kecil, dan ajak teman serta keluargamu ikut menjaga bumi!","body_en":"The good news is, we can all help with the 3R: Reduce, Reuse, Recycle! Reduce means using less plastic, like bringing a cloth bag and your own water bottle. Reuse means using plastic items again while they are still good. Recycle means sorting trash so it can be made into new things. Start with small steps, and invite your friends and family to care for the Earth too!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Satu botol plastik bisa bertahan jauh lebih lama daripada usia kita.","en":"One plastic bottle can last far longer than we live."},{"id":"Penyu sering mengira kantong plastik adalah ubur-ubur dan memakannya.","en":"Turtles often mistake plastic bags for jellyfish and eat them."},{"id":"Sampah plastik bisa terbawa dari selokan sampai ke laut.","en":"Plastic waste can travel from drains all the way to the sea."},{"id":"3R berarti Reduce, Reuse, dan Recycle.","en":"3R means Reduce, Reuse, and Recycle."},{"id":"Membawa tas kain dan botol minum sendiri mengurangi banyak sampah.","en":"Bringing a cloth bag and your own bottle cuts down a lot of waste."},{"id":"Setiap orang, termasuk anak-anak, bisa membantu menjaga bumi.","en":"Everyone, including children, can help protect the Earth."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Plastik","def_id":"Bahan buatan manusia yang ringan dan kuat, tetapi sulit terurai di alam.","def_en":"A human-made material that is light and strong, but hard for nature to break down."},{"term":"Terurai","def_id":"Hancur dan menyatu kembali dengan tanah secara alami.","def_en":"To break apart and return to the soil naturally."},{"term":"Mencemari","def_id":"Membuat air, tanah, atau udara menjadi kotor dan tidak sehat.","def_en":"To make water, soil, or air dirty and unhealthy."},{"term":"Daur ulang","def_id":"Mengolah sampah lama menjadi barang baru yang bisa dipakai lagi.","def_en":"Turning old waste into new items that can be used again."},{"term":"3R","def_id":"Tiga cara menjaga lingkungan: Reduce (kurangi), Reuse (pakai ulang), Recycle (daur ulang).","def_en":"Three ways to care for the environment: Reduce, Reuse, and Recycle."},{"term":"Lingkungan","def_id":"Semua yang ada di sekeliling kita, seperti tanah, air, udara, tumbuhan, dan hewan.","def_en":"Everything around us, such as land, water, air, plants, and animals."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/afd95d4975886c08.jpg","caption_id":"Barang-barang plastik sehari-hari seperti botol susu, gelas takar, dan keping CD. Banyak benda di rumah kita terbuat dari plastik.","caption_en":"Everyday plastic items like a milk jug, measuring cup, and a CD. Many things in our homes are made of plastic.","credit":"Marek Slusarczyk (Tupungato)","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d2856e4ea50c9047.jpg","caption_id":"Botol-botol plastik tersangkut di antara batu di sebuah sungai kecil. Sampah seperti ini bisa mengalir hingga ke laut.","caption_en":"Plastic bottles caught among the rocks of a small stream. Trash like this can flow all the way to the sea.","credit":"Vysotsky","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d129f5d4353e022b.jpg","caption_id":"Serpihan plastik berwarna-warni terdampar di pantai pasir putih, terbawa arus laut dari tempat yang jauh.","caption_en":"Colorful bits of plastic washed up on a white sandy beach, carried by ocean currents from far away.","credit":"American at German Wikipedia","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polusi_plastik"},"lingkungan_terumbu_karang":{"id":"lingkungan_terumbu_karang","title_id":"Terumbu Karang","title_en":"Coral Reef","subtitle_id":"Hutan hujan di dalam laut yang penuh warna","subtitle_en":"A colorful rainforest beneath the sea","data_card":[{"icon":"phishing","label_id":"Apa itu","label_en":"What it is","value_id":"Hewan kecil bernama polip yang membentuk karang","value_en":"Tiny animals called polyps that build the reef"},{"icon":"water","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Laut tropis yang dangkal, hangat, dan jernih","value_en":"Shallow tropical seas that are warm and clear"},{"icon":"set_meal","label_id":"Penghuni","label_en":"Life","value_id":"Rumah bagi ikan, kepiting, dan banyak satwa laut","value_en":"Home to fish, crabs, and many sea creatures"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Manfaat","label_en":"Benefit","value_id":"Melindungi pantai dan menjadi tempat ikan hidup","value_en":"Protects the coast and gives fish a place to live"},{"icon":"thermostat","label_id":"Ancaman","label_en":"Threat","value_id":"Pemutihan karang saat air laut terlalu panas","value_en":"Coral bleaching when the sea gets too hot"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Banyak terdapat di perairan Indonesia","value_en":"Found in great numbers in Indonesian waters"}],"sections":[{"icon":"phishing","h_id":"Apa Itu Terumbu Karang?","h_en":"What Is a Coral Reef?","body_id":"Banyak orang mengira terumbu karang adalah batu atau tumbuhan, padahal sebenarnya ia dibangun oleh hewan! Hewan kecil mungil itu bernama polip. Ribuan polip hidup bersama dan membentuk koloni yang besar. Setiap polip membuat rumah keras dari kapur, dan rumah-rumah ini bertumpuk selama bertahun-tahun hingga menjadi terumbu karang yang indah.","body_en":"Many people think a coral reef is rock or a plant, but it is actually built by animals! These tiny little animals are called polyps. Thousands of polyps live together and form a large colony. Each polyp builds a hard house of limestone, and these houses stack up over many years to become a beautiful coral reef."},{"icon":"water","h_id":"Di Mana Karang Tumbuh?","h_en":"Where Do Corals Grow?","body_id":"Terumbu karang suka tempat yang hangat, jadi mereka tumbuh di laut tropis yang dangkal. Air di sana harus jernih dan bersih supaya sinar matahari bisa menembus sampai ke karang. Indonesia berada di daerah tropis, sehingga negara kita punya terumbu karang yang sangat banyak dan beraneka warna. Beruntung sekali kita memilikinya!","body_en":"Coral reefs love warm places, so they grow in shallow tropical seas. The water there must be clear and clean so that sunlight can reach the coral. Indonesia lies in the tropics, so our country has a great many colorful coral reefs. How lucky we are to have them!"},{"icon":"set_meal","h_id":"Hutan Hujan di Dalam Laut","h_en":"A Rainforest Under the Sea","body_id":"Terumbu karang sering disebut hutan hujan lautan karena penuh dengan kehidupan. Walaupun luasnya sangat kecil di lautan dunia, terumbu karang menjadi rumah bagi seperempat dari semua hewan laut! Ikan badut, ikan warna-warni, bintang laut, kepiting, dan udang semuanya hidup berdampingan di celah-celah karang yang aman.","body_en":"A coral reef is often called the rainforest of the sea because it is full of life. Even though it covers only a tiny part of the world's oceans, a coral reef is home to a quarter of all sea animals! Clownfish, colorful fish, starfish, crabs, and shrimp all live together in the safe nooks of the reef."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Penjaga Pantai dan Penyedia Ikan","h_en":"Coast Guard and Fish Provider","body_id":"Selain indah, terumbu karang juga sangat berguna bagi manusia. Karang yang kokoh memecah ombak besar sebelum sampai ke pantai, sehingga melindungi desa-desa di tepi laut. Terumbu karang juga menjadi tempat ikan-ikan berkembang biak, sehingga para nelayan bisa menangkap ikan untuk makanan. Karang adalah sahabat baik bagi laut dan manusia.","body_en":"Besides being beautiful, coral reefs are also very useful to people. Sturdy coral breaks big waves before they reach the shore, protecting seaside villages. Coral reefs are also where fish breed, so fishers can catch fish for food. Coral is a good friend to both the sea and people."},{"icon":"thermostat","h_id":"Menjaga Karang Tetap Sehat","h_en":"Keeping Corals Healthy","body_id":"Karang sangat peka terhadap perubahan air laut. Jika air menjadi terlalu panas atau kotor, karang bisa kehilangan warnanya dan berubah pucat. Peristiwa ini disebut pemutihan karang. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga laut tetap bersih, tidak membuang sampah ke laut, dan tidak menginjak karang saat berenang. Dengan begitu, terumbu karang akan tetap berwarna-warni untuk kita semua.","body_en":"Coral is very sensitive to changes in seawater. If the water becomes too hot or dirty, coral can lose its color and turn pale. This is called coral bleaching. We can help by keeping the sea clean, not throwing trash into the ocean, and not stepping on coral while swimming. That way, coral reefs will stay colorful for us all."}],"facts":[{"id":"Terumbu karang dibangun oleh hewan kecil bernama polip.","en":"Coral reefs are built by tiny animals called polyps."},{"id":"Terumbu karang disebut hutan hujan lautan karena penuh kehidupan.","en":"Coral reefs are called the rainforest of the sea because they are full of life."},{"id":"Seperempat dari semua hewan laut tinggal di terumbu karang.","en":"A quarter of all sea animals live in coral reefs."},{"id":"Karang melindungi pantai dengan memecah ombak besar.","en":"Coral protects the coast by breaking big waves."},{"id":"Saat air laut terlalu panas, karang bisa memutih dan kehilangan warnanya.","en":"When the sea gets too hot, coral can bleach and lose its color."},{"id":"Indonesia memiliki terumbu karang yang sangat banyak dan beragam.","en":"Indonesia has very many and very diverse coral reefs."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Polip","def_id":"Hewan laut kecil bertentakel yang membangun terumbu karang.","def_en":"A tiny sea animal with tentacles that builds the coral reef."},{"term":"Koloni","def_id":"Kumpulan banyak polip yang hidup bersama menjadi satu karang.","def_en":"A group of many polyps living together as one coral."},{"term":"Tropis","def_id":"Daerah di bumi yang hangat sepanjang tahun, seperti Indonesia.","def_en":"A part of the Earth that is warm all year round, like Indonesia."},{"term":"Pemutihan karang","def_id":"Saat karang berubah pucat karena air laut terlalu panas atau kotor.","def_en":"When coral turns pale because the seawater is too hot or dirty."},{"term":"Ekosistem","def_id":"Tempat tumbuhan, hewan, dan alam hidup bersama dan saling membutuhkan.","def_en":"A place where plants, animals, and nature live together and need each other."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3bd8d9fdc6fa533b.jpg","caption_id":"Terumbu karang berwarna-warni dipenuhi kawanan ikan yang berenang di air laut yang biru jernih.","caption_en":"A colorful coral reef filled with schools of fish swimming in clear blue seawater.","credit":"Dr. Randi Rotjan, New England Aquarium","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b01546972cd71381.jpg","caption_id":"Bintang laut biru cerah beristirahat di antara karang bercabang sementara ikan-ikan oranye berenang di sekitarnya.","caption_en":"A bright blue starfish rests among branching coral while orange fish swim nearby.","credit":"Richard Ling","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/54988b62c3cfa7af.jpg","caption_id":"Ikan badut oranye bersembunyi dengan aman di antara tentakel anemon laut, salah satu penghuni terumbu karang.","caption_en":"An orange clownfish hides safely among the tentacles of a sea anemone, one of the reef's residents.","credit":"Janderk","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terumbu_karang"},"olahraga_bulu_tangkis":{"id":"olahraga_bulu_tangkis","title_id":"Bulu Tangkis","title_en":"Badminton","subtitle_id":"Olahraga raket cepat memukul kok melewati jaring, kebanggaan juara Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"A fast racket sport hitting a shuttlecock over the net, the pride of Indonesia's champions!","data_card":[{"icon":"sports_tennis","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Olahraga raket","value_en":"Racket sport"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Pemain","label_en":"Players","value_id":"1 lawan 1, atau 2 lawan 2","value_en":"1 vs 1, or 2 vs 2"},{"icon":"sports_tennis","label_id":"Peralatan","label_en":"Equipment","value_id":"Raket dan kok (shuttlecock)","value_en":"Racket and shuttlecock"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Tempat","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Lapangan dengan jaring di tengah","value_en":"A court with a net in the middle"},{"icon":"emoji_events","label_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","label_en":"Indonesia's pride","value_id":"Juara dunia dan emas Olimpiade","value_en":"World and Olympic gold champions"}],"sections":[{"icon":"sports_tennis","h_id":"Apa Itu Bulu Tangkis?","h_en":"What Is Badminton?","body_id":"Bulu tangkis adalah olahraga raket yang dimainkan dengan memukul kok melewati jaring. Kok bukanlah bola biasa, melainkan benda ringan berbulu yang melayang di udara. Dua pemain atau dua pasangan berdiri di sisi yang berlawanan, lalu saling memukul kok bolak-balik. Olahraga ini sangat digemari di Indonesia dan dimainkan di sekolah, kampung, sampai gelanggang besar.","body_en":"Badminton is a racket sport played by hitting a shuttlecock over a net. The shuttlecock is not an ordinary ball but a light, feathered object that floats through the air. Two players or two pairs stand on opposite sides and hit the shuttlecock back and forth. This sport is very popular in Indonesia and is played in schools, villages, and big arenas alike."},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Cara Bermain","h_en":"How to Play","body_id":"Permainan dimulai dengan servis, yaitu memukul kok pertama kali ke sisi lawan. Setiap pemain berusaha memukul kok agar jatuh di lapangan lawan, dan menjaga agar kok tidak jatuh di lapangannya sendiri. Kalau kok menyangkut di jaring atau jatuh di luar garis, lawan mendapat poin. Bulu tangkis bisa dimainkan tunggal (satu lawan satu) atau ganda (dua lawan dua).","body_en":"The game begins with a serve, the first hit of the shuttlecock to the other side. Each player tries to make the shuttlecock land in the opponent's court while keeping it from landing in their own. If the shuttlecock hits the net or falls outside the lines, the opponent gets a point. Badminton can be played as singles (one against one) or doubles (two against two)."},{"icon":"sports_tennis","h_id":"Raket dan Kok","h_en":"Racket and Shuttlecock","body_id":"Alat utama bulu tangkis adalah raket dan kok. Raket modern sangat ringan karena dibuat dari serat karbon, dengan senar yang dianyam rapat di kepalanya. Kok yang asli dibuat dari bulu angsa yang disusun seperti kerucut, dengan gabus di ujungnya. Untuk latihan, sering dipakai kok dari plastik yang lebih awet. Pemain juga memakai sepatu khusus bersol karet agar tidak mudah tergelincir.","body_en":"The main gear in badminton is the racket and the shuttlecock. A modern racket is very light because it is made of carbon fiber, with strings woven tightly across its head. A real shuttlecock is made from goose feathers arranged like a cone, with cork at the tip. For practice, plastic shuttlecocks that last longer are often used. Players also wear special rubber-soled shoes so they do not slip easily."},{"icon":"emoji_events","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Bulu tangkis adalah olahraga yang paling membanggakan bagi Indonesia. Para atlet kita sudah berkali-kali menjadi juara dunia dan meraih medali emas di Olimpiade. Saat pemain Indonesia bertanding, banyak keluarga berkumpul di depan televisi untuk mendukung. Nama-nama pebulu tangkis hebat seperti Taufik Hidayat dikenal di seluruh dunia dan menjadi pahlawan olahraga bangsa.","body_en":"Badminton is the sport that makes Indonesia most proud. Our athletes have become world champions and won Olympic gold medals many times. When Indonesian players compete, many families gather in front of the television to cheer. Great badminton players such as Taufik Hidayat are known all over the world and are heroes of the nation's sport."},{"icon":"lightbulb","h_id":"Tahukah Kamu?","h_en":"Did You Know?","body_id":"Kok bulu tangkis bisa terbang sangat kencang! Saat dipukul keras dengan pukulan smash, kok dapat melaju lebih cepat daripada mobil di jalan tol. Itulah mengapa pemain bulu tangkis harus punya mata yang awas, kaki yang lincah, dan tangan yang cepat untuk mengejar kok ke segala arah lapangan.","body_en":"A badminton shuttlecock can fly incredibly fast! When struck hard with a smash, it can travel faster than a car on the highway. That is why badminton players must have sharp eyes, nimble feet, and quick hands to chase the shuttlecock to every corner of the court."}],"facts":[{"id":"Saat di-smash, kok bisa melaju lebih cepat daripada mobil di jalan tol.","en":"When smashed, a shuttlecock can fly faster than a car on the highway."},{"id":"Kok asli dibuat dari bulu angsa yang disusun membentuk kerucut.","en":"A real shuttlecock is made from goose feathers arranged into a cone."},{"id":"Bulu tangkis bisa dimainkan tunggal (satu lawan satu) atau ganda (dua lawan dua).","en":"Badminton can be played as singles (one vs one) or doubles (two vs two)."},{"id":"Indonesia sudah berkali-kali meraih medali emas Olimpiade dari bulu tangkis.","en":"Indonesia has won Olympic gold medals in badminton many times."},{"id":"Raket bulu tangkis modern dibuat dari serat karbon agar sangat ringan.","en":"Modern badminton rackets are made of carbon fiber to be very light."},{"id":"Kejuaraan bulu tangkis tertua di dunia bernama All England.","en":"The oldest badminton championship in the world is called the All England."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Kok","def_id":"Bola berbulu ringan yang dipukul dalam bulu tangkis; disebut juga shuttlecock.","def_en":"The light feathered ball hit in badminton; also called the shuttlecock."},{"term":"Raket","def_id":"Alat pemukul bertangkai dengan senar di kepalanya untuk memukul kok.","def_en":"A handled bat with strings on its head used to hit the shuttlecock."},{"term":"Servis","def_id":"Pukulan pertama untuk memulai permainan ke sisi lawan.","def_en":"The first hit that starts the game to the opponent's side."},{"term":"Smash","def_id":"Pukulan keras dan cepat ke arah bawah untuk mengejutkan lawan.","def_en":"A hard, fast downward hit to surprise the opponent."},{"term":"Tunggal","def_id":"Permainan satu pemain melawan satu pemain.","def_en":"A game of one player against one player."},{"term":"Ganda","def_id":"Permainan dua pemain berpasangan melawan dua pemain lain.","def_en":"A game of two players as a pair against two other players."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f103935b838e11d4.jpg","caption_id":"Pertandingan ganda campuran di Olimpiade London 2012; pemain melompat memukul kok.","caption_en":"A mixed doubles match at the London 2012 Olympics; a player jumps to hit the shuttlecock.","credit":"Peter","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ced8abc8eb66b706.jpg","caption_id":"Taufik Hidayat, juara bulu tangkis Indonesia, mengangkat raket setelah bermain.","caption_en":"Taufik Hidayat, an Indonesian badminton champion, raises his racket after playing.","credit":"Mayeres","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6d09c60c471b7629.jpg","caption_id":"Raket bulu tangkis modern yang ringan dengan senar dianyam rapat di kepalanya.","caption_en":"A light modern badminton racket with strings woven tightly across its head.","credit":"hvshop","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulu_tangkis"},"olahraga_pencak_silat":{"id":"olahraga_pencak_silat","title_id":"Pencak Silat","title_en":"Pencak Silat","subtitle_id":"Bela diri asli Indonesia yang memadukan kekuatan, kelincahan, dan keindahan gerak!","subtitle_en":"Indonesia's own martial art blending strength, agility, and beautiful movement!","data_card":[{"icon":"sports_martial_arts","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Seni bela diri","value_en":"Martial art"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Asli dari Indonesia (Nusantara)","value_en":"Native to Indonesia (the archipelago)"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Pemain","label_en":"Players","value_id":"Sendiri atau berpasangan","value_en":"Solo or in pairs"},{"icon":"sports_martial_arts","label_id":"Latihan","label_en":"Training","value_id":"Jurus, kuda-kuda, dan senjata","value_en":"Moves, stances, and weapons"},{"icon":"emoji_events","label_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","label_en":"Indonesia's pride","value_id":"Warisan Budaya Dunia UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO World Cultural Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"sports_martial_arts","h_id":"Apa Itu Pencak Silat?","h_en":"What Is Pencak Silat?","body_id":"Pencak silat adalah seni bela diri asli Indonesia. Bela diri ini melatih seluruh tubuh untuk menyerang, menangkis, mengelak, dan menjaga diri. Pencak silat bukan hanya soal bertarung, tetapi juga soal keindahan gerak dan kesabaran hati. Orang yang ahli pencak silat disebut pesilat. Ada ratusan aliran pencak silat yang berbeda-beda di seluruh Indonesia.","body_en":"Pencak silat is a martial art native to Indonesia. It trains the whole body to attack, block, dodge, and protect oneself. Pencak silat is not only about fighting but also about beautiful movement and a patient heart. A person skilled in pencak silat is called a pesilat. There are hundreds of different pencak silat styles all across Indonesia."},{"icon":"self_improvement","h_id":"Gerakan dan Jurus","h_en":"Movements and Moves","body_id":"Dalam pencak silat, pesilat belajar kuda-kuda, yaitu cara berdiri yang kuat dan seimbang. Lalu mereka berlatih jurus, yaitu rangkaian gerakan menyerang dan bertahan. Banyak gerakan silat terinspirasi dari binatang seperti harimau, ular, monyet, dan burung elang. Semua gerakan ini dilatih berulang-ulang sampai menjadi cepat, kuat, dan indah dipandang.","body_en":"In pencak silat, a pesilat learns stances, which are strong and balanced ways of standing. Then they practice jurus, which are sequences of attacking and defending movements. Many silat movements are inspired by animals such as the tiger, snake, monkey, and eagle. All of these moves are practiced over and over until they become fast, strong, and beautiful to watch."},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Seni, Olahraga, dan Pertandingan","h_en":"Art, Sport, and Competition","body_id":"Pencak silat punya banyak sisi. Sebagai seni, gerakannya yang indah sering ditampilkan dengan iringan musik dalam acara adat dan pernikahan. Sebagai olahraga, pencak silat dipertandingkan; dua pesilat bertanding di atas gelanggang dengan memakai pelindung tubuh dan diawasi wasit. Pencak silat dipertandingkan di Pekan Olahraga Nasional (PON) dan SEA Games sejak tahun 1987.","body_en":"Pencak silat has many sides. As an art, its beautiful movements are often performed with music at traditional ceremonies and weddings. As a sport, pencak silat is contested; two pesilat compete on a mat wearing body protectors and watched by a referee. Pencak silat has been a competition sport at the National Sports Week (PON) and the SEA Games since 1987."},{"icon":"emoji_events","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pencak silat adalah warisan asli dari nenek moyang bangsa Indonesia. Pada 13 Desember 2019, UNESCO menetapkan pencak silat sebagai Warisan Budaya Tak Benda Dunia. Pengakuan ini membuat seluruh rakyat Indonesia bangga. Pencak silat juga menjadi alat pemersatu, karena di setiap daerah ada aliran khasnya sendiri, dari Cimande di Jawa Barat sampai Merpati Putih di Jawa Tengah.","body_en":"Pencak silat is a heritage handed down from the ancestors of the Indonesian people. On 13 December 2019, UNESCO named pencak silat a World Intangible Cultural Heritage. This recognition made all of Indonesia proud. Pencak silat is also a uniting force, because every region has its own special style, from Cimande in West Java to Merpati Putih in Central Java."},{"icon":"lightbulb","h_id":"Tahukah Kamu?","h_en":"Did You Know?","body_id":"Dahulu, pencak silat diajarkan bersama pelajaran agama di surau dan pesantren. Latihan silat dianggap melatih bukan hanya tubuh yang kuat, tetapi juga hati yang sabar dan sopan. Sampai sekarang, banyak perguruan silat mengajarkan murid-muridnya untuk rendah hati, menghormati guru, dan hanya menggunakan ilmunya untuk kebaikan.","body_en":"Long ago, pencak silat was taught together with religious lessons in prayer houses and Islamic schools. Silat training was believed to build not only a strong body but also a patient and polite heart. Even today, many silat schools teach their students to be humble, to respect their teacher, and to use their skill only for good."}],"facts":[{"id":"Pencak silat adalah seni bela diri yang asli berasal dari Indonesia.","en":"Pencak silat is a martial art that originated in Indonesia."},{"id":"UNESCO menetapkan pencak silat sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2019.","en":"UNESCO named pencak silat a World Cultural Heritage in 2019."},{"id":"Banyak gerakan silat meniru binatang seperti harimau, ular, dan elang.","en":"Many silat movements imitate animals such as the tiger, snake, and eagle."},{"id":"Orang yang ahli pencak silat disebut pesilat.","en":"A person skilled in pencak silat is called a pesilat."},{"id":"Pencak silat dipertandingkan di SEA Games sejak tahun 1987.","en":"Pencak silat has been a competition sport at the SEA Games since 1987."},{"id":"Ada ratusan aliran pencak silat yang berbeda di seluruh Indonesia.","en":"There are hundreds of different pencak silat styles across Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Pesilat","def_id":"Orang yang berlatih dan ahli dalam pencak silat.","def_en":"A person who trains in and is skilled at pencak silat."},{"term":"Jurus","def_id":"Rangkaian gerakan menyerang dan bertahan dalam silat.","def_en":"A sequence of attacking and defending movements in silat."},{"term":"Kuda-kuda","def_id":"Cara berdiri yang kuat dan seimbang sebagai dasar gerakan silat.","def_en":"A strong, balanced stance that is the base for silat movements."},{"term":"Aliran","def_id":"Gaya atau jenis pencak silat yang khas dari suatu daerah atau perguruan.","def_en":"A style or type of pencak silat special to a region or school."},{"term":"Bela diri","def_id":"Ilmu dan keterampilan untuk melindungi diri dari bahaya.","def_en":"The knowledge and skill of protecting oneself from danger."},{"term":"Warisan budaya","def_id":"Sesuatu yang berharga dari nenek moyang yang harus kita jaga.","def_en":"Something precious from our ancestors that we must protect."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/bb33cdd110b409cc.jpg","caption_id":"Pertandingan pencak silat putri Indonesia melawan Malaysia di atas gelanggang.","caption_en":"A women's pencak silat match between Indonesia and Malaysia on the contest mat.","credit":"Gunawan Kartapranata","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cfbb4f7e01254e6a.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang pesilat berseragam hitam memperagakan kuda-kuda rendah yang kokoh.","caption_en":"A pesilat in black uniform shows a low, sturdy stance.","credit":"Agus Triyanto","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2061aab71dd601db.jpg","caption_id":"Peragaan pencak silat Betawi dengan golok dalam tradisi 'palang pintu'.","caption_en":"A Betawi pencak silat demonstration with a machete in the 'palang pintu' tradition.","credit":"Gunawan Kartapranata","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b3525b0ef765f807.jpg","caption_id":"Tari Randai dari Minangkabau yang gerakannya berasal dari silek (silat).","caption_en":"The Randai dance from Minangkabau, whose moves come from silek (silat).","credit":"MichaelJLowe","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/97e0c2e403ce7a46.jpg","caption_id":"Murid-murid satu perguruan silat berseragam hitam dengan sabuk berwarna.","caption_en":"Students of one silat school in black uniforms with colored belts.","credit":"prsh","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pencak_silat"},"olahraga_sepak_bola":{"id":"olahraga_sepak_bola","title_id":"Sepak Bola","title_en":"Football (Soccer)","subtitle_id":"Olahraga paling populer di dunia, dimainkan dua tim sebelas pemain demi mencetak gol!","subtitle_en":"The world's most popular sport, played by two teams of eleven to score goals!","data_card":[{"icon":"sports_soccer","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Olahraga tim dengan bola","value_en":"A team ball sport"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Pemain","label_en":"Players","value_id":"11 pemain di tiap tim","value_en":"11 players on each team"},{"icon":"sports_soccer","label_id":"Peralatan","label_en":"Equipment","value_id":"Satu bola dan dua gawang","value_en":"One ball and two goals"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Tempat","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Lapangan rumput persegi panjang","value_en":"A rectangular grass field"},{"icon":"emoji_events","label_id":"Kebanggaan dunia","label_en":"World's pride","value_id":"Olahraga paling populer di dunia","value_en":"The most popular sport on Earth"}],"sections":[{"icon":"sports_soccer","h_id":"Apa Itu Sepak Bola?","h_en":"What Is Football?","body_id":"Sepak bola adalah olahraga yang dimainkan oleh dua tim, masing-masing terdiri dari sebelas pemain. Tujuannya sederhana: memasukkan bola ke gawang lawan sebanyak mungkin. Tim yang mencetak gol paling banyak menjadi pemenang. Sepak bola dimainkan di lapangan rumput yang luas berbentuk persegi panjang, dengan satu gawang di setiap ujungnya.","body_en":"Football is a sport played by two teams, each with eleven players. The goal is simple: put the ball into the opponent's goal as many times as possible. The team that scores the most goals wins. Football is played on a large rectangular grass field, with one goal at each end."},{"icon":"directions_run","h_id":"Cara Bermain","h_en":"How to Play","body_id":"Dalam sepak bola, pemain hanya boleh menggunakan kaki, dada, dan kepala untuk menggerakkan bola. Tangan tidak boleh dipakai sama sekali! Hanya satu pemain istimewa, yaitu penjaga gawang, yang boleh menangkap bola dengan tangan, tetapi hanya di dekat gawangnya sendiri. Pemain mengoper bola kepada teman setim, menggiringnya melewati lawan, lalu menendangnya ke gawang untuk mencetak gol.","body_en":"In football, players may only use their feet, chest, and head to move the ball. Hands may not be used at all! Only one special player, the goalkeeper, may catch the ball with their hands, and only near their own goal. Players pass the ball to teammates, dribble it past opponents, then kick it into the goal to score."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Aturan dan Waktu Bermain","h_en":"Rules and Playing Time","body_id":"Satu pertandingan sepak bola berlangsung dua babak, masing-masing 45 menit, jadi total 90 menit. Di tengah ada waktu istirahat. Seorang wasit memimpin pertandingan dan memastikan semua pemain bermain jujur. Kalau ada pemain melanggar aturan, wasit bisa meniup peluit dan memberi hukuman. Bola yang keluar lapangan harus dimainkan kembali dari pinggir.","body_en":"A football match has two halves of 45 minutes each, so 90 minutes in total. There is a rest break in the middle. A referee leads the match and makes sure all players play fairly. If a player breaks the rules, the referee can blow the whistle and give a punishment. A ball that goes out of the field must be brought back into play from the side."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Sepak Bola dan Indonesia","h_en":"Football and Indonesia","body_id":"Sepak bola adalah olahraga paling populer di dunia, dengan lebih dari 250 juta pemain di lebih dari 200 negara. Pertandingan terbesarnya adalah Piala Dunia FIFA, yang ditonton oleh miliaran orang. Di Indonesia, sepak bola sangat dicintai. Anak-anak bermain bola di mana saja, di lapangan, di gang, bahkan di tanah kosong. Banyak orang Indonesia setia mendukung tim kesayangannya.","body_en":"Football is the most popular sport in the world, with more than 250 million players in over 200 countries. Its biggest tournament is the FIFA World Cup, watched by billions of people. In Indonesia, football is deeply loved. Children play it everywhere, on fields, in alleys, and even on empty land. Many Indonesians loyally support their favorite team."},{"icon":"lightbulb","h_id":"Tahukah Kamu?","h_en":"Did You Know?","body_id":"Permainan menendang bola sudah ada sejak ribuan tahun lalu! Di Tiongkok kuno ada permainan bernama cuju, yaitu menendang bola ke dalam jaring tanpa memakai tangan, mirip sepak bola sekarang. Aturan sepak bola modern yang kita kenal mulai ditulis di Inggris pada tahun 1863, dan sejak itu olahraga ini menyebar ke seluruh dunia.","body_en":"Kicking-ball games have existed for thousands of years! In ancient China there was a game called cuju, kicking a ball into a net without using the hands, much like football today. The modern football rules we know were first written in England in 1863, and since then the sport has spread all over the world."}],"facts":[{"id":"Sepak bola adalah olahraga paling populer di dunia, dengan sekitar 250 juta pemain.","en":"Football is the most popular sport in the world, with about 250 million players."},{"id":"Setiap tim sepak bola terdiri dari sebelas pemain di lapangan.","en":"Each football team has eleven players on the field."},{"id":"Hanya penjaga gawang yang boleh menangkap bola dengan tangan.","en":"Only the goalkeeper is allowed to catch the ball with their hands."},{"id":"Satu pertandingan berlangsung 90 menit, dibagi dua babak 45 menit.","en":"A match lasts 90 minutes, split into two halves of 45 minutes."},{"id":"Aturan sepak bola modern mulai ditulis di Inggris pada tahun 1863.","en":"The modern rules of football were first written in England in 1863."},{"id":"Piala Dunia FIFA adalah acara olahraga yang paling banyak ditonton di dunia.","en":"The FIFA World Cup is the most watched sporting event in the world."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Gol","def_id":"Saat bola masuk ke gawang lawan dan tim mendapat satu angka.","def_en":"When the ball goes into the opponent's goal and the team gets a point."},{"term":"Gawang","def_id":"Bingkai tempat bola harus masuk untuk mencetak gol.","def_en":"The frame the ball must enter to score a goal."},{"term":"Penjaga gawang","def_id":"Pemain yang menjaga gawang dan boleh memakai tangan di dekat gawangnya.","def_en":"The player who guards the goal and may use their hands near it."},{"term":"Wasit","def_id":"Orang yang memimpin pertandingan dan menjaga agar permainan adil.","def_en":"The person who leads the match and keeps the game fair."},{"term":"Babak","def_id":"Bagian waktu permainan; sepak bola punya dua babak masing-masing 45 menit.","def_en":"A part of the playing time; football has two halves of 45 minutes each."},{"term":"Mengoper","def_id":"Menendang bola kepada teman satu tim.","def_en":"Kicking the ball to a teammate."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2d512f5f5b56435e.jpg","caption_id":"Dua pemain berlari berebut bola di lapangan rumput saat pertandingan.","caption_en":"Two players run and chase the ball on the grass field during a match.","credit":"U.S. Navy photo by Photographer's Mate 2nd Class Damon J. Moritz.","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e14b6b837ec42fda.jpg","caption_id":"Anak-anak di Jakarta memegang bola sepak; sepak bola bisa dimainkan di mana saja.","caption_en":"Children in Jakarta hold a football; the game can be played anywhere.","credit":"Jonathan McIntosh","license":"CC BY 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepak_bola"},"pahlawan_bung_tomo":{"id":"pahlawan_bung_tomo","title_id":"Bung Tomo","title_en":"Bung Tomo","subtitle_id":"Pembakar semangat arek-arek Surabaya","subtitle_en":"The fiery voice of Surabaya's youth","data_card":[{"icon":"cake","label_id":"Lahir","label_en":"Born","value_id":"3 Oktober 1920, Surabaya","value_en":"3 October 1920, Surabaya"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"From","value_id":"Surabaya, Jawa Timur","value_en":"Surabaya, East Java"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Dikenal","label_en":"Known for","value_id":"Orasi yang membakar semangat","value_en":"His rousing speeches"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Peristiwa","label_en":"Event","value_id":"Pertempuran 10 November 1945","value_en":"Battle of Surabaya, 10 Nov 1945"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Gelar","label_en":"Title","value_id":"Pahlawan Nasional (2008)","value_en":"National Hero (2008)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"person","h_id":"Siapa Bung Tomo?","h_en":"Who Was Bung Tomo?","body_id":"Bung Tomo bernama asli Sutomo. Ia adalah pejuang dari Surabaya yang terkenal saat Indonesia berjuang mempertahankan kemerdekaan. Suaranya yang lantang di radio membuat rakyat berani melawan penjajah. Karena itu ia dijuluki 'pembakar semangat'.","body_en":"Bung Tomo's real name was Sutomo. He was a fighter from Surabaya, famous when Indonesia struggled to keep its freedom. His powerful voice on the radio gave people the courage to stand up to the colonizers. That is why he was called the one who 'lit the fire of spirit'."},{"icon":"school","h_id":"Masa Muda yang Gigih","h_en":"A Hard-working Youth","body_id":"Bung Tomo tumbuh dalam keluarga yang menghargai pendidikan, tapi sempat berhenti sekolah dan bekerja untuk membantu keluarga. Ia rajin dan pemberani. Saat berusia 17 tahun, ia menjadi salah satu anak Indonesia pertama yang meraih tingkat Pramuka Garuda, tingkat tertinggi dalam kepanduan.","body_en":"Bung Tomo grew up in a family that valued education, but he had to stop school and work to help his family. He was hard-working and brave. At age 17 he became one of the first Indonesian children to reach Garuda Scout, the highest rank in scouting."},{"icon":"campaign","h_id":"Pertempuran 10 November","h_en":"The Battle of 10 November","body_id":"Pada November 1945, pasukan asing datang ke Surabaya. Lewat radio, Bung Tomo berseru agar rakyat tidak menyerah. Arek-arek (anak-anak muda) Surabaya pun berjuang dengan gagah berani. Peristiwa ini menjadi salah satu pertempuran paling penting dalam sejarah Indonesia.","body_en":"In November 1945, foreign troops came to Surabaya. Over the radio, Bung Tomo called on people not to give up. The young people of Surabaya fought bravely. This became one of the most important battles in Indonesian history."},{"icon":"military_tech","h_id":"Hari Pahlawan","h_en":"Heroes' Day","body_id":"Karena keberaniannya, tanggal 10 November diperingati sebagai Hari Pahlawan setiap tahun. Bung Tomo diangkat menjadi Pahlawan Nasional pada tahun 2008. Sebuah stadion besar di Surabaya juga diberi nama Gelora Bung Tomo untuk mengenangnya.","body_en":"Because of his bravery, 10 November is remembered as Heroes' Day every year. Bung Tomo was named a National Hero in 2008. A big stadium in Surabaya is also named Gelora Bung Tomo in his honor."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Yang Bisa Kita Teladani","h_en":"What We Can Learn","body_id":"Dari Bung Tomo kita belajar keberanian dan cinta tanah air. Ia menunjukkan bahwa kata-kata yang baik bisa menyemangati banyak orang. Kita bisa meneladaninya dengan berani membela kebenaran dan mencintai Indonesia.","body_en":"From Bung Tomo we learn courage and love for our homeland. He showed that good words can inspire many people. We can follow his example by bravely standing up for what is right and loving Indonesia."}],"facts":[{"id":"Nama asli Bung Tomo adalah Sutomo.","en":"Bung Tomo's real name was Sutomo."},{"id":"Usia 17 tahun ia meraih Pramuka Garuda, tingkat tertinggi kepanduan.","en":"At 17 he reached Garuda Scout, scouting's highest rank."},{"id":"Suaranya di radio membakar semangat rakyat Surabaya.","en":"His radio voice fired up the people of Surabaya."},{"id":"10 November diperingati sebagai Hari Pahlawan.","en":"10 November is remembered as Heroes' Day."},{"id":"Stadion Gelora Bung Tomo di Surabaya dinamai untuk mengenangnya.","en":"Surabaya's Gelora Bung Tomo Stadium is named in his honor."},{"id":"Ia menjadi Pahlawan Nasional pada tahun 2008.","en":"He was named a National Hero in 2008."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Pahlawan Nasional","def_id":"Gelar kehormatan untuk orang yang sangat berjasa bagi bangsa dan negara.","def_en":"An honorary title for someone who served the nation greatly."},{"term":"Orasi","def_id":"Pidato yang berapi-api untuk membangkitkan semangat.","def_en":"A fiery speech meant to stir up spirit."},{"term":"Kemerdekaan","def_id":"Keadaan bebas dari penjajahan dan menentukan nasib sendiri.","def_en":"Being free from colonial rule and choosing one's own path."},{"term":"Arek","def_id":"Sebutan khas Surabaya untuk anak muda.","def_en":"A Surabaya word for young people."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/dbf0432c3c7bb06b.jpg","caption_id":"Foto terkenal Bung Tomo, sang pembakar semangat.","caption_en":"The famous photo of Bung Tomo, who fired up the people's spirit.","credit":"Alex Mendur","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2136c5c0c3c67da2.jpg","caption_id":"Bung Tomo saat menjadi wakil rakyat tahun 1955.","caption_en":"Bung Tomo as a people's representative in 1955.","credit":"People's Representative Council of Indonesia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/683b5803f350922d.jpg","caption_id":"Stadion Gelora Bung Tomo di Surabaya, dinamai untuk menghormatinya.","caption_en":"Gelora Bung Tomo Stadium in Surabaya, named in his honor.","credit":"d.limantara","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sutomo"},"pahlawan_jenderal_sudirman":{"id":"pahlawan_jenderal_sudirman","title_id":"Jenderal Sudirman","title_en":"General Sudirman","subtitle_id":"Panglima Besar pertama TNI dan teladan keberanian","subtitle_en":"The first Commander-in-Chief of the Indonesian army and a model of courage","data_card":[{"icon":"cake","label_id":"Lahir","label_en":"Born","value_id":"24 Januari 1916, Purbalingga","value_en":"24 January 1916, Purbalingga"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"From","value_id":"Purbalingga, Jawa Tengah","value_en":"Purbalingga, Central Java"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Dikenal sebagai","label_en":"Known as","value_id":"Panglima Besar TNI pertama","value_en":"First Commander-in-Chief of the army"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Legacy","value_id":"Memimpin perang gerilya kemerdekaan","value_en":"Led the guerrilla war for independence"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Gelar","label_en":"Title","value_id":"Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia","value_en":"National Hero of Indonesia"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Wafat","label_en":"Died","value_id":"29 Januari 1950, Magelang","value_en":"29 January 1950, Magelang"}],"sections":[{"icon":"person","h_id":"Siapakah Jenderal Sudirman?","h_en":"Who Was General Sudirman?","body_id":"Jenderal Sudirman adalah Panglima Besar pertama tentara Indonesia, yang sekarang kita kenal sebagai TNI. Ia memimpin para pejuang membela kemerdekaan Indonesia dari penjajah yang ingin kembali berkuasa. Walau usianya masih muda saat menjadi panglima, ia sangat dihormati karena berani, jujur, dan taat beragama.","body_en":"General Sudirman was the first Commander-in-Chief of the Indonesian army, which we now know as the TNI. He led the fighters to defend Indonesia's independence from colonizers who wanted to rule again. Although he was still young when he became commander, he was greatly respected for being brave, honest, and devout."},{"icon":"school","h_id":"Masa Kecil & Guru","h_en":"Childhood & Teaching","body_id":"Sudirman lahir tahun 1916 di Purbalingga, Jawa Tengah, dari keluarga sederhana. Sejak kecil ia rajin belajar dan suka memimpin teman-temannya dalam kegiatan kepanduan (pramuka). Sebelum menjadi tentara, Sudirman bekerja sebagai guru dan bahkan menjadi kepala sekolah. Ia sangat dicintai murid-muridnya karena sabar dan baik hati.","body_en":"Sudirman was born in 1916 in Purbalingga, Central Java, into a simple family. From a young age he studied hard and loved leading his friends in scouting activities. Before becoming a soldier, Sudirman worked as a teacher and even became a school principal. His students loved him very much because he was patient and kind."},{"icon":"military_tech","h_id":"Perang Gerilya yang Gagah Berani","h_en":"The Brave Guerrilla War","body_id":"Saat Belanda menyerang kota Yogyakarta, Sudirman sedang sangat sakit karena penyakit di paru-parunya. Tetapi ia tidak mau menyerah. Sambil ditandu para prajuritnya, ia memimpin perang gerilya berpindah-pindah di hutan dan gunung selama tujuh bulan. Keberaniannya membuat semangat rakyat dan tentara semakin berkobar.","body_en":"When the Dutch attacked the city of Yogyakarta, Sudirman was very ill from a disease in his lungs. But he refused to give up. Carried on a stretcher by his soldiers, he led a guerrilla war, moving through forests and mountains for seven months. His courage made the spirit of the people and the army burn even brighter."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Dikenang Sepanjang Masa","h_en":"Remembered Forever","body_id":"Jenderal Sudirman wafat tahun 1950, tak lama setelah Indonesia merdeka sepenuhnya. Seluruh rakyat berduka dan mengenangnya sebagai pahlawan sejati. Namanya kini dipakai untuk jalan-jalan besar, universitas, museum, dan monumen di banyak kota. Taruna tentara bahkan harus menapaki kembali rute gerilyanya sebelum lulus.","body_en":"General Sudirman passed away in 1950, not long after Indonesia became fully independent. The whole nation mourned and remembered him as a true hero. His name is now used for major streets, a university, museums, and monuments in many cities. Army cadets even have to retrace his guerrilla route before they graduate."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Apa yang Bisa Kita Pelajari?","h_en":"What Can We Learn?","body_id":"Dari Jenderal Sudirman kita belajar untuk pantang menyerah, walau keadaan sulit dan tubuh sedang lemah. Ia mengajarkan kita mencintai tanah air dan selalu setia pada apa yang kita percayai. Semangat, kejujuran, dan keberaniannya bisa kita tiru dalam belajar dan membantu sesama setiap hari.","body_en":"From General Sudirman we learn never to give up, even when things are hard and the body is weak. He teaches us to love our homeland and to always stay loyal to what we believe in. We can copy his spirit, honesty, and courage in our studies and in helping others every day."}],"facts":[{"id":"Sudirman menjadi Panglima Besar tentara Indonesia di usia yang masih muda, sekitar 29 tahun.","en":"Sudirman became Commander-in-Chief of the Indonesian army at a young age, around 29 years old."},{"id":"Sebelum jadi tentara, ia adalah seorang guru dan kepala sekolah.","en":"Before becoming a soldier, he was a teacher and a school principal."},{"id":"Ia memimpin perang gerilya selama tujuh bulan sambil sakit dan ditandu prajuritnya.","en":"He led the guerrilla war for seven months while sick and carried on a stretcher."},{"id":"Rute gerilyanya sepanjang sekitar 100 kilometer kini diikuti oleh taruna militer.","en":"His roughly 100-kilometer guerrilla route is now retraced by military cadets."},{"id":"Wajah Jenderal Sudirman pernah ditampilkan pada uang kertas rupiah tahun 1968.","en":"General Sudirman's face once appeared on a rupiah banknote in 1968."},{"id":"Banyak jalan utama di kota-kota Indonesia diberi nama Jalan Jenderal Sudirman.","en":"Many main streets in Indonesian cities are named Jalan Jenderal Sudirman."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Panglima Besar","def_id":"Pemimpin tertinggi seluruh pasukan tentara dalam sebuah negara.","def_en":"The highest leader of all the army's troops in a country."},{"term":"Gerilya","def_id":"Cara berperang dengan berpindah-pindah secara diam-diam, lalu menyerang dengan tiba-tiba.","def_en":"A way of fighting by moving secretly from place to place, then attacking suddenly."},{"term":"TNI","def_id":"Tentara Nasional Indonesia, pasukan yang menjaga keamanan negara Indonesia.","def_en":"The Indonesian National Army, the force that guards Indonesia's safety."},{"term":"Pahlawan Nasional","def_id":"Gelar kehormatan tertinggi bagi orang yang sangat berjasa bagi bangsa Indonesia.","def_en":"The highest honorary title for someone who served the Indonesian nation greatly."},{"term":"Tandu","def_id":"Alat untuk membawa orang yang sakit dengan cara dipikul oleh beberapa orang.","def_en":"A device for carrying a sick person, lifted on the shoulders of several people."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9f71f5a427d3deff.jpg","caption_id":"Potret Jenderal Sudirman, Panglima Besar pertama tentara Indonesia.","caption_en":"A portrait of General Sudirman, the first Commander-in-Chief of the Indonesian army.","credit":"IPPHOS / Indonesian Ministry of Defense","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b5c8b2bcf9474449.jpg","caption_id":"Jenderal Sudirman memberi hormat, foto tahun 1946.","caption_en":"General Sudirman gives a salute, photographed in 1946.","credit":"IPPHOS (Indonesia Press Photo Service)","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/12fc6a4f65864a39.jpg","caption_id":"Sudirman dikelilingi rakyat yang bersemangat di Jakarta, tahun 1946.","caption_en":"Sudirman surrounded by an enthusiastic crowd in Jakarta, 1946.","credit":"IPPHOS (Indonesia Press Photo Service)","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/93cff07d10b42672.jpg","caption_id":"Museum Sasmitaloka Panglima Besar Jenderal Sudirman, lengkap dengan patungnya menunggang kuda.","caption_en":"The Sasmitaloka Museum of Commander Sudirman, complete with his statue riding a horse.","credit":"Orangescale Studio","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soedirman"},"pahlawan_ki_hajar_dewantara_1":{"id":"pahlawan_ki_hajar_dewantara_1","title_id":"Ki Hajar Dewantara","title_en":"Ki Hajar Dewantara","subtitle_id":"Bapak Pendidikan Nasional Indonesia","subtitle_en":"Father of Indonesia's national education","data_card":[{"icon":"cake","label_id":"Lahir","label_en":"Born","value_id":"2 Mei 1889, Yogyakarta","value_en":"2 May 1889, Yogyakarta"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"From","value_id":"Keluarga bangsawan Pakualaman","value_en":"The Pakualaman noble family"},{"icon":"school","label_id":"Dikenal","label_en":"Known as","value_id":"Bapak Pendidikan Nasional","value_en":"Father of National Education"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Legacy","value_id":"Pendiri Taman Siswa","value_en":"Founder of Taman Siswa schools"},{"icon":"format_quote","label_id":"Semboyan","label_en":"Motto","value_id":"Tut Wuri Handayani","value_en":"Tut Wuri Handayani"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Gelar","label_en":"Title","value_id":"Pahlawan Nasional","value_en":"National Hero"}],"sections":[{"icon":"person","h_id":"Siapa Ki Hajar Dewantara?","h_en":"Who Was Ki Hajar Dewantara?","body_id":"Nama aslinya Raden Mas Soewardi Soerjaningrat. Ia lahir dari keluarga bangsawan, tapi ia berjuang agar SEMUA anak Indonesia bisa bersekolah, bukan hanya anak orang kaya atau bangsawan. Karena jasanya, ia disebut Bapak Pendidikan Nasional.","body_en":"His real name was Raden Mas Soewardi Soerjaningrat. He was born into a noble family, but he fought so that ALL Indonesian children could go to school, not only the rich or the nobles. For this, he is called the Father of National Education."},{"icon":"edit","h_id":"Berjuang Lewat Tulisan","h_en":"Fighting With Words","body_id":"Saat muda, Ki Hajar adalah wartawan yang berani. Ia menulis kritik terkenal berjudul 'Seandainya Aku Seorang Belanda'. Tulisannya membuat penjajah marah, sehingga ia diasingkan ke negeri Belanda bersama dua sahabatnya — mereka dikenal sebagai 'Tiga Serangkai'.","body_en":"As a young man, Ki Hajar was a brave journalist. He wrote a famous criticism titled 'If I Were a Dutchman'. His writing angered the colonizers, so he was exiled to the Netherlands with two friends — together they were known as the 'Three Comrades'."},{"icon":"school","h_id":"Mendirikan Taman Siswa","h_en":"Founding Taman Siswa","body_id":"Sepulang dari pengasingan, ia mendirikan sekolah bernama Taman Siswa pada tahun 1922. Ini sekolah pertama yang memberi anak-anak pribumi kesempatan belajar. Baginya, pendidikan adalah jalan untuk memerdekakan bangsa.","body_en":"After returning from exile, he founded a school called Taman Siswa in 1922. It was the first school that gave native Indonesian children the chance to learn. To him, education was the path to freeing the nation."},{"icon":"format_quote","h_id":"Tut Wuri Handayani","h_en":"Tut Wuri Handayani","body_id":"Ki Hajar menciptakan semboyan 'Tut Wuri Handayani', artinya 'dari belakang memberi dorongan'. Seorang guru sebaiknya mendukung muridnya dari belakang. Semboyan ini sekarang menjadi lambang pendidikan Indonesia. Hari lahirnya, 2 Mei, diperingati sebagai Hari Pendidikan Nasional.","body_en":"Ki Hajar created the motto 'Tut Wuri Handayani', meaning 'from behind, giving encouragement'. A teacher should support students from behind. This motto is now the symbol of Indonesian education. His birthday, 2 May, is celebrated as National Education Day."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Yang Bisa Kita Teladani","h_en":"What We Can Learn","body_id":"Dari Ki Hajar kita belajar bahwa belajar itu hak setiap anak. Kita bisa meneladaninya dengan rajin belajar, menghargai guru, dan menolong teman agar sama-sama pintar.","body_en":"From Ki Hajar we learn that learning is every child's right. We can follow his example by studying hard, respecting teachers, and helping friends so everyone can grow smart together."}],"facts":[{"id":"Nama aslinya Raden Mas Soewardi Soerjaningrat.","en":"His real name was Raden Mas Soewardi Soerjaningrat."},{"id":"Ia mendirikan sekolah Taman Siswa pada tahun 1922.","en":"He founded the Taman Siswa schools in 1922."},{"id":"Hari lahirnya, 2 Mei, menjadi Hari Pendidikan Nasional.","en":"His birthday, 2 May, is National Education Day."},{"id":"Semboyannya 'Tut Wuri Handayani' menjadi lambang pendidikan Indonesia.","en":"His motto 'Tut Wuri Handayani' is the symbol of Indonesian education."},{"id":"Potretnya pernah dipakai pada uang kertas Rp20.000.","en":"His portrait once appeared on the 20,000-rupiah banknote."},{"id":"Ia menjadi Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia yang ke-2.","en":"He was Indonesia's 2nd-ever National Hero."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Taman Siswa","def_id":"Sekolah yang didirikan Ki Hajar agar anak pribumi bisa belajar.","def_en":"The schools Ki Hajar founded so native children could learn."},{"term":"Semboyan","def_id":"Kalimat pendek yang menjadi pegangan atau semangat.","def_en":"A short saying that becomes a guiding spirit."},{"term":"Pribumi","def_id":"Penduduk asli suatu daerah atau negeri.","def_en":"The native people of a land."},{"term":"Pengasingan","def_id":"Dijauhkan atau dibuang ke tempat lain sebagai hukuman.","def_en":"Being sent far away to another place as punishment."},{"term":"Pahlawan Nasional","def_id":"Gelar kehormatan bagi orang yang sangat berjasa bagi bangsa.","def_en":"An honorary title for someone who served the nation greatly."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/22d3507f2d88dc56.jpg","caption_id":"Ki Hajar Dewantara dengan peci dan kacamata bundar khasnya.","caption_en":"Ki Hajar Dewantara with his trademark cap and round glasses.","credit":"Uncredited","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/973afd69a6198ea5.jpg","caption_id":"Ki Hajar bersama murid-muridnya di Taman Siswa.","caption_en":"Ki Hajar with his students at Taman Siswa.","credit":"Uncredited","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c0c9ce6dcc0de3c1.jpg","caption_id":"Foto Ki Hajar Dewantara di masa mudanya.","caption_en":"A photo of Ki Hajar Dewantara in his younger years.","credit":"Uncredited","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/368d392ac84e5b40.jpg","caption_id":"'Tiga Serangkai': Douwes Dekker, Tjipto Mangoenkoesoemo, dan Soewardi.","caption_en":"The 'Three Comrades': Douwes Dekker, Tjipto Mangoenkoesoemo, and Soewardi.","credit":"Uncredited","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ki_Hadjar_Dewantara"},"pahlawan_pangeran_diponegoro_1":{"id":"pahlawan_pangeran_diponegoro_1","title_id":"Pangeran Diponegoro","title_en":"Prince Diponegoro","subtitle_id":"Pangeran Jawa pemberani yang memimpin Perang Jawa melawan penjajah Belanda demi membela rakyatnya.","subtitle_en":"A brave Javanese prince who led the Java War against Dutch colonizers to defend his people.","data_card":[{"icon":"cake","label_id":"Lahir","label_en":"Born","value_id":"11 November 1785 di Yogyakarta","value_en":"11 November 1785 in Yogyakarta"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"From","value_id":"Yogyakarta, Pulau Jawa","value_en":"Yogyakarta, Java Island"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Dikenal sebagai","label_en":"Known as","value_id":"Pemimpin Perang Jawa (1825-1830)","value_en":"Leader of the Java War (1825-1830)"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Legacy","value_id":"Lima tahun berjuang membela rakyat dari penjajah","value_en":"Five years of fighting to defend the people from colonizers"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Gelar","label_en":"Title","value_id":"Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia","value_en":"National Hero of Indonesia"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Wafat","label_en":"Died","value_id":"8 Januari 1855 di Makassar","value_en":"8 January 1855 in Makassar"}],"sections":[{"icon":"person","h_id":"Siapakah Pangeran Diponegoro?","h_en":"Who Was Prince Diponegoro?","body_id":"Pangeran Diponegoro adalah seorang pangeran dari Keraton Yogyakarta yang lahir pada tahun 1785. Ayahnya adalah Sultan Hamengkubuwana III, raja Yogyakarta. Walaupun ia seorang bangsawan, Diponegoro lebih suka tinggal bersama rakyat biasa di desa Tegalrejo daripada di istana yang mewah. Ia dikenal sebagai pribadi yang cerdas, taat beragama, dan sangat peduli kepada rakyat kecil.","body_en":"Prince Diponegoro was a prince of the Yogyakarta palace, born in 1785. His father was Sultan Hamengkubuwana III, the king of Yogyakarta. Even though he was a nobleman, Diponegoro preferred to live among ordinary people in the village of Tegalrejo rather than in the grand palace. He was known as a clever, deeply religious person who cared greatly for ordinary people."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Dekat dengan Rakyat","h_en":"Close to the People","body_id":"Sejak kecil, Diponegoro diasuh oleh nenek buyutnya di Tegalrejo. Di sana ia diajari menanam padi dan ikut bekerja bersama para petani. Karena itulah ia mengerti betul betapa berat hidup rakyat Jawa di bawah tekanan pemerintah penjajah. Ia juga sangat pandai menunggang kuda. Kuda hitamnya yang gagah bernama Kiai Gentayu, dan keahliannya berkuda kelak sangat membantunya saat berperang.","body_en":"From childhood, Diponegoro was raised by his great-grandmother in Tegalrejo. There he was taught to plant rice and worked alongside the farmers. That is why he understood so well how hard life was for the Javanese people under the colonial government. He was also a skilled horse rider. His mighty black horse was named Kiai Gentayu, and his riding skill would later help him greatly in battle."},{"icon":"military_tech","h_id":"Perang Jawa Dimulai","h_en":"The Java War Begins","body_id":"Pada tahun 1825, Diponegoro merasa marah karena Belanda memperlakukan rakyat dengan tidak adil dan membuat jalan melewati tanah miliknya tanpa izin. Maka ia bangkit memimpin perlawanan yang disebut Perang Jawa. Ribuan rakyat bergabung di bawah panji-panjinya. Selama lima tahun, dari 1825 sampai 1830, pasukan Diponegoro bertempur dengan berani melawan tentara Belanda di berbagai pelosok Pulau Jawa.","body_en":"In 1825, Diponegoro became angry because the Dutch treated the people unfairly and built a road across his land without permission. So he rose to lead a resistance called the Java War. Thousands of people joined under his banner. For five years, from 1825 to 1830, Diponegoro's forces fought bravely against the Dutch army across many corners of Java Island."},{"icon":"flag","h_id":"Pemimpin yang Cerdik","h_en":"A Clever Leader","body_id":"Diponegoro adalah pemimpin yang cerdik dan sulit ditangkap. Ia hafal seluruh medan, hutan, dan sungai di Jawa. Saat dikejar musuh, ia bisa menyeberangi Sungai Progo yang lebar lewat tempat-tempat dangkal yang hanya ia ketahui. Karena keberaniannya, ia menjadi pemimpin yang sangat dicintai rakyat dan ditakuti penjajah. Perjuangannya membuat pasukan Belanda kewalahan selama bertahun-tahun.","body_en":"Diponegoro was a clever leader who was hard to capture. He knew by heart all the terrain, forests, and rivers of Java. When chased by the enemy, he could cross the wide Progo River through shallow spots that only he knew. Because of his courage, he became a leader deeply loved by the people and feared by the colonizers. His struggle kept the Dutch troops in difficulty for many years."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Pahlawan yang Dikenang","h_en":"A Hero Remembered","body_id":"Setelah lima tahun berjuang, Diponegoro akhirnya ditangkap melalui sebuah perundingan dan diasingkan jauh ke Manado, lalu ke Makassar. Ia wafat di Makassar pada tahun 1855. Meskipun begitu, semangatnya tidak pernah padam. Pangeran Diponegoro dihormati sebagai Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia, dan kisah keberaniannya menjadi sumber semangat bagi para pejuang kemerdekaan Indonesia hingga hari ini.","body_en":"After five years of struggle, Diponegoro was finally captured through a negotiation and exiled far away to Manado, then to Makassar. He passed away in Makassar in 1855. Even so, his spirit never faded. Prince Diponegoro is honored as a National Hero of Indonesia, and the story of his courage became a source of inspiration for Indonesia's freedom fighters to this day."}],"facts":[{"id":"Perang Jawa yang dipimpin Diponegoro berlangsung selama lima tahun, dari 1825 sampai 1830.","en":"The Java War led by Diponegoro lasted five years, from 1825 to 1830."},{"id":"Nama \"Diponegoro\" berarti seseorang yang memberi pencerahan dan kemakmuran kepada negara.","en":"The name \"Diponegoro\" means a person who brings enlightenment and prosperity to the country."},{"id":"Kuda hitam kesayangannya yang gagah bernama Kiai Gentayu.","en":"His beloved mighty black horse was named Kiai Gentayu."},{"id":"Walaupun seorang pangeran, ia lebih suka tinggal bersama rakyat di desa Tegalrejo.","en":"Although he was a prince, he preferred to live among the people in the village of Tegalrejo."},{"id":"Diponegoro diasingkan ke Manado dan Makassar setelah tertangkap pada tahun 1830.","en":"Diponegoro was exiled to Manado and Makassar after being captured in 1830."},{"id":"Ia dihormati sebagai salah satu Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia yang paling terkenal.","en":"He is honored as one of Indonesia's most famous National Heroes."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Pangeran","def_id":"Anak laki-laki seorang raja atau sultan dari keluarga kerajaan.","def_en":"The son of a king or sultan, a member of the royal family."},{"term":"Penjajah","def_id":"Bangsa asing yang menguasai dan menindas negeri lain.","def_en":"A foreign nation that takes control of and oppresses another land."},{"term":"Perang Jawa","def_id":"Perlawanan besar rakyat Jawa melawan Belanda yang dipimpin Diponegoro.","def_en":"The great resistance of the Javanese people against the Dutch, led by Diponegoro."},{"term":"Keraton","def_id":"Istana tempat tinggal raja atau sultan di Jawa.","def_en":"The palace where a king or sultan lives in Java."},{"term":"Diasingkan","def_id":"Dipaksa pergi jauh dari kampung halaman sebagai hukuman.","def_en":"Forced to live far away from one's homeland as a punishment."},{"term":"Pahlawan Nasional","def_id":"Gelar kehormatan untuk orang yang sangat berjasa bagi bangsa.","def_en":"An honorary title for someone who has greatly served the nation."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2bad97a1315842df.jpg","caption_id":"Potret Pangeran Diponegoro mengenakan sorban dan keris di pinggangnya, gambar terkenal dari tahun 1835.","caption_en":"A portrait of Prince Diponegoro wearing a turban with a kris dagger at his waist, a famous image from 1835.","credit":"Lithograph by C. C. A. Last (1835), after a drawing by A. J. Bik","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b316a77cff52a889.jpg","caption_id":"Lukisan terkenal karya Raden Saleh yang menggambarkan saat Pangeran Diponegoro (berjubah putih di tengah) ditangkap Belanda.","caption_en":"A famous painting by Raden Saleh showing the moment Prince Diponegoro (in white robes at the center) was captured by the Dutch.","credit":"Raden Saleh","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diponegoro"},"pahlawan_pattimura":{"id":"pahlawan_pattimura","title_id":"Kapitan Pattimura","title_en":"Captain Pattimura","subtitle_id":"Pahlawan pemberani dari Maluku yang memimpin rakyat melawan penjajah, dan wajahnya kini ada di uang Rp1.000.","subtitle_en":"A brave hero from Maluku who led the people against colonizers, and whose face is now on the 1,000 rupiah note.","data_card":[{"icon":"cake","label_id":"Lahir","label_en":"Born","value_id":"8 Juni 1783 di Negeri Haria, Saparua","value_en":"8 June 1783 in Haria, Saparua"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"From","value_id":"Pulau Saparua, Maluku","value_en":"Saparua Island, Maluku"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Dikenal sebagai","label_en":"Known as","value_id":"Pemimpin perlawanan rakyat Maluku tahun 1817","value_en":"Leader of the Maluku people's resistance in 1817"},{"icon":"payments","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Legacy","value_id":"Wajahnya diabadikan pada uang kertas Rp1.000","value_en":"His face is honored on the 1,000 rupiah banknote"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Gelar","label_en":"Title","value_id":"Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia","value_en":"National Hero of Indonesia"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Wafat","label_en":"Died","value_id":"16 Desember 1817 di Ambon","value_en":"16 December 1817 in Ambon"}],"sections":[{"icon":"person","h_id":"Siapakah Kapitan Pattimura?","h_en":"Who Was Captain Pattimura?","body_id":"Kapitan Pattimura bernama asli Thomas Matulessy. Ia lahir pada tahun 1783 di Negeri Haria, di Pulau Saparua, Maluku. Sejak muda, ia dikenal pemberani, kuat, dan pandai memimpin. Rakyat Maluku sangat menghormatinya. Karena keberanian dan jiwa kepemimpinannya, ia diangkat menjadi kapitan, yaitu pemimpin pasukan yang dipercaya untuk memimpin perjuangan rakyat.","body_en":"Captain Pattimura's real name was Thomas Matulessy. He was born in 1783 in the village of Haria, on Saparua Island, Maluku. From a young age, he was known as brave, strong, and a good leader. The people of Maluku respected him greatly. Because of his courage and leadership, he was chosen as a kapitan, a trusted commander to lead the people's struggle."},{"icon":"sailing","h_id":"Negeri Rempah-rempah","h_en":"The Land of Spices","body_id":"Maluku terkenal di seluruh dunia sebagai Kepulauan Rempah-rempah. Di sanalah tumbuh cengkih dan pala yang sangat berharga. Karena rempah-rempah itu, bangsa Belanda datang dan ingin menguasai semuanya sendiri. Mereka memaksa rakyat menjual hasil panen dengan harga murah dan menebang pohon cengkih milik rakyat. Aturan yang berat dan tidak adil itu membuat rakyat Maluku menderita dan marah.","body_en":"Maluku was famous all over the world as the Spice Islands. There grew cloves and nutmeg that were extremely valuable. Because of these spices, the Dutch came and wanted to control everything for themselves. They forced the people to sell their harvest cheaply and cut down the people's clove trees. These harsh and unfair rules made the people of Maluku suffer and grow angry."},{"icon":"military_tech","h_id":"Perlawanan di Saparua","h_en":"The Resistance at Saparua","body_id":"Pada tahun 1817, rakyat Maluku tidak mau lagi ditindas. Mereka memilih Thomas Matulessy sebagai pemimpin perjuangan dan memberinya gelar Kapitan Pattimura. Dengan senjata sederhana seperti parang dan tombak, pasukannya berani menyerang benteng Belanda yang kuat di Pulau Saparua. Keberanian rakyat Maluku di bawah pimpinan Pattimura membuat penjajah terkejut dan kewalahan.","body_en":"In 1817, the people of Maluku refused to be oppressed any longer. They chose Thomas Matulessy as their leader and gave him the title Captain Pattimura. With simple weapons like machetes and spears, his forces bravely attacked the strong Dutch fort on Saparua Island. The courage of the Maluku people under Pattimura's leadership shocked and overwhelmed the colonizers."},{"icon":"flag","h_id":"Pemimpin yang Pemberani","h_en":"A Courageous Leader","body_id":"Pattimura memimpin dengan gagah berani dan tidak pernah takut. Ia bertempur bersama para kapitan lain dan rakyat yang bersatu padu. Walaupun pasukan Belanda jauh lebih besar dan bersenjata lengkap, semangat Pattimura tidak pernah goyah. Ia berjuang sampai akhir demi tanah airnya dan kebebasan rakyat Maluku, menjadi teladan keberanian bagi semua orang.","body_en":"Pattimura led with great courage and was never afraid. He fought alongside other captains and a united people. Even though the Dutch army was far larger and fully armed, Pattimura's spirit never wavered. He fought to the very end for his homeland and the freedom of the Maluku people, becoming an example of bravery for everyone."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Pahlawan di Uang Rupiah","h_en":"A Hero on the Rupiah","body_id":"Setelah berjuang dengan gigih, Pattimura akhirnya tertangkap dan gugur sebagai pahlawan pada tahun 1817. Bangsa Indonesia tidak pernah melupakan jasanya. Pada tahun 1973, ia ditetapkan sebagai Pahlawan Nasional. Untuk mengenangnya, wajah Kapitan Pattimura diabadikan pada uang kertas Rp1.000. Setiap kali kita melihat uang itu, kita diingatkan pada keberanian sang pahlawan dari Maluku.","body_en":"After fighting fiercely, Pattimura was finally captured and died as a hero in 1817. The Indonesian nation has never forgotten his service. In 1973, he was named a National Hero. To remember him, Captain Pattimura's face is honored on the 1,000 rupiah banknote. Every time we see that money, we are reminded of the courage of the hero from Maluku."}],"facts":[{"id":"Nama asli Kapitan Pattimura adalah Thomas Matulessy.","en":"Captain Pattimura's real name was Thomas Matulessy."},{"id":"Wajah Pattimura ada pada uang kertas Indonesia pecahan Rp1.000.","en":"Pattimura's face appears on Indonesia's 1,000 rupiah banknote."},{"id":"Ia memimpin perlawanan rakyat Maluku melawan Belanda pada tahun 1817 di Saparua.","en":"He led the Maluku people's resistance against the Dutch in 1817 at Saparua."},{"id":"Senjata khas Maluku yang terkenal adalah parang dan salawaku (perisai).","en":"The famous traditional Maluku weapons are the machete and the salawaku (shield)."},{"id":"Maluku dijuluki Kepulauan Rempah-rempah karena kaya akan cengkih dan pala.","en":"Maluku is nicknamed the Spice Islands because it is rich in cloves and nutmeg."},{"id":"Pattimura ditetapkan sebagai Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia pada tahun 1973.","en":"Pattimura was named a National Hero of Indonesia in 1973."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Kapitan","def_id":"Sebutan untuk pemimpin pasukan atau panglima perang di Maluku.","def_en":"A title for a troop leader or war commander in Maluku."},{"term":"Maluku","def_id":"Daerah kepulauan di timur Indonesia yang kaya akan rempah-rempah.","def_en":"A group of islands in eastern Indonesia rich in spices."},{"term":"Rempah-rempah","def_id":"Tanaman beraroma seperti cengkih dan pala yang dipakai untuk masakan.","def_en":"Fragrant plants like cloves and nutmeg used to flavor food."},{"term":"Cengkih","def_id":"Bunga kering beraroma kuat yang dahulu sangat mahal harganya.","def_en":"A dried flower bud with a strong aroma that was once very expensive."},{"term":"Penjajah","def_id":"Bangsa asing yang menguasai dan menindas negeri lain.","def_en":"A foreign nation that takes control of and oppresses another land."},{"term":"Pahlawan Nasional","def_id":"Gelar kehormatan untuk orang yang sangat berjasa bagi bangsa.","def_en":"An honorary title for someone who has greatly served the nation."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/859101e56ab04b26.jpg","caption_id":"Pemandangan Teluk Ambon di Maluku, tanah air Kapitan Pattimura, dengan perahu kora-kora khas Maluku di laut.","caption_en":"A view of Ambon Bay in Maluku, the homeland of Captain Pattimura, with a traditional Maluku kora-kora boat at sea.","credit":"Q.M.R. Ver Huell (1787-1860)","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/28106139b5dffc5b.jpg","caption_id":"Cengkih, rempah berharga dari Maluku. Karena rempah inilah penjajah datang, dan rakyat pun bangkit melawan.","caption_en":"Cloves, the precious spice of Maluku. It was for this spice that colonizers came, and the people rose up to fight back.","credit":"Jorge Barrios","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pattimura"},"pahlawan_ra_kartini":{"id":"pahlawan_ra_kartini","title_id":"R.A. Kartini","title_en":"R.A. Kartini","subtitle_id":"Pelopor emansipasi dan pendidikan untuk anak perempuan Indonesia","subtitle_en":"Pioneer of women's rights and education for Indonesian girls","data_card":[{"icon":"cake","label_id":"Lahir","label_en":"Born","value_id":"21 April 1879, Jepara","value_en":"21 April 1879, Jepara"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"From","value_id":"Jepara, Jawa Tengah","value_en":"Jepara, Central Java"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Dikenal sebagai","label_en":"Known as","value_id":"Pelopor emansipasi wanita","value_en":"Pioneer of women's emancipation"},{"icon":"school","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Legacy","value_id":"Pendidikan untuk anak perempuan","value_en":"Education for girls"},{"icon":"military_tech","label_id":"Gelar","label_en":"Title","value_id":"Pahlawan Nasional Indonesia","value_en":"National Hero of Indonesia"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Wafat","label_en":"Died","value_id":"17 September 1904, Rembang","value_en":"17 September 1904, Rembang"}],"sections":[{"icon":"person","h_id":"Siapakah Kartini?","h_en":"Who Was Kartini?","body_id":"Raden Ajeng Kartini adalah seorang pahlawan nasional Indonesia yang berjuang agar perempuan punya hak yang sama dengan laki-laki, terutama hak untuk belajar. Ia lahir tahun 1879 di Jepara, Jawa Tengah, dari keluarga bangsawan Jawa. Pada zamannya, anak perempuan tidak boleh sekolah tinggi, tetapi Kartini berani bermimpi besar untuk mengubahnya.","body_en":"Raden Ajeng Kartini was a national hero of Indonesia who fought so that women could have the same rights as men, especially the right to learn. She was born in 1879 in Jepara, Central Java, into a Javanese noble family. In her time, girls were not allowed to attend higher school, but Kartini bravely dreamed big to change that."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Masa Kecil & Cita-cita","h_en":"Childhood & Dreams","body_id":"Sejak kecil, Kartini sangat suka membaca buku, koran, dan majalah dari Eropa. Ia boleh bersekolah sampai umur 12 tahun, lalu harus tinggal di rumah karena adat 'pingitan'. Walau begitu, ia tetap belajar sendiri dan menulis surat kepada teman-temannya. Dari buku-buku itu, Kartini ingin perempuan Indonesia menjadi pintar dan bebas memilih masa depannya.","body_en":"From a young age, Kartini loved reading books, newspapers, and magazines from Europe. She was allowed to go to school until she was 12, then had to stay at home because of the custom of 'pingitan' (seclusion). Even so, she kept studying on her own and wrote letters to her friends. From those books, Kartini wished for Indonesian women to become smart and free to choose their own future."},{"icon":"campaign","h_id":"Perjuangan Kartini","h_en":"Kartini's Struggle","body_id":"Kartini menulis banyak surat tentang impiannya agar anak perempuan boleh bersekolah dan hidup setara. Ia bahkan mendirikan sekolah kecil untuk perempuan di rumahnya. Surat-suratnya penuh harapan dan keberanian. Setelah ia wafat, surat-surat itu dikumpulkan menjadi sebuah buku terkenal berjudul 'Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang'.","body_en":"Kartini wrote many letters about her dream that girls could go to school and live as equals. She even started a small school for women in her own home. Her letters were full of hope and courage. After she passed away, those letters were collected into a famous book called 'Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang' (After Darkness Comes Light)."},{"icon":"school","h_id":"Warisan untuk Indonesia","h_en":"A Legacy for Indonesia","body_id":"Berkat semangat Kartini, makin banyak sekolah dibuka untuk anak perempuan di seluruh Indonesia. Banyak sekolah bahkan diberi nama 'Sekolah Kartini' untuk menghormatinya. Wajahnya pernah dicetak di uang kertas Indonesia. Setiap tanggal 21 April, seluruh Indonesia merayakan Hari Kartini untuk mengenang jasanya.","body_en":"Thanks to Kartini's spirit, more and more schools opened for girls all across Indonesia. Many schools were even named 'Kartini Schools' in her honor. Her face once appeared on Indonesian banknotes. Every 21 April, all of Indonesia celebrates Kartini Day to remember her good deeds."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Apa yang Bisa Kita Pelajari?","h_en":"What Can We Learn?","body_id":"Dari Kartini kita belajar bahwa setiap anak, laki-laki maupun perempuan, berhak untuk belajar dan bermimpi besar. Ia mengajarkan kita untuk berani memperjuangkan apa yang benar, walau keadaan terasa sulit. Seperti judul bukunya, sesudah gelap pasti akan terbit terang. Ayo terus belajar dan saling membantu!","body_en":"From Kartini we learn that every child, boy or girl, has the right to learn and dream big. She teaches us to bravely stand up for what is right, even when things feel hard. Just like the title of her book, after darkness, light will always come. Let's keep learning and helping one another!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Kartini lahir pada 21 April 1879, dan tanggal itu kini dirayakan sebagai Hari Kartini.","en":"Kartini was born on 21 April 1879, and that date is now celebrated as Kartini Day."},{"id":"Karena bisa berbahasa Belanda, Kartini bersahabat lewat surat dengan teman-teman di Eropa.","en":"Because she could speak Dutch, Kartini made friends in Europe through letters."},{"id":"Surat-suratnya dibukukan menjadi 'Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang' pada tahun 1911.","en":"Her letters became the book 'After Darkness Comes Light' in 1911."},{"id":"Kartini mendirikan sekolah untuk anak perempuan di Jepara dan kemudian di Rembang.","en":"Kartini founded schools for girls in Jepara and later in Rembang."},{"id":"Banyak sekolah di Indonesia diberi nama 'Sekolah Kartini' untuk menghormatinya.","en":"Many schools in Indonesia are named 'Kartini Schools' to honor her."},{"id":"Wajah Kartini pernah muncul di uang kertas 5 rupiah keluaran tahun 1952.","en":"Kartini's face once appeared on the 5-rupiah banknote issued in 1952."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Emansipasi","def_id":"Perjuangan agar perempuan punya hak dan kesempatan yang sama dengan laki-laki.","def_en":"The struggle for women to have the same rights and chances as men."},{"term":"Pahlawan Nasional","def_id":"Gelar kehormatan tertinggi bagi orang yang sangat berjasa bagi bangsa Indonesia.","def_en":"The highest honorary title for someone who served the Indonesian nation greatly."},{"term":"Bangsawan","def_id":"Keluarga keturunan raja atau pejabat tinggi, seperti keluarga Kartini.","def_en":"A family descended from kings or high officials, like Kartini's family."},{"term":"Pingitan","def_id":"Adat lama yang mengharuskan anak perempuan tinggal di rumah dan tidak keluar bebas.","def_en":"An old custom that required girls to stay at home and not go out freely."},{"term":"Hari Kartini","def_id":"Hari peringatan setiap 21 April untuk mengenang jasa R.A. Kartini.","def_en":"A day of remembrance every 21 April to honor R.A. Kartini's service."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5e77550865536d42.jpg","caption_id":"Potret Raden Ajeng Kartini, pahlawan emansipasi perempuan Indonesia.","caption_en":"A portrait of Raden Ajeng Kartini, hero of Indonesian women's emancipation.","credit":"Tropenmuseum (fotografer tidak diketahui)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/90c76ad81eca510a.jpg","caption_id":"Sampul buku 'Door Duisternis tot Licht' (Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang), kumpulan surat Kartini.","caption_en":"Cover of 'Door Duisternis tot Licht' (After Darkness Comes Light), the collection of Kartini's letters.","credit":"G.C.T. van Dorp & Co.","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1db5e7847bf8e055.jpg","caption_id":"Gedung Sekolah Kartini, salah satu sekolah yang dinamai untuk menghormati Kartini.","caption_en":"A Kartini School building, one of the schools named in Kartini's honor.","credit":"Tropenmuseum (fotografer tidak diketahui)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e9522d7e9f14dd85.jpg","caption_id":"Wajah Kartini pada uang kertas 5 rupiah Indonesia tahun 1952.","caption_en":"Kartini's face on the Indonesian 5-rupiah banknote of 1952.","credit":"Bank Indonesia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kartini"},"profesi_dokter":{"id":"profesi_dokter","title_id":"Dokter","title_en":"Doctor","subtitle_id":"Orang yang menolong dan merawat kita ketika sakit agar bisa sehat kembali.","subtitle_en":"The person who helps and cares for us when we are sick so we can get well again.","data_card":[{"icon":"medical_services","label_id":"Tugas","label_en":"Job","value_id":"Memeriksa dan menyembuhkan orang sakit","value_en":"Checks and heals people who are sick"},{"icon":"local_hospital","label_id":"Tempat kerja","label_en":"Workplace","value_id":"Rumah sakit, klinik, dan puskesmas","value_en":"Hospitals, clinics, and health centers"},{"icon":"stethoscope","label_id":"Alat","label_en":"Tools","value_id":"Stetoskop, termometer, dan obat","value_en":"Stethoscope, thermometer, and medicine"},{"icon":"school","label_id":"Pendidikan","label_en":"Training","value_id":"Sekolah kedokteran bertahun-tahun","value_en":"Many years of medical school"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Why important","value_id":"Menolong orang agar sehat kembali","value_en":"Helps people become healthy again"}],"sections":[{"icon":"medical_services","h_id":"Apa Itu Dokter?","h_en":"What Is a Doctor?","body_id":"Dokter adalah orang yang belajar khusus untuk menyembuhkan orang yang sakit. Ketika kita demam, batuk, atau terluka, dokterlah yang memeriksa tubuh kita dan mencari tahu apa yang salah. Setelah itu dokter memberi obat atau saran agar kita cepat sembuh. Dokter selalu berusaha membuat kita merasa lebih baik dan tetap sehat.","body_en":"A doctor is someone who has studied specially to heal people who are sick. When we have a fever, a cough, or a wound, it is the doctor who examines our body and finds out what is wrong. After that the doctor gives medicine or advice so we get better quickly. A doctor always tries to make us feel better and stay healthy."},{"icon":"local_hospital","h_id":"Di Mana Dokter Bekerja?","h_en":"Where Do Doctors Work?","body_id":"Dokter bekerja di banyak tempat. Ada yang bertugas di rumah sakit besar, ada juga yang di klinik atau puskesmas dekat rumah kita. Beberapa dokter pergi ke desa-desa yang jauh untuk menolong orang yang tinggal di sana. Di mana pun mereka berada, dokter siap membantu siapa saja yang membutuhkan, baik anak-anak maupun orang dewasa.","body_en":"Doctors work in many places. Some serve in big hospitals, while others are at clinics or health centers near our home. Some doctors travel to faraway villages to help the people who live there. Wherever they are, doctors are ready to help anyone in need, both children and grown-ups."},{"icon":"stethoscope","h_id":"Alat dan Sekolahnya","h_en":"Tools and Schooling","body_id":"Untuk memeriksa pasien, dokter memakai alat seperti stetoskop untuk mendengar detak jantung dan termometer untuk mengukur suhu tubuh. Mereka juga memberi obat yang tepat. Menjadi dokter tidaklah mudah. Mereka harus bersekolah di sekolah kedokteran selama bertahun-tahun dan banyak berlatih sebelum boleh merawat pasien sendiri.","body_en":"To examine patients, doctors use tools such as a stethoscope to listen to the heartbeat and a thermometer to measure body temperature. They also give the right medicine. Becoming a doctor is not easy. They must study at medical school for many years and practice a lot before they are allowed to care for patients on their own."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Mengapa Dokter Penting?","h_en":"Why Are Doctors Important?","body_id":"Dokter sangat penting karena mereka menjaga kesehatan kita semua. Mereka menolong orang yang sakit agar sembuh dan mengajari kita cara hidup sehat, seperti rajin mencuci tangan dan makan makanan bergizi. Berkat dokter, banyak penyakit bisa dicegah dan disembuhkan, sehingga kita bisa terus bermain dan belajar dengan ceria.","body_en":"Doctors are very important because they keep us all healthy. They help sick people recover and teach us how to live healthily, such as washing our hands often and eating nutritious food. Thanks to doctors, many illnesses can be prevented and cured, so we can keep playing and learning happily."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Cara Kita Berterima Kasih","h_en":"How We Can Say Thank You","body_id":"Kita bisa berterima kasih kepada dokter dengan menjaga tubuh kita sendiri agar tetap sehat. Saat berkunjung ke dokter, kita sebaiknya bersikap tenang, menjawab pertanyaan dengan jujur, dan menuruti nasihatnya. Tidak lupa, kita bisa mengucapkan terima kasih dengan senyuman karena mereka telah bekerja keras menolong kita.","body_en":"We can thank doctors by taking care of our own body so it stays healthy. When we visit a doctor, we should stay calm, answer questions honestly, and follow their advice. And we must not forget to say thank you with a smile, because they have worked hard to help us."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kata \"dokter\" berasal dari bahasa Latin yang berarti guru atau pengajar.","en":"The word \"doctor\" comes from a Latin word that means teacher."},{"id":"Dokter memakai stetoskop untuk mendengarkan detak jantung dan napas kita.","en":"Doctors use a stethoscope to listen to our heartbeat and breathing."},{"id":"Di Indonesia, seseorang harus belajar sekitar lima tahun untuk menjadi dokter.","en":"In Indonesia, a person must study for about five years to become a doctor."},{"id":"Dokter mengucapkan janji khusus untuk selalu menolong orang sakit.","en":"Doctors take a special promise to always help sick people."},{"id":"Ada dokter gigi yang khusus merawat dan menjaga kesehatan gigi kita.","en":"There are dentists who especially care for and protect our teeth."},{"id":"Beberapa dokter bahkan menolong pasien dari jarak jauh lewat layar.","en":"Some doctors even help patients from far away through a screen."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Dokter","def_id":"Orang yang belajar khusus untuk menyembuhkan orang yang sakit.","def_en":"A person trained specially to heal people who are sick."},{"term":"Stetoskop","def_id":"Alat yang dipakai dokter untuk mendengar detak jantung dan napas.","def_en":"A tool doctors use to listen to the heartbeat and breathing."},{"term":"Pasien","def_id":"Orang sakit yang sedang diperiksa atau dirawat oleh dokter.","def_en":"A sick person who is being examined or cared for by a doctor."},{"term":"Rumah sakit","def_id":"Tempat besar untuk merawat orang sakit dengan banyak dokter dan perawat.","def_en":"A large place to care for sick people with many doctors and nurses."},{"term":"Puskesmas","def_id":"Pusat kesehatan kecil di dekat rumah untuk berobat sehari-hari.","def_en":"A small health center near home for everyday medical care."},{"term":"Obat","def_id":"Sesuatu yang diminum atau dipakai agar tubuh cepat sembuh.","def_en":"Something taken or used to help the body heal quickly."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/97c64c2e2155c589.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang dokter berjas putih sedang berbincang di halaman sebuah rumah sakit.","caption_en":"A doctor in a white coat talking in the yard of a hospital.","credit":"IICD from The Hague, The Netherlands","license":"CC BY 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dokter"},"profesi_guru":{"id":"profesi_guru","title_id":"Guru","title_en":"Teacher","subtitle_id":"Orang yang mengajar dan mendidik kita agar pintar dan menjadi anak yang baik.","subtitle_en":"The person who teaches and guides us to become smart and kind.","data_card":[{"icon":"menu_book","label_id":"Tugas","label_en":"Job","value_id":"Mengajar, mendidik, dan membimbing murid","value_en":"Teaches, educates, and guides students"},{"icon":"school","label_id":"Tempat kerja","label_en":"Workplace","value_id":"Sekolah dan ruang kelas","value_en":"Schools and classrooms"},{"icon":"edit","label_id":"Alat","label_en":"Tools","value_id":"Papan tulis, buku, dan spidol","value_en":"Whiteboard, books, and markers"},{"icon":"cast_for_education","label_id":"Pendidikan","label_en":"Training","value_id":"Kuliah keguruan di perguruan tinggi","value_en":"Teacher training at university"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Why important","value_id":"Membuat kita pandai dan berbudi baik","value_en":"Helps us become clever and good-hearted"}],"sections":[{"icon":"menu_book","h_id":"Apa Itu Guru?","h_en":"What Is a Teacher?","body_id":"Guru adalah orang yang mengajarkan ilmu kepada kita. Di sekolah, guru membantu kita belajar membaca, menulis, berhitung, dan banyak hal menarik lainnya. Tetapi guru tidak hanya mengajar pelajaran. Mereka juga mendidik kita agar menjadi anak yang jujur, sopan, dan suka menolong. Karena itu guru sering disebut pahlawan tanpa tanda jasa.","body_en":"A teacher is someone who shares knowledge with us. At school, teachers help us learn to read, write, count, and many other interesting things. But teachers do not only teach lessons. They also guide us to become honest, polite, and helpful children. That is why teachers are often called heroes without medals."},{"icon":"school","h_id":"Di Mana Guru Bekerja?","h_en":"Where Do Teachers Work?","body_id":"Kebanyakan guru bekerja di sekolah, di dalam ruang kelas bersama murid-muridnya. Ada guru taman kanak-kanak, guru sekolah dasar, sampai guru sekolah menengah. Ada juga guru yang mengajar di tempat lain, seperti tempat les atau di rumah. Di mana pun mereka mengajar, guru selalu berusaha agar setiap murid bisa mengerti pelajaran.","body_en":"Most teachers work in schools, inside classrooms together with their students. There are kindergarten teachers, primary school teachers, and high school teachers. Some teachers also teach in other places, such as tutoring centers or at home. Wherever they teach, teachers always try to help every student understand the lesson."},{"icon":"edit","h_id":"Alat dan Sekolahnya","h_en":"Tools and Schooling","body_id":"Untuk mengajar, guru memakai papan tulis, buku, kapur atau spidol, dan kadang gambar serta layar. Dengan alat-alat itu, pelajaran menjadi lebih mudah dimengerti. Sebelum menjadi guru, seseorang harus kuliah dulu di sekolah keguruan agar pandai mengajar. Mereka belajar cara menjelaskan pelajaran dengan sabar dan menyenangkan.","body_en":"To teach, teachers use a whiteboard, books, chalk or markers, and sometimes pictures and screens. With these tools, lessons become easier to understand. Before becoming a teacher, a person must first study at a teaching college so they can teach well. They learn how to explain lessons with patience and in a fun way."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Mengapa Guru Penting?","h_en":"Why Are Teachers Important?","body_id":"Guru sangat penting karena merekalah yang membuat kita pandai. Hampir semua orang hebat, seperti dokter, pilot, dan ilmuwan, dulu diajar oleh seorang guru. Guru membuka pintu ilmu untuk kita dan menolong kita menggapai cita-cita. Tanpa guru, kita akan sulit belajar membaca, menulis, dan memahami dunia di sekitar kita.","body_en":"Teachers are very important because they are the ones who make us clever. Almost every great person, such as doctors, pilots, and scientists, was once taught by a teacher. Teachers open the door of knowledge for us and help us reach our dreams. Without teachers, it would be hard for us to learn to read, write, and understand the world around us."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Cara Kita Berterima Kasih","h_en":"How We Can Say Thank You","body_id":"Kita bisa membahagiakan guru dengan rajin belajar dan mendengarkan saat mereka mengajar. Bersikap sopan, mengerjakan tugas, dan tidak ribut di kelas adalah cara menghormati guru. Di Indonesia, setiap tanggal 25 November kita merayakan Hari Guru untuk berterima kasih atas semua jasa mereka. Ucapan terima kasih yang tulus pun sangat berarti bagi guru.","body_en":"We can make teachers happy by studying hard and listening when they teach. Being polite, doing our homework, and not being noisy in class are ways to respect teachers. In Indonesia, every 25th of November we celebrate Teacher's Day to thank them for all they do. Even a sincere thank-you means a great deal to a teacher."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kata \"guru\" berasal dari bahasa Sanskerta yang artinya \"berat\" atau dihormati.","en":"The word \"guru\" comes from Sanskrit and means \"heavy\" or respected."},{"id":"Guru sering disebut pahlawan tanpa tanda jasa karena jasanya sangat besar.","en":"Teachers are often called heroes without medals because they do so much."},{"id":"Di Indonesia, Hari Guru dirayakan setiap tanggal 25 November.","en":"In Indonesia, Teacher's Day is celebrated every 25th of November."},{"id":"Hampir semua pekerjaan hebat dimulai dari belajar bersama seorang guru.","en":"Almost every great job begins with learning from a teacher."},{"id":"Guru tidak hanya mengajar ilmu, tetapi juga mengajarkan sopan santun.","en":"Teachers do not only teach knowledge, but also good manners."},{"id":"Seorang guru harus kuliah dulu sebelum boleh mengajar di sekolah.","en":"A teacher must study at college first before being allowed to teach at school."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Guru","def_id":"Orang yang mengajar ilmu dan mendidik murid agar menjadi baik.","def_en":"A person who teaches knowledge and guides students to be good."},{"term":"Murid","def_id":"Anak atau orang yang sedang belajar dari seorang guru.","def_en":"A child or person who is learning from a teacher."},{"term":"Kelas","def_id":"Ruang di sekolah tempat guru mengajar para murid.","def_en":"A room at school where a teacher teaches the students."},{"term":"Papan tulis","def_id":"Papan tempat guru menulis pelajaran agar dilihat semua murid.","def_en":"A board where a teacher writes lessons for all students to see."},{"term":"Mendidik","def_id":"Membimbing seseorang agar pandai dan berperilaku baik.","def_en":"To guide someone to become clever and behave well."},{"term":"Hari Guru","def_id":"Hari khusus untuk menghormati dan berterima kasih kepada guru.","def_en":"A special day to honor and thank teachers."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2579f0e657ceb61a.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang guru di Indonesia mengajar para murid berseragam di dalam kelas.","caption_en":"A teacher in Indonesia teaches uniformed students inside a classroom.","credit":"Achmad Fazeri","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9439ef773aef2681.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang guru menjelaskan pelajaran sambil menunjuk papan tulis di depan kelas.","caption_en":"A teacher explains a lesson while pointing at the whiteboard in front of the class.","credit":"Harrison Keely","license":"CC BY 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guru"},"profesi_petani":{"id":"profesi_petani","title_id":"Petani","title_en":"Farmer","subtitle_id":"Orang yang menanam padi, sayur, dan buah agar kita semua punya makanan.","subtitle_en":"The person who grows rice, vegetables, and fruit so we all have food.","data_card":[{"icon":"agriculture","label_id":"Tugas","label_en":"Job","value_id":"Menanam dan merawat tanaman pangan","value_en":"Plants and cares for food crops"},{"icon":"grass","label_id":"Tempat kerja","label_en":"Workplace","value_id":"Sawah, ladang, dan kebun","value_en":"Rice fields, farms, and gardens"},{"icon":"construction","label_id":"Alat","label_en":"Tools","value_id":"Cangkul, sabit, dan traktor","value_en":"Hoe, sickle, and tractor"},{"icon":"wb_sunny","label_id":"Cara kerja","label_en":"How they work","value_id":"Bekerja keras mengikuti musim","value_en":"Works hard following the seasons"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Jasa","label_en":"Why important","value_id":"Menanam makanan untuk kita semua","value_en":"Grows the food for all of us"}],"sections":[{"icon":"agriculture","h_id":"Apa Itu Petani?","h_en":"What Is a Farmer?","body_id":"Petani adalah orang yang mengolah tanah untuk menanam tanaman, seperti padi, jagung, sayur, dan buah. Mereka menanam benih, menyiramnya, dan merawatnya sampai tumbuh besar. Setelah masak, hasil panen itu dipanen lalu dikirim ke pasar. Berkat petani, kita bisa makan nasi setiap hari dan menikmati banyak makanan lezat lainnya.","body_en":"A farmer is a person who works the land to grow plants, such as rice, corn, vegetables, and fruit. They plant seeds, water them, and care for them until they grow big. Once ripe, the harvest is gathered and sent to the market. Thanks to farmers, we can eat rice every day and enjoy many other delicious foods."},{"icon":"grass","h_id":"Di Mana Petani Bekerja?","h_en":"Where Do Farmers Work?","body_id":"Petani bekerja di luar ruangan, di sawah, ladang, dan kebun. Di Indonesia, banyak petani menanam padi di sawah yang berair dan berwarna hijau. Ada juga petani yang menanam sayur di ladang, berkebun buah, atau bahkan memanen rumput laut di tepi laut. Mereka bekerja di bawah sinar matahari, mengikuti musim hujan dan musim kemarau.","body_en":"Farmers work outdoors, in rice fields, farms, and gardens. In Indonesia, many farmers grow rice in green, watery paddy fields. There are also farmers who grow vegetables in the fields, tend fruit gardens, or even harvest seaweed by the sea. They work under the sun, following the rainy and dry seasons."},{"icon":"construction","h_id":"Alat-Alat Petani","h_en":"A Farmer's Tools","body_id":"Petani memakai banyak alat untuk bekerja. Cangkul dipakai untuk menggemburkan tanah, dan sabit untuk memotong padi saat panen. Dahulu, petani membajak sawah dengan bantuan kerbau atau sapi. Sekarang banyak petani memakai mesin yang disebut traktor agar pekerjaan menjadi lebih cepat dan ringan. Alat-alat ini sangat membantu petani.","body_en":"Farmers use many tools to work. A hoe is used to loosen the soil, and a sickle to cut the rice at harvest time. Long ago, farmers plowed the fields with the help of a buffalo or an ox. Now many farmers use a machine called a tractor so the work becomes faster and easier. These tools are a great help to farmers."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Mengapa Petani Penting?","h_en":"Why Are Farmers Important?","body_id":"Petani sangat penting karena mereka menanam makanan untuk kita semua. Hampir semua yang kita makan, seperti nasi, sayur, dan buah, berasal dari kerja keras petani. Tanpa petani, akan sulit bagi kita untuk mendapatkan makanan. Karena itu kita patut menghargai petani yang setiap hari bekerja keras agar piring kita selalu terisi.","body_en":"Farmers are very important because they grow the food for all of us. Almost everything we eat, such as rice, vegetables, and fruit, comes from the hard work of farmers. Without farmers, it would be hard for us to get food. That is why we should appreciate farmers, who work hard every day so that our plates are always full."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Cara Kita Berterima Kasih","h_en":"How We Can Say Thank You","body_id":"Kita bisa berterima kasih kepada petani dengan menghabiskan makanan di piring kita dan tidak membuangnya. Setiap butir nasi adalah hasil jerih payah petani. Kita juga bisa menghargai mereka dengan membeli hasil panen lokal dan menjaga lingkungan agar tanah tetap subur. Sikap hemat dan tidak menyia-nyiakan makanan adalah cara terbaik berterima kasih.","body_en":"We can thank farmers by finishing the food on our plate and not wasting it. Every grain of rice is the result of a farmer's hard work. We can also appreciate them by buying local harvests and protecting the environment so the soil stays fertile. Being thrifty and not wasting food is the best way to say thank you."}],"facts":[{"id":"Hampir semua nasi yang kita makan ditanam oleh petani di sawah.","en":"Almost all the rice we eat is grown by farmers in the fields."},{"id":"Manusia sudah bercocok tanam sejak ribuan tahun yang lalu.","en":"People have been growing crops for thousands of years."},{"id":"Dahulu petani membajak sawah dengan bantuan kerbau atau sapi.","en":"Long ago, farmers plowed fields with the help of a buffalo or ox."},{"id":"Banyak petani modern memakai traktor agar bekerja lebih cepat.","en":"Many modern farmers use a tractor so they can work faster."},{"id":"Petani topi caping melindungi kepala mereka dari panas matahari.","en":"Farmers wear a cone-shaped hat to shield their heads from the sun."},{"id":"Selain di sawah, ada petani yang memanen rumput laut di tepi laut.","en":"Besides rice fields, some farmers harvest seaweed by the sea."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Petani","def_id":"Orang yang mengolah tanah untuk menanam tanaman pangan.","def_en":"A person who works the land to grow food crops."},{"term":"Sawah","def_id":"Lahan berair tempat petani menanam padi.","def_en":"A watery field where farmers grow rice."},{"term":"Panen","def_id":"Memetik atau mengumpulkan tanaman yang sudah siap diambil hasilnya.","def_en":"To pick or gather crops that are ready to be collected."},{"term":"Cangkul","def_id":"Alat bergagang panjang untuk menggali dan menggemburkan tanah.","def_en":"A long-handled tool for digging and loosening soil."},{"term":"Traktor","def_id":"Mesin besar yang membantu petani membajak dan mengolah lahan.","def_en":"A big machine that helps farmers plow and work the land."},{"term":"Caping","def_id":"Topi lebar berbentuk kerucut dari anyaman bambu pelindung matahari.","def_en":"A wide cone-shaped hat woven from bamboo to block the sun."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d75cf545ea17e071.jpg","caption_id":"Petani bertopi caping sedang memanen padi di sawah bersama petani lain.","caption_en":"A farmer in a cone-shaped hat harvests rice in a paddy field with others.","credit":"ESCapade","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4605bbdaf07eba94.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang petani membajak ladang yang luas dengan traktor hijau.","caption_en":"A farmer plows a wide field with a green tractor.","credit":"Jesster79","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2f1efd40a067b821.jpg","caption_id":"Petani membajak sawah berlumpur dengan bantuan dua ekor sapi.","caption_en":"A farmer plows a muddy paddy field with the help of two oxen.","credit":"Krish Dulal","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ece7269a3a052fcf.jpg","caption_id":"Dua petani memanggul ikatan jerami di tengah sawah yang hijau segar.","caption_en":"Two farmers carry bundles of straw in the middle of a fresh green field.","credit":"Ingo Mehling","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e03e2561aba992c5.jpg","caption_id":"Petani memanen rumput laut di air laut yang dangkal dan jernih.","caption_en":"Farmers harvest seaweed in shallow, clear sea water.","credit":"Yann Macherez","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petani"},"sains_dunia_robotik":{"id":"sains_dunia_robotik","title_id":"Robot","title_en":"Robots","subtitle_id":"Mesin pintar yang bisa bekerja membantu manusia","subtitle_en":"Smart machines that can work to help people","data_card":[{"icon":"smart_toy","label_id":"Apa itu","label_en":"What it is","value_id":"Mesin pintar","value_en":"A smart machine"},{"icon":"sensors","label_id":"Bagian","label_en":"Parts","value_id":"Sensor, motor, program","value_en":"Sensors, motors, program"},{"icon":"code","label_id":"Dikendalikan oleh","label_en":"Controlled by","value_id":"Program komputer","value_en":"A computer program"},{"icon":"precision_manufacturing","label_id":"Kegunaan","label_en":"Used for","value_id":"Pabrik, medis, rumah","value_en":"Factory, medical, home"},{"icon":"history_edu","label_id":"Asal kata","label_en":"Word from","value_id":"Robota (Ceko)","value_en":"Robota (Czech)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"smart_toy","h_id":"Apa Itu Robot?","h_en":"What Is a Robot?","body_id":"Robot adalah mesin pintar yang bisa melakukan pekerjaan, baik diatur oleh manusia maupun mengikuti program yang sudah dibuat. Robot sering dipakai untuk pekerjaan yang berat, berbahaya, kotor, atau yang harus diulang terus-menerus. Banyak orang mengira robot pasti berbentuk seperti manusia. Padahal robot yang mirip manusia, yang disebut humanoid, hanyalah salah satu jenis dari banyak bentuk robot.","body_en":"A robot is a smart machine that can do work, either guided by a person or by following a program that has been made for it. Robots are often used for jobs that are heavy, dangerous, dirty, or have to be repeated over and over. Many people think a robot must be shaped like a human. But a human-shaped robot, called a humanoid, is only one type among many kinds of robots."},{"icon":"sensors","h_id":"Bagian-Bagian Robot","h_en":"The Parts of a Robot","body_id":"Sebuah robot biasanya memiliki tiga bagian penting. Yang pertama adalah sensor, yaitu indra robot yang dipakai untuk merasakan lingkungan, seperti melihat, mendengar, atau merasakan sentuhan. Yang kedua adalah motor dan sendi, yang membuat robot bisa bergerak. Yang ketiga adalah program komputer, yaitu otak robot yang memberi tahu apa yang harus dilakukan. Ketiga bagian ini bekerja sama agar robot bisa bertindak.","body_en":"A robot usually has three important parts. The first is the sensor, the robot's senses used to feel its surroundings, like seeing, hearing, or feeling touch. The second is the motors and joints, which let the robot move. The third is the computer program, the robot's brain that tells it what to do. These three parts work together so the robot can act."},{"icon":"code","h_id":"Bagaimana Robot Bekerja","h_en":"How Robots Work","body_id":"Robot bekerja dengan mengikuti perintah dari program komputer di dalamnya. Mula-mula, sensor mengumpulkan informasi dari sekitarnya. Lalu otak robot mengolah informasi itu dan memutuskan apa yang harus dilakukan. Setelah itu, motor menggerakkan bagian tubuh robot sesuai keputusan tadi. Robot mampu mengulang tugas yang sama berkali-kali tanpa pernah merasa lelah atau bosan.","body_en":"A robot works by following orders from the computer program inside it. First, the sensors gather information from around it. Then the robot's brain works out that information and decides what to do. After that, the motors move the robot's body to carry out the decision. A robot can repeat the same task many times without ever feeling tired or bored."},{"icon":"precision_manufacturing","h_id":"Robot yang Membantu Manusia","h_en":"Robots That Help People","body_id":"Robot membantu manusia di banyak tempat. Di pabrik, lengan robot merakit mobil dan mengangkat barang berat. Di rumah sakit, robot membantu dokter melakukan operasi yang sangat teliti. Di rumah, ada robot kecil yang menyedot debu dan memotong rumput. Robot bahkan dikirim ke tempat yang berbahaya bagi manusia, seperti dasar laut, gunung berapi, dan jauh di luar angkasa.","body_en":"Robots help people in many places. In factories, robot arms put cars together and lift heavy loads. In hospitals, robots help doctors do very careful operations. At home, there are little robots that vacuum the floor and mow the lawn. Robots are even sent to places that are dangerous for people, like the bottom of the sea, volcanoes, and far out in space."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Cerita di Balik Kata Robot","h_en":"The Story Behind the Word Robot","body_id":"Kata robot berasal dari bahasa Ceko, robota, yang berarti pekerjaan berat. Kata ini pertama kali dipakai oleh penulis Karel Capek pada tahun 1920 dalam sebuah cerita panggung. Kemudian penulis Isaac Asimov memperkenalkan kata robotika dan membuat tiga aturan terkenal tentang robot agar selalu aman dan menolong manusia. Sejak itu, robot menjadi tokoh yang sering muncul dalam buku dan film.","body_en":"The word robot comes from the Czech word robota, which means heavy work. It was first used by the writer Karel Capek in 1920 in a stage story. Later, the writer Isaac Asimov introduced the word robotics and made three famous rules for robots so they would always be safe and help people. Since then, robots have become characters that often appear in books and films."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kata robot berasal dari bahasa Ceko robota yang berarti kerja berat.","en":"The word robot comes from the Czech word robota, meaning heavy work."},{"id":"Robot yang berbentuk seperti manusia disebut humanoid.","en":"A robot shaped like a human is called a humanoid."},{"id":"Sensor adalah indra robot untuk merasakan lingkungannya.","en":"Sensors are a robot's senses for feeling its surroundings."},{"id":"Robot bisa mengulang tugas yang sama tanpa pernah lelah.","en":"Robots can repeat the same task without ever getting tired."},{"id":"Lengan robot di pabrik membantu merakit mobil.","en":"Robot arms in factories help put cars together."},{"id":"Robot dikirim ke tempat berbahaya seperti luar angkasa dan dasar laut.","en":"Robots are sent to dangerous places like outer space and the deep sea."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Robot","def_id":"Mesin pintar yang bisa melakukan tugas sendiri atau dengan kendali manusia.","def_en":"A smart machine that can do tasks by itself or under human control."},{"term":"Humanoid","def_id":"Robot yang bentuknya menyerupai tubuh manusia.","def_en":"A robot whose shape looks like a human body."},{"term":"Sensor","def_id":"Bagian robot yang dipakai untuk merasakan cahaya, suara, atau sentuhan.","def_en":"The part of a robot used to sense light, sound, or touch."},{"term":"Program","def_id":"Kumpulan perintah yang memberi tahu robot apa yang harus dilakukan.","def_en":"A set of instructions that tells a robot what to do."},{"term":"Robotika","def_id":"Ilmu tentang cara merancang, membuat, dan menggunakan robot.","def_en":"The study of how to design, build, and use robots."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a8de439b94025340.jpg","caption_id":"Sophia, robot humanoid yang wajahnya dibuat mirip manusia dan bisa berbicara.","caption_en":"Sophia, a humanoid robot with a human-like face that can talk.","credit":"UNCTAD","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0c72ccf3ea681c53.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang insinyur berdiri di samping robot pembantu yang berwajah ramah.","caption_en":"An engineer stands beside a friendly-faced helper robot.","credit":"Nicholas-halodi","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6a48449bc8f10e59.jpg","caption_id":"Dua robot humanoid sedang bermain sepak bola dalam lomba robot.","caption_en":"Two humanoid robots play football in a robot competition.","credit":"Sven Behnke","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/04a2437fdeba97d2.jpg","caption_id":"Robot buatan Toyota ini bahkan bisa meniup terompet seperti pemusik.","caption_en":"This Toyota robot can even play a trumpet like a musician.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robot"},"sains_gunung_berapi_ring_of_fire_1":{"id":"sains_gunung_berapi_ring_of_fire_1","title_id":"Gunung Berapi & Cincin Api Pasifik","title_en":"Volcanoes & the Pacific Ring of Fire","subtitle_id":"Gunung ajaib yang bisa memuntahkan lava panas!","subtitle_en":"Amazing mountains that can spout hot lava!","data_card":[{"icon":"volcano","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Gunung api","value_en":"Fire mountain"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Cincin Api Pasifik","value_en":"Pacific Ring of Fire"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Yang keluar","label_en":"Erupts","value_id":"Lava, abu, & gas","value_en":"Lava, ash, & gas"},{"icon":"terrain","label_id":"Asalnya","label_en":"Comes from","value_id":"Magma dari dalam bumi","value_en":"Magma deep in the Earth"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Manfaat","label_en":"Benefit","value_id":"Tanah jadi subur","value_en":"Makes soil fertile"},{"icon":"place","label_id":"Contoh","label_en":"Example","value_id":"Merapi, Bromo, Semeru, Rinjani","value_en":"Merapi, Bromo, Semeru, Rinjani"}],"sections":[{"icon":"volcano","h_id":"Apa Itu Gunung Berapi?","h_en":"What Is a Volcano?","body_id":"Gunung berapi, atau gunung api, adalah gunung istimewa yang punya saluran sampai jauh ke dalam bumi. Di kedalaman sekitar 10 kilometer di bawah kaki kita, ada batuan yang sangat panas sampai meleleh menjadi cairan. Batuan cair ini bisa naik ke atas lewat gunung. Saat keluar ke permukaan, kita menyebutnya lava!","body_en":"A volcano, or 'fire mountain', is a special mountain with a tube reaching deep into the Earth. About 10 kilometers below our feet, there is rock so hot that it melts into a liquid. This liquid rock can rise up through the mountain. When it comes out at the surface, we call it lava!"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","h_id":"Bagaimana Gunung Meletus?","h_en":"How Does a Volcano Erupt?","body_id":"Jauh di bawah gunung ada kamar magma, seperti kantong berisi batuan cair panas yang disebut magma. Saat magma naik melewati kerak bumi dan muncul ke permukaan, terjadilah letusan! Magma yang keluar menjadi lava, lalu ada juga abu vulkanik dan gas yang menyembur ke udara. Kadang lava mengalir pelan, kadang menyembur tinggi seperti air mancur raksasa.","body_en":"Deep below the mountain is a magma chamber, like a pocket full of hot liquid rock called magma. When the magma rises through the Earth's crust and reaches the surface, an eruption happens! The magma that comes out becomes lava, and there is also volcanic ash and gas that shoot into the air. Sometimes lava flows slowly, and sometimes it sprays up high like a giant fountain."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Cincin Api Pasifik","h_en":"The Pacific Ring of Fire","body_id":"Kulit bumi pecah menjadi potongan-potongan besar yang disebut lempeng tektonik. Saat lempeng-lempeng ini bertemu dan saling menekan, sering muncul gunung berapi. Di sekeliling Samudra Pasifik ada barisan gunung berapi yang sangat panjang, namanya Cincin Api Pasifik. Indonesia berada tepat di cincin ini, jadi negara kita punya banyak sekali gunung berapi!","body_en":"The Earth's skin is cracked into big pieces called tectonic plates. When these plates meet and push against each other, volcanoes often appear. Around the Pacific Ocean there is a very long line of volcanoes called the Pacific Ring of Fire. Indonesia sits right on this ring, so our country has very many volcanoes!"},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Gunung Berapi Itu Bermanfaat","h_en":"Volcanoes Are Useful","body_id":"Gunung berapi tidak hanya seru dilihat, tetapi juga bermanfaat. Abu vulkanik membuat tanah di sekitarnya menjadi sangat subur, sehingga petani bisa menanam padi, sayur, dan buah dengan baik. Gunung berapi juga membentuk pemandangan yang indah dan menyimpan panas bumi yang bisa dijadikan listrik. Itulah mengapa banyak orang tinggal dekat gunung berapi.","body_en":"Volcanoes are not only exciting to look at, they are also useful. Volcanic ash makes the soil around them very fertile, so farmers can grow rice, vegetables, and fruit well. Volcanoes also create beautiful scenery and store underground heat that can be turned into electricity. That is why many people live near volcanoes."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Bagaimana Orang Tetap Aman?","h_en":"How Do People Stay Safe?","body_id":"Ada ilmuwan khusus yang mempelajari gunung berapi, namanya ahli vulkanologi. Mereka mengamati gunung setiap hari untuk memperkirakan kapan gunung akan meletus. Jika sebuah gunung mulai aktif, warga di sekitarnya diberi tahu lebih awal agar bisa pindah ke tempat aman. Dengan begitu, kita tetap bisa mengagumi gunung berapi tanpa perlu takut.","body_en":"There are special scientists who study volcanoes, called volcanologists. They watch the mountains every day to predict when one might erupt. If a volcano starts to become active, the people nearby are warned early so they can move to a safe place. That way, we can still admire volcanoes without being afraid."}],"facts":[{"id":"Batuan cair panas disebut magma saat di dalam bumi, dan lava saat sudah keluar.","en":"Hot liquid rock is called magma inside the Earth, and lava once it comes out."},{"id":"Indonesia punya lebih dari 100 gunung berapi, paling banyak di dunia!","en":"Indonesia has more than 100 volcanoes, the most of any country in the world!"},{"id":"Cincin Api Pasifik adalah barisan gunung berapi yang mengelilingi Samudra Pasifik.","en":"The Pacific Ring of Fire is a line of volcanoes circling the Pacific Ocean."},{"id":"Abu vulkanik membuat tanah menjadi subur untuk bercocok tanam.","en":"Volcanic ash makes soil fertile and great for growing plants."},{"id":"Lubang di puncak gunung berapi tempat keluarnya lava disebut kawah.","en":"The opening at a volcano's top where lava comes out is called a crater."},{"id":"Kadang petir muncul di awan abu saat gunung berapi meletus di malam hari.","en":"Sometimes lightning appears in the ash cloud when a volcano erupts at night."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Magma","def_id":"Batuan yang sangat panas dan meleleh menjadi cairan di dalam bumi.","def_en":"Rock that is very hot and melted into liquid inside the Earth."},{"term":"Lava","def_id":"Magma yang sudah keluar dan mengalir di permukaan bumi.","def_en":"Magma that has come out and flows on the Earth's surface."},{"term":"Erupsi","def_id":"Saat gunung berapi meletus dan mengeluarkan lava, abu, serta gas.","def_en":"When a volcano erupts and releases lava, ash, and gas."},{"term":"Kawah","def_id":"Lubang berbentuk mangkuk di puncak gunung berapi.","def_en":"A bowl-shaped opening at the top of a volcano."},{"term":"Abu vulkanik","def_id":"Butiran halus seperti debu yang disemburkan gunung berapi ke udara.","def_en":"Fine dust-like grains that a volcano throws into the air."},{"term":"Lempeng tektonik","def_id":"Potongan besar kulit bumi yang bisa bergerak perlahan.","def_en":"Large pieces of the Earth's crust that can move slowly."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c5322b4815235aa8.jpg","caption_id":"Gunung Semeru di Jawa menyemburkan asap dan abu tinggi ke langit senja.","caption_en":"Mount Semeru in Java puffs a tall plume of smoke and ash into the evening sky.","credit":"Jan-Pieter Nap","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/958052f17c0e875d.jpg","caption_id":"Gunung Rinjani meletus di malam hari, lava pijar dan petir bersinar terang.","caption_en":"Mount Rinjani erupts at night, with glowing lava and bright lightning.","credit":"Oliver Spalt (talk · contribs), http://www.artweise.de","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b392586cefa1d02f.jpg","caption_id":"Gunung Bromo dan Semeru di Jawa Timur, salah satu pemandangan paling indah.","caption_en":"Mount Bromo and Mount Semeru in East Java, one of the most beautiful views.","credit":"Jakub Hałun","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9e111f66632d0d9d.jpg","caption_id":"Pendaki berjalan menuju Gunung Merapi, gunung berapi yang masih sangat aktif.","caption_en":"Hikers walk toward Mount Merapi, a volcano that is still very active.","credit":"Hildaniar Novitasari","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b63d0bd249c6b6a5.jpg","caption_id":"Asap putih (fumarol) mengepul dari celah gunung berapi yang tertutup salju.","caption_en":"White steam (fumaroles) rises from cracks in a snow-covered volcano.","credit":"Cyrus Read, USGS","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gunung_berapi"},"sains_keajaiban_energi_matahari_1":{"id":"sains_keajaiban_energi_matahari_1","title_id":"Keajaiban Energi Matahari","title_en":"The Wonder of Solar Energy","subtitle_id":"Mengubah sinar matahari menjadi listrik yang bersih!","subtitle_en":"Turning sunlight into clean electricity!","data_card":[{"icon":"wb_sunny","label_id":"Sumber","label_en":"Source","value_id":"Matahari","value_en":"The Sun"},{"icon":"solar_power","label_id":"Alat","label_en":"Device","value_id":"Panel surya (sel surya)","value_en":"Solar panels (solar cells)"},{"icon":"recycling","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Energi terbarukan","value_en":"Renewable energy"},{"icon":"bolt","label_id":"Hasil","label_en":"Output","value_id":"Listrik & panas","value_en":"Electricity & heat"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Kelebihan","label_en":"Pros","value_id":"Bersih & tidak habis","value_en":"Clean & never runs out"}],"sections":[{"icon":"wb_sunny","h_id":"Apa Itu Energi Matahari?","h_en":"What Is Solar Energy?","body_id":"Energi matahari, atau energi surya, adalah energi berupa cahaya dan panas yang datang dari matahari. Setiap hari matahari mengirimkan sinar yang sangat banyak ke bumi. Sinar ini bisa kita tangkap dan ubah menjadi listrik untuk menyalakan lampu, televisi, dan banyak alat lain. Hebatnya, energi ini gratis dan tidak akan pernah habis selama matahari masih bersinar!","body_en":"Solar energy is energy in the form of light and heat that comes from the Sun. Every day the Sun sends a huge amount of light to Earth. We can catch this light and turn it into electricity to power lamps, televisions, and many other devices. The best part is that this energy is free and will never run out as long as the Sun keeps shining!"},{"icon":"solar_power","h_id":"Bagaimana Panel Surya Bekerja?","h_en":"How Do Solar Panels Work?","body_id":"Untuk menangkap sinar matahari, kita memakai panel surya. Panel ini berbentuk papan datar berwarna gelap yang berisi banyak sel surya kecil, atau fotovoltaik. Saat sinar matahari mengenai sel-sel itu, sel surya langsung mengubahnya menjadi listrik. Panel surya biasanya dipasang di atap rumah atau di lapangan luas, lalu diarahkan menghadap matahari agar dapat sinar sebanyak mungkin.","body_en":"To catch sunlight, we use solar panels. A panel is a flat, dark board filled with many tiny solar cells, also called photovoltaics. When sunlight hits those cells, the solar cells turn it straight into electricity. Solar panels are usually placed on rooftops or in big open fields, facing the Sun so they catch as much light as possible."},{"icon":"thermostat","h_id":"Cahaya dan Panas dari Matahari","h_en":"Light and Heat from the Sun","body_id":"Energi matahari bisa dipakai dengan dua cara. Cara pertama mengubah cahaya menjadi listrik memakai panel surya. Cara kedua memanfaatkan panasnya, misalnya untuk menghangatkan air atau membuat rumah terasa nyaman. Bangunan pintar dibuat menghadap matahari agar bagian dalamnya terang dan hangat tanpa boros listrik. Matahari juga menghangatkan laut dan udara, sehingga lahir angin, awan, dan hujan.","body_en":"Solar energy can be used in two ways. The first way turns light into electricity using solar panels. The second way uses its heat, for example to warm water or to make a house feel comfortable. Smart buildings are made to face the Sun so the inside stays bright and warm without wasting electricity. The Sun also warms the sea and air, which creates wind, clouds, and rain."},{"icon":"recycling","h_id":"Energi yang Bersih dan Ramah","h_en":"Clean and Friendly Energy","body_id":"Energi matahari termasuk energi terbarukan, artinya tidak akan habis dan bisa dipakai terus-menerus. Berbeda dengan batu bara atau minyak bumi, energi matahari tidak menghasilkan asap kotor yang mengotori udara. Karena itu energi surya disebut energi bersih. Memakai energi matahari membantu menjaga udara tetap segar dan bumi tetap sehat untuk kita semua.","body_en":"Solar energy is a renewable energy, which means it will not run out and can be used again and again. Unlike coal or oil, solar energy does not make dirty smoke that pollutes the air. That is why solar energy is called clean energy. Using solar energy helps keep the air fresh and the Earth healthy for all of us."},{"icon":"rocket_launch","h_id":"Energi Matahari di Mana-Mana","h_en":"Solar Energy Everywhere","body_id":"Energi matahari bisa menggerakkan banyak hal yang seru! Ada mobil bertenaga surya yang seluruh badannya ditutupi panel surya dan ikut lomba balapan. Ada pula pesawat surya yang terbang tinggi tanpa bahan bakar, hanya menggunakan sinar matahari. Kalkulator, lampu taman, dan satelit di luar angkasa juga banyak yang memakai energi matahari. Keren sekali, bukan?","body_en":"Solar energy can power many exciting things! There are solar cars whose whole bodies are covered in solar panels and that join races. There are also solar planes that fly high with no fuel, using only sunlight. Calculators, garden lamps, and satellites in space also use solar energy. How cool is that?"}],"facts":[{"id":"Dalam satu jam, matahari mengirim energi ke bumi lebih banyak dari yang dipakai dunia selama satu tahun!","en":"In just one hour, the Sun sends Earth more energy than the whole world uses in a year!"},{"id":"Panel surya bekerja tanpa suara dan tanpa bagian yang berputar.","en":"Solar panels work with no noise and no moving parts."},{"id":"Energi matahari tidak akan habis selama matahari masih bersinar.","en":"Solar energy will never run out as long as the Sun keeps shining."},{"id":"Tumbuhan juga memakai energi matahari untuk membuat makanan lewat fotosintesis.","en":"Plants also use solar energy to make food through photosynthesis."},{"id":"Ada pesawat dan mobil yang berjalan hanya dengan tenaga matahari.","en":"There are planes and cars that run on solar power alone."},{"id":"Negara dekat khatulistiwa seperti Indonesia mendapat banyak sinar matahari sepanjang tahun.","en":"Countries near the equator, like Indonesia, get plenty of sunlight all year round."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Energi surya","def_id":"Energi berupa cahaya dan panas yang berasal dari matahari.","def_en":"Energy in the form of light and heat that comes from the Sun."},{"term":"Panel surya","def_id":"Papan datar berisi sel surya yang menangkap sinar matahari.","def_en":"A flat board with solar cells that catches sunlight."},{"term":"Fotovoltaik","def_id":"Sel surya kecil yang mengubah cahaya matahari menjadi listrik.","def_en":"A tiny solar cell that changes sunlight into electricity."},{"term":"Terbarukan","def_id":"Energi yang tidak akan habis dan bisa dipakai terus-menerus.","def_en":"Energy that will not run out and can be used again and again."},{"term":"Energi bersih","def_id":"Energi yang tidak menghasilkan asap atau kotoran yang mencemari udara.","def_en":"Energy that does not make smoke or dirt that pollutes the air."},{"term":"Fotosintesis","def_id":"Cara tumbuhan membuat makanan dengan bantuan sinar matahari.","def_en":"The way plants make food with the help of sunlight."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2b351ed86f22e032.jpg","caption_id":"Mobil bertenaga surya yang seluruh badannya ditutupi panel surya bersama timnya.","caption_en":"A solar-powered car covered entirely in solar panels, with its team.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/29db9b776965328f.jpg","caption_id":"Pesawat surya milik NASA terbang di atas laut, sayapnya penuh sel surya.","caption_en":"NASA's solar plane flies above the sea, its wings packed with solar cells.","credit":"NASA","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e3882587c2481e21.jpg","caption_id":"Rumah hemat energi yang dirancang menghadap matahari agar terang dan hangat.","caption_en":"An energy-saving house designed to face the Sun so it stays bright and warm.","credit":"Jeff Kubina from the milky way galaxy","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energi_surya"},"sains_keajaiban_siklus_air":{"id":"sains_keajaiban_siklus_air","title_id":"Keajaiban Siklus Air","title_en":"The Wonder of the Water Cycle","subtitle_id":"Perjalanan air yang tidak pernah berhenti, dari laut ke langit dan kembali lagi","subtitle_en":"Water's never-ending journey, from the sea to the sky and back again","data_card":[{"icon":"wb_sunny","label_id":"Digerakkan oleh","label_en":"Driven by","value_id":"Panas Matahari","value_en":"Heat from the Sun"},{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Tahap utama","label_en":"Main steps","value_id":"Penguapan, pengembunan, hujan","value_en":"Evaporation, condensation, rain"},{"icon":"waves","label_id":"Terjadi di","label_en":"Where it happens","value_id":"Laut, langit, dan darat","value_en":"Sea, sky, and land"},{"icon":"recycling","label_id":"Air yang sama","label_en":"The same water","value_id":"Dipakai ulang selama miliaran tahun","value_en":"Reused for billions of years"},{"icon":"rainy","label_id":"Mengapa penting","label_en":"Why it matters","value_id":"Memberi air bersih untuk semua makhluk hidup","value_en":"Provides fresh water for all living things"}],"sections":[{"icon":"cycle","h_id":"Apa itu siklus air?","h_en":"What is the water cycle?","body_id":"Siklus air, atau daur hidrologi, adalah perjalanan air yang tidak pernah berhenti. Air bergerak dari laut dan permukaan Bumi naik ke langit, lalu jatuh lagi sebagai hujan atau salju, dan akhirnya kembali ke laut. Lingkaran ini berputar terus-menerus, siang dan malam, di seluruh dunia. Yang menakjubkan, air di Bumi sekarang adalah air yang sama yang sudah ada sejak miliaran tahun lalu. Tetesan hujan yang kamu lihat hari ini mungkin pernah menjadi bagian dari laut purba atau bahkan diminum oleh dinosaurus!","body_en":"The water cycle, or hydrological cycle, is water's never-ending journey. Water moves up from the sea and the Earth's surface into the sky, then falls again as rain or snow, and finally returns to the sea. This loop turns around and around, day and night, all over the world. The amazing part is that the water on Earth today is the very same water that has existed for billions of years. The raindrop you see today may once have been part of an ancient ocean, or even sipped by a dinosaur!"},{"icon":"wb_sunny","h_id":"Matahari sang penggerak","h_en":"The Sun is the engine","body_id":"Matahari adalah mesin yang menjalankan seluruh siklus air. Sinar Matahari menghangatkan permukaan laut, sungai, dan danau. Panas ini mengubah air dari cair menjadi uap air, sebuah gas yang tidak terlihat, dalam proses yang disebut penguapan atau evaporasi. Hampir 90% uap di langit berasal dari laut. Sisanya datang dari tumbuhan, yang melepaskan uap air lewat daunnya dalam proses bernama transpirasi. Tanpa panas Matahari, air akan diam di tempat dan siklus tidak akan pernah dimulai.","body_en":"The Sun is the engine that runs the whole water cycle. Sunlight warms the surface of seas, rivers, and lakes. This heat turns water from a liquid into water vapour, an invisible gas, in a process called evaporation. Almost 90% of the vapour in the sky comes from the ocean. The rest comes from plants, which release water vapour through their leaves in a process called transpiration. Without the Sun's heat, water would stay still and the cycle would never begin."},{"icon":"cloud","h_id":"Awan dan hujan terbentuk","h_en":"Clouds and rain form","body_id":"Saat uap air naik tinggi ke langit, udara di atas menjadi semakin dingin. Udara dingin membuat uap air berubah kembali menjadi tetesan air kecil. Proses ini disebut pengembunan atau kondensasi. Jutaan tetesan kecil ini berkumpul dan membentuk awan. Ketika tetesan di dalam awan menjadi terlalu banyak dan terlalu berat untuk melayang, mereka jatuh ke Bumi sebagai presipitasi, bisa berupa hujan, salju, atau hujan es. Itulah mengapa langit yang cerah bisa berubah mendung dan menurunkan hujan.","body_en":"As water vapour rises high into the sky, the air up there gets colder and colder. Cold air makes the vapour turn back into tiny water droplets. This process is called condensation. Millions of these tiny droplets gather together to form clouds. When the droplets inside a cloud become too many and too heavy to float, they fall to Earth as precipitation, which can be rain, snow, or hail. That is why a clear sky can turn cloudy and bring rain."},{"icon":"water","h_id":"Kembali ke laut","h_en":"Back to the sea","body_id":"Setelah hujan jatuh ke tanah, air memulai perjalanan pulang. Sebagian air meresap ke dalam tanah dan menjadi air tanah yang tersimpan di bawah kaki kita. Sebagian lagi mengalir di permukaan, mengisi sungai dan danau. Sungai-sungai ini perlahan membawa air kembali ke laut yang luas. Begitu air sampai di laut, Matahari kembali memanaskannya, dan seluruh siklus dimulai lagi dari awal. Lingkaran ajaib ini sudah berputar tanpa henti sejak Bumi masih sangat muda.","body_en":"After rain falls on the ground, the water begins its journey home. Some of it soaks into the soil and becomes groundwater, stored beneath our feet. Some flows across the surface, filling rivers and lakes. These rivers slowly carry the water back to the vast ocean. Once the water reaches the sea, the Sun heats it up again, and the whole cycle starts over from the beginning. This magical loop has been turning without stopping since the Earth was very young."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Mengapa siklus air penting","h_en":"Why the water cycle matters","body_id":"Siklus air adalah salah satu keajaiban terpenting di Bumi. Ia membersihkan dan mendaur ulang air, sehingga kita selalu punya air tawar yang segar untuk minum, mandi, dan menyiram tanaman. Hujan menyuburkan ladang dan hutan, mengisi sungai tempat ikan hidup, dan memberi minum semua hewan. Tanpa siklus air, tidak akan ada air tawar di darat, dan kehidupan seperti yang kita kenal tidak mungkin ada. Menjaga air tetap bersih berarti menjaga keajaiban ini tetap bekerja untuk semua makhluk hidup.","body_en":"The water cycle is one of Earth's most important wonders. It cleans and recycles water, so we always have fresh water to drink, wash with, and water our plants. Rain feeds fields and forests, fills the rivers where fish live, and gives every animal a drink. Without the water cycle, there would be no fresh water on land, and life as we know it could not exist. Keeping water clean means keeping this wonder working for all living things."}],"facts":[{"id":"Air di Bumi sekarang adalah air yang sama sejak siklus air dimulai sekitar 3,8 miliar tahun lalu, hanya didaur ulang berulang kali.","en":"The water on Earth today is the same water from when the cycle began about 3.8 billion years ago, just recycled over and over."},{"id":"Sekitar 97% air di Bumi adalah air asin di lautan, dan hanya sebagian kecil yang berupa air tawar yang bisa kita minum.","en":"About 97% of Earth's water is salty ocean water, and only a tiny part is fresh water that we can drink."},{"id":"Hampir 90% uap air di udara berasal dari penguapan air laut; sisanya dilepaskan oleh tumbuhan.","en":"Almost 90% of the water vapour in the air comes from evaporating sea water; the rest is released by plants."},{"id":"Sebuah awan bisa menyimpan jutaan tetesan air kecil sebelum tetesan itu cukup berat untuk jatuh sebagai hujan.","en":"A single cloud can hold millions of tiny water droplets before they grow heavy enough to fall as rain."},{"id":"Air bisa berpindah wujud antara cair (air), gas (uap air), dan padat (es atau salju) selama perjalanannya dalam siklus.","en":"Water can change between liquid (water), gas (vapour), and solid (ice or snow) during its journey through the cycle."},{"id":"Sebagian besar air tawar di Bumi tidak berada di sungai, melainkan membeku sebagai es di kutub atau tersimpan di bawah tanah.","en":"Most of Earth's fresh water is not in rivers, but frozen as ice at the poles or stored underground."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Penguapan (Evaporasi)","def_id":"Proses ketika air berubah dari cair menjadi uap air karena dipanaskan oleh Matahari.","def_en":"The process when water changes from a liquid into water vapour because it is heated by the Sun."},{"term":"Pengembunan (Kondensasi)","def_id":"Proses ketika uap air di langit mendingin dan berubah kembali menjadi tetesan air kecil yang membentuk awan.","def_en":"The process when water vapour in the sky cools and turns back into tiny droplets that form clouds."},{"term":"Presipitasi","def_id":"Air yang jatuh dari awan ke Bumi, berupa hujan, salju, atau hujan es.","def_en":"Water that falls from clouds to Earth, such as rain, snow, or hail."},{"term":"Transpirasi","def_id":"Pelepasan uap air ke udara melalui daun tumbuhan.","def_en":"The release of water vapour into the air through the leaves of plants."},{"term":"Air tanah","def_id":"Air yang meresap ke dalam tanah dan tersimpan di antara batuan di bawah permukaan Bumi.","def_en":"Water that soaks into the ground and is stored between rocks beneath the Earth's surface."},{"term":"Limpasan","def_id":"Air hujan yang mengalir di atas permukaan tanah menuju sungai, danau, dan laut.","def_en":"Rainwater that flows across the surface of the land towards rivers, lakes, and the sea."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/06097c0e9ca007f5.jpg","caption_id":"Awan tebal di langit terpantul di genangan air hujan, menunjukkan hubungan antara air di langit dan air di Bumi.","caption_en":"Big clouds in the sky reflected in a rain puddle, showing the link between water in the sky and water on Earth.","credit":"John Robert McPherson","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d1240b21cc5bea1a.jpg","caption_id":"Setelah hujan, awan putih dan langit biru tampak memantul di air yang tergenang di jalan setapak taman.","caption_en":"After the rain, white clouds and blue sky are mirrored in water pooled on a park path.","credit":"John Robert McPherson","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2043f0b8373c205c.jpg","caption_id":"Genangan hujan memantulkan awan seperti cermin, bukti bahwa air baru saja jatuh dari langit.","caption_en":"A rain puddle mirrors the clouds above, proof that water has just fallen from the sky.","credit":"John Robert McPherson","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2549ddf0b4ec0136.jpg","caption_id":"Pantulan awan yang sangat jelas di genangan air, memperlihatkan tetesan air yang sama yang bisa menguap kembali ke langit.","caption_en":"A clear reflection of clouds in a puddle, showing the same water that can evaporate back into the sky.","credit":"John Robert McPherson","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siklus_air"},"sains_menjelajah_luar_angkasa":{"id":"sains_menjelajah_luar_angkasa","title_id":"Tata Surya","title_en":"The Solar System","subtitle_id":"Matahari, delapan planet, dan keluarga benda langit yang mengelilinginya","subtitle_en":"The Sun, eight planets, and the family of space objects that orbit it","data_card":[{"icon":"wb_sunny","label_id":"Pusat","label_en":"Center","value_id":"Matahari, sebuah bintang","value_en":"The Sun, a star"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Jumlah planet","label_en":"Number of planets","value_id":"8 planet","value_en":"8 planets"},{"icon":"home","label_id":"Planet kita","label_en":"Our planet","value_id":"Bumi, planet ketiga","value_en":"Earth, the third planet"},{"icon":"brightness_7","label_id":"Planet terbesar","label_en":"Largest planet","value_id":"Jupiter","value_en":"Jupiter"},{"icon":"orbit","label_id":"Gerakan planet","label_en":"How planets move","value_id":"Mengelilingi Matahari (mengorbit)","value_en":"They circle the Sun (orbit)"},{"icon":"dark_mode","label_id":"Satelit alami","label_en":"Natural moons","value_id":"Ratusan, termasuk Bulan kita","value_en":"Hundreds, including our Moon"}],"sections":[{"icon":"auto_awesome","h_id":"Apa itu Tata Surya?","h_en":"What is the Solar System?","body_id":"Tata Surya adalah keluarga besar benda langit di luar angkasa. Di tengahnya ada sebuah bintang bersinar yang kita sebut Matahari. Semua benda lain, termasuk planet, bulan, asteroid, dan komet, terikat oleh gaya gravitasi Matahari dan bergerak mengelilinginya. Selain Matahari, Tata Surya memiliki delapan planet, lima planet kerdil, ratusan satelit alami (bulan), dan jutaan benda kecil lainnya. Semuanya bergerak dalam jalur yang teratur, menjadikan Tata Surya seperti sebuah orkestra raksasa di luar angkasa.","body_en":"The Solar System is a big family of objects in space. At its center is a shining star we call the Sun. Everything else, including planets, moons, asteroids, and comets, is held by the Sun's gravity and moves around it. Besides the Sun, the Solar System has eight planets, five dwarf planets, hundreds of natural moons, and millions of smaller objects. They all move along orderly paths, making the Solar System like a giant orchestra in space."},{"icon":"wb_sunny","h_id":"Matahari, sang bintang","h_en":"The Sun, our star","body_id":"Matahari adalah bintang, yaitu bola gas raksasa yang sangat panas dan bercahaya. Matahari jauh lebih besar daripada semua planet jika digabungkan, dan gravitasinya yang sangat kuat menahan seluruh Tata Surya agar tetap bersama. Cahaya dan panas Matahari membuat Bumi cukup hangat untuk ditinggali makhluk hidup. Tanpa Matahari, langit akan gelap gulita, tidak ada siang dan malam, dan planet-planet akan melayang sendirian tanpa arah. Matahari adalah sumber energi utama bagi hampir semua kehidupan di Bumi.","body_en":"The Sun is a star, a giant ball of very hot, glowing gas. The Sun is far bigger than all the planets put together, and its powerful gravity holds the whole Solar System together. The Sun's light and heat keep Earth warm enough for living things. Without the Sun, the sky would be pitch black, there would be no day and night, and the planets would drift alone with no direction. The Sun is the main source of energy for almost all life on Earth."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Delapan planet","h_en":"The eight planets","body_id":"Berdasarkan jaraknya dari Matahari, kedelapan planet adalah Merkurius, Venus, Bumi, Mars, Jupiter, Saturnus, Uranus, dan Neptunus. Empat planet terdekat, yaitu Merkurius, Venus, Bumi, dan Mars, disebut planet kebumian karena terbuat dari batuan dan logam. Empat planet terjauh jauh lebih besar: Jupiter dan Saturnus adalah raksasa gas yang sebagian besar terdiri dari hidrogen dan helium, sedangkan Uranus dan Neptunus adalah raksasa es. Setiap planet luar dikelilingi oleh cincin tipis dari debu dan partikel, dengan cincin Saturnus yang paling indah.","body_en":"Ordered by their distance from the Sun, the eight planets are Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune. The four nearest planets, Mercury, Venus, Earth, and Mars, are called terrestrial planets because they are made of rock and metal. The four farthest planets are much bigger: Jupiter and Saturn are gas giants made mostly of hydrogen and helium, while Uranus and Neptune are ice giants. Each outer planet is circled by thin rings of dust and particles, with Saturn's rings being the most beautiful."},{"icon":"orbit","h_id":"Bergerak mengelilingi Matahari","h_en":"Moving around the Sun","body_id":"Setiap planet bergerak dalam jalur berbentuk lonjong yang disebut orbit, mengelilingi Matahari tanpa pernah bertabrakan. Planet yang lebih dekat ke Matahari bergerak lebih cepat dan menyelesaikan satu putaran lebih singkat. Bumi membutuhkan waktu satu tahun untuk mengelilingi Matahari satu kali. Di antara Mars dan Jupiter terdapat sabuk asteroid, sebuah daerah berisi jutaan batuan luar angkasa. Jauh di luar Neptunus ada Sabuk Kuiper, tempat planet kerdil seperti Pluto berada, dan lebih jauh lagi terbentang Awan Oort yang menjadi rumah bagi komet.","body_en":"Each planet moves along an oval-shaped path called an orbit, circling the Sun without ever crashing into each other. Planets closer to the Sun move faster and finish one lap more quickly. Earth takes one year to travel around the Sun once. Between Mars and Jupiter lies the asteroid belt, a region full of millions of space rocks. Far beyond Neptune is the Kuiper Belt, home to dwarf planets like Pluto, and even farther out stretches the Oort Cloud, the home of comets."},{"icon":"rocket_launch","h_id":"Menjelajah luar angkasa","h_en":"Exploring outer space","body_id":"Tata Surya begitu luas sehingga jika kamu naik mobil tercepat, butuh ribuan tahun untuk mencapai planet terjauh. Para ilmuwan mengirim teleskop, satelit, dan wahana antariksa untuk mempelajarinya. Berkat penjelajahan ini, kita tahu Mars berwarna kemerahan, Jupiter memiliki badai raksasa, dan Saturnus dikelilingi cincin yang menakjubkan. Mempelajari Tata Surya membantu kita memahami dari mana Bumi berasal dan apakah ada tempat lain di luar angkasa yang bisa mendukung kehidupan. Langit malam yang penuh bintang adalah undangan untuk terus bertanya dan menjelajah.","body_en":"The Solar System is so vast that even in the fastest car, it would take thousands of years to reach the farthest planet. Scientists send telescopes, satellites, and space probes to study it. Thanks to this exploration, we know that Mars is reddish, Jupiter has a giant storm, and Saturn is wrapped in stunning rings. Studying the Solar System helps us understand where Earth came from and whether anywhere else in space could support life. The night sky full of stars is an invitation to keep asking questions and exploring."}],"facts":[{"id":"Tata Surya memiliki delapan planet, dan Bumi adalah planet ketiga yang terdekat dari Matahari.","en":"The Solar System has eight planets, and Earth is the third closest planet to the Sun."},{"id":"Jupiter adalah planet terbesar di Tata Surya, jauh lebih besar daripada Bumi.","en":"Jupiter is the largest planet in the Solar System, far bigger than Earth."},{"id":"Empat planet terdekat dengan Matahari terbuat dari batuan, sedangkan empat planet terjauh adalah raksasa gas dan es.","en":"The four planets nearest the Sun are made of rock, while the four farthest are gas and ice giants."},{"id":"Di antara Mars dan Jupiter terdapat sabuk asteroid yang berisi jutaan batuan luar angkasa.","en":"Between Mars and Jupiter lies the asteroid belt, which contains millions of space rocks."},{"id":"Setiap planet bagian luar dikelilingi cincin, tetapi cincin Saturnus adalah yang paling terkenal dan indah.","en":"Every outer planet is surrounded by rings, but Saturn's rings are the most famous and beautiful."},{"id":"Para ilmuwan memperkirakan ada lebih dari 290 satelit alami (bulan) yang mengelilingi planet-planet di Tata Surya.","en":"Scientists have identified more than 290 natural moons orbiting the planets of the Solar System."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Planet","def_id":"Benda langit besar yang berbentuk hampir bulat dan bergerak mengelilingi Matahari.","def_en":"A large, nearly round space object that moves around the Sun."},{"term":"Orbit","def_id":"Jalur berbentuk lonjong yang dilalui sebuah planet atau benda langit saat mengelilingi Matahari.","def_en":"The oval-shaped path a planet or space object follows as it travels around the Sun."},{"term":"Bintang","def_id":"Bola gas raksasa yang sangat panas dan memancarkan cahayanya sendiri, seperti Matahari.","def_en":"A giant ball of very hot gas that gives off its own light, like the Sun."},{"term":"Asteroid","def_id":"Batuan luar angkasa berukuran kecil yang mengelilingi Matahari, sebagian besar berada di sabuk asteroid.","def_en":"A small space rock that orbits the Sun, mostly found in the asteroid belt."},{"term":"Komet","def_id":"Benda langit dari es dan debu yang membentuk ekor bercahaya ketika mendekati Matahari.","def_en":"A space object made of ice and dust that forms a glowing tail when it nears the Sun."},{"term":"Satelit alami","def_id":"Benda langit yang mengelilingi sebuah planet, seperti Bulan yang mengelilingi Bumi.","def_en":"A space object that circles a planet, like the Moon orbiting Earth."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9f928d998deb3b6e.png","caption_id":"Empat planet kebumian dengan ukuran sebenarnya: Merkurius, Venus, Bumi, dan Mars. Hanya Bumi yang tampak biru karena memiliki lautan.","caption_en":"The four terrestrial planets shown at their true sizes: Mercury, Venus, Earth, and Mars. Only Earth looks blue because it has oceans.","credit":"Scooter20 / NASA","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tata_Surya"},"sains_rahasia_gravitasi":{"id":"sains_rahasia_gravitasi","title_id":"Gravitasi","title_en":"Gravity","subtitle_id":"Gaya tak terlihat yang menarik segala benda ke bawah","subtitle_en":"The invisible force that pulls everything down","data_card":[{"icon":"arrow_downward","label_id":"Apa itu","label_en":"What it is","value_id":"Gaya tarik-menarik","value_en":"A pulling force"},{"icon":"person","label_id":"Dijelaskan oleh","label_en":"Explained by","value_id":"Isaac Newton","value_en":"Isaac Newton"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Di mana","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Semua benda bermassa","value_en":"Every object with mass"},{"icon":"fitness_center","label_id":"Efek di Bumi","label_en":"Effect on Earth","value_id":"Benda jatuh & punya berat","value_en":"Things fall & have weight"},{"icon":"orbit","label_id":"Efek di langit","label_en":"Effect in space","value_id":"Planet tetap mengorbit","value_en":"Planets stay in orbit"}],"sections":[{"icon":"arrow_downward","h_id":"Apa Itu Gravitasi?","h_en":"What Is Gravity?","body_id":"Gravitasi adalah gaya tarik yang tidak bisa kita lihat, tetapi selalu bekerja di sekitar kita. Gravitasi membuat semua benda saling tarik-menarik. Kalau kamu melompat, gravitasi menarikmu kembali ke tanah. Kalau bola dilempar ke atas, gravitasi membuatnya jatuh lagi. Karena gravitasi pula, air mengalir ke bawah dan kita bisa berdiri di Bumi tanpa melayang ke langit.","body_en":"Gravity is a pulling force that we cannot see, but it is always working around us. Gravity makes every object pull toward every other object. When you jump, gravity pulls you back down to the ground. When a ball is thrown up, gravity makes it fall again. Because of gravity, water flows downward and we can stand on Earth without floating off into the sky."},{"icon":"scale","h_id":"Massa, Berat, dan Tarikan","h_en":"Mass, Weight, and Pull","body_id":"Semakin besar massa sebuah benda, semakin kuat tarikan gravitasinya. Bumi sangat besar, jadi tarikannya kuat dan membuat kita punya berat. Berat adalah gaya gravitasi yang menarik tubuh kita ke bawah. Gravitasi juga melemah jika benda saling menjauh. Itulah sebabnya tarikan gravitasi terasa paling kuat ketika kita berada di permukaan Bumi.","body_en":"The bigger an object's mass, the stronger its gravity pulls. Earth is very large, so its pull is strong and gives us weight. Weight is the force of gravity pulling our body downward. Gravity also grows weaker when objects move farther apart. That is why gravity's pull feels strongest when we are right on the surface of the Earth."},{"icon":"person","h_id":"Newton dan Galileo","h_en":"Newton and Galileo","body_id":"Ratusan tahun lalu, ilmuwan bernama Galileo menjatuhkan bola dari menara tinggi dan menemukan bahwa benda berat dan benda ringan jatuh dengan kecepatan yang sama. Kemudian Isaac Newton menjelaskan gravitasi sebagai gaya yang menarik dua benda. Konon, ide itu muncul saat ia melihat apel jatuh dari pohon. Ide Newton membantu kita memahami mengapa benda jatuh dan mengapa planet mengorbit.","body_en":"Hundreds of years ago, a scientist named Galileo dropped balls from a tall tower and found that heavy and light objects fall at the same speed. Later, Isaac Newton explained gravity as a force that pulls two objects together. The story says the idea came to him when he saw an apple fall from a tree. Newton's idea helps us understand why things fall and why planets orbit."},{"icon":"orbit","h_id":"Gravitasi di Luar Angkasa","h_en":"Gravity in Space","body_id":"Gravitasi bekerja jauh sampai ke luar angkasa. Tarikan gravitasi Matahari yang sangat kuat membuat Bumi dan planet-planet lain terus bergerak mengelilinginya, dan tidak terlempar jauh. Gravitasi Bulan menarik air laut sehingga terjadi pasang dan surut. Bahkan bintang-bintang bisa berkumpul membentuk galaksi karena gravitasi. Tanpa gravitasi, seluruh alam semesta akan berantakan.","body_en":"Gravity works far out into space. The Sun's very strong gravity keeps Earth and the other planets moving around it instead of flying away. The Moon's gravity pulls the ocean water, making the tides rise and fall. Even the stars can gather together into galaxies because of gravity. Without gravity, the whole universe would fall apart."},{"icon":"rocket_launch","h_id":"Melayang di Antariksa","h_en":"Floating in Space","body_id":"Di stasiun luar angkasa, astronaut terlihat melayang seolah tanpa gravitasi. Sebenarnya gravitasi tetap ada, tetapi astronaut dan pesawatnya jatuh bersama-sama mengelilingi Bumi, sehingga semuanya terasa ringan dan mengambang. Keadaan ini disebut tanpa bobot. Para ilmuwan kadang melatih keadaan ini di pesawat khusus agar bisa merasakan melayang seperti di antariksa.","body_en":"On a space station, astronauts seem to float as if there is no gravity. Gravity is really still there, but the astronauts and their spacecraft are falling together around the Earth, so everything feels light and floaty. This condition is called weightlessness. Scientists sometimes practice this in a special airplane so they can feel what floating in space is like."}],"facts":[{"id":"Gravitasi membuat semua benda jatuh ke bawah, bukan ke atas.","en":"Gravity makes all objects fall down, not up."},{"id":"Benda berat dan benda ringan jatuh dengan kecepatan yang sama.","en":"Heavy and light objects fall at the same speed."},{"id":"Berat badanmu adalah gaya gravitasi yang menarikmu ke Bumi.","en":"Your weight is the force of gravity pulling you to the Earth."},{"id":"Gravitasi Matahari menjaga Bumi tetap pada orbitnya.","en":"The Sun's gravity keeps the Earth in its orbit."},{"id":"Pasang surut air laut terjadi karena gravitasi Bulan.","en":"Ocean tides happen because of the Moon's gravity."},{"id":"Di Bulan gravitasi lebih lemah, jadi kamu bisa melompat lebih tinggi.","en":"On the Moon gravity is weaker, so you could jump much higher."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Gravitasi","def_id":"Gaya tak terlihat yang membuat semua benda saling tarik-menarik.","def_en":"The invisible force that makes all objects pull toward each other."},{"term":"Gaya","def_id":"Dorongan atau tarikan yang bisa menggerakkan atau menghentikan benda.","def_en":"A push or a pull that can move or stop an object."},{"term":"Massa","def_id":"Banyaknya materi di dalam sebuah benda; makin besar massa, makin kuat gravitasinya.","def_en":"How much matter is inside an object; more mass means stronger gravity."},{"term":"Berat","def_id":"Gaya gravitasi yang menarik sebuah benda ke bawah.","def_en":"The force of gravity pulling an object downward."},{"term":"Orbit","def_id":"Jalur melingkar yang ditempuh sebuah benda saat mengelilingi benda lain.","def_en":"The curved path an object takes as it travels around another object."},{"term":"Tanpa bobot","def_id":"Keadaan saat benda terasa ringan dan melayang karena jatuh bersama-sama.","def_en":"The condition when things feel light and float because they fall together."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/eba093f5752f8877.jpg","caption_id":"Ilmuwan Stephen Hawking melayang tanpa bobot di dalam pesawat khusus.","caption_en":"Scientist Stephen Hawking floats weightless inside a special airplane.","credit":"Jim Campbell/Aero-News Network","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a098d5a55e793301.jpg","caption_id":"Gravitasi Matahari menahan semua planet agar tetap mengorbit di tata surya.","caption_en":"The Sun's gravity holds all the planets in orbit across the solar system.","credit":"Harman Smith and Laura Generosa, NASA","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gravitasi"},"sains_rahasia_kekuatan_magnet":{"id":"sains_rahasia_kekuatan_magnet","title_id":"Magnet","title_en":"Magnets","subtitle_id":"Benda ajaib yang bisa menarik besi tanpa menyentuhnya","subtitle_en":"The amazing object that can pull iron without touching it","data_card":[{"icon":"north","label_id":"Kutub","label_en":"Poles","value_id":"Utara & Selatan","value_en":"North & South"},{"icon":"filter_tilt_shift","label_id":"Menarik","label_en":"Attracts","value_id":"Besi & baja","value_en":"Iron & steel"},{"icon":"settings_input_component","label_id":"Memiliki","label_en":"Has","value_id":"Medan magnet","value_en":"A magnetic field"},{"icon":"explore","label_id":"Digunakan untuk","label_en":"Used in","value_id":"Kompas, motor, kulkas","value_en":"Compass, motor, fridge"},{"icon":"swap_horiz","label_id":"Aturan kutub","label_en":"Pole rule","value_id":"Sejenis menolak","value_en":"Same poles repel"}],"sections":[{"icon":"filter_tilt_shift","h_id":"Apa Itu Magnet?","h_en":"What Is a Magnet?","body_id":"Magnet adalah benda yang bisa menarik benda lain dari logam, terutama besi dan baja. Tarikan ini disebut gaya magnet, dan hebatnya gaya ini bekerja tanpa harus menyentuh. Kamu pasti pernah melihat magnet menempel di pintu kulkas. Tetapi magnet tidak menarik semua benda; kertas, kayu, plastik, dan karet tidak akan tertarik oleh magnet.","body_en":"A magnet is an object that can pull other metal objects toward it, especially iron and steel. This pull is called magnetic force, and the amazing thing is that it works without even touching. You have surely seen a magnet stick to a fridge door. But a magnet does not attract everything; paper, wood, plastic, and rubber are not pulled by a magnet."},{"icon":"swap_horiz","h_id":"Dua Kutub Magnet","h_en":"The Two Poles","body_id":"Setiap magnet punya dua ujung istimewa yang disebut kutub: kutub utara dan kutub selatan. Di kedua kutub inilah gaya magnet paling kuat. Ada aturan yang menarik: kutub yang berbeda saling tarik-menarik, sedangkan kutub yang sejenis saling tolak-menolak. Uniknya, kalau sebuah magnet dipotong menjadi dua, setiap potongan tetap punya kutub utara dan kutub selatan sendiri.","body_en":"Every magnet has two special ends called poles: a north pole and a south pole. The magnetic force is strongest at these two poles. There is an interesting rule: opposite poles pull toward each other, while same poles push each other away. The strange part is that if you cut a magnet in two, each piece still has its own north pole and south pole."},{"icon":"blur_on","h_id":"Medan Magnet yang Tak Terlihat","h_en":"The Invisible Magnetic Field","body_id":"Di sekeliling setiap magnet ada wilayah tak terlihat tempat gaya magnet bekerja. Wilayah ini disebut medan magnet. Kita memang tidak bisa melihatnya, tetapi kita bisa membuktikannya. Taburkan serbuk besi halus di sekitar magnet, lalu serbuk itu akan tersusun mengikuti garis-garis melengkung dari kutub yang satu ke kutub yang lain. Garis-garis itu menunjukkan bentuk medan magnet.","body_en":"All around every magnet there is an invisible area where the magnetic force works. This area is called a magnetic field. We cannot see it, but we can prove it is there. Sprinkle fine iron filings around a magnet, and they will line up along curved lines running from one pole to the other. Those lines show us the shape of the magnetic field."},{"icon":"explore","h_id":"Magnet di Sekitar Kita","h_en":"Magnets All Around Us","body_id":"Magnet sangat berguna dalam kehidupan sehari-hari. Jarum kompas adalah magnet kecil yang selalu menunjuk ke utara, sehingga membantu orang menemukan arah. Magnet ada di dalam motor listrik, pengeras suara, dan dinamo. Magnet juga menempelkan catatan di pintu kulkas. Bumi sendiri sebenarnya bagaikan magnet raksasa, dan itulah sebabnya jarum kompas bisa bekerja.","body_en":"Magnets are very useful in everyday life. A compass needle is a tiny magnet that always points north, so it helps people find their way. Magnets are inside electric motors, loudspeakers, and dynamos. Magnets also hold notes onto the fridge door. The Earth itself is really like a giant magnet, and that is why a compass needle works."},{"icon":"bolt","h_id":"Magnet dari Listrik","h_en":"Magnets from Electricity","body_id":"Tahukah kamu bahwa listrik bisa membuat magnet? Jika kawat dililitkan pada sebuah paku lalu dialiri arus listrik, paku itu berubah menjadi magnet dan bisa menarik benda logam. Magnet seperti ini disebut elektromagnet. Hebatnya, ketika listrik dimatikan, sifat magnetnya langsung hilang. Elektromagnet yang sangat besar dipakai untuk mengangkat mobil dan besi tua di tempat rongsokan.","body_en":"Did you know that electricity can make a magnet? If a wire is coiled around a nail and an electric current flows through it, the nail turns into a magnet and can pull metal objects. A magnet like this is called an electromagnet. The clever part is that when the electricity is switched off, the magnetism disappears at once. Very large electromagnets are used to lift cars and scrap iron in junkyards."}],"facts":[{"id":"Magnet hanya menarik logam tertentu seperti besi dan baja.","en":"Magnets only attract certain metals like iron and steel."},{"id":"Setiap magnet selalu punya kutub utara dan kutub selatan.","en":"Every magnet always has a north pole and a south pole."},{"id":"Kutub yang sejenis saling menolak, kutub yang berbeda saling menarik.","en":"Same poles push apart, opposite poles pull together."},{"id":"Jika magnet dipotong, setiap potongan tetap punya dua kutub.","en":"If a magnet is cut, each piece still has two poles."},{"id":"Kata magnet berasal dari Magnesia, sebuah daerah penghasil batu magnet.","en":"The word magnet comes from Magnesia, a place rich in magnetic stone."},{"id":"Listrik bisa membuat magnet, yang disebut elektromagnet.","en":"Electricity can make a magnet, called an electromagnet."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Magnet","def_id":"Benda yang dapat menarik logam seperti besi dan baja.","def_en":"An object that can attract metals such as iron and steel."},{"term":"Kutub","def_id":"Ujung magnet tempat gaya magnet paling kuat: kutub utara dan selatan.","def_en":"The end of a magnet where the magnetic force is strongest: north and south."},{"term":"Medan magnet","def_id":"Wilayah tak terlihat di sekitar magnet tempat gaya magnet bekerja.","def_en":"The invisible area around a magnet where the magnetic force works."},{"term":"Serbuk besi","def_id":"Butiran besi halus yang dipakai untuk memperlihatkan garis medan magnet.","def_en":"Tiny grains of iron used to show the lines of a magnetic field."},{"term":"Kompas","def_id":"Alat penunjuk arah yang jarumnya berupa magnet kecil dan menunjuk utara.","def_en":"A direction tool whose needle is a tiny magnet that points north."},{"term":"Elektromagnet","def_id":"Magnet yang dibuat dengan mengalirkan listrik melalui kawat yang dililitkan.","def_en":"A magnet made by running electricity through a coiled wire."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e36b27b40ac9a055.jpg","caption_id":"Magnet ladam dengan serbuk besi menempel di kutub Utara (N) dan Selatan (S).","caption_en":"A horseshoe magnet with iron filings clinging to its North (N) and South (S) poles.","credit":"Oguraclutch","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/45a3db1e948ef024.jpg","caption_id":"Magnet ladam berbentuk seperti tapal kuda, salah satu bentuk magnet buatan.","caption_en":"A horseshoe magnet shaped like a horse's shoe, one common kind of magnet.","credit":"Eurico Zimbres FGEL/UERJ","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0 br"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/bbb5aaa0109b1e3c.jpg","caption_id":"Serbuk besi tersusun mengikuti garis medan magnet di sekitar magnet ladam.","caption_en":"Iron filings line up along the magnetic field lines around a horseshoe magnet.","credit":"Noguarde","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magnet"},"sejarah_proklamasi_kemerdekaan":{"id":"sejarah_proklamasi_kemerdekaan","title_id":"Proklamasi Kemerdekaan","title_en":"The Proclamation of Independence","subtitle_id":"Hari Indonesia menjadi negara merdeka!","subtitle_en":"The day Indonesia became a free country!","data_card":[{"icon":"calendar_today","label_id":"Kapan","label_en":"When","value_id":"Jumat, 17 Agustus 1945","value_en":"Friday, 17 August 1945"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Di Mana","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Jalan Pegangsaan Timur No. 56, Jakarta","value_en":"Pegangsaan Timur Street No. 56, Jakarta"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Tokoh","label_en":"By","value_id":"Soekarno & Mohammad Hatta","value_en":"Soekarno & Mohammad Hatta"},{"icon":"flag","label_id":"Makna","label_en":"Meaning","value_id":"Indonesia merdeka & berdiri sendiri","value_en":"Indonesia is free and stands on its own"},{"icon":"celebration","label_id":"Diperingati","label_en":"Celebrated","value_id":"Setiap HUT RI, 17 Agustus","value_en":"Every Independence Day, 17 August"}],"sections":[{"icon":"flag","h_id":"Apa Itu Proklamasi?","h_en":"What Is the Proclamation?","body_id":"Proklamasi adalah pengumuman bahwa Indonesia sudah merdeka. Pada pagi hari tanggal 17 Agustus 1945, Soekarno membacakan sebuah naskah pendek di depan banyak orang. Di sampingnya berdiri Mohammad Hatta. Sejak hari itu, Indonesia bukan lagi negara jajahan, melainkan bangsa yang bebas mengatur dirinya sendiri.","body_en":"The Proclamation is the announcement that Indonesia was now free. On the morning of 17 August 1945, Soekarno read out a short text in front of many people. Beside him stood Mohammad Hatta. From that day on, Indonesia was no longer a colony, but a nation free to govern itself."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Mengapa Terjadi Saat Itu?","h_en":"Why Did It Happen Then?","body_id":"Selama ratusan tahun, Indonesia dijajah oleh bangsa lain. Pada tahun 1945, Jepang yang sedang berkuasa kalah dalam perang besar dunia. Para pemuda mendesak Soekarno dan Hatta agar segera memproklamasikan kemerdekaan. Mereka tidak mau menunggu pemberian dari siapa pun. Kemerdekaan harus diraih oleh bangsa Indonesia sendiri.","body_en":"For hundreds of years, Indonesia was ruled by other nations. In 1945, Japan, who was in power, lost a great world war. Young people urged Soekarno and Hatta to declare independence right away. They did not want to wait for it to be handed to them. Freedom had to be won by the Indonesian people themselves."},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Soekarno & Hatta","h_en":"Soekarno & Hatta","body_id":"Soekarno dan Mohammad Hatta adalah dua pemimpin pergerakan. Mereka berdua menandatangani naskah Proklamasi atas nama bangsa Indonesia. Sehari kemudian, Soekarno diangkat menjadi presiden pertama dan Hatta menjadi wakil presiden pertama. Mereka sering disebut sebagai Bapak Proklamator Indonesia.","body_en":"Soekarno and Mohammad Hatta were two leaders of the freedom movement. The two of them signed the Proclamation text in the name of the Indonesian people. A day later, Soekarno became the first president and Hatta the first vice-president. They are often called the Founding Fathers, the Proclaimers of Indonesia."},{"icon":"edit_note","h_id":"Naskah yang Bersejarah","h_en":"A Historic Text","body_id":"Naskah Proklamasi sangat pendek, hanya dua kalimat. Mula-mula tulisan itu dibuat dengan tangan, lalu diketik dengan mesin tik. Walaupun pendek, kalimat itu mengubah sejarah selamanya. Kata-katanya berisi pernyataan bahwa rakyat Indonesia menyatakan kemerdekaannya.","body_en":"The Proclamation text is very short, only two sentences. At first it was written by hand, then typed on a typewriter. Even though it is short, those sentences changed history forever. The words declare that the people of Indonesia announce their independence."},{"icon":"celebration","h_id":"Dirayakan Setiap Tahun","h_en":"Celebrated Every Year","body_id":"Setiap tanggal 17 Agustus, seluruh Indonesia merayakan Hari Ulang Tahun Kemerdekaan. Bendera Merah Putih dikibarkan di mana-mana. Anak-anak ikut lomba balap karung, panjat pinang, dan makan kerupuk. Upacara bendera diadakan untuk mengenang jasa para pahlawan.","body_en":"Every 17 August, all of Indonesia celebrates Independence Day. The Red-and-White flag is raised everywhere. Children join sack races, the greasy-pole climb, and the cracker-eating game. A flag ceremony is held to remember the heroes' sacrifices."}],"facts":[{"id":"Proklamasi dibacakan oleh Soekarno pada pukul 10 pagi, 17 Agustus 1945.","en":"The Proclamation was read by Soekarno at 10 in the morning on 17 August 1945."},{"id":"Naskah Proklamasi hanya terdiri dari dua kalimat pendek.","en":"The Proclamation text is made up of only two short sentences."},{"id":"Soekarno menjadi presiden pertama dan Hatta wakil presiden pertama Indonesia.","en":"Soekarno became the first president and Hatta the first vice-president of Indonesia."},{"id":"Bendera Merah Putih pertama dijahit oleh Fatmawati, istri Soekarno.","en":"The first Red-and-White flag was sewn by Fatmawati, Soekarno's wife."},{"id":"Tanggal 17 Agustus dirayakan sebagai HUT Kemerdekaan Republik Indonesia.","en":"17 August is celebrated as the Independence Day of the Republic of Indonesia."},{"id":"Foto Soekarno membaca Proklamasi diam-diam diabadikan oleh fotografer Frans Mendur.","en":"The photo of Soekarno reading the Proclamation was secretly captured by photographer Frans Mendur."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Proklamasi","def_id":"Pengumuman resmi kepada dunia bahwa sebuah bangsa sudah merdeka.","def_en":"An official announcement to the world that a nation is now free."},{"term":"Kemerdekaan","def_id":"Keadaan bebas dari penjajahan dan bisa mengatur diri sendiri.","def_en":"Being free from colonial rule and able to govern oneself."},{"term":"Penjajahan","def_id":"Saat sebuah negara dikuasai dan diperintah oleh bangsa lain.","def_en":"When a country is controlled and ruled by another nation."},{"term":"Naskah","def_id":"Tulisan atau teks penting, seperti teks Proklamasi.","def_en":"An important piece of writing or text, like the Proclamation text."},{"term":"Merah Putih","def_id":"Nama bendera Indonesia yang berwarna merah dan putih.","def_en":"The name of Indonesia's flag, colored red and white."},{"term":"Proklamator","def_id":"Orang yang membacakan dan menyatakan proklamasi kemerdekaan.","def_en":"The person who reads out and declares the proclamation of independence."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/32cf4b60930174d0.jpg","caption_id":"Soekarno membacakan teks Proklamasi pada 17 Agustus 1945, dengan Mohammad Hatta berdiri di kanannya.","caption_en":"Soekarno reads the Proclamation text on 17 August 1945, with Mohammad Hatta standing to his right.","credit":"Frans Mendur (1913-1971)","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/70f001e6664e3b71.jpg","caption_id":"Gedung tempat naskah Proklamasi disusun, kini menjadi Museum Perumusan Naskah Proklamasi di Jakarta.","caption_en":"The building where the Proclamation text was drafted, now the Museum of the Drafting of the Proclamation in Jakarta.","credit":"Davidelit","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d8e56554ff015153.jpg","caption_id":"Tugu peringatan Proklamasi di Pegangsaan Timur, Jakarta, pada foto lama sekitar tahun 1950-an.","caption_en":"The Proclamation monument at Pegangsaan Timur, Jakarta, in an old photo from around the 1950s.","credit":"Kementerian Penerangan (KEMPEN)","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proklamasi_Kemerdekaan_Indonesia"},"sejarah_sumpah_pemuda":{"id":"sejarah_sumpah_pemuda","title_id":"Sumpah Pemuda","title_en":"The Youth Pledge","subtitle_id":"Satu tanah air, satu bangsa, satu bahasa","subtitle_en":"One homeland, one nation, one language","data_card":[{"icon":"calendar_today","label_id":"Kapan","label_en":"When","value_id":"28 Oktober 1928","value_en":"28 October 1928"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Di mana","label_en":"Where","value_id":"Batavia (Jakarta)","value_en":"Batavia (Jakarta)"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Tokoh","label_en":"By","value_id":"Pemuda-pemudi Indonesia","value_en":"Indonesia's young people"},{"icon":"handshake","label_id":"Makna","label_en":"Meaning","value_id":"Persatuan bangsa Indonesia","value_en":"The unity of the Indonesian nation"},{"icon":"flag","label_id":"Diperingati","label_en":"Remembered as","value_id":"Hari Sumpah Pemuda","value_en":"Youth Pledge Day"}],"sections":[{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Apa Itu Sumpah Pemuda?","h_en":"What Is the Youth Pledge?","body_id":"Sumpah Pemuda adalah janji yang diucapkan pemuda-pemudi Indonesia pada 28 Oktober 1928. Saat itu Indonesia belum merdeka dan masih terpecah dalam banyak suku dan daerah. Para pemuda berkumpul dan berjanji untuk bersatu sebagai satu bangsa.","body_en":"The Youth Pledge is a promise spoken by young Indonesians on 28 October 1928. Back then Indonesia was not yet free and was split into many tribes and regions. The youth gathered and promised to unite as one nation."},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Kongres Pemuda","h_en":"The Youth Congress","body_id":"Para pemuda dari berbagai daerah mengadakan pertemuan besar bernama Kongres Pemuda di Jakarta. Mereka berasal dari Jawa, Sumatra, Sulawesi, dan banyak pulau lain, tapi mereka punya satu mimpi: Indonesia yang bersatu dan merdeka.","body_en":"Young people from many regions held a big meeting called the Youth Congress in Jakarta. They came from Java, Sumatra, Sulawesi, and many other islands, but they shared one dream: a united and free Indonesia."},{"icon":"format_list_numbered","h_id":"Tiga Janji Penting","h_en":"Three Important Promises","body_id":"Isi Sumpah Pemuda ada tiga: (1) Kami bertumpah darah yang satu, tanah air Indonesia; (2) Kami berbangsa yang satu, bangsa Indonesia; (3) Kami menjunjung bahasa persatuan, bahasa Indonesia. Inilah awal mula Bahasa Indonesia menjadi bahasa kita bersama.","body_en":"The Youth Pledge has three promises: (1) We have one homeland, Indonesia; (2) We are one nation, the Indonesian nation; (3) We uphold one language of unity, the Indonesian language. This was the beginning of Indonesian becoming our shared language."},{"icon":"music_note","h_id":"Lagu Indonesia Raya","h_en":"The Song Indonesia Raya","body_id":"Pada kongres itulah lagu 'Indonesia Raya' ciptaan Wage Rudolf Supratman pertama kali diperdengarkan dengan biola. Lagu ini kelak menjadi lagu kebangsaan Indonesia yang kita nyanyikan sampai sekarang.","body_en":"It was at this congress that the song 'Indonesia Raya' by Wage Rudolf Supratman was first played on the violin. This song later became Indonesia's national anthem, which we still sing today."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Maknanya untuk Kita","h_en":"What It Means for Us","body_id":"Sumpah Pemuda mengajarkan kita untuk bersatu walaupun berbeda suku, bahasa daerah, dan agama. Kita bisa meneladaninya dengan saling menghargai teman dari mana pun asalnya.","body_en":"The Youth Pledge teaches us to stay united even though we have different tribes, local languages, and religions. We can follow its spirit by respecting friends no matter where they come from."}],"facts":[{"id":"Sumpah Pemuda diucapkan pada 28 Oktober 1928.","en":"The Youth Pledge was spoken on 28 October 1928."},{"id":"Isinya tiga: satu tanah air, satu bangsa, satu bahasa.","en":"It has three parts: one homeland, one nation, one language."},{"id":"Lagu 'Indonesia Raya' pertama kali dimainkan di kongres ini.","en":"'Indonesia Raya' was first played at this congress."},{"id":"Rumusannya ditulis oleh Mohammad Yamin.","en":"Its words were written by Mohammad Yamin."},{"id":"28 Oktober kini diperingati sebagai Hari Sumpah Pemuda.","en":"28 October is now Youth Pledge Day."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Ikrar","def_id":"Janji atau sumpah yang diucapkan dengan sungguh-sungguh.","def_en":"A promise or oath spoken seriously."},{"term":"Kongres","def_id":"Pertemuan besar untuk membahas hal penting.","def_en":"A big meeting to discuss important matters."},{"term":"Persatuan","def_id":"Keadaan bersatu menjadi satu, tidak terpecah-pecah.","def_en":"Being united as one, not divided."},{"term":"Tanah air","def_id":"Negeri tempat kita lahir dan tinggal, yaitu Indonesia.","def_en":"The land where we are born and live — Indonesia."},{"term":"Bahasa persatuan","def_id":"Bahasa yang dipakai bersama agar semua bisa saling mengerti.","def_en":"A shared language so everyone can understand each other."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9aebb87ef3050252.jpg","caption_id":"Naskah bersejarah Sumpah Pemuda tahun 1928.","caption_en":"The historic text of the 1928 Youth Pledge.","credit":"Edogang1","license":"CC BY 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/fe10c7c37ef6d465.jpg","caption_id":"Tugu 'Api Sumpah Pemuda' yang mengenang peristiwa ini.","caption_en":"The 'Flame of the Youth Pledge' monument honoring this event.","credit":"Edogang1","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/32f9640fce401c44.jpg","caption_id":"Lukisan yang menggambarkan semangat persatuan dan kemerdekaan.","caption_en":"A painting showing the spirit of unity and independence.","credit":"Henk van Rinsum","license":"CC BY 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sumpah_Pemuda"}};
